translation: 常见的（经常发生的；大量存在或存在于多处的）
definition: happening often; existing in large numbers or in many places
example: a common problem/occurrence/practice

translation: 通常，普遍（通常地；非常频繁地；被大多数人地）
definition: usually; very often; by most people
example: Christopher is commonly known as Kit.

translation: 交流，沟通（分享或交换信息、新闻、想法、情感等）
definition: to share or exchange information, news, ideas, feelings, etc.
example: We only communicate by email.

translation: 交流，沟通（表达思想、情感或向人传递信息的活动或过程）
definition: the activity or process of expressing ideas and feelings or of giving people information
example: communication between A and B, Good communication between team leaders and members is essential.

translation: 共产主义的（与共产主义有关的）
definition: connected with communism
example: communist ideology

translation: 社区，群体（作为一个整体谈论的居住在特定地区或国家的所有人）
definition: all the people who live in a particular area, country, etc. when talked about as a group
example: The local community supported us from the start.

translation: 同伴（与你一起旅行或共度大量时间的人或动物）
definition: a person or an animal that travels with you or spends a lot of time with you
example: travelling companions

translation: 公司（通过生产或销售商品、服务赚钱的商业组织）
definition: a business organization that makes money by producing or selling goods or services
example: insurance/oil/tech/technology/pharmaceutical companies

translation: 可比的（与他物相似且可以进行比较的）
definition: similar to somebody/something else and able to be compared
example: A comparable house in the south of the city would cost twice as much.

translation: 相对的，比较而言的（通过与他物比较来衡量或判断的）
definition: measured or judged by how similar or different it is to something else
example: Then he was living in comparative comfort (= compared with others or with his own life at a previous time).

translation: 比较（检查人或物以找出其相似和不同之处）
definition: to examine people or things to see how they are similar and how they are different
example: compare A and B, It is interesting to compare their situation and ours.

translation: 比较（比较两个或更多人或事的过程）
definition: the process of comparing two or more people or things
example: For Durkheim, comparison was the most important method of analysis in sociology.

translation: 同情，怜悯（对受苦的人或动物的强烈同情及帮助欲望）
definition: a strong feeling of sympathy for people or animals who are suffering and a desire to help them
example: to feel/show compassion

translation: 强迫（迫使某人做某事；使某事成为必要）
definition: to force somebody to do something; to make something necessary
example: compel somebody to do something, The law can compel fathers to make regular payments for their children.

translation: 引人入胜的（因非常有趣而使你不得不关注的）
definition: that makes you pay attention to it because it is so interesting and exciting
example: Her latest book makes compelling reading.

translation: 补偿，弥补（提供好事以平衡或减轻损失、伤害等带来的负面影响）
definition: to provide something good to balance or reduce the bad effects of damage, loss, etc.
example: Nothing can compensate for the loss of a loved one.

translation: 补偿，赔偿（因伤害或损失而给予某人的金钱或其他补偿）
definition: something, especially money, that somebody gives you because they have hurt you, or damaged something that you own; the act of giving this to somebody
example: to claim/award/receive compensation

translation: 竞争（参加竞赛或比赛）
definition: to take part in a contest or game
example: The games were an outstanding success, with almost 2?400 athletes competing.

translation: 能力，胜任（做好某事的能力）
definition: the ability to do something well
example: to gain a high level of competence in English

translation: 胜任的（具备做好某事或达到必要标准所需的技能或知识）
definition: having enough skill or knowledge to do something well or to the necessary standard
example: He's very competent in his work.

translation: 竞争，比赛（人们互相竞争以找出谁在某方面最出色的活动）
definition: an event in which people compete with each other to find out who is the best at something
example: a design/an art/a talent competition

translation: 竞争的（描述人或组织相互竞争的情况）
definition: used to describe a situation in which people or organizations compete against each other
example: competitive games/sports

translation: 竞争者（参加比赛的人）
definition: a person who takes part in a competition
example: Over 200 competitors entered the race.

translation: 汇编，编辑（通过收集不同的项目、文章、歌曲等制作书、列表或报告）
definition: to produce a book, list, report, etc. by bringing together different items, articles, songs, etc.; to collect information in order to produce a book, list, etc.
example: We are trying to compile a list of suitable people for the job.

translation: 抱怨（表示对某人/某事感到烦恼、不快或不满意）
definition: to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about somebody/something
example: She never complains, but she's obviously exhausted.

translation: 投诉，抱怨（不满意的理由；表示不满意的陈述）
definition: a reason for not being satisfied; a statement that somebody makes saying that they are not satisfied
example: a formal complaint

translation: 补充（以改善某物或使其更具吸引力的方式添加内容）
definition: to add to something in a way that improves it or makes it more attractive
example: The excellent menu is complemented by a good wine list.

translation: 完整的（包括所有必要部分的；整体的）
definition: including all the parts, etc. that are necessary; whole
example: a complete list/sequence/picture/profile

translation: 完成（结束制造或做某事）
definition: to finish making or doing something
example: to complete a course/project

translation: 完全地（在每一个可能的方面；在每一个部分）
definition: in every way possible; in every part
example: It was completely different from how I had imagined it.

translation: 完成，完工（结束某事的行为或过程；完成的状态）
definition: the act or process of finishing something; the state of being finished and complete
example: the completion of the new hospital building

translation: 复杂的（由许多不同且相连的事物或部分组成的；难以理解的）
definition: made of many different things or parts that are connected; difficult to understand
example: a complex problem/issue/process/system

translation: 综合体（在同一地点的一组类似类型的建筑，如体育或购物综合体）
definition: a group of buildings of a similar type together in one place
example: a sports/leisure/shopping complex

translation: 复杂性（由许多部分组成的状态；难以理解的状态）
definition: the state of being formed of many parts; the state of being difficult to understand
example: the increasing complexity of modern telecommunication systems

translation: 服从，遵守（遵守由权力部门制定的规则或请求的行为）
definition: the practice of obeying rules or requests made by people in authority
example: compliance (with something), procedures that must be followed to ensure full compliance with the law

translation: 复杂的（由许多不同且相连的部分组成的；难以理解的）
definition: made of many different things or parts that are connected; difficult to understand
example: a complicated issue/process/system

translation: 并发症，使复杂化的因素（使情况变得更复杂或困难的事物）
definition: a thing that makes a situation more complicated or difficult
example: The bad weather added a further complication to our journey.

translation: 遵守（服从规则、命令等；达到特定标准）
definition: to obey a rule, an order, etc.; to meet particular standards
example: They refused to comply with the UN resolution.

translation: 组件，部件（构成某物的几个部分之一）
definition: one of several parts of which something is made
example: the different organizations involved in the design of the various components

translation: 作曲（创作音乐）
definition: to write music
example: Mozart composed his last opera shortly before he died.

translation: 作曲家（创作者，尤指古典音乐的创作者）
definition: a person who writes music, especially classical music
example: Verdi was a prolific composer of operas.

translation: 构成，成分（某物所由构成的不同部分；各部分组织的方式）
definition: the different parts that something is made of; the way in which the different parts are organized
example: the chemical composition of the soil

translation: 化合物，复合物（由两个或更多独立事物结合而成的物体）
definition: a thing consisting of two or more separate things combined together
example: compounds derived from rainforest plants

translation: 全面的（包括几乎所有可能涉及的项目、细节、事实或信息）
definition: including all, or almost all, the items, details, facts, information, etc., that may be involved
example: a comprehensive list of addresses

translation: 包含，构成（以某人/某物作为部分或成员）
definition: to have somebody/something as parts or members
example: comprise something, The collection comprises 327 paintings.

translation: 妥协，让步（两人或团体达成的各让一步的协议，使双方都满意）
definition: an agreement made between two people or groups in which each side gives up some of the things they want so that both sides are happy at the end
example: After lengthy talks the two sides finally reached a compromise.

translation: 妥协，折衷（放弃部分要求以达成协议）
definition: to give up some of your demands in order to reach an agreement after disagreeing with somebody
example: Neither side is prepared to compromise.

translation: 强制的（因法律或规则而必须做的）
definition: that must be done because of a law or a rule
example: English is a compulsory subject at this level.

translation: 计算（计算某事，如损失金额）
definition: to calculate something
example: The losses were computed at ￡5 million.

translation: 计算机（能存储、组织和查找信息、处理数据及控制其他机器的电子设备）
definition: an electronic machine that can store, organize and find information, do processes with numbers and other data, and control other machines
example: a home computer

translation: 隐藏（隐藏某人/某物）
definition: to hide somebody/something
example: conceal somebody/something, The paintings were concealed beneath a thick layer of plaster.

translation: 承认（在否认或抵制后，承认某事是真实的或合乎逻辑的）
definition: to admit that something is true, logical, etc. after first denying it or resisting it
example: + speech, ‘Not bad,’ she conceded grudgingly.

translation: 构思（在脑中形成主意、计划等）
definition: to form an idea, a plan, etc. in your mind
example: He conceived the idea of transforming the old power station into an arts centre.

translation: 集中，专注（将全部注意力放在某事上，不考虑其他）
definition: to give all your attention to something and not think about anything else
example: I can't concentrate with all that noise going on.

translation: 专注，浓度（不考虑其他事物而将努力和注意力导向一件事的能力）
definition: the ability to direct all your effort and attention on one thing, without thinking of other things
example: This book requires a great deal of concentration.

translation: 概念（与抽象事物相关的想法或原则）
definition: an idea or a principle that is connected with something abstract
example: concept of something, the concept of social class

translation: 观念，理解（对某事物/某人是什么或应该是什的理解或信念）
definition: an understanding or a belief of what something/somebody is or what something/somebody should be
example: conception of something, Marx’s conception of social justice

translation: 忧虑，关切（担心的感觉，尤指由许多人共有的）
definition: a feeling of worry, especially one that is shared by many people
example: concern about something/somebody, Villagers expressed concern about the level of traffic.

translation: 涉及，关系到（影响某人/某物；与某人/某物有关）
definition: to affect somebody/something; to involve somebody/something
example: Don't interfere in what doesn't concern you.

translation: 担心的，有关的（感到忧虑或担心的）
definition: worried and feeling concern about something/somebody
example: Concerned citizens can have a huge impact.

translation: 音乐会（音乐的公开演出）
definition: a public performance of music
example: to attend/go to a concert

translation: 让步（为了结束争论或缓解困难局面而允许或做出的事情）
definition: something that you allow or do, or allow somebody to have, in order to end an argument or to make a situation less difficult
example: The firm will be forced to make concessions if it wants to avoid a strike.

translation: 推断出（根据所听或所见做出的决定或相信的事）
definition: to decide or believe something as a result of what you have heard or seen
example: conclude something, It is too early for us to conclude anything.

translation: 结论（在思考了所有相关信息后做出的决定）
definition: something that you decide when you have thought about all the information connected with the situation
example: We can safely draw some conclusions from our discussion.

translation: 混凝土制的（由混凝土制成的）
definition: made of concrete
example: a concrete floor

translation: 混凝土（由水泥、沙、碎石和水混合而成的建筑材料）
definition: building material that is made by mixing together cement, sand, small stones and water
example: a slab of concrete

translation: 谴责（通常出于道德原因强烈表示认为某事是错误的）
definition: to say very strongly that you think something is bad, usually for moral reasons
example: condemn somebody/something, The government issued a statement condemning the killings.

translation: 状态，状况（事物所处的状况）
definition: the state that something is in
example: in… condition, to be in pristine/excellent/perfect condition

translation: 品行，行为（一个人在特定场所或情况下的表现）
definition: a person’s behaviour in a particular place or in a particular situation
example: The sport has a strict code of conduct.

translation: 组织，进行（组织和/或进行特定的活动，如实验或调查）
definition: to organize and/or do a particular activity
example: to conduct an experiment/inquiry/investigation/interview

translation: 商议（与某人讨论以交换意见或获得建议）
definition: to discuss something with somebody, in order to exchange opinions or get advice
example: He wanted to confer with his colleagues before reaching a decision.

translation: 会议（大型正式会议，通常持续数天，同行业或同兴趣的人在此讨论观点）
definition: a large official meeting, usually lasting for a few days, at which people with the same work or interests come together to discuss their views
example: The hotel is used for exhibitions, conferences and social events.

translation: 承认，供认（承认，尤指正式或向警方承认做了错事或违法的事）
definition: to admit, especially formally or to the police, that you have done something wrong or illegal
example: After hours of questioning, the suspect confessed.

translation: 供词，坦白（承认犯罪的陈述；这种承认行为）
definition: a statement that a person makes, admitting that they are guilty of a crime; the act of making such a statement
example: After hours of questioning by police, she made a full confession.

translation: 信心，信任（信任、相信并确信某人/某事的能力或优良品质的感觉）
definition: the feeling that you can trust, believe in and be sure about the abilities or good qualities of somebody/something
example: The president's actions hardly inspire confidence.

translation: 自信的（对自己的能力和成功感到确信的）
definition: feeling sure about your own ability to do things and be successful
example: She was in a relaxed, confident mood.

translation: 配置（某物各部分的排列，或这种排列产生的形式或形状）
definition: an arrangement of the parts of something or a group of things; the form or shape that this arrangement produces
example: configuration of something, The design is based on four configurations of squares.

translation: 限制（将某人/某物保持在特定活动、主题或区域的范围内）
definition: to keep somebody/something inside the limits of a particular activity, subject, area, etc.
example: be confined to (doing) something, The work will not be confined to the Glasgow area.

translation: 确认（通过提供证据说明某事肯定是真实或正确的）
definition: to state or show that something is definitely true or correct, especially by providing evidence
example: confirm something, His guilty expression confirmed my suspicions.

translation: 确认，证实（说明某事真实、正确或确定的声明、信件等）
definition: a statement, letter, etc. that shows that something is true, correct or definite
example: I'm still waiting for confirmation of the test results.

translation: 冲突（人、团体或国家之间强烈分歧或陷入严重争论的情况）
definition: a situation in which people, groups or countries disagree strongly or are involved in a serious argument
example: The violence was the result of political conflicts.

translation: 冲突，矛盾（如果两个想法、信仰等冲突，指它们不能共同存在或不同时为真）
definition: if two ideas, beliefs, stories, etc. conflict, it is not possible for them to exist together or for them both to be true
example: Reports conflicted on how much of the aid was reaching the famine victims.

translation: 面对，面临（出现并需要由某人处理）
definition: to appear and need to be dealt with by somebody
example: What is to be done about the economic problems confronting the country?

translation: 对峙（因意见不同而在人或团体之间产生的愤怒局面）
definition: a situation in which there is anger between people or groups who disagree because they have different opinions
example: confrontation (with somebody), She wanted to avoid another confrontation with her father.

translation: 使困惑（使某人无法清晰思考或理解某事）
definition: to make somebody unable to think clearly or understand something
example: confuse somebody, These two sets of statistics are guaranteed to confuse the public.

translation: 困惑的（无法清晰思考或理解正在发生的事或某人所说的话）
definition: unable to think clearly or to understand what is happening or what somebody is saying
example: I'm confused―say all that again.

translation: 令人困惑的（难以理解的；不清晰的）
definition: difficult to understand; not clear
example: The instructions on the box are very confusing.

translation: 混乱（对发生的事、该做什么或某事的含义不确定的状态）
definition: a state of not being certain about what is happening, what you should do, what something means, etc.
example: The announcement caused a lot of confusion.

translation: 祝贺（告诉某人你对其成功或成就感到高兴）
definition: to tell somebody that you are pleased about their success or achievements
example: I congratulated them all on their results.

translation: 会众（聚集在教堂进行宗教仪式的一群人，不包括牧师和合唱团）
definition: a group of people who are gathered together in a church for a religious service, not including the priest and choir
example: The congregation stood to sing the hymn.

translation: 国会的（与国会或美国国会有关的）
definition: related to or belonging to a congress or the Congress in the US
example: a congressional committee/bill

translation: 连接（将两个或更多事物连接在一起；被连接在一起）
definition: to join together two or more things; to be joined together
example: connect A and B, The towns are connected by train and bus services.

translation: 连接的，相关的（两个或更多事物或人之间有联系的）
definition: (of two or more things or people) having a link between them
example: We do not believe that the incidents are connected.

translation: 连接，联系（连接两个事实、想法等的事物）
definition: something that connects two facts, ideas, etc.
example: connection between A and B, Scientists have established a connection between cholesterol levels and heart disease.

translation: 征服（通过武力夺取对国家或城市的控制权）
definition: to take control of a country or city and its people by force
example: The Normans conquered England in 1066.

translation: 良心（头脑中告诉你行为对错的部分）
definition: the part of your mind that tells you whether your actions are right or wrong
example: to have a clear/guilty conscience (= to feel that you have done right/wrong)

translation: 意识到的（意识到某事；注意到某事）
definition: aware of something; noticing something
example: conscious of something, She's very conscious of the problems involved.

translation: 意识（能够使用感官和思维能力理解正在发生的事的状态）
definition: the state of being able to use your senses and mental powers to understand what is happening
example: I can't remember any more―I must have lost consciousness.

translation: 连续的（在一个连续系列中一个接一个发生的）
definition: following one after another in a continuous series
example: She was absent for nine consecutive days.

translation: 共识（群体中所有成员都同意的意见）
definition: an opinion that all members of a group agree with
example: consensus (about/on something), She is skilled at achieving consensus on sensitive issues.

translation: 准许，同意（做某事的许可，尤指权力部门给予的）
definition: permission to do something, especially given by somebody in authority
example: The written consent of a parent is required.

translation: 同意（同意某事或给予某事许可）
definition: to agree to something or give your permission for something
example: When she told them what she intended, they readily consented.

translation: 后果（发生之事的结果，尤指不愉快的结果）
definition: a result of something that has happened, especially an unpleasant result
example: Remember that actions have consequences.

translation: 因此，结果（作为结果；因此）
definition: as a result; therefore
example: This poses a threat to agriculture and the food chain, and consequently to human health.

translation: 保护，保护区（对自然环境的保护）
definition: the protection of the natural environment
example: to be interested in wildlife conservation

translation: 保守的（反对重大或突然的社会变革；表现出更喜欢传统风格和价值）
definition: opposed to great or sudden social change; showing that you prefer traditional styles and values
example: the conservative views of his parents

translation: 保守主义者（保守的人）
definition: a conservative person
example: social/religious conservatives

translation: 保护（保护某物并防止其被改变或破坏）
definition: to protect something and prevent it from being changed or destroyed
example: new laws to conserve wildlife in the area

translation: 考虑（仔细思考某事，尤指为了做出决定）
definition: to think about something carefully, especially in order to make a decision
example: I'd like some time to consider.

translation: 相当大的（在数量、规模、重要性等方面很大的）
definition: great in amount, size, importance, etc.
example: The project wasted a considerable amount of time and money.

translation: 相当地（很大程度上；很多地）
definition: much; a lot
example: The need for sleep varies considerably from person to person.

translation: 考虑，思考（仔细思考某事的行为）
definition: the act of thinking carefully about something
example: An employer is legally bound to give due consideration to the request.

translation: 由...组成（由...组成）
一致性（始终以相同方式行事或具有相同看法、标准的品质）
definition: the quality of always behaving in the same way or of having the same opinions, standard, etc.; the quality of being consistent
example: She has played with great consistency all season.

translation: 一致的（始终以相同方式行事，或具有相同的看法、标准等）
definition: always behaving in the same way, or having the same opinions, standards, etc.
example: a consistent approach to the problem

translation: 一致地（始终如一地）
definition: always the same
example: Her work has been of a consistently high standard.

translation: 巩固（使权力或成功的地位更稳固，使其更可能持续）
definition: to make a position of power or success stronger so that it is more likely to continue
example: With this new movie he has consolidated his position as the country's leading director.

translation: 阴谋（一群人为了做有害或违法的事而进行的秘密计划）
definition: a secret plan by a group of people to do something harmful or illegal
example: conspiracy (to do something), a conspiracy to overthrow the government

translation: 不断的（一直发生或重复发生的）
definition: happening all the time or repeatedly
example: There were constant interruptions.

translation: 不断地（一直；重复地）
definition: all the time; repeatedly
example: Fashion is constantly changing.

translation: 选区（选举其议会代表的地区）
definition: a district that elects its own representative to parliament
example: Unemployment is high in her constituency.

translation: 构成（被认为是什么；组成）
definition: to be considered to be something
example: Does such an activity constitute a criminal offence?

translation: 宪法，章程（管理国家、州或组织的法律和基本原则体系）
definition: the system of laws and basic principles that a state, a country or an organization is governed by
example: your right to vote under the constitution

translation: 宪法的（与宪法有关的）
限制，约束（限制某事或限制做某事自由的事物）
definition: a thing that limits something, or limits your freedom to do something
example: constraints of time/money/space

translation: 建造（建造或制造某物，如道路、建筑或机器）
definition: to build or make something such as a road, building or machine
example: construct something, The building was constructed in 1993.

translation: 建筑，施工（建造或制造某物――尤指道路、建筑、桥梁等――的过程或方法）
definition: the process or method of building or making something, especially roads, buildings, bridges, etc.
example: Construction began this year and will take approximately 18 months.

translation: 咨询（向某人寻求信息或建议）
definition: to go to somebody for information or advice
example: consult somebody, If the pain continues, consult your doctor.

translation: 顾问（在特定领域知识丰富并被雇佣提供建议的人）
definition: a person who knows a lot about a particular subject and is employed to give advice about it to other people
example: a technology/design consultant

translation: 商议，咨询（在做出决定前与某人或某群体讨论某事）
definition: the act of discussing something with somebody or with a group of people before making a decision about it
example: a consultation document/paper/period/process

translation: 消耗（使用某物，尤指燃料、能量或时间）
definition: to use something, especially fuel, energy or time
example: The electricity industry consumes large amounts of fossil fuels.

translation: 消费者（购买商品或使用服务的人）
definition: a person who buys goods or uses services
example: consumer spending/demand

translation: 消费，消耗量（使用能源、食物或材料的行为；使用的数额）
definition: the act of using energy, food or materials; the amount used
example: the production of fuel for domestic consumption (= to be used in the country where it is produced)

translation: 接触，联系（与某人交流的行为，尤其是定期的交流）
definition: the act of communicating with somebody, especially regularly
example: contact with somebody, I don't have much contact with my uncle.

translation: 联系（与某人交流，例如通过电话、信件或电子邮件）
definition: to communicate with somebody, for example by phone, letter or email
example: I've been trying to contact you all day.

translation: 包含（如果一物包含另一物，指后者在前者内部或作为其一部分）
definition: if something contains something else, it has that thing inside it or as part of it
example: This drink doesn't contain any alcohol.

translation: 容器（用于储存或运输物品的盒子、瓶子等）
definition: a box, bottle, etc. in which something can be stored or transported
example: a plastic container

translation: 沉思，打算（思考是否应该或如何去做某事）
definition: to think about whether you should do something, or how you should do something
example: contemplate something, You're too young to be contemplating retirement.

translation: 同时代的，当代的（属于同一时代的）
definition: belonging to the same time
example: We have no contemporary account of the battle (= written near the time that it happened).

translation: 蔑视（觉得某人/某事毫无价值且完全不值得尊敬的感觉）
definition: the feeling that somebody/something is without value and deserves no respect at all
example: with contempt, She looked at him with contempt.

translation: 主张，争辩（声称某事为真，尤指在争论中）
definition: to say that something is true, especially in an argument
example: I would contend that the minister's thinking is flawed on this point.

translation: 竞争者（有权参与竞争并有机会获胜的人或团队）
definition: a person or team with a chance of winning a competition
example: contender (for something), a contender for a gold medal in the Olympics

translation: 满意的（对自己所拥有的感到快乐和满足）
definition: happy and satisfied with what you have
example: He seemed more content, less bitter.

translation: 内容（某物中所包含的事物）
definition: the things that are contained in something
example: He tipped the contents of the bag onto the table.

translation: 争论，分歧（持不同意见的人之间的愤怒或争议）
definition: anger between people who disagree
example: One area of contention is the availability of nursery care.

translation: 竞赛（人们试图赢得某物的比赛）
definition: a competition in which people try to win something
example: to hold a singing/talent contest

translation: 参加竞赛（参加比赛、选举等并试图获胜）
definition: to take part in a competition, election, etc. and try to win it
example: Three candidates contested the leadership.

translation: 背景，语境（事情发生的背景及其有助于理解的情况）
definition: the situation in which something happens and that helps you to understand it
example: Such databases are being used in a wide range of contexts.

translation: 大陆，洲（地球上的大型陆地块，如欧洲、亚洲或非洲）
definition: one of the large land masses of the earth such as Europe, Asia or Africa
example: the continent of Africa

translation: 不断地（多次重复以至于令人烦恼）
definition: in a way that is repeated many times so that it is annoying
example: They argue continually about money.

translation: 继续（持续存在或发生而不停止）
definition: to keep existing or happening without stopping
example: If the current trend continues, that number will increase 165 per cent by 2050.

translation: 连续的（在一段时间内持续发生或存在而不间断的）
definition: happening or existing for a period of time without being interrupted
example: Recovery after the accident will be a continuous process that may take several months.

translation: 合同（正式的书面协议）
definition: an official written agreement
example: All employees have a written contract of employment.

translation: 收缩（变小或变少；使某物变小或变少）
definition: to become less or smaller; to make something become less or smaller
example: Glass contracts as it cools.

translation: 承包商（签订合同为另一公司工作、提供商品或服务的个人或公司）
definition: a person or company that has a contract to do work or provide goods or services for another company
example: a building/roofing/electrical contractor

translation: 矛盾（事实、观点、行动等之间缺乏一致性）
definition: a lack of agreement between facts, opinions, actions, etc.
example: contradiction (between A and B), There is a contradiction between the two sets of figures.

translation: 相反的（相反的）
相反的事物（相反的事实、事件或情况）
definition: the opposite fact, event or situation
example: In the end the contrary was proved true: he was innocent and she was guilty.

translation: 对比（当两个或多个人/物被比较或靠近放置时可清晰看到的差异）
definition: a difference between two or more people or things that you can see clearly when they are compared or put close together; the fact of comparing two or more things in order to show the differences between them
example: The two cities make an interesting contrast.

translation: 对比（比较两个事物以展示其间的差异）
definition: to compare two things in order to show the differences between them
example: contrast A and B, The poem contrasts youth and age.

translation: 贡献（给予某物，尤指金钱或财物，以帮助实现或提供某事）
definition: to give something, especially money or goods, to help achieve or provide something
example: Do you wish to contribute?

translation: 捐助，贡献（给予个人或组织的以帮助支付某项费用的礼物或款项）
definition: a gift or payment that is made to a person or an organization in order to help pay for something
example: All contributions will be gratefully received.

translation: 投稿人，贡献者（为杂志、书籍等撰写文章的人，或在节目、会议中发言的人）
definition: a person who writes articles for a magazine, book or website, or who talks on a radio or television programme or at a meeting
example: a regular contributor to this magazine

translation: 控制，控制权（对国家、地区、组织等运行方式做出决定的权力）
definition: the power to make decisions about how a country, an area, an organization, etc. is run
example: control of somebody/something, The party expects to gain control of the council in the next election.

translation: 控制（对人、公司、国家等拥有权力，能决定其必须做什么或其如何运行）
definition: to have power over a person, company, country, etc. so that you are able to decide what they must do or how it is run
example: By the age of 21 he controlled the company.

translation: 有争议的（引起大量愤怒的公众讨论和分歧的）
definition: causing a lot of angry public discussion and disagreement
example: a highly controversial topic

translation: 争议（关于许多人强烈反对、认为不好或感到震惊之事的公众讨论和争论）
definition: public discussion and argument about something that many people strongly disagree about, think is bad, or are shocked by
example: to arouse/cause controversy

translation: 便利，方便（对某人有用、容易或合适的品质）
definition: the quality of being useful, easy or suitable for somebody
example: We have provided seats for the convenience of our customers.

translation: 方便的（有用、容易或能快速完成的；不引起问题的）
definition: useful, easy or quick to do; not causing problems
example: Fruit is a convenient source of vitamins and energy.

translation: 惯例，公约（社会中大多数人期望并认为是礼貌或正确的做事方式）
definition: the way in which something is done that most people in a society expect and consider to be polite or the right way to do it
example: the rigid social conventions of Victorian Britain

translation: 传统的（趋向于遵循社会普遍认可的做法；寻常的，可能不怎么有趣的）
definition: tending to follow what is done or considered acceptable by society in general; normal and ordinary, and perhaps not very interesting
example: conventional behaviour/morality

translation: 谈话（涉及两人或小团体的非正式谈话；谈话这种活动）
definition: an informal talk involving a small group of people or only two; the activity of talking in this way
example: a phone conversation

translation: 转换，变换（将某物从一种形式、用途或系统改变为另一种的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of changing something from one form, use or system to another
example: Their main business is the conversion of farm buildings into family homes.

translation: 转换（使某物从一种形式、目的、系统等改变为另一种）
definition: to change or make something change from one form, purpose, system, etc. to another
example: convert something, They took just nine months to convert the building.

translation: 传达（使想法、感情等被他人知晓）
definition: to make ideas, feelings, etc. known to somebody
example: convey something, Colours like red convey a sense of energy and strength.

translation: 定罪（在法庭上正式裁定并宣布某人有罪）
definition: to decide and state officially in court that somebody is guilty of a crime
example: be convicted (of something), He was convicted of fraud.

translation: 定罪（法庭裁定某人有罪的行为；被裁定有罪的事实）
definition: the act of finding somebody guilty of a crime in court; the fact of having been found guilty
example: He plans to appeal against his conviction.

translation: 说服（使某人/自己相信某事是真实的）
definition: to make somebody/yourself believe that something is true
example: convince somebody/yourself, Are the prime minister's assurances enough to convince the public?

translation: 确信的（对某事完全确定的）
definition: completely sure about something
example: Sam nodded but he didn't look convinced.

translation: 有说服力的（使人相信某事属实的）
definition: that makes somebody believe that something is true
example: a convincing argument/explanation/case

translation: 厨师（烹制食物的人或以此为业的人）
definition: a person who cooks food or whose job is cooking
example: John is a very good cook (= he cooks well).

translation: 烹饪（通过加热准备食物，如煮、烤或炸）
definition: to prepare food by heating it, for example by boiling, baking or frying it
example: Where did you learn to cook?

translation: 炊具（用于烹饪的大型设备，包含烤箱和上方的炉圈）
definition: a large piece of equipment for cooking food, containing an oven and gas or electric rings on top
example: a gas cooker

translation: 烹调（通过加热准备食物的过程）
definition: the process of preparing food by heating it
example: My husband does all the cooking.

translation: 凉爽的（相当冷；不热或不暖）
definition: fairly cold; not hot or warm
example: cool air/water

translation: 变凉，冷却（变凉；使某人/某物变凉）
definition: to become cool or cooler; to make somebody/something become cool or cooler
example: Glass contracts as it cools.

translation: 合作（与他人共同工作以实现某事）
definition: to work together with somebody else in order to achieve something
example: The two groups agreed to cooperate with each other.

translation: 合作的（涉及共同行事或与他人为了共同目标而工作的）
definition: involving doing something together or working together with others towards a shared aim
example: Cooperative activity is essential to effective community work.

translation: 协调（组织活动的不同部分及相关人员，使其运作良好）
definition: to organize the different parts of an activity and the people involved in it so that it works well
example: coordinate something, They appointed a new manager to coordinate the work of the team.

translation: 协调（使事物各部分、各群体等以高效、有组织的方式共同工作的行为）
definition: the act of making parts of something, groups of people, etc. work together in an efficient and organized way
example: The aim was to improve the coordination of services.

translation: 协调员（组织活动不同部分及相关人员使其运作良好的人）
definition: a person who organizes the different parts of an activity and the people involved in it so that it works well
example: The campaign needs an effective coordinator.

translation: 警察（警察的俗称）
definition: a police officer
example: Somebody call the cops!

translation: 应对（成功处理困难的事情）
definition: to deal successfully with something difficult
example: I got to the stage where I wasn't coping any more.

translation: 铜（一种化学元素，红棕色软金属，用于电线、管道和硬币）
definition: a chemical element. Copper is a soft red-brown metal used for making electric wires, pipes and coins.
example: a copper mine

translation: 副本，复印件（制作得与他物――尤指文件或艺术品――相同的东西）
definition: a thing that is made to be the same as something else, especially a document or a work of art
example: The thieves replaced the original painting with a copy.

translation: 复制，抄袭（制作与他物完全相同的东西）
definition: to make something that is exactly like something else
example: copy something, He taught himself by copying paintings in the Louvre.

translation: 版权（个人或组织对作品享有的法律出版、播放等权利）
definition: if a person or an organization holds the copyright on a piece of writing, music, etc., they are the only people who have the legal right to publish, broadcast, perform it, etc., and other people must ask their permission to use it or any part of it
example: Copyright expires seventy years after the death of the author.

translation: 核心的（最重要的；主要的或本质的）
definition: most important; main or essential
example: core subjects (= subjects that all the students have to study) such as English and mathematics

translation: 核心（某物最重要或最中心的部分）
definition: the most important or central part of something
example: This report goes to the core of the argument.

translation: 角落（两个或更多边、线、边缘连接的地方）
definition: a part of something where two or more sides, lines or edges join
example: the four corners of a square

translation: 公司的，社团的（与大型商业公司有关的）
definition: connected with a large business company
example: corporate finance/profits/tax

translation: 法人公司，大企业（大型商业公司）
definition: a large business company
example: multinational corporations

translation: 正确的（准确或真实的，没有任何错误）
definition: accurate or true, without any mistakes
example: Do you have the correct time?

translation: 纠正（使某事变正确或准确，例如通过改变或删除错误）
definition: to make something right or accurate, for example by changing it or removing mistakes
example: correct something, to correct an error

translation: 纠正，改正（使某事比以前更准确的变化）
definition: a change that makes something more accurate than it was before
example: I've made a few small corrections to your report.

translation: 正确地（以准确或真实且无误的方式）
definition: in a way that is accurate or true, without any mistakes
example: Have you spelled it correctly?

translation: 相关（如果两个事实等相关，指它们紧密相连且相互影响或依赖）
definition: if two or more facts, figures, etc. correlate or if a fact, figure, etc. correlates with another, the facts are closely connected and affect or depend on each other
example: The figures do not seem to correlate.

translation: 相关性（两事物间的一方随另一方改变的联系）
definition: a connection between two things in which one thing changes as the other does
example: correlation between A and B, There is a direct correlation between exposure to sun and skin cancer.

translation: 符合，一致（与某物相同或相匹配）
definition: to be the same as or match something
example: Your account and hers do not correspond.

translation: 通信，信件（一个人发送和收到的信件、电子邮件等）
definition: the letters, emails, etc. a person sends and receives
example: personal/private correspondence

translation: 通讯员，记者（为报社或电台报道特定国家或特定主题新闻的人）
definition: a person who reports news from a particular country or on a particular subject for a newspaper or a television or radio station
example: She's the BBC's political correspondent.

translation: 相应的（与刚提到的事物相匹配或相连的）
definition: matching or connected with something that you have just mentioned
example: A change in the money supply brings a corresponding change in expenditure.

translation: 走廊（建筑内狭长的通道，两侧有通往房间的门）
definition: a long narrow passage in a building, with doors that open into rooms on either side
example: His room is along the corridor.

translation: 腐败的（为了金钱或利益而愿意利用权力做不诚实或违法之事的）
definition: willing to use their power to do dishonest or illegal things in return for money or to get an advantage
example: It was seen as the only way to overthrow a corrupt regime.

translation: 腐败（不诚实或违法的行为，尤指权力部门人员）
definition: dishonest or illegal behaviour, especially of people in authority
example: allegations of bribery and corruption

translation: 成本，费用（购买、制造或做某事所需的金额）
definition: the amount of money that you need in order to buy, make or do something
example: cost of something, the high/low cost of housing

translation: 花费（如果某物花费一定金额，指你需要支付该数额才能买、做或制造它）
definition: if something costs a particular amount of money, you need to pay that amount in order to buy, make or do it
example: cost something, How much did it cost?

translation: 昂贵的（花费很多钱，尤指超过你所愿支付的）
definition: costing a lot of money, especially more than you want to pay
example: Buying new furniture may prove too costly.

translation: 服装（特定地区或历史时期的穿着）
definition: the clothes worn by people from a particular place or during a particular historical period
example: an exhibition of Victorian costumes

translation: 小屋（小房子，尤指在农村）
definition: a small house, especially in the country
example: a thatched cottage

translation: 棉花（热带植物，其种子周围的软白毛用于制作布料和线）
definition: a plant grown in warm countries for the soft white hairs around its seeds that are used to make cloth and thread
example: From the age of six she worked in the fields, picking cotton.

translation: 能够（can的过去式）
definition: used as the past tense of ‘can’
example: She said that she couldn't come.

translation: 委员会，政务会（选出以管理城市或县等地区的团体）
definition: a group of people who are elected to govern an area such as a city or county
example: a town council

translation: 议员（市或县委员会的成员）
definition: a member of a city or county council
example: Councillor Ann Jones

translation: 心理咨询（关于问题的专业建议）
definition: professional advice about a problem
example: The couple decided to go for relationship counselling.

translation: 顾问，辅导员（经过培训为有个人等问题的人提供建议的人）
definition: a person who has been trained to advise people with problems, especially personal problems
example: I went to see a debt counsellor and she agreed to come to the bank with me.

translation: 计数（计数以找出总数的行为）
definition: an act of counting to find the total number of somebody/something
example: If the election result is close, there will be a second count.

translation: 计数（按正确顺序说出数字）
definition: to say numbers in the correct order
example: Billy can't count yet.

translation: 柜台（商店、银行等进行交易的长平表面）
definition: a long flat surface over which goods are sold or business is done in a shop, bank, etc.
example: behind the counter, I asked the woman behind the counter if they had any postcards.

translation: 反驳（通过试图证明对方所说不实来回应某人）
definition: to reply to somebody by trying to prove that what they said is not true
example: counter somebody/something, Such arguments are not easily countered.

translation: 对应的人或物（在不同地点或情况下具有相同职位或功能的人或物）
definition: a person or thing that has the same position or function as somebody/something else in a different place or situation
example: The Foreign Minister held talks with his Chinese counterpart.

translation: 无数的（极多的；多得数不清或说不完的）
definition: very many; too many to be counted or mentioned
example: I've warned her countless times.

translation: 国家（拥有或曾拥有自己政府和法律的一块陆地区域）
definition: an area of land that has or used to have its own government and laws
example: European countries

translation: 农村（城镇以外的有田野、树林等的土地）
definition: land outside towns and cities, with fields, woods, etc.
example: The surrounding countryside is windswept and rocky.

translation: 县，郡（一些国家划分出的行政区域，各设地方政府）
definition: one of a number of areas that some countries are divided into, each with its own local government
example: rural counties west of the Mississippi

translation: 政变（非法且通常伴随暴力的突然政权更迭）
definition: a sudden change of government that is illegal and often violent
example: He seized power in a military coup in 2008.

translation: 两个，几个（两个人或事物；几个）
definition: two people or things
example: I saw a couple of men get out.

translation: 勇气（在不表现出恐惧的情况下做危险之事或面对痛苦、反对的能力）
definition: the ability to do something dangerous, or to face pain or opposition, without showing fear
example: He showed great courage and determination.

translation: 课程（关于特定主题的一系列课或讲座）
definition: a series of lessons or lectures on a particular subject
example: a French/chemistry course

translation: 法院，法庭（进行法律审判及裁决犯罪等的地方）
definition: the place where legal trials take place and where crimes, etc. are judged
example: the civil/criminal courts

translation: 礼貌，谦恭（表现出对他人的尊敬的礼貌行为）
definition: polite behaviour that shows respect for other people
example: I was treated with the utmost courtesy by the staff.

translation: 堂/表兄弟姐妹（姨妈或叔叔的孩子）
definition: a child of your aunt or uncle
example: She's my cousin.

translation: 覆盖物，封面（放在另一物之上或其上的东西，通常为了保护或装饰）
definition: a thing that is put over or on another thing, usually to protect it or to decorate it
example: Brighten up your room with some colourful cushion covers.

translation: 覆盖（将某物置于另一物之上或前面以隐藏、保护或装饰）
definition: to place something over or in front of something in order to hide, protect or decorate it
example: cover something with something, Cover the chicken loosely with foil.

translation: 报道（媒体对新闻和体育的报道）
definition: the reporting of news and sport in the media
example: media/newspaper/press coverage

translation: 覆盖着的（其上有某一层或一定量的东西）
definition: having a layer or amount of something on it
example: His face was covered in blood.

translation: 奶牛（农场饲养的大型动物，用于产奶或牛肉）
definition: a large animal kept on farms to produce milk or beef
example: to milk a cow

translation: 裂纹（物体表面破裂但未完全碎开的线）
definition: a line on the surface of something where it has broken but not split into separate parts
example: This cup has a crack in it.

translation: 使破裂（破裂但未完全碎开；以此方式弄破某物）
definition: to break without dividing into separate parts; to break something in this way
example: The ice cracked as I stepped onto it.

translation: 手工艺（涉及手工制作物品的特殊技能的活动）
definition: an activity involving a special skill at making things with your hands
example: traditional crafts like basket-weaving

translation: 精心制作（利用特殊技能――尤指手工――制作某物）
definition: to make something using special skills, especially with your hands
example: be crafted (from something), All the furniture is crafted from natural materials.

translation: 撞击，坠毁（车辆撞上某物――如另一辆车――的事故）
definition: an accident in which a vehicle hits something, for example another vehicle, usually causing damage and often injuring or killing the passengers
example: a car/plane crash

translation: 撞击，坠毁（如果车辆撞击，指其撞上了物体或另一辆车并造成损坏）
definition: if a vehicle crashes or the driver crashes it, it hits an object or another vehicle, causing damage
example: I was terrified that the plane would crash.

translation: 爬行（手脚着地或贴地向前移动）
definition: to move forward on your hands and knees or with your body close to the ground
example: Our baby is just starting to crawl.

translation: 疯狂的（不明智的；愚蠢的）
definition: not sensible; stupid
example: Are you crazy? We could get killed doing that.

translation: 米色的（介于黄色和白色之间的颜色）
definition: between yellow and white in colour
example: a cream linen suit

translation: 奶油（牛奶表面上升的厚白色或淡黄色脂肪液体，用于烹饪或调味）
definition: the thick white or pale yellow fatty liquid that rises to the top of milk, used in cooking or as a type of sauce to put on fruit, etc.
example: We had strawberries and cream for dessert.

translation: 创造（使某事发生或存在）
definition: to make something happen or exist
example: Scientists disagree about how the universe was created.

translation: 创造，创作（制造新事物或使原本不存在的事物存在的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of making something that is new, or of causing something to exist that did not exist before
example: Job creation needs to be the top priority.

translation: 创造性的（涉及使用技能和想象力来产生新事物或艺术作品）
definition: involving the use of skill and the imagination to produce something new or a work of art
example: a course on creative writing (= writing stories, plays and poems)

translation: 创造力（使用技能和想象力来产生新事物或艺术）
definition: the use of skill and imagination to produce something new or to produce art
example: Creativity and originality are more important than technical skill.

translation: 创造者（制造或发明了某特定事物的人）
definition: a person who has made or invented a particular thing
example: Walt Disney, the creator of Mickey Mouse

translation: 生物（可以移动的真实或想象的生命体，如动物）
definition: a living thing, real or imaginary, that can move around, such as an animal
example: respect for all living creatures

translation: 信誉（某人/某物具有的使人相信或信任的品质）
definition: the quality that somebody/something has that makes people believe or trust them
example: to gain/lack/lose credibility

translation: 可信的（可以被相信或信任的）
definition: that can be believed or trusted
example: a credible explanation/witness

translation: 信用（例如与商店达成的先取货后付钱的安排）
definition: an arrangement that you make, with a shop for example, to pay later for something you buy
example: to get credit

translation: 存入（将一笔钱加入某人的银行账户）
definition: to add an amount of money to somebody’s bank account
example: credit something, They credited my account two days later.

translation: 轻手轻脚地走（缓慢、安静且小心地移动，因不想被看见或听见）
definition: to move slowly, quietly and carefully, because you do not want to be seen or heard
example: I crept up the stairs, trying not to wake my parents.

translation: 全体船员/机组人员（在船、飞机等上工作的所有人员）
definition: all the people working on a ship, plane, etc.
example: crew members

translation: 犯罪（涉及触犯法律的活动）
definition: activities that involve breaking the law
example: This month's figures show an increase in violent crime.

translation: 犯罪的（与犯罪有关或涉及犯罪的）
definition: connected with or involving crime
example: criminal offences/activities

translation: 罪犯（实施犯罪的人）
definition: a person who commits a crime
example: a convicted criminal

translation: 危机（必须解决问题或做出重大决定的大型危险、困难或怀疑时刻）
definition: a time of great danger, difficulty or doubt when problems must be solved or important decisions must be made
example: an economic/a financial crisis

translation: 标准（评判某事或帮助做出决定的准则或原则）
definition: a standard or principle by which something is judged, or with the help of which a decision is made
example: The main criterion is value for money.

translation: 评论家（对书籍、音乐等优劣发表评论的人）
definition: a person who expresses opinions about the good and bad qualities of books, music, etc.
example: a film/an art/a music critic

translation: 批评的，批判性的（表达你认为某人/某事不好的看法）
definition: saying what you think is bad about somebody/something
example: You should just ignore any critical comments.

translation: 批评地（以表达你认为某人/某事不好的方式）
definition: in a way that says what you think is bad about somebody/something
example: She spoke critically of her father.

translation: 批评（表达对某人/某事的不认可及对其缺点的看法；这种不认可的陈述）
definition: the act of expressing disapproval of somebody/something and opinions about their faults or bad qualities; a statement showing this disapproval
example: to draw/face/receive criticism

translation: 批评（说你认为某人/某事不好；指出你认为不对或不喜欢的地方）
definition: to say that you think somebody/something is bad; to say what you do not like or think is wrong about somebody/something
example: All you ever do is criticize!

translation: 评论文章（对一套想法、艺术作品等进行书面批评的文章）
definition: a piece of written criticism of a set of ideas, a work of art, etc.
example: She wrote a feminist critique of Freud's theories.

translation: 农作物（大量种植的植物，尤指作为食物）
definition: a plant that is grown in large quantities, especially as food
example: Sugar is an important crop on the island.

translation: 十字，叉（由两条线交叉形成的标记或物体；常用于在纸上标示某物）
definition: a mark or an object formed by two lines crossing each other (X or +); the mark (X) is often used on paper to show something
example: I've put a cross on the map to show where the hotel is.

translation: 横过，穿越（穿过；从一侧经过或延伸到另一侧）
definition: to go across; to pass or stretch from one side to the other
example: As soon as traffic slowed down enough to safely cross, I started walking.

translation: 人群（聚集在公共场所的一大群人，如在街上或体育赛场）
definition: a large number of people gathered together in a public place, for example in the streets or at a sports game
example: He pushed his way through the crowd.

translation: 拥挤的（有很多人或太多人的）
definition: having a lot of people or too many people
example: We made our way through the crowded streets.

translation: 王冠（国王或女王在正式场合戴在头上的通常由黄金和宝石制成的圆状物）
definition: an object in the shape of a circle, usually made of gold and precious stones, that a king or queen wears on his or her head on official occasions
example: The crown was placed upon the new monarch's head.

translation: 至关重要的（极其重要，因为它会影响其他事情）
definition: extremely important, because it will affect other things
example: The next few weeks are going to be crucial.

translation: 天然的，原生的（处于自然状态，未经加工或精炼的）
definition: in its natural state, before it has been processed or refined
example: crude oil/metal

translation: 残忍的（渴望造成身体或心理痛苦并使人受苦的）
definition: having a desire to cause physical or mental pain and make somebody suffer
example: He was known to be a cruel dictator.

translation: 邮轮游（乘船游览不同地方的旅行，尤其是作为度假）
definition: a journey by sea, visiting different places, especially as a holiday
example: I'd love to go on a round-the-world cruise.

translation: 乘船游览（乘船访问不同地方，尤其是作为度假）
definition: to travel in a ship or boat visiting different places, especially as a holiday
example: (+ adv./prep.), They cruised down the Nile.

translation: 压碎（用力挤压某物使其损坏或变形）
definition: to press something so hard that it is damaged or injured, or loses its shape
example: The car was completely crushed under the truck.

translation: 叫喊（表达强烈情感的无词响声）
definition: a loud sound without words that expresses a strong feeling
example: cry of something, to give a cry of anguish/despair/pain/joy/alarm, etc.

translation: 哭（因不快乐或疼痛而流泪）
definition: to produce tears from your eyes because you are unhappy or hurt
example: It's all right. Don't cry.

translation: 结晶，晶体（物质自然凝固时形成的带平面的小块，如冰晶）
definition: a small piece of a substance with many even sides, that is formed naturally when the substance becomes solid
example: ice/salt crystals

translation: 信号，提示（作为信号提示某人做某事的行动或事件）
definition: an action or event that is a signal for somebody to do something
example: cue (for something), Jon's arrival was a cue for more champagne.

translation: 崇拜的，小众追捧的（在特定群体中非常受欢迎的）
definition: very popular with a particular group of people
example: a cult movie/book

translation: 狂热，崇拜（变得非常流行的生活方式、态度或想法）
definition: a way of life, an attitude, an idea, etc. that has become very popular
example: the cult of physical fitness

translation: 耕种（准备并利用土地种植植物或庄稼）
definition: to prepare and use land for growing plants or crops
example: The land around here has never been cultivated.

translation: 文化的（与特定社会或群体的文化、习俗、信仰等有关的）
definition: connected with the culture of a particular society or group, its customs, beliefs, etc.
example: Teachers need to be aware of cultural differences.

translation: 文化（特定国家或群体的习俗、信仰、艺术、生活方式和组织）
definition: the customs and beliefs, art, way of life and social organization of a particular country or group
example: African/American/European/Islamic culture

translation: 杯子（碗状的小容器，通常带柄，用于喝茶、咖啡等）
definition: a small container that is like a bowl in shape, usually with a handle, used for drinking tea, coffee, etc.
example: He filled the cup with water.

translation: 橱柜（带有门和搁板的用于存放餐具、食物、衣服等的家具）
definition: a piece of furniture with doors and shelves used for storing dishes, food, clothes, etc.
example: kitchen cupboards

translation: 药物，疗法（治愈疾病的药物或医疗手段）
definition: a medicine or medical treatment that cures an illness
example: cure for something, the search for a cure for cancer

translation: 治愈（在疾病后使人或动物恢复健康）
definition: to make a person or an animal healthy again after an illness
example: cure somebody, Will you be able to cure him, Doctor?

translation: 好奇心（想了解某事的强烈欲望）
definition: a strong desire to know about something
example: Children show curiosity about everything.

translation: 好奇的（有想了解某事的强烈欲望的）
definition: having a strong desire to know about something
example: He is such a curious boy, always asking questions.

translation: 卷曲的（有很多卷曲或呈弯曲形状的）
definition: having a lot of curls or a curved shape
example: long curly hair

translation: 货币（国家使用的货币制度）
definition: the system of money that a country uses
example: trading in foreign currencies

translation: 当前的（现在发生的；当今时代的）
definition: happening now; of the present time
example: The necklace would be worth over $5?000 at current prices.

translation: 洋流，气流（海洋或河流中水的移动；朝特定方向的空气移动）
definition: the movement of water in the sea or a river; the movement of air in a particular direction
example: with the current, It's easier to go with the current.

translation: 当前（在现时）
definition: at the present time
example: The hourly charge is currently ￡35.

translation: 课程（课程或学校中教授的科目）
definition: the subjects that are included in a course of study or taught in a school, college, etc.
example: The school curriculum should be as broad as possible.

translation: 窗帘（挂起来遮挡窗口的布料）
definition: a piece of cloth that is hung to cover a window
example: to draw/pull/close the curtains (= to pull them across the window so they cover it)

translation: 曲线（逐渐弯曲的线条或表面；平滑的弯曲）
definition: a line or surface that bends gradually; a smooth bend
example: curve of something, He admired the delicate curve of her ear.

translation: 弯曲（以曲线形状移动或使之移动；呈曲线形状）
definition: to move or make something move in the shape of a curve; to be in the shape of a curve
example: a curving staircase

translation: 弯曲的（呈圆形的）
definition: having a round shape
example: a curved edge/surface

translation: 监护，拘留（照顾或保管某人/某物的法律权利或义务；照顾的行为）
definition: the legal right or duty to take care of or keep somebody/something; the act of taking care of something/somebody
example: Who will have custody of the children?

translation: 习俗（社会或社区中公认的行事或表现方式）
definition: an accepted way of behaving or of doing things in a society or a community
example: It's a local custom.

translation: 顾客（从商店或企业购买商品或服务的个人或组织）
definition: a person or an organization that buys goods or services from a shop or business
example: marketing strategies to target potential customers

translation: 切口，伤口（由锋利物品造成的伤口）
definition: a wound caused by something sharp
example: cuts and bruises on the face

translation: 切，割（在某物上弄出开口或伤口，尤指用刀或剪刀）
definition: to make an opening or a wound in something, especially with a sharp tool such as a knife or scissors
example: cut something, She cut her finger on a piece of glass.

translation: 可爱的（漂亮且吸引人的）
definition: pretty and attractive
example: a cute little baby

translation: 剪报（从报纸或杂志上剪下的文章或故事）
definition: an article or a story that you cut from a newspaper or magazine and keep
example: newspaper/press cuttings

translation: 自行车，摩托车（两轮车辆）
definition: a bicycle or motorcycle
example: He was riding his cycle home when he was hit by a lorry.

translation: 骑自行车（骑自行车或通过其旅行）
definition: to ride a bicycle; to travel by bicycle
example: measures to encourage more people to cycle

translation: 愤世嫉俗的，悲观的（认为人们做事仅出于自私而非诚实动机的）
definition: believing that people only do things to help themselves rather than for good or honest reasons
example: a cynical view/smile

translation: 爸爸（父亲）
definition: father
example: That's my dad over there.

translation: 每日的（每天发生、执行或制作的）
definition: happening, done or produced every day
example: Many people still read a daily newspaper.

translation: 每日地（每天）
definition: every day
example: The machines are inspected twice daily.

translation: 奶制的（由牛奶制成的）
definition: made from milk
example: dairy products/produce

translation: 奶制品（牛奶、奶酪及其他乳制品）
definition: milk, cheese and other milk products
example: The doctor told me to eat less red meat and dairy.

translation: 大坝，堤坝（横跨河流以拦截水流的屏障，常用于水库或发电）
definition: a barrier that is built across a river in order to stop the water from flowing, used especially to make a reservoir (= a lake for storing water) or to produce electricity
example: the Narmada dam in India

translation: 损坏，破坏（对某物造成的物理伤害，使其价值降低）
definition: physical harm caused to something which makes it less attractive, useful or valuable
example: serious/severe damage

translation: 损害，伤害（对某人/某物产生不良或有害影响）
definition: to have a bad or harmful effect on something/somebody
example: The church was badly damaged by the 1997 earthquake.

translation: 破坏性的（造成损坏的；有不良影响的）
definition: causing damage; having a bad effect on somebody/something
example: damaging consequences/effects

translation: 舞蹈（伴随音乐进行的一系列动作和步伐）
definition: a series of movements and steps that are usually performed to music; a particular example of these movements and steps
example: Do you know any other Latin American dances?

translation: 跳舞（随音乐的声音和节奏移动身体）
definition: to move your body to the sound and rhythm of music
example: Do you want to dance?

translation: 舞者（跳舞的人或以此为业的人）
definition: a person who dances or whose job is dancing
example: She's a fantastic dancer.

translation: 跳舞（随音乐移动身体的行为）
definition: moving your body to music
example: There was music and dancing till two in the morning.

translation: 危险（可能造成伤害、死亡或破坏的可能性）
definition: the possibility of something happening that will injure, harm or kill somebody, or damage or destroy something
example: Danger! Keep Out!

translation: 危险的（可能伤害某人或破坏某物的）
definition: likely to injure or harm somebody, or to damage or destroy something
example: The situation is extremely dangerous.

translation: 敢（勇敢地去做某事）
definition: to be brave enough to do something
example: She said it as loudly as she dared.

translation: 黑暗的（光线很少或没有的，尤指在夜晚）
definition: with no or very little light, especially because it is night
example: a dark room/street/forest/night

translation: 黑暗（地方缺乏光亮的状态，尤指在夜晚）
definition: the lack of light in a place, especially because it is night
example: Are the children afraid of the dark?

translation: 黑暗（处于黑暗、无光的状态）
definition: the state of being dark, without any light
example: After a few minutes our eyes got used to the darkness.

translation: 数据，资料（事实或信息，尤指经过检查用于决策或发现事实的）
definition: facts or information, especially when examined and used to find out things or to make decisions
example: We collected publicly available data over a 10-day period.

translation: 数据库（存储在电脑中并可以多种方式查看使用的有组织的数据集）
definition: an organized set of data that is stored in a computer and can be looked at and used in various ways
example: The database is updated monthly.

translation: 日期（特定的日期，有时包括年份）
definition: a particular day of the month, sometimes in a particular year, given in numbers and words
example: ‘What's the date today?’ ‘The 10th.’

translation: 注明日期（在某物上写上或印上日期）
definition: to write or print the date on something
example: Thank you for your letter dated 24th March.

translation: 女儿（女性孩子）
definition: a person’s female child
example: We have two sons and a daughter.

translation: 黎明（光线初现的时间点）
definition: the time of day when light first appears
example: at dawn, They start work at dawn.

translation: 天，白昼（24小时的时间段）
definition: a period of 24 hours
example: ‘What day is it today?’ ‘Monday.’

translation: 死的（不再活着的）
definition: no longer alive
example: My mother's dead; she died in 2017.

translation: 截止日期（必须完成某事的时间点）
definition: a point in time by which something must be done
example: I prefer to work to a deadline.

translation: 致命的（造成或可能造成死亡的）
definition: causing or likely to cause death
example: a deadly weapon/disease

translation: 交易，协议（尤指商业中关于买卖或做事的特定条件的协议）
definition: an agreement, especially in business, on particular conditions for buying or doing something
example: to sign/strike/finalize/close a deal

translation: 发牌（在纸牌游戏中给每个玩家分牌）
definition: to give cards to each player in a game of cards
example: Whose turn is it to deal?

translation: 商人，交易商（以买卖特定产品为业的人）
definition: a person whose business is buying and selling a particular product
example: an art/antique dealer

translation: 亲爱的（信件开头，置于称呼前）
definition: used at the beginning of a letter before the name or title of the person that you are writing to
example: Dear Sir or Madam

translation: 天哪（用于表达惊讶、沮丧、烦恼或忧虑）
definition: used in expressions that show that you are surprised, upset, annoyed or worried
example: Oh dear! I think I've lost my purse!

translation: 死亡（某人死亡或被杀的事实）
definition: the fact of somebody dying or being killed
example: the anniversary of his wife’s death

translation: 辩论（在公共会议或议会中对问题的正式讨论）
definition: a formal discussion of an issue at a public meeting or in a parliament. In a debate two or more speakers express opposite views and then there is often a vote on the issue.
example: the first ever televised presidential debate

translation: 辩论（正式讨论某事以做出决定或寻找方案）
definition: to discuss something, especially formally, before making a decision or finding a solution
example: debate (something), Politicians will be debating the bill later this week.

translation: 残骸，碎片（某物被毁后留下的木头、金属等碎片）
definition: pieces of wood, metal, building materials, etc. that are left after something has been destroyed
example: Emergency teams are still clearing the debris from the plane crash.

translation: 债务（欠他人的钱款总额）
definition: a sum of money that somebody owes
example: to pay/repay a debt

translation: 首演，处女秀（演艺人员或运动员的首次公开亮相）
definition: the first public appearance of a performer or sports player
example: He will make his debut for the first team this week.

translation: 十年（十年的时间，如1910-1919年）
definition: a period of ten years, especially a continuous period, such as 1910C1919 or 2000C2009
example: the early decades of the nineteenth century

translation: 十二月（一年中的最后一个月）
definition: the 12th and last month of the year
example: She was born in December.

translation: 体面的，像样的（具有足够好的标准或质量的）
definition: of a good enough standard or quality
example: a decent meal/place to live

translation: 决定（仔细考虑各种可能性并做出选择）
definition: to think carefully about the different possibilities that are available and choose one of them
example: It's up to you to decide.

translation: 决定（在思考和讨论什么是最好做法后做出的选择或判断）
definition: a choice or judgement that you make after thinking and talking about what is the best thing to do
example: I think I've made the right decision.

translation: 决策（决定重要事情的过程，尤指在群体或组织中）

translation: 决定性的（对特定情况最终结果至关重要的）

translation: 声明，宣言（官方或正式的陈述，尤指关于政府计划；这种陈述行为）
definition: an official or formal statement, especially about the plans of a government or an organization; the act of making such a statement

translation: 宣布，声明（正式或公开地表达某事）
definition: to say something officially or publicly

translation: 装饰品（在特殊场合使某物看起来更有吸引力的物品）

translation: 减少（减少某物的过程；缩减的数额）
definition: the process of reducing something; the amount that something is reduced by

translation: 减少（在规模、数量等方面变小；使某物变小）
definition: to become smaller in size, number, etc.; to make something smaller in size, number, etc.
example: Donations have decreased significantly over the past few years.

translation: 献身的，专注的（因为某事对你很重要而努力工作）

translation: 奉献（因认为重要而投入到某项活动或目标中的辛勤工作和努力）
definition: the hard work and effort that somebody puts into an activity or a purpose because they think it is important

translation: 行为，事迹（某人所做的通常是非常好或非常坏的事）

translation: 认为，视作（对某人/某物持有特定看法）

translation: 深深地（在某物表面之下很远或进入某物内部很深处）

translation: 深深地，非常（很大程度上）

translation: 默认（在没有做出其他选择时发生或出现的情况，尤指在电脑程序中）

translation: 失败，战败（未能获胜或成功）

translation: 击败，战胜（在战争、比赛或运动中赢过某人）

definition: a fault in something or in the way it has been made that means that it is not perfect

translation: 防御，防御工事（保护某人/某物免受攻击、批评的行为）
definition: the act of protecting somebody/something from attack, criticism, etc.

translation: 保卫，防御（保护某人/某物免受攻击）
definition: to protect somebody/something from attack
example: defend somebody/something, The role of the military is to defend the country.

translation: 后卫，维护者（在球类运动中阻止对方得分的球员；或人权的维护者）
definition: a player who must stop the other team from scoring in games such as football (soccer), hockey, etc.

translation: 防御性的（保护某人/某物免受攻击的）

translation: 缺乏，不足（没有或没有足够的必需品的状态）

translation: 赤字（特定时期内支出超过收入的数额）
definition: the amount by which money spent or owed is greater than money earned in a particular period of time

definition: to say or explain what the meaning of a word or phrase is

translation: 确定的（确信的；不太可能改变的）

translation: 肯定，无疑（强调某事属实且毫无疑问的方式）

translation: 定义（对词语含义的解释，尤指词典中的）
definition: an explanation of the meaning of a word or phrase, especially in a dictionary

definition: to refuse to obey or show respect for somebody in authority, a law, a rule, etc.

definition: to remove something that has been written or printed, or that has been stored on a computer

translation: 故意地（以计划好的而非偶然的方式）

translation: 递送（将货物、信件等送到人手中的行为）
definition: the act of taking goods, letters, etc. to the people they have been sent to

translation: 民主的（由民选代表控制的；与此制度相关的）

translation: 密度（密集的性质；密集的程度）

translation: 描绘（在图片中展示某人/某物的形象）

translation: 部署（将士兵或武器调到准备战斗的位置）
definition: to move soldiers or weapons into a position where they are ready for military action
example: 2?000 troops were deployed in the area.

translation: 部署（将士兵或武器调到准备战斗位置的行为）
definition: the act of moving soldiers or weapons into a position where they are ready for military action
example: the deployment of peacekeeping forces

translation: 定金（作为总款项的第一部分支付的钱）

下降（从高处向低处移动）

translation: 下降（向下移动的动作）
definition: an action of coming or going down

translation: 描述（说明某人/某物是什么样的）

translation: 描述（说明某人/某物是什么样的文字或言语；这种说明行为）

definition: to leave somebody without help or support

definition: the general arrangement of the different parts of something that is made, such as a building, book, machine, etc.

translation: 绝望的（感到或表现出几乎没有希望且准备不顾危险做任何事）

translation: 绝望地（以表现出几乎没有希望且不顾危险的方式）

example: She looked desperately around for a weapon.

translation: 破坏性的（造成破坏或损坏的）

translation: 详述（列出某事的事实或所有可用信息）

translation: 详细的（提供许多细节和信息的；非常注重细节的）

translation: 发现，侦察（发现或察觉某事的过程；被发现的事实）
definition: the process of discovering or noticing something, especially something that is not easy to see, hear, etc.; the fact of being discovered or noticed

definition: to gradually grow or become bigger, more advanced, stronger, etc.; to make something do this

definition: the steady growth of something so that it becomes more advanced, stronger, etc.

translation: 设备，装置（为了完成特定工作而设计的物体或设备）
definition: an object or a piece of equipment that has been designed to do a particular job
example: a tracking/recording/listening device

translation: 魔鬼（最强大的邪恶存在）
definition: the most powerful evil being
example: belief in the Devil

translation: 设计，构思（发明新事物或新的做事方式）
definition: to invent something new or a new way of doing something
example: A new system has been devised to control traffic in the city.

诊断（确切说明疾病是什么或问题的原因是什么）
definition: to say exactly what an illness or the cause of a problem is

translation: 日记（记录每天经历、私人想法等的本子）
definition: a book in which you can write down the experiences you have each day, your private thoughts, etc.
