translation: 合身（尺寸或形状对某人/某物合适）
definition: to be the right shape and size for somebody/something
example: I tried the dress on but it didn't fit.

translation: 健康，强健（身体健康且强壮的状态）
definition: the state of being physically healthy and strong
example: a magazine on health and fitness

translation: 五（数字5）
example: There are only five cookies left.

translation: 解决方法（问题的解决方案，尤指简便或暂时的）
definition: a solution to a problem, especially an easy or temporary one
example: Luckily there is an easy fix.

translation: 修理，固定（修理或纠正某物）
definition: to repair or correct something
example: The car won't start―can you fix it?

translation: 固定的（保持不变的；不能改变的）
definition: staying the same; not changing or able to be changed
example: These fixed prices give farmers a degree of financial security.

translation: 常规赛，固定项目（安排在特定日期和地点进行的体育赛事）
definition: a sports event that has been arranged to take place on a particular date and at a particular place
example: There are plans to make the race an annual fixture.

translation: 旗帜（带有特定颜色设计的布片，作为国家、组织的象征或信号）
definition: a piece of cloth with a special coloured design on it that may be the symbol of a particular country or organization, may be used to give a signal or may have a particular meaning. A flag can be attached to a pole (= a long thin straight piece of wood or metal) or held in the hand.
example: the Italian flag

translation: 火焰（从燃烧物体中冒出的炽热明亮的气流）
definition: a hot bright stream of burning gas that comes from something that is on fire
example: the tiny yellow flame of a match

translation: 闪光（瞬间闪烁随后消失的突然强光）
definition: a sudden bright light that shines for a moment and then disappears
example: a flash of lightning

translation: 闪烁（短时间内发出非常亮的光；使某物闪光）
definition: to shine very brightly for a short time; to make something shine in this way
example: Lightning flashed in the distance.

translation: 平坦的（表面平整，无弯曲、倾斜、孔洞或突出的）
definition: having a level surface, not curved or sloping, and without holes or any bits sticking out
example: low buildings with flat roofs

translation: 公寓（通常位于建筑一层的一套住房）
definition: a set of rooms for living in, usually on one floor of a building
example: They're renting a furnished flat on the third floor.

translation: 味道，风味（食物或饮料尝起来的味道）
definition: how food or drink tastes
example: The tomatoes give extra flavour to the sauce.

translation: 缺陷，瑕疵（某物中的错误，使其不正确或无法正常工作）
definition: a mistake in something that means that it is not correct or does not work correctly
example: The argument is full of fundamental flaws.

translation: 有缺陷的（有瑕疵的；不完美或不正确的）
definition: having a flaw; not perfect or correct
example: seriously/fundamentally/fatally flawed

translation: 逃跑（极快地离开人或地方，尤指因害怕潜在危险）
definition: to leave a person or place very quickly, especially because you are afraid of possible danger
example: She burst into tears and fled.

translation: 舰队（由同一人指挥的一组军舰）
definition: a group of military ships commanded by the same person
example: a fleet of destroyers

translation: 肉，血肉（动物或人体内皮肤与骨骼之间的柔软物质）
definition: the soft substance between the skin and bones of animal or human bodies
example: The trap had cut deeply into the rabbit's flesh.

translation: 灵活性（适应新条件或新情况的能力）
definition: the ability to change to suit new conditions or situations
example: The new system offers a much greater degree of flexibility in the way work is organized.

translation: 灵活的（能改变以适应新条件或新情况的）
definition: able to change to suit new conditions or situations
example: a more flexible approach

translation: 飞行，航班（空中旅行，尤指乘飞机）
definition: a journey made by air, especially in a plane
example: a smooth/comfortable/bumpy flight

translation: 漂浮（在水面或空气中缓慢移动）
definition: to move slowly on water or in the air
example: A group of swans floated by.

translation: 洪水（覆盖通常干燥区域的大量积水）
definition: a large amount of water covering an area that is usually dry
example: The heavy rain has caused floods in many parts of the country.

translation: 淹没（如果地方被淹没，指其被水充满或覆盖）
definition: if a place floods or something floods it, it becomes filled or covered with water
example: The cellar floods whenever it rains heavily.

translation: 地板，地面（房间内行走的表面）
definition: the surface of a room that you walk on
example: a wooden/concrete/tiled floor

translation: 面粉（由谷物――尤指小麦――磨成的粉末，用于烹饪烘焙）
definition: a fine white or brown powder made from grain, especially wheat, and used in cooking for making bread, cakes, etc.
example: Sift the flour and salt into a bowl.

translation: 繁荣，兴旺（快速发展并变得成功或普遍）
definition: to develop quickly and become successful or common
example: Few businesses are flourishing in the present economic climate.

translation: 流动（某物/某人向一个方向的稳步连续移动）
definition: the steady and continuous movement of something/somebody in one direction
example: the flow of an electric current

translation: 流，流动（稳步且连续地向一个方向移动）
definition: to move steadily and continuously in one direction
example: She lost control and the tears began to flow.

translation: 花（植物中产生种子或果实的彩色部分，通常长在茎端）
definition: the coloured part of a plant from which the seed or fruit develops. Flowers usually grow at the end of a stem and last only a short time.
example: The plant has a beautiful bright red flower.

translation: 流感（由病毒引起的严重疾病，伴有高烧、疼痛和虚弱）
definition: a serious disease caused by a virus, that causes a high temperature, severe pains and weakness
example: The whole family has the flu.

translation: 流体，液体（液体；能流动的物质）
definition: a liquid; a substance that can flow
example: body fluids (= for example, blood)

translation: 苍蝇（有两只翅膀的小型飞行昆虫，常传播疾病）
definition: a small flying insect with two wings. There are many different types of fly and many of them spread disease.
example: A fly was buzzing against the window.

translation: 飞（利用翅膀在空中移动）
definition: to move through the air, using wings
example: Penguins can't fly.

translation: 飞行的（能够飞行的）
definition: able to fly
example: flying insects

translation: 飞行，航空（乘飞机旅行的行为）
definition: travelling in an aircraft
example: I'm terrified of flying.

translation: 焦点，中心（人们最感兴趣的事物或人；给予特别关注的行为）
definition: the thing or person that people are most interested in; the act of paying special attention to something and making people interested in it
example: focus of something, It was the main focus of attention at the meeting.

translation: 集中，聚焦（将注意力、努力等投入到特定主题、情况或人上）
definition: to give attention, effort, etc. to one particular subject, situation or person rather than another
example: She was distracted and finding it hard to focus.

translation: 褶皱（某物――尤指布料――折叠或垂挂产生的部分）
definition: a part of something, especially cloth, that is folded or hangs as if it had been folded
example: the folds of her dress

translation: 折叠（折弯某物――尤指纸或布――使一部分叠在另一部分上）
definition: to bend something, especially paper or cloth, so that one part lies on top of another part
example: fold something, First, fold the paper in half/in two.

translation: 可折叠的（可以折叠以便携带或存放于狭小空间的）
definition: that can be folded, so that it can be carried or stored in a small space
example: a folding chair/bike/knife

translation: 民间的（传统的且属于国家或社区普通人的）
definition: traditional and typical of the ordinary people of a country or community
example: We visited an exhibition of folk art.

translation: 人们，各位（通常指一般的人，或普通劳动阶层）
definition: people in general
example: ordinary working-class folk

translation: 跟随（在某人/某物之后移动或行进）
definition: to come or go after or behind somebody/something
example: follow somebody/something, Follow me please.

translation: 接下来的（紧接着要提到的）
definition: that is/are going to be mentioned next
example: Answer the following questions.

translation: 下述内容（紧接着要提到的事物或人）
definition: the thing or things that you will mention next; the person or people that you will mention next
example: The following is a summary of events.

translation: 在...之后（在特定事件之后或由于该事件）
definition: after or as a result of a particular event
example: He took charge of the family business following his father's death.

translation: 喜爱的（对某人有温暖或爱慕的情感，尤指认识很久的人）
definition: having warm or loving feelings for somebody, especially somebody you have known for a long time
example: Over the years, I have grown quite fond of her.

translation: 食物（人或动物吃的食物）
definition: things that people or animals eat
example: Pat had prepared food and drink for the work party.

translation: 傻瓜（表现或言谈缺乏智慧或良好判断的人）
definition: a person who you think behaves or speaks in a way that lacks intelligence or good judgement
example: Don't be such a fool!

translation: 脚（腿部最低的部分，位于脚踝以下，用于站立移动）
definition: the lowest part of the leg, below the ankle, on which a person or an animal stands
example: My feet are aching.

translation: 素材，片段（电影中展示特定事件的一部分）
definition: part of a film showing a particular event
example: old film footage of the moon landing

translation: 足球（两队各11名球员使用圆球踢入对方球门的比赛）
definition: a game played by two teams of 11 players, using a round ball that players kick up and down the playing field. Teams try to kick the ball into the other team’s goal.
example: The kids were outside playing football.

translation: 为了，给（显示某物预定给谁使用或放在何处）
definition: used to show who is intended to have or use something or where something is intended to be put
example: There's a letter for you.

translation: 禁止（命令某人不做某事；命令某事不得进行）
definition: to order somebody not to do something; to order that something must not be done
example: forbid somebody (from doing something), He forbade them from mentioning the subject again.

translation: 武力，力量（为了获得或实现某事而使用的暴力物理行为）
definition: violent physical action used to obtain or achieve something
example: The release of the hostages could not be achieved without the use of force.

translation: 强迫（使某人做其不想做的事）
definition: to make somebody do something that they do not want to do
example: be forced into doing something, The President was forced into resigning.

translation: 预报，预测（基于现有信息对未来将发生之事的陈述）
definition: a statement about what will happen in the future, based on information that is available now
example: The sales forecasts are encouraging.

translation: 预报，预测（根据现有信息说明你认为未来会发生什么）
definition: to say what you think will happen in the future based on information that you have now
example: forecast something, Experts are forecasting a recovery in the economy.

translation: 外国的（在或来自非本国的国家）
definition: in or from a country that is not your own
example: What foreign languages do you speak?

translation: 外国人（来自不同国家的人）
definition: a person who comes from a different country
example: The fact that I was a foreigner was a big disadvantage.

translation: 森林（覆盖着茂密树木的大片土地）
definition: a large area of land that is thickly covered with trees
example: a tropical/pine forest

translation: 永远（用于表示某种情况或状态将一直存在）
definition: used to say that a particular situation or state will always exist
example: I'll love you forever!

translation: 锻造，建立（投入大量努力使某事成功、稳固且持久）
definition: to put a lot of effort into making something successful or strong so that it will last
example: a move to forge new links between management and workers

translation: 忘记（不记得应该做某事，或忘记带、买应该有的东西）
definition: to not remember to do something that you ought to do, or to bring or buy something that you ought to bring or buy
example: ‘Why weren't you at the meeting?’ ‘Sorry―I forgot.’

translation: 原谅（停止对伤害、困扰或让你不快的人――或你自己――感到生气）
definition: to stop feeling angry with somebody who has done something to harm, annoy or upset you; to stop feeling angry with yourself
example: forgive somebody, Can you ever forgive me?

translation: 叉子（带有柄和三四个尖头的餐具，用于叉取和食用食物）
definition: a tool with a handle and three or four sharp points (called prongs), used for picking up and eating food
example: to eat with a knife and fork

translation: 形式，类型（某事物的种类或品种）
definition: a type or variety of something
example: all the millions of different life forms on the planet today

translation: 形成（以特定方式产生某物或使其具有特定形状）
definition: to produce something in a particular way or make it have a particular shape
example: form something, Bend the wire so that it forms a ‘V’.

translation: 正式的（非常正确且适合官方或重要场合的）
definition: very correct and suitable for official or important occasions
example: ladies in formal evening wear

translation: 格式，安排（某事物的总体安排、计划、设计等）
definition: the general arrangement, plan, design, etc. of something
example: The format of the new quiz show has proved popular.

translation: 形成（形成某物的动作；被形成的过程）
definition: the action of forming something; the process of being formed
example: the formation of a new government

translation: 以前的，前任的（在早期时代存在的）
definition: that existed in earlier times
example: This fine ruin was, in former times, a royal castle.

translation: 以前，从前（在过去；以前被称为...）
definition: in the past
example: Namibia, formerly known as South West Africa

translation: 公式（代表规则或法律的一系列字母、数字或符号）
definition: a series of letters, numbers or symbols that represent a rule or law
example: This formula is used to calculate the area of a circle.

translation: 制定，阐述（仔细地创建或准备某事，特别注重细节）
definition: to create or prepare something carefully, giving particular attention to the details
example: formulate something, to formulate a policy/theory/plan/proposal

translation: 向前，出来（离开某地；出来）
definition: away from a place; out
example: They set forth at dawn.

translation: 即将到来的（很快将发生、出版等的）
definition: going to happen, be published, etc. very soon
example: the forthcoming elections

translation: 幸运的（拥有或带来优势、机会、好运等的）
definition: having or bringing an advantage, an opportunity, a piece of good luck, etc.
example: Remember those less fortunate than yourselves.

translation: 幸运地（靠好运气）
definition: by good luck
example: I was late, but fortunately the meeting hadn't started.

translation: 财产，财富（一大笔钱）
definition: a large amount of money
example: He made a fortune in real estate.

translation: 四十（数字40）
论坛（人们可以就特定问题交换意见和想法的场合或媒介）
definition: an event or medium where people can exchange opinions and ideas on a particular issue; a meeting organized for this purpose
example: forum (on something), to hold an international forum on drug abuse

translation: 向前的（指向或朝向前方移动的）
definition: directed or moving towards the front
example: The door opened, blocking his forward movement.

translation: 向前（朝向前方的位置或位置）
definition: towards a place or position that is in front
example: She leaned forward and kissed him on the cheek.

translation: 化石（变成岩石的死后动物或植物的部分）
definition: the parts of a dead animal or a plant that have become hard and turned into rock
example: fossils over two million years old

translation: 培养，促进（鼓励某事发展）
definition: to encourage something to develop
example: The club's aim is to foster better relations within the community.

translation: 创立，建立（创办组织或机构，尤指通过提供资金）
definition: to start something, such as an organization or an institution, especially by providing money
example: to found a club/company/school

translation: 基础（某事物基于其上并由此发展的原则、想法或事实）
definition: a principle, an idea or a fact that something is based on and that it grows from
example: Respect and friendship provide a solid foundation for marriage.

translation: 创始人（创办组织、机构等或发起某项建设的人）
definition: a person who starts an organization, institution, etc. or causes something to be built
example: the founder and president of the company

translation: 四（数字4）
十四（数字14）
第四（序数词4th）
definition: 4th
example: Today is the fourth (of May).

translation: 小部分，分数（某物的一小部分或少量）
definition: a small part or amount of something
example: Only a small fraction of a bank's total deposits will be withdrawn at any one time.

translation: 易碎的（容易破碎或损坏的）
definition: easily broken or damaged
example: fragile china/glass/bones

translation: 碎片（从某物上折断或脱落的小部分）
definition: a small part of something that has broken off or comes from something larger
example: fragment (of something), Police found fragments of glass near the scene.

translation: 框架，框（固定图片、门、玻璃等位置的坚固边缘或结构）
definition: a strong border or structure of wood, metal, etc. that holds a picture, door, piece of glass, etc. in position
example: a picture/photo frame

translation: 给...装框（在某物周围放置或制作框架）
definition: to put or make a frame or border around something
example: be framed, The photograph had been framed.

translation: 框架，结构（建筑或物体中支撑重量并赋予形状的部分）
definition: the parts of a building or an object that support its weight and give it shape
example: built on a wooden framework

translation: 特许经营权（公司给予他人销售其商品/服务的正式许可；或政府给出的经营许可）
definition: formal permission given by a company to somebody who wants to sell its goods or services in a particular area; formal permission given by a government to somebody who wants to operate a public service as a business
example: a franchise agreement/company

translation: 坦率地（以诚实、直接但可能不讨人喜欢的方式）
definition: in an honest and direct way that people might not like
example: He spoke frankly about the ordeal.

translation: 欺诈（为了非法获得金钱或商品而欺骗他人的罪行）
definition: the crime of cheating somebody in order to get money or goods illegally
example: She was charged with credit card fraud.

translation: 空闲的（没有特别计划或安排的；不忙的）
definition: without particular plans or arrangements; not busy
example: Are you free on Saturday? We're having a barbecue.

translation: 免费地（无需付费地）
definition: without payment
example: Children under five travel free.

translation: 释放（允许某人离开监狱或违背其意愿被关押的地方）
definition: to allow somebody to leave prison or somewhere they have been kept against their will
example: free somebody, The hijackers agreed to free a further ten hostages.

translation: 自由（在没有阻碍的情况下做或说你想做之事的权力或权利）
definition: the power or right to do or say what you want without anyone stopping you
example: to defend/protect academic freedom

translation: 自由地（在没有人试图阻碍或控制的情况下）
definition: without anyone trying to prevent or control something
example: the country’s first freely elected president

translation: 冻结（因极冷而变得坚硬，常转变为冰；使某物这样做）
definition: to become hard, and often turn to ice, as a result of extreme cold; to make something do this
example: Water freezes at 0°C.

translation: 频率（某事发生或重复的速率）
definition: the rate at which something happens or is repeated
example: Fatal road accidents have decreased in frequency over recent years.

translation: 频繁的（经常发生的或经常做某事的）
definition: happening or doing something often
example: He is a frequent visitor to this country.

translation: 经常地（常常地）
definition: often
example: Buses run frequently between the city and the airport.

translation: 新鲜的（最近生产或采摘的，且未经冷冻、干燥或罐装保存的）
definition: recently produced or picked and not frozen, dried or preserved in tins or cans
example: Is this milk fresh?

translation: 星期五（周四之后、周六之前的一天）
definition: the day of the week after Thursday and before Saturday
example: It's Friday today, isn't it?

translation: 冰箱（保持食物寒冷以防变质的电器）
definition: a piece of electrical equipment in which food is kept cold so that it stays fresh
example: The kids tend to raid the fridge when they get home from school.

translation: 朋友（你熟悉且喜欢的人，通常不是家庭成员）
definition: a person you know well and like, and who is not usually a member of your family
example: This is my friend Tom.

translation: 友好的（因为喜欢某人或想帮助某人而表现得和蔼愉快）
definition: behaving in a kind and pleasant way because you like somebody or want to help them
example: a warm and friendly person

translation: 友谊（朋友之间的关系）
definition: a relationship between friends
example: They formed a close friendship at college.

translation: 吓唬（使某人突然感到害怕）
definition: to make somebody suddenly feel afraid
example: frighten (somebody), Sorry, I didn't mean to frighten you.

translation: 受惊的（害怕的；感到恐惧的）
definition: afraid; feeling fear
example: a frightened child

translation: 吓人的（使你感到害怕的）
definition: making you feel afraid
example: a frightening experience/prospect/thought

translation: 青蛙（皮肤光滑、生活在陆地和水中的两栖动物）
definition: a small animal with smooth skin, that lives both on land and in water (= is an amphibian). Frogs have very long back legs for jumping, and no tail.
example: the croaking of frogs

translation: 从，来自（用于说明某人/某物起始的地点）
definition: used to show where somebody/something starts
example: She began to walk away from him.

translation: 前面的（在某物的前部或位于前部的）
definition: on or at the front of something
example: (British English), the front garden

translation: 前部（朝向前方的一面或部分；你首先看到的一面）
definition: the part or side of something that faces forward; the side of something that you look at first
example: The front of the building was covered with ivy.

translation: 冷冻的（保持在极低温度下以保存的）
definition: kept at a very low temperature in order to preserve it
example: frozen peas/fish/pizza

translation: 水果（植物中含种子和柔软内部、可食用的部分，通常味甜）
definition: the part of a plant that consists of one or more seeds and a soft inner part, can be eaten as food and usually tastes sweet
example: tropical fruits, such as bananas and pineapples

translation: 沮丧的（因无法实现目标而感到恼火和不耐烦的）
definition: feeling annoyed and impatient because you cannot do or achieve what you want
example: It's very easy to get frustrated in this job.

translation: 令人沮丧的（使人因无法实现目标而感到恼火和不耐烦的）
definition: causing you to feel annoyed and impatient because you cannot do or achieve what you want
example: It's frustrating to have to wait so long.

translation: 沮丧，挫败感（感到沮丧的情绪）
definition: the feeling of being frustrated
example: in frustration, Dave thumped the table in frustration.

translation: 油炸（在热油脂或油中烹制食物；被油炸）
definition: to cook something in hot fat or oil; to be cooked in hot fat or oil
example: fry (something), fried fish

translation: 燃料（燃烧时产生热量或动力的任何材料）
definition: any material that produces heat or power, usually when it is burnt
example: diesel/jet/rocket fuel

translation: 为...提供动力（为某物提供可燃烧产生热量或动力的材料）
definition: to supply something with material that can be burnt to produce heat or power
example: Uranium is used to fuel nuclear plants.

translation: 实现，履行（做或实现所希望或预期的事情）
definition: to do or achieve what was hoped for or expected
example: to fulfil your dream/ambition/potential

translation: 满的（装满或容纳了尽可能多的；没有空位的）

example: New York’s grid of streets

translation: 悲伤（非常难过的感觉，尤指有人去世时）
definition: a very sad feeling, especially when somebody dies
example: She was overcome with grief when her husband died.

translation: 露齿而笑（灿烂的笑容）
definition: a wide smile
example: She gave a broad grin.

translation: 咧嘴笑（灿烂地笑）
definition: to smile widely
example: They grinned with delight when they heard our news.

translation: 磨碎（在硬表面间或使用机器将某物压碎成细小碎片）
definition: to break or press something into very small pieces between two hard surfaces or using a special machine
example: to grind coffee/corn

translation: 紧握，控制（紧紧握住某人/某物的行为；特定方式）
definition: an act of holding somebody/something tightly; a particular way of doing this
example: Keep a tight grip on the rope.

translation: 紧握（紧紧拿住某物）
definition: to hold something tightly
example: grip something, ‘Please don't go,’ he said, gripping her arm.

translation: 杂货店（出售食品和家居用品的商店；美式英语常指超市）
definition: a shop that sells food and other things used in the home. In American English ‘grocery store’ is often used to mean ‘supermarket’.
example: the corner grocery store

translation: 总的（扣除前的总数，如总重量）
definition: being the total amount of something before anything is taken away
example: gross weight (= including the container or wrapping)

translation: 地面（地球的坚实表面）
definition: the solid surface of the earth
example: on the ground, I found her lying on the ground.

translation: 组，群体（在一起或有某种联系的若干人或物）
definition: a number of people or things that are together in the same place or that are connected in some way
example: group of somebody/something, a group of people/students/friends

translation: 生长，增加（在大小、数量、强度或质量上增加）
definition: to increase in size, number, strength or quality
example: The sector is growing at a phenomenal rate.

translation: 增长（人、动物或植物在生理、心理或情感上的成长过程）
definition: the process in people, animals or plants of growing physically, mentally or emotionally
example: Lack of water will stunt the plant's growth.

translation: 保证，担保（你会做某事或某事将发生的正式承诺）
definition: a formal promise that you will do something or that something will happen
example: They are demanding certain guarantees before they sign the treaty.

translation: 保证（承诺做某事；承诺某事会发生）
definition: to promise to do something; to promise something will happen
example: guarantee something, Basic human rights, including freedom of speech, are now guaranteed.

translation: 卫兵，警卫（保护场所或人、或防止囚犯逃跑的士兵/警察等）
definition: a person, such as a soldier, a police officer or a prison officer, who protects a place or people, or prevents prisoners from escaping
example: prison/border guards

translation: 守卫，保护（保护财产、场所或人免受攻击或危险）
definition: to protect property, places or people from attack or danger
example: Armed officers guarded the entrance.

translation: 游击队员（非正规军的小组成员，通常为改变政权而战）
definition: a member of a small group of soldiers who are not part of an official army and who fight against official soldiers, usually to try to change the government
example: urban guerrillas (= those who fight in towns)

translation: 猜测（在不确定的情况下尝试给出答案或观点）
definition: an attempt to give an answer or an opinion when you cannot be certain if you are right
example: (British English), to have/make a guess

translation: 猜测（在不确定所有事实的情况下尝试给出答案或判断）
definition: to try and give an answer or make a judgement about something without being sure of all the facts
example: I don't really know. I'm just guessing.

translation: 客人（被邀请到家或参加由你付钱的活动的人）
definition: a person that you have invited to your house or to a particular event that you are paying for
example: They only use the dining room when they have guests.

translation: 指导，咨询（给予某人的帮助或建议，尤指来自长辈或经验丰富者）
definition: help or advice that is given to somebody, especially by somebody older or with more experience
example: guidance for teachers on how to use video in the classroom

translation: 导游，向导（向他人指路的人，尤指受雇带游客参观者）
definition: a person who shows other people the way to a place, especially somebody employed to show tourists around interesting places
example: Our tour guide showed us around the old town.

translation: 指引，引导（向某人指路，常通过陪同；或介绍熟悉的地方）
definition: to show somebody the way to a place, often by going with them; to show somebody a place that you know well
example: guide somebody, It's a dangerous route―you'll need someone to guide you.

translation: 指导方针（官方组织给出的说明如何做某事的规则或指示）
definition: a set of rules or instructions that are given by an official organization telling you how to do something, especially something difficult
example: The government has drawn up guidelines for schools during the pandemic.

translation: 内疚（因知道或认为自己做了错事而产生的不快感觉）
definition: the unhappy feelings caused by knowing or thinking that you have done something wrong
example: She had feelings of guilt about leaving her children and going to work.

translation: 内疚的，有罪的（因做错事或未尽责而感到羞愧的；被判有罪的）
definition: feeling ashamed because you have done something that you know is wrong or have not done something that you should have done
example: Matt and Chrissy both looked equally guilty.

translation: 吉他（通常有六根弦、用手指或拨片弹奏的乐器）
definition: a musical instrument that usually has six strings and that you play with your fingers or with a plectrum
example: an acoustic/electric guitar

translation: 枪（用于发射子弹或炮弹的武器）
definition: a weapon that is used for firing bullets or shells
example: I have never fired a gun in my life.

translation: 肠道（食物离开胃后经过的身体管道）
definition: the tube in the body through which food passes when it leaves the stomach
example: It can take up to 72 hours for food to pass through the gut.

translation: 家伙（男子，男人）
definition: a man
example: a big/little guy

translation: 健身房，体育馆（配备健身器材的房间或大厅，如在学校中）
definition: a room or hall with equipment for doing physical exercise, for example in a school
example: The school has recently built a new gym.

translation: 习惯（经常做且几乎不假思索的事，尤指难以戒掉的）
definition: a thing that you do often and almost without thinking, especially something that is hard to stop doing
example: You need to change your eating habits.

translation: 栖息地（特定类型的动物或植物通常被发现的地方）
definition: the place where a particular type of animal or plant is normally found
example: The panda's natural habitat is the bamboo forest.

translation: 称赞（将某人/某物描述为非常好或特别，尤指在报纸等媒介中）
definition: to describe somebody/something as being very good or special, especially in newspapers, etc.
example: be hailed (as) something, The conference was hailed as a great success.

translation: 头发（长在人头上的丝状物质）
definition: the substance that looks like a mass of fine threads growing on a person's head
example: She has long dark hair.

translation: 一半地（达到一半的程度）
definition: to the extent of half
example: The glass was half full.

translation: 一半的（等于某物一半的量）
definition: an amount equal to half of something/somebody
example: I'll see you in half an hour.

translation: 一半（事物可以被平分成的两部分之一）
definition: either of two equal parts into which something is or can be divided
example: two and a half kilos (= 2?)

translation: 一半（等于某物一半的量）
definition: an amount equal to half of something/somebody
example: I'll see you in half an hour.

translation: 半路（在两点间相距相等的位置；在时间段的中间）
definition: at an equal distance between two points; in the middle of a period of time
example: It's about halfway between London and Bristol.

translation: 大厅，门厅（建筑入口或正门内的空间或过道）
definition: a space or passage inside the entrance or front door of a building
example: in a hall, Her brother was standing in the front hall.

translation: 停顿，停止（停止移动或进展的行为）
definition: an act of stopping the movement or progress of somebody/something
example: Work came to a halt when the machine broke down.

translation: 停下（停止；使某人/某事停止）
definition: to stop; to make somebody/something stop
example: She walked towards him and then halted.

translation: 手（手臂末端的部分，包括手指和拇指）
definition: the part of the body at the end of the arm, including the fingers and thumb
example: Ian placed a hand on her shoulder.

translation: 递给（将某物传递或给予某人）
definition: to pass or give something to somebody
example: hand something to somebody, She handed the letter to me.

translation: 一把（一只手能握住的量）
definition: the amount of something that can be held in one hand
example: a handful of rice

translation: 把手（门、窗等用于开启的部分）
definition: the part of a door, window, etc. that you use to open it
example: She turned the handle and opened the door.

translation: 处理（处理情况、人、工作领域或强烈情感）
definition: to deal with a situation, a person, an area of work or a strong emotion
example: handle something/somebody, A new man was appointed to handle the crisis.

translation: 处理方式（某人处理或对待情况、人、动物等的方式）
definition: the way that somebody deals with or treats a situation, a person, an animal, etc.
example: I was impressed by his handling of the affair.

translation: 便利的，手边的（易于使用或完成的；在手边的）
definition: easy to use or to do
example: a handy little tool

translation: 悬挂（在顶部连接使下部自由垂下；挂起）
definition: to attach something, or to be attached, at the top so that the lower part is free or loose
example: hang something + adv./prep., Hang your coat on the hook.

translation: 发生（发生，尤指非计划地）
definition: to take place, especially without being planned
example: You'll never guess what's happened!

translation: 快乐地（以愉快的方式；带着愉快的情绪）
definition: in a cheerful way; with feelings of pleasure
example: children playing happily on the beach

translation: 幸福（感到或表现出愉快的状态）
definition: the state of feeling or showing pleasure
example: to find true happiness

translation: 快乐的（感到或表现出愉快的；高兴的）
definition: feeling or showing pleasure; pleased
example: a happy family

translation: 骚扰（通过施压或言行不快来烦扰或困扰某人的行为）
definition: the act of annoying or worrying somebody by putting pressure on them or saying or doing unpleasant things to them
example: sexual/racial harassment

translation: 港口（海岸边受围墙保护、供船只避风的水域）
definition: an area of water on the coast, protected from the open sea by strong walls, where ships can shelter
example: Several boats lay at anchor in the harbour.

translation: 困难的（难以做、理解或回答的）
definition: difficult to do, understand or answer
example: a hard choice/decision/question

translation: 努力地（费力地；困难地）
definition: with great effort; with difficulty
example: to work hard

translation: 几乎不（几乎没有；几乎不）
definition: almost no; almost not; almost none
example: There's hardly any tea left.

translation: 硬件（电脑或其他电子系统中的机器和电子零件）
definition: the machines and electronic parts in a computer or other electronic system
example: We supply computer hardware to businesses.

translation: 伤害（由人或事件造成的损害或受伤）
definition: damage or injury that is caused by a person or an event
example: He would never frighten anyone or cause them any harm.

translation: 伤害（伤害某人或损坏某物）
definition: to hurt or injure somebody or to damage something
example: He would never harm anyone.

translation: 有害的（对某人/某物造成损坏或伤害的，尤指健康或环境）
definition: causing damage or injury to somebody/something, especially to a person’s health or to the environment
example: the harmful effects of alcohol

translation: 和谐（和平共处与一致的状态）
definition: a state of peaceful existence and agreement
example: social/racial harmony

translation: 严厉的，残酷的（残忍、严厉且不友善的）
definition: cruel, severe and unkind
example: The punishment was harsh and unfair.

translation: 收获，收获期（农场庄稼收割的时节；收割行为）
definition: the time of year when the crops are gathered in on a farm, etc.; the act of cutting and gathering crops
example: harvest time

translation: 收获（收割庄稼；捕获动物或鱼食用）
definition: to cut and gather a crop; to catch a number of animals or fish to eat
example: The nuts are ready to harvest in September.

translation: 帽子（贴合头部的衣物，常带边，通常在室外戴）
definition: a piece of clothing made to fit the head, often with a brim (= a flat edge that sticks out), usually worn out of doors
example: a straw/woolly hat

translation: 恨（对某人的极其强烈的厌恶感）
definition: a very strong feeling of dislike for somebody
example: She gave him a look of real hate.

translation: 恨（非常不喜欢某人/某物）
definition: to dislike somebody/something very much
example: hate somebody/yourself, The two boys hated each other.

translation: 仇恨（对某人/某物非常强烈的厌恶感）
definition: a very strong feeling of dislike for somebody/something
example: He looked at me with intense hatred.

translation: 出没，常去（如果死者的鬼魂出没于某处，指人们称在此见过它）
definition: if the ghost of a dead person haunts a place, people say that they have seen it there
example: A headless rider haunts the country lanes.

translation: 有（拥有、持有或具有某物）
definition: to own, hold or possess something
example: He had a new car and a boat.

translation: （助动词）（与过去分词连用构成完成时态）
definition: used with the past participle to form perfect tenses
example: I've finished my work.

translation: 必须（用于表示必须做某事）
definition: used to show that you must do something
example: Sorry, I've got to go.

translation: 危险，隐患（可能造成危险或损坏的事物）
definition: something that can be dangerous or cause damage
example: a fire/safety hazard

translation: 他（代指已提到或易识别的男性或雄性动物）
definition: a male person or animal that has already been mentioned or is easily identified
example: Everyone liked my father―he was the perfect gentleman.

translation: 头（脖子上方包含眼、鼻、嘴和脑的部分）
definition: the part of the body on top of the neck containing the eyes, nose, mouth and brain
example: She nodded her head in agreement.

translation: 朝...前进（向特定方向移动）
definition: to move in a particular direction
example: Where are we heading?

translation: 头痛（头部持续的疼痛）
definition: a continuous pain in the head
example: He had a terrible headache.

translation: 标题，头条（新闻文章的大字标题，尤指报纸头版或网站主页）
definition: the title of a news article printed in large letters, especially at the top of the front page on a newspaper or the home page on a news website
example: a newspaper headline

translation: 总部（管理组织或军事行动的地点；其工作人员）
definition: a place from which an organization or a military operation is controlled; the people who work there
example: The firm’s headquarters is/are in London.

translation: 愈合，治愈（恢复健康；使健康）
definition: to become healthy again; to make something healthy again
example: It took a long time for the wounds to heal.

translation: 健康（人身体或精神的状况）
definition: the condition of a person’s body or mind
example: to be good/bad for your health

translation: 医疗保健（提供医疗服务的业务）
definition: the service of providing medical care
example: the costs of healthcare for the elderly

translation: 健康的（身体健康且不易生病的）
definition: having good health and not likely to become ill
example: a healthy child/baby/adult

translation: 听见（用耳朵感知声音）
definition: to be aware of sounds with your ears
example: I can't hear very well.

translation: 听觉（听的能力）
definition: the ability to hear
example: Her hearing is poor.

translation: 心脏（胸腔内向全身输送血液的器官，人类常在左侧）
definition: the organ in the chest that sends blood around the body, usually on the left in humans
example: The patient's heart stopped beating for a few seconds.

translation: 热度（热的状态）
definition: the quality of being hot
example: Heat rises.

translation: 加热，变热（使某物变热或变暖；变热）
definition: to make something hot or warm; to become hot or warm
example: heat (something), Heat the oil and add the onions.

translation: 取暖，供暖（向房间或建筑提供热量的过程；这种系统）
definition: the process of supplying heat to a room or building; a system used to do this
example: to put/turn the heating on

translation: 天堂（被认为是上帝住所、好人死后去的地方，有时想象在空中）
definition: the place believed to be the home of God where good people go when they die, sometimes imagined to be in the sky
example: the kingdom of heaven

translation: 重地，剧烈地（程度极大地；大量地）
definition: to a great degree; in large amounts
example: It was raining heavily.

translation: 重的（重量大的；难以举起或移动的）
definition: weighing a lot; difficult to lift or move
example: a heavy weight/load

translation: 脚后跟（足部在脚踝下方的后部）
definition: the back part of the foot below the ankle
example: Apply the cream to dry, cracked heels before bed.

translation: 高度（人或物多高的测量值）
definition: the measurement of how tall a person or thing is
example: Height: 210 mm. Width: 57 mm. Length: 170 mm.

translation: 加剧，增强（如果情感或效果加剧，指其变得更强或增加）
definition: if a feeling or an effect heightens, or something heightens it, it becomes stronger or increases
example: Tension has heightened after the recent bomb attack.

translation: 直升机（无翼飞机，顶部有大型旋转叶片，能垂直起降和悬停）
definition: an aircraft without wings that has large blades (= long flat parts) on top that go round. It can fly straight up from the ground and can also stay in one position in the air.
example: a police/rescue helicopter

translation: 地狱（被认为是恶魔住所、坏人死后去的地方）
definition: the place believed to be the home of devils and where bad people go after death
example: He was terrified of going to hell when he died.

translation: 你好（打招呼、接电话或吸引注意力时使用）
definition: used as a greeting when you meet somebody, in an email, when you answer the phone or when you want to attract somebody’s attention
example: Hello John, how are you?

translation: 你好（打招呼、接电话或吸引注意力时使用）
definition: used as a greeting when you meet somebody, in an email, when you answer the phone or when you want to attract somebody’s attention
example: Hello John, how are you?

translation: 头盔（保护头部的硬帽，如警察、士兵、骑车人戴的）
definition: a type of hard hat that protects the head, worn, for example, by a police officer, a soldier or a person riding a bike or motorbike or playing some sports
example: Police in riot helmets lined the streets.

translation: 帮助（帮助某人做某事的行为）
definition: the act of helping somebody to do something
example: Thank you for all your help.

translation: 帮助（通过为他人做某事或提供所需使之更容易或可能）
definition: to make it easier or possible for somebody to do something by doing something for them or by giving them something that they need
example: What can I do to help?

translation: 有帮助的（能改善特定情况的）
definition: able to improve a particular situation
example: helpful advice/information

translation: 因此（出于这个原因）
definition: for this reason
example: We suspect they are trying to hide something, hence the need for an independent inquiry.

translation: 她的（属于已提到或易识别的女性或雌性动物的）
definition: of or belonging to a woman or girl who has already been mentioned or is easily identified
example: Meg loves her job.

translation: 她（用作宾语、介词后或be动词后，指代已提到的女性）
definition: used as the object of a verb, after the verb be or after a preposition to refer to a woman or girl who has already been mentioned or is easily identified
example: We're going to call her Sophie.

translation: 草本植物，香草（叶、花、子用于调味、药用或散发香味的植物，如薄荷）
definition: a plant whose leaves, flowers or seeds are used to add taste to food, in medicines or for their pleasant smell. parsley, mint and oregano are all herbs.
example: a herb garden

translation: 这里（在动词或介词后使用，意为“在此位置或地点”）
definition: used after a verb or preposition to mean ‘in, at or to this position or place’
example: I live here.

translation: 遗产（国家或社会长期拥有的历史、传统、建筑及被视为其特征重要部分的物品）
definition: the history, traditions, buildings and objects that a country or society has had for many years and that are considered an important part of its character
example: Spain’s rich cultural heritage

translation: 英雄（因英勇或善举而受多人钦佩的人）
definition: a person who is admired by many people for doing something brave or good
example: a war hero (= somebody who was very brave during a war)

translation: 她的（属于她的东西）
definition: of or belonging to her
example: His eyes met hers.

translation: 她自己（当女性执行者同时也受到动作影响时使用）
definition: used when the woman or girl who performs an action is also affected by it
example: She hurt herself.

translation: 犹豫（因不确定或紧张而说话或行动缓慢）
definition: to be slow to speak or act because you feel uncertain or nervous
example: She hesitated before replying.

translation: 嘿（用于吸引注意力或表达兴趣、惊讶或愤怒）
definition: used to attract somebody’s attention or to express interest, surprise or anger
example: Hey, can I just ask you something?

translation: 嗨（用于打招呼）
definition: used to say hello
example: Hi guys!

translation: 隐藏的（被保存在或位于看不见的地方的）
definition: something that is hidden is kept or located in a place where it cannot be seen
example: Hidden dangers lurk in the ocean depths.

translation: 隐藏（将某人/某物放在看不见或找不到的地方）
definition: to put or keep somebody/something in a place where they/it cannot be seen or found
example: hide somebody/something + adv./prep., He hid the letter in a drawer.

translation: 等级制度（尤指社会或组织中按重要性从高到低排列的体系）
definition: a system, especially in a society or an organization, in which people are organized into different levels of importance from highest to lowest
example: the social/political hierarchy

translation: 高的（从底部到顶部距离长的）
definition: measuring a long distance from the bottom to the top
example: What's the highest mountain in the US?

translation: 高高地（在地面或底部之上很高的位置）
definition: at or to a position or level that is a long way up from the ground or from the bottom
example: to climb/jump/leap high

translation: 最高水平（最高水平或最高数字）
definition: the highest level or number
example: to hit/reach a high

translation: 高调的，引人注目的（在媒体中受到大量关注和讨论的）
definition: receiving or involving a lot of attention and discussion in the media
example: a high-profile campaign

translation: 亮点（某事物中最精彩、最有趣或最令人兴奋的部分）
definition: the best, most interesting or most exciting part of something
example: One of the highlights of the trip was seeing the Taj Mahal.

translation: 强调，突出（强调某事，尤指为了使其获得更多关注）
definition: to emphasize something, especially so that people give it more attention
example: The report highlighted the importance of exercise to maintain a healthy body.

translation: 高度地，非常（非常）
definition: very
example: It is highly unlikely that she'll be late.

translation: 公路（连接城市间长距离旅行的主要道路）
definition: a main road for travelling long distances, especially one connecting and going through cities and towns
example: Plans were being made for the construction of a new interstate highway system.

translation: 极滑稽的（极其搞笑的）
definition: extremely funny
example: a hilarious joke/story

translation: 小山（高出周围土地但不如山脉高的区域）
definition: an area of land that is higher than the land around it, but not as high as a mountain
example: a region of gently rolling hills

translation: 他（用作宾语、介词后或be动词后，指代已提到的男性）
definition: used as the object of a verb, after the verb be or after a preposition to refer to a male person or animal that has already been mentioned or is easily identified
example: When did you see him?

translation: 他自己（当男性执行者同时也受到动作影响时使用）
definition: used when the man or boy who performs an action is also affected by it
example: He introduced himself.

translation: 暗示，提示（以间接方式表达想法的言行）
definition: something that you say or do in an indirect way in order to show somebody what you are thinking
example: He gave a broad hint (= one that was obvious) that he was thinking of retiring.

translation: 暗示（以间接方式提议或说明某事）
definition: to suggest something in an indirect way
example: hint at something, What are you hinting at?

translation: 臀部，髋部（腿部顶端与身体中部连接的区域或关节）
definition: the area at either side of the body between the top of the leg and the middle part of the body; the joint at the top of the leg that connects it with the top part of the body
example: She stood with her hands on her hips.

translation: 租用（付钱短时间使用某物的行为）
definition: the act of paying to use something for a short time
example: a hire car

translation: 雇用（给某人一份工作）
definition: to give somebody a job
example: She was hired three years ago.

translation: 他的（属于已提到或易识别的男性或雄性动物的）
definition: of or belonging to a man or boy who has already been mentioned or is easily identified
example: James has sold his car.

translation: 他的（属于他的东西）
definition: of or belonging to him
example: He took my hand in his.

translation: 历史学家（研究或撰写历史的人；历史专家）
definition: a person who studies or writes about history; an expert in history
example: No serious historian today accepts this theory.

translation: 有历史意义的（在历史上重要的；未来可能被认为重要的）
definition: important in history; likely to be thought of as important at some time in the future
example: the restoration of historic buildings

translation: 历史的（与过去相关的）
definition: connected with the past
example: You must place these events in their historical context.

translation: 历史（过去发生的所有事件）
definition: all the events that happened in the past
example: in history, The battle was a turning point in human history.

translation: 击打（用手或手中物体打击的行为）
definition: an act of hitting somebody/something with your hand or with an object held in your hand
example: Give it a good hit.

translation: 击中（迅速有力地将手或手中物体撞向某人/某物）
definition: to bring your hand, or an object you are holding, against somebody/something quickly and with force
example: hit somebody/something, I was afraid he was going to hit me.

translation: 爱好（工作之余为了消遣而进行的活动）
definition: an activity that you do for pleasure when you are not working
example: Do you have any hobbies?

translation: 曲棍球（两队各11名球员在场上使用弯曲球棍击打硬球入网的比赛）
definition: a game played on a field by two teams of 11 players, with curved sticks and a small hard ball. Teams try to hit the ball into the other team’s goal.
example: to play hockey

translation: 握住，控制（握住某人/某物的动作；握持的方式）
definition: the action of holding somebody/something; the way you are holding somebody/something
example: hold on somebody/something, His hold on her arm tightened.

translation: 拿，握（手中拿住或怀中抱着某人/某物等）
definition: to have somebody/something in your hand, arms, etc.
example: hold somebody/something, She was holding a large box.

translation: 洞，坑（固体中或物体表面的中空空间）
definition: a hollow space in something solid or in the surface of something
example: He dug a deep hole in the garden.

translation: 假期（不工作或不上学的时段）
definition: a period of time when you are not at work or school
example: the school/summer/Christmas holidays

translation: 中空的（内部有孔或空的空间的）
definition: having a hole or empty space inside
example: a hollow ball/centre/tube/tree

translation: 神圣的（与上帝或特定宗教相关的）
definition: connected with God or a particular religion
example: the Holy Bible

translation: 家里的（与居住地相关的）
definition: connected with the place where you live
example: home life (= with your family)

translation: 回家（向着或处于你居住的地方）
definition: to or at the place where you live
example: Come on, it's time to go home.

translation: 家（你居住的房子或公寓，尤指与家人同住）
definition: the house or flat that you live in, especially with your family
example: Old people prefer to stay in their own homes.

translation: 祖国（一个人出生所在的国家）
definition: the country where a person was born
example: Many refugees have been forced to flee their homeland.

translation: 无家可归的（没有房子，通常生活在街头的）
definition: having no home, and therefore typically living on the streets
example: The scheme has been set up to help homeless people.

translation: 家庭作业（教师布置给学生在家里完成的工作）
definition: work that is given by teachers for students to do at home
example: I always do my homework on the bus.

translation: 诚实的（始终说实话，从不偷窃或欺骗的）
definition: always telling the truth, and never stealing or cheating
example: an honest man/woman

translation: 诚实（诚实的品质）
definition: the quality of being honest
example: She answered all my questions with her usual honesty.

translation: 荣誉（对他人的极度尊敬；荣幸）
definition: great respect for somebody
example: the guest of honour (= the most important one)

translation: 尊敬，授予荣誉（通过行动展示对他人的极大尊敬）
definition: to do something that shows great respect for somebody/something
example: honour somebody/something, our honoured guests

translation: 钩子（金属、塑料或金属丝制成的弯曲物，用于挂东西、钓鱼等）
definition: a curved piece of metal, plastic or wire for hanging things on, catching fish with, etc.
example: a picture/curtain/coat hook

translation: 钩住，挂（用钩子将一物固定或挂在另一物上）
definition: to fasten or hang something on something else using a hook; to be fastened or hanging in this way
example: hook something + adv./prep., We hooked the trailer to the back of the car.

translation: 希望（渴望并期待某事发生的感觉；愿望）
definition: a feeling of wanting and expecting a particular thing to happen; something that you wish for
example: Don't lose hope―we'll find her.

translation: 希望（想要某事发生并认为有可能）
definition: to want something to happen and think that it is possible
example: All we can do now is wait and hope.

translation: 有希望的（相信想要的事会发生的）
definition: believing that something you want will happen
example: hopeful (that…), I feel hopeful that we'll find a suitable house very soon.

translation: 有希望地（用于表达希望会发生什么）
definition: used to express what you hope will happen
example: Hopefully, we'll arrive before dark.

translation: 地平线（天与地或海交接的最远处）
definition: the furthest that you can see, where the sky seems to meet the land or the sea
example: The sun sank below the horizon.

translation: 角（部分动物头上成对生长的硬尖物，常弯曲，如牛羊角）
definition: a hard pointed part that grows, usually in pairs, on the heads of some animals, such as sheep and cows. Horns are often curved.
example: a large bull with curved horns

translation: 可怕的（非常坏或令人不快的；描述不喜欢的事物）
definition: very bad or unpleasant; used to describe something that you do not like
example: What horrible weather!

translation: 恐惧，恐怖（极度震惊或害怕的感觉）
definition: a feeling of great shock or fear
example: The thought of being left alone filled her with horror.

translation: 马（四条腿的大型动物，有鬃毛和尾巴，用于骑行或拉车）
definition: a large animal with four legs, a mane (= long thick hair on its neck) and a tail. Horses are used for riding on, pulling carriages, etc.
example: to ride a horse

translation: 医院（为伤病员提供医疗和护理的大型建筑）
definition: a large building where people who are ill or injured are given medical treatment and care
example: to/into (the) hospital, (British English), He had to go to/into hospital for treatment.

translation: 主人（邀请客人用餐、聚会或留宿的人）
definition: a person who invites guests to a meal, a party, etc. or who has people staying at their house
example: Ian, our host, introduced us to the other guests.

translation: 主办，主持（组织他人参加的活动并做出所有安排）
definition: to organize an event to which others are invited and make all the arrangements for them
example: to host an event/a conference/a meeting

translation: 人质（被他人抓获并扣押的人，若要求未满足可能受伤害或被杀）
definition: a person who is captured and held prisoner by a person or group, and who may be injured or killed if people do not do what the person or group is asking
example: Three children were taken hostage during the bank robbery.

translation: 敌对的（具有攻击性或不友好的，准备争吵或战斗的）
definition: aggressive or unfriendly and ready to argue or fight
example: The speaker got a hostile reception from the audience.

translation: 敌意（攻击性或不友好的情感或行为）
definition: aggressive or unfriendly feelings or behaviour
example: There was a barely veiled hostility in her tone.

translation: 热的（温度高的；产生热量的）
definition: having a high temperature; producing heat
example: It's hot today, isn't it?

translation: 旅馆，酒店（供人住宿并付房费和餐费的建筑）
definition: a building where people stay, usually for a short time, paying for their rooms and meals
example: a two-star/five-star, etc. hotel

translation: 小时（60分钟；一天的24分之一）
definition: 60 minutes; one of the 24 parts that a day is divided into
example: I spent an hour on the phone.

translation: 房子（供人们居住的建筑，通常供一个家庭使用）
definition: a building for people to live in, usually for one family
example: in a house, We live in a two-bedroom house.

translation: 提供住房（为某人或动物提供居住地）
definition: to provide a place for a person or an animal to live
example: The government is committed to housing the refugees.

translation: 住户，家庭（住在一起的一家人或一群人）
definition: all the people living together in a house or flat
example: Most households now own at least one car.

translation: 住房（供人居住的房子、公寓等，尤指其类型、价格或状况）
definition: houses, flats, etc. that people live in, especially when referring to their type, price or condition
example: rental/student housing

translation: 如何（以何种方式或方法）
definition: in what way or manner
example: How does it work?

translation: 然而（用于引入与前述内容对比的陈述）
definition: used to introduce a statement that contrasts with something that has just been said
example: He was feeling bad. He went to work, however, and tried to concentrate.

translation: 巨大的（在规模、数量或程度上极大的）
definition: extremely large in size or amount; great in degree
example: The sums of money involved are potentially huge.

translation: 人的（与人而非动物、机器或神相关的）
definition: of or connected with people rather than animals, machines or gods
example: the human body/brain

translation: 人（作为个体的人，而非动物或机器）
definition: a person rather than an animal or a machine
example: Dogs can hear much better than humans.

translation: 人道主义的（与帮助受难者及改善其生活条件相关的）
definition: connected with helping people who are suffering and improving the conditions that they are living in
example: to provide humanitarian aid to the war zone

translation: 人类（通常指一般的人类）
definition: people in general
example: He was found guilty of crimes against humanity.

translation: 谦卑的（表现出不认为自己比他人重要的）
definition: showing you do not think that you are as important as other people
example: Be humble enough to learn from your mistakes.

translation: 幽默的（滑稽的；展现幽默感的）
definition: funny; showing a sense of humour
example: He gave a humorous account of their trip to Spain.

translation: 幽默（事物中滑稽的特质；对滑稽事物的发笑能力）
definition: the quality in something that makes it funny; the ability to laugh at things that are funny
example: It was a story full of gentle humour.

translation: 一百（数字100）
example: One hundred (of the children) have already been placed with foster families.

translation: 饥饿（没有足够食物吃的状态，尤指引起疾病或死亡时）
definition: the state of not having enough food to eat, especially when this causes illness or death
example: Around fifty people die of hunger every day in the camp.

translation: 饥饿的（感到想吃东西的）
definition: feeling that you want to eat something
example: I'm really hungry.

translation: 寻找，搜寻（寻找难以找到的人或物的行为）
definition: an act of looking for somebody/something that is difficult to find
example: The hunt is on for a suitable candidate.

translation: 打猎，猎取（追捕野生动物以获取食物、运动或金钱）
definition: to go after wild animals in order to catch or kill them for food, sport or to make money
example: Lions sometimes hunt alone.

translation: 打猎（作为运动或为了食物追捕并杀死野生动物）
definition: going after and killing wild animals as a sport or for food
example: He goes hunting every weekend.

translation: 飓风（伴有强风的剧烈风暴，尤指在西大西洋）
definition: a violent storm with very strong winds, especially in the western Atlantic Ocean
example: A powerful hurricane hit the Florida coast.

translation: 匆忙（快速完成某事的需要或愿望）
definition: the need or wish to get something done quickly
example: Take your time―there's no hurry.

translation: 赶快（因时间不多而快速移动或行动）
definition: to move or act quickly because there is not much time
example: You'll have to hurry if you want to catch that train.

translation: 受伤的（身体受损的）
definition: injured physically
example: None of the passengers were badly hurt.

translation: 伤害（因他人不友善或不公平而产生的不快乐感）
definition: a feeling of unhappiness because somebody has been unkind or unfair to you
example: There was hurt and real anger in her voice.

translation: 伤害（造成身体疼痛；使某人/自己受伤）
definition: to cause physical pain to somebody/yourself; to injure somebody/yourself
example: hurt something, He hurt his back playing squash.

translation: 丈夫（某人与之结婚的男子；已婚男子）
definition: the man that somebody is married to; a married man
example: This is my husband, Steve.

translation: 氢（氢气）
假设（基于少数事实但尚未证实的想法或解释）
definition: an idea or explanation of something that is based on a few known facts but that has not yet been proved to be true or correct
example: to formulate/confirm a hypothesis

translation: 我（当说话者指代自己时用作主语）
definition: used as the subject of a verb when the speaker or writer is referring to himself/herself
example: I think I'd better go now.

translation: 冰（冻结成固体的水）
definition: water that has frozen and become solid
example: There was ice on the windows.

translation: 冰淇淋（由乳脂制成的甜味冷冻食品，味道多样）
definition: a type of sweet frozen food made from milk fat, tasting of fruit, chocolate, etc. and often eaten as a dessert; a small amount of this food intended for one person, often served in a container made of biscuit that is like a cone in shape
example: Desserts are served with cream or ice cream.

translation: 图标（电脑或手机屏幕上代表程序或文件的微小符号）
definition: a small symbol on a computer or smartphone screen that represents a program or a file
example: Click on the printer icon with the mouse.

translation: 身份证件（证明身份的官方方式，如带名字、生日和照片的文件）
definition: an official way of showing who you are, for example a document with your name, date of birth and often a photograph on it (the abbreviation for ‘identity’ or ‘identification’)
example: You must carry ID at all times.

translation: 主意，想法（计划、思考或建议，尤指在特定情况下做什么）
definition: a plan, thought or suggestion, especially about what to do in a particular situation
example: It would be a good idea to call before we leave.

translation: 理想的（完美的；最合适的）
definition: perfect; most suitable
example: an ideal location/place

translation: 理想（似乎完美且值得努力实现的观念或标准）
definition: an idea or standard that seems perfect, and worth trying to achieve or obtain
example: He was accused of betraying his political ideals.

translation: 完全相同的（在每个细节上都相似的）
definition: similar in every detail
example: a row of identical houses

translation: 识别，鉴定（显示、证明或认出某人/某物是谁/是什么的过程）
definition: the process of showing, proving or recognizing who or what somebody/something is
example: The identification of the crash victims was a long and difficult task.

translation: 识别，认出（认出某人/某物并能说出其是谁/是什么）
definition: to recognize somebody/something and be able to say who or what they are
example: identify somebody/something, She was able to identify her attacker.

translation: 身份（某人/某物是谁或是什么）
definition: who or what somebody/something is
example: The police are trying to discover the identity of the killer.

translation: 意识形态的（基于或与意识形态相关的）
definition: based on or connected with an ideology
example: ideological differences

translation: 意识形态（经济或政治体系所基于的一套想法）
definition: a set of ideas that an economic or political system is based on
example: Marxist/capitalist ideology

translation: 笨蛋（指责某人非常愚蠢的粗鲁说法）
definition: a rude way to refer to somebody who you think is very stupid
example: When I lost my passport, I felt such an idiot.

translation: 如果（用于说明一件事的发生取决于另一件事）
definition: used to say that one thing can, will or might happen or be true, depending on another thing happening or being true
example: If you see him, give him this note.

translation: 无知（对某事缺乏知识或信息）
definition: a lack of knowledge or information about something
example: They fought a long battle against prejudice and ignorance.

translation: 忽视（不对某事给予关注）
definition: to pay no attention to something
example: He ignored all the ‘No Smoking’ signs and lit up a cigarette.

translation: 生病的（患有疾病的；感觉不舒服的）
definition: suffering from an illness or disease; not feeling well
example: Her father is seriously ill in St Luke's hospital.

translation: 非法的（法律不允许的）
definition: not allowed by the law
example: illegal drugs/firearms/substances

translation: 疾病（身体或精神生病的状态）
definition: the state of being physically or mentally ill
example: The virus can cause illness in humans.

translation: 错觉，幻想（虚假的想法或信念，尤指关于某人或某情况）
definition: a false idea or belief, especially about somebody or about a situation
example: under the illusion that…, She's under the illusion that (= believes wrongly that) she'll get the job.

translation: 说明，图解（在书中使用图片、照片、图表等）
definition: to use pictures, photographs, diagrams, etc. in a book, etc.
example: illustrate something, She illustrated her own books.

translation: 插图（书、杂志中用于装饰或解释的图画或图片）
definition: a drawing or picture in a book, magazine, for decoration or to explain something
example: 50 full-colour illustrations

translation: 图像，形象（代表某人/某物的图片、照片或雕像）
definition: a picture, photograph or statue that represents somebody/something
example: Most simple leaflets will include text and images.

translation: 意象（在读音或听众脑海中产生画面的语言）
definition: language that produces pictures in the minds of people reading or listening
example: poetic imagery

translation: 想象的（仅存在于头脑或想象中的）
definition: existing only in your mind or imagination
example: The equator is an imaginary line around the middle of the earth.

translation: 想象力（在脑中创造画面的能力；这种能力的来源）
definition: the ability to create pictures in your mind; the part of your mind that does this
example: a vivid/fertile imagination

translation: 想象（在脑中构思某事可能的样子）
definition: to form a picture in your mind of what something might be like
example: imagine something, The house was just as she had imagined it.

translation: 立即的（不延迟地发生或完成的）
definition: happening or done without delay
example: an immediate reaction/response

translation: 立即（毫不延迟地）
definition: without delay
example: She answered almost immediately.

translation: 巨大的（极其大的或伟大的）
definition: extremely large or great
example: There is still an immense amount of work to be done.

translation: 移民（永久定居于非出生国的人）
definition: a person who has come to live permanently in a different country from the one they were born in
example: immigrant from…, immigrants from other European countries

translation: 移民（永久定居于非出生国的过程；进行此行为的人数）
definition: the process of coming to live permanently in a different country from the one you were born in; the number of people who do this
example: legal/illegal immigration

translation: 即将来临的（很可能很快发生的）
definition: likely to happen very soon
example: the imminent threat of invasion

translation: 免疫的（不会感染或受特定疾病影响的）
definition: that cannot catch or be affected by a particular disease or illness
example: Adults are often immune to German measles.

translation: 影响，冲击（某事物对某人/某物产生的强大效果）
definition: the powerful effect that something has on somebody/something
example: a positive/a negative/an adverse impact

translation: 产生影响（对某人/某物产生效果）
definition: to have an effect on somebody/something
example: impact on/upon somebody/something, Her father's death impacted greatly on her childhood years.

translation: 不耐烦的（对某人/某事感到恼火，尤指因等待时间过长）
definition: annoyed by somebody/something, especially because you have to wait for a long time
example: I'd been waiting for twenty minutes and I was getting impatient.

translation: 实施，执行（使官方决定的事项开始发生或被使用）
definition: to make something that has been officially decided start to happen or be used
example: to implement changes/decisions/policies/reforms

translation: 实施，执行（使官方决定事项开始发生或被使用的行为）
definition: the act of making something that has been officially decided start to happen or be used
example: the implementation of the new system

translation: 影响，暗示（行动或决定的可能效果或结果）
definition: a possible effect or result of an action or a decision
example: They failed to consider the wider implications of their actions.

translation: 暗示（间接提议某事为真或表达某种感觉/想法）
definition: to suggest that something is true or that you feel or think something, without saying so directly
example: imply (that)…, Are you implying (that) I am wrong?

translation: 进口（从他国带入本国的产品或服务）
definition: a product or service that is brought into one country from another
example: import from…, food imports from abroad

translation: 进口（将产品、服务、想法等从他国带入本国）
definition: to bring a product, a service, an idea, etc. into one country from another
example: import something, The country has to import most of its raw materials.

translation: 重要性（重要的品质）
definition: the quality of being important
example: She stressed the importance of careful preparation.

translation: 重要的（对人或物有重大影响的；有巨大价值的）
definition: having a great effect on people or things; of great value
example: an important issue/question/point/factor

translation: 强加（引入新法律、规则等；命令使用某种规则、惩罚）
definition: to introduce a new law, rule, tax, etc.; to order that a rule, punishment, etc. be used
example: impose something, The UN Security Council imposed sanctions in 1992.

translation: 不可能的（不能存在或做到的；不可行的）
definition: that cannot exist or be done; not possible
example: almost/virtually/nearly impossible

translation: 给人留下深刻印象（如果你使某人钦佩你，指你给其留下了深刻印象）
definition: if a person or thing impresses you, you admire them or it
example: impress (somebody), We interviewed a number of candidates but none of them impressed us.

translation: 印象深刻的（因认为某人/某物特别好或有趣而钦佩的）
definition: admiring somebody/something because you think they are particularly good, interesting, etc.
example: I must admit I am impressed.

translation: 印象（你对某人/某物的看法、感觉或其给你的感觉）
definition: an idea, a feeling or an opinion that you get about somebody/something, or that somebody/something gives you
example: My first impression of him was favourable.

translation: 给人深刻印象的（因规模大、质量好、技艺高而使你钦佩的）
definition: making you admire them, because they are very large, good, skilful, etc.
example: an impressive performance

translation: 监禁（将某人关入监狱或其他无法逃脱的地方）
definition: to put somebody in a prison or another place from which they cannot escape
example: be imprisoned (for something), They were imprisoned for possession of drugs.

translation: 监禁（将某人关入监狱的行为；被关在那里的状态）
definition: the act of putting somebody in a prison or another place from which they cannot escape; the state of being there
example: to be sentenced to life imprisonment for murder

translation: 改进，提高（变得比以前更好；使某人/某物变得更好）
definition: to become better than before; to make something/somebody better than before
example: Overall the situation has improved dramatically.

translation: 改进，提高（使某事变好的行为；变好的过程）
definition: the act of making something better; the process of something becoming better
example: The economy has shown significant improvement over the past 9 months.

translation: 在里面（进入一个物体、区域或物质内部）
definition: into an object, an area or a substance
example: She opened the door and went in.

translation: 在...中（在某个区域或空间内的某一点）
definition: at a point within an area or a space
example: a country in Africa

translation: 无能，无力（不能做某事的事实）
definition: the fact of not being able to do something
example: the government’s inability to provide basic services

translation: 不充足的（不够的；不够好的）
definition: not enough; not good enough
example: inadequate supplies

translation: 不恰当的（在特定情况下不合适或不恰当的）
definition: not suitable or appropriate in a particular situation
example: inappropriate behaviour/language

translation: 激励，动机（鼓励你去做某事的事物）
definition: something that encourages you to do something
example: There is no incentive for people to save fuel.

translation: 英寸（长度单位，等于2.54厘米；12英寸等于1英尺）
definition: a unit for measuring length or height, equal to 2.54 centimetres. There are 12 inches in a foot.
example: She's a few inches taller than me.

translation: 发生率（某事发生或产生效果的程度）
definition: the extent to which something happens or has an effect
example: an area with a high incidence of crime

translation: 事件（发生的事情，尤指不寻常或不愉快的）
definition: something that happens, especially something unusual or unpleasant
example: His bad behaviour was just an isolated incident.

translation: 倾向于（想要去做某事）
definition: wanting to do something
example: She was inclined to trust him.

translation: 包括（如果一物包含另一物，指后者是前者的一部分）
definition: if one thing includes another, it has the second thing as one of its parts
example: include something, The tour included a visit to the Science Museum.

translation: 包括在内的（作为某事的一部分包含在内的）
definition: contained as part of something
example: all of Europe (Britain included)

translation: 包括（作为群体或集合的一部分包含某物）
definition: having something as part of a group or set
example: I've got three days' holiday including New Year's Day.

translation: 包含，包括（包含某人/某事的事实；被包含的事实）
definition: the fact of including somebody/something; the fact of being included
example: His inclusion in the team is in doubt.

translation: 收入（个人、地区、国家等从工作、投资或业务中赚得的钱）
definition: the money that a person, a region, a country, etc. earns from work, from investing money, from business, etc.
example: Average household income fell slightly.

translation: 包含，并入（包括某物使其成为另一物的一部分）
definition: to include something so that it forms a part of something
example: incorporate something, The new car design incorporates all the latest safety features.

translation: 不正确的（不准确或不真实的）
definition: not accurate or true
example: incorrect information/spelling

translation: 增加（某物在数量、数额或价值上的上升）
definition: a rise in the amount, number or value of something
example: price/tax/wage increases

translation: 增加（在数量、价值等方面变大；使某物变大）
definition: to become greater in amount, number, value, etc.; to make something greater in amount, number, value, etc.
example: Costs have increased significantly.

translation: 日益，越来越多地（一直不断地增加）
definition: more and more all the time
example: Tourism is playing an increasingly important role in the region's economy

translation: 难以置信的（不可能或非常难以相信的）
definition: impossible or very difficult to believe
example: an incredible story

translation: 难以置信地（极其地）
definition: extremely
example: It was all incredibly difficult.

translation: 引起，遭受（如果你遭遇不快的事，指你处于必须处理它的境地）
definition: if you incur something unpleasant, you are in a situation in which you have to deal with it
example: She had incurred the wrath of her father by marrying without his consent.

translation: 确实，的确（用于very及形容词/副词后以强调陈述）
definition: used after very and an adjective or adverb to emphasize a statement, description, etc.
example: Thank you very much indeed!

translation: 独立（不受他国政治控制的自由）
definition: freedom from political control by other countries
example: Cuba gained independence from Spain in 1898.

translation: 独立的（拥有自己政府的）
definition: having its own government
example: an independent state/nation/country

translation: 索引，索引表（书中提到的名称或主题列表，通常按字母序排列）
definition: a list of names or topics that are referred to in a book, etc., usually arranged at the end of a book in alphabetical order or listed in a separate file or book
example: Look it up in the index.

translation: 表明，指示（显示某事属实或存在）
definition: to show that something is true or exists
example: indicate something, Initial tests indicate the presence of oxygen.

translation: 迹象，暗示（显示事情正在发生或某人想法、感觉的言语或迹象）
definition: a remark or sign that shows that something is happening or what somebody is thinking or feeling
example: indication of something, They gave no indication of how the work should be done.

translation: 指标（显示某物是什么样的或情况如何变化的标志）
definition: a sign that shows you what something is like or how a situation is changing
example: The economic indicators are better than expected.

translation: 控诉，控告（体系、社会等非常糟糕或错误的迹象）
definition: a sign that a system, society, etc. is very bad or very wrong
example: The poverty in our cities is a damning indictment of modern society.

translation: 土著的，原住民的（来自特定地方并在此居住很久的；与这些人相关的）
definition: coming from a particular place and having lived there for a long time before other people came there; relating to, belonging to or developed by these people
example: the indigenous peoples/languages of an area

translation: 间接的（非作为主要目标或结果发生，而是作为其补充发生的）
definition: happening not as the main aim, cause or result of a particular action, but in addition to it
example: the indirect effects of the war

translation: 个人的，个体的（单独考虑而非作为群体一部分的）
definition: considered separately rather than as part of a group
example: We interviewed each individual member of the community.

translation: 个人，个体（被单独考虑的人）
definition: a person considered separately rather than as part of a group
example: The competition is open to both teams and individuals.

translation: 室内的（位于、在建筑内部完成或使用的）
definition: located, done or used inside a building
example: an indoor swimming pool

translation: 在室内（在建筑内部或进入建筑内部）
definition: inside or into a building
example: I prefer to stay indoors in this really hot weather.

translation: 引诱，导致（劝说或影响某人做某事）
definition: to persuade or influence somebody to do something
example: Nothing would induce me to take the job.

translation: 沉溺，纵容（允许自己拥有或做喜欢的事，尤指被认为不好的事）
definition: to allow yourself to have or do something that you like, especially something that is considered bad for you
example: indulge in something, They went into town to indulge in some serious shopping.

translation: 工业的，工业化的（与工业相关的）
definition: connected with industry
example: an industrial dispute

translation: 工业（从原材料生产商品，尤指在工厂中）
definition: the production of goods from raw materials, especially in factories
example: the needs of British industry

translation: 不平等（社会中群体间的这种不公平差异，如财富、地位或机会的不同）
definition: the unfair difference between groups of people in society, when some have more wealth, status or opportunities than others
example: We need to tackle inequality of opportunity wherever we find it.

translation: 不可避免的（无法回避或防止的）
definition: that you cannot avoid or prevent
example: It was an inevitable consequence of the decision.

translation: 不可避免地（必然会发生地）
definition: as is certain to happen
example: Inevitably, the press exaggerated the story.

translation: 声名狼藉的（因坏事或邪恶而众所周知的）
definition: well known for being bad or evil
example: a general who was infamous for his brutality

translation: 婴儿（婴儿或极年幼的儿童）
definition: a baby or very young child
example: a nursery for infants under two

translation: 感染（使疾病传染给他人、动物或植物）
definition: to make a disease or an illness spread to a person, an animal or a plant
example: infect somebody/something (with something), It is not possible to infect another person through kissing.

translation: 感染（导致或患上疾病的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of causing or getting a disease
example: to cause/prevent infection

translation: 推断（根据现有信息得出观点或判断某事属实）
definition: to reach an opinion or decide that something is true on the basis of information that is available
example: infer something (from something), Much of the meaning must be inferred from the context.

translation: 通货膨胀（国家商品和服务价格的普遍上涨，导致货币贬值；通胀率）
definition: a general rise in the prices of services and goods in a particular country, resulting in a fall in the value of money; the rate at which this happens
example: the fight against rising inflation

translation: 造成，施加（使某人/某物遭受不快之事，如失败或打击）
definition: to make somebody/something suffer something unpleasant
example: inflict something on/upon somebody/something, They inflicted a humiliating defeat on the home team.

translation: 影响（某人/某事对他人思维、行为或事物运作、发展产生的作用）
definition: the effect that somebody/something has on the way a person thinks or behaves or on the way that something works or develops
example: His early work shows the influence of Cézanne and Matisse.

translation: 影响（对某人的行为或思维产生作用，尤指通过榜样作用）
definition: to have an effect on the way that somebody behaves or thinks, especially by giving them an example to follow
example: influence somebody/something, His writings have influenced the lives of millions.

translation: 有影响力的（对某人/某事有很大影响的）
definition: having a lot of influence on somebody/something
example: a highly influential book

translation: 信息（information的缩写）
definition: information
example: For more info, click here.

translation: 通知，告知（告诉某人某事，尤指以官方方式）
definition: to tell somebody about something, especially in an official way
example: inform somebody, The government took this decision without consulting Parliament or informing the public.

translation: 非正式的（放松友好的；不遵循严格规则的）
definition: relaxed and friendly; not following strict rules of how to behave or do something
example: an informal atmosphere

translation: 信息（关于某人/某事的事实或细节）
definition: facts or details about somebody/something
example: a piece of information

translation: 基础设施（基础设施）
原料，成分（构成某物的要素之一，尤指烹饪中的食材）
definition: one of the things from which something is made, especially one of the foods that are used together to make a particular dish
example: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.

translation: 居民（居住在特定地方的人或动物）
definition: a person or an animal that lives in a particular place
example: the oldest inhabitant of the village

translation: 固有的（某人/某物基本或永久的一部分，且无法去除的）
definition: that is a basic or permanent part of somebody/something and that cannot be removed
example: the difficulties inherent in a study of this type

translation: 继承（在某人死后收到其金钱、财产等）
definition: to receive money, property, etc. from somebody when they die
example: inherit something from somebody, She inherited a fortune from her father.

translation: 抑制（阻止某事发生或使其发生得更慢、更不频繁）
definition: to prevent something from happening or make it happen more slowly or less frequently than normal
example: A lack of oxygen may inhibit brain development in the unborn child.

translation: 最初的（开始时发生的；第一的）
definition: happening at the beginning; first
example: There is an initial payment of ￡60 followed by ten instalments of ￡25.

translation: 最初（在开始时）
definition: at the beginning
example: Initially, the system worked well.

translation: 开始，发起（使某事开始，如发起法律诉讼）
definition: to make something begin
example: to initiate legal proceedings against somebody

translation: 倡议，主动性（处理问题或实现目标的新的计划）
definition: a new plan for dealing with a particular problem or for achieving a particular purpose
example: a United Nations peace initiative

translation: 注射（使用注射器将药物等注入人体或动物体）
definition: to put a drug or other substance into a person’s or an animal’s body using a syringe
example: inject something (into yourself/somebody/something), Adrenaline was injected into the muscle.

translation: 注射（给某人注射药物的行为）
definition: an act of injecting somebody with a drug or other substance
example: to give somebody an injection

translation: 伤害（使自己或他人身体受损，尤指在事故中）
definition: to harm yourself or somebody else physically, especially in an accident
example: He injured his knee playing hockey.

translation: 受伤的（身体受损的；患伤的）
definition: physically hurt; having an injury
example: His injured leg prevented him from walking.

translation: 伤害（对人或动物身体造成的损害，例如在事故中）
definition: harm done to a person’s or an animal’s body, for example in an accident
example: Two people sustained minor injuries.

translation: 不公正（情况不公平、人们未受平等对待的事实；不公平的行为）
definition: the fact of a situation being unfair and of people not being treated equally; an unfair act or an example of unfair treatment
example: We are committed to fighting against poverty and injustice.

translation: 墨水（用于书写、绘画和打印的彩色液体）
definition: coloured liquid for writing, drawing and printing
example: in ink, written in ink

translation: 囚犯，同住者（住在监狱或精神病院等机构中的人）
definition: one of the people living in an institution such as a prison or a psychiatric hospital
example: The jail has 500 inmates.

translation: 内部的（在里面的；朝向或靠近地方中心的）
definition: inside; towards or close to the centre of a place
example: an inner courtyard

translation: 无罪的，天真的（未犯罪的；未做错事的；单纯的）
definition: not guilty of a crime, etc.; not having done something wrong
example: They have imprisoned an innocent man.

translation: 创新（新事物、想法或做事方式的引入）
definition: the introduction of new things, ideas or ways of doing something
example: an age of technological innovation

translation: 创新的（引入或使用新想法、新方式的）
definition: introducing or using new ideas, ways of doing something, etc.
example: There will be a prize for the most innovative design.

translation: 投入，输入（投入工作、项目等的资源、知识或主意；输入的行为）
definition: time, knowledge, ideas, etc. that you put into work, a project, etc. in order to make it succeed; the act of putting something in
example: I'd appreciate your input on this.

translation: 调查，询问（找出某事原因或信息的官方过程）
