definition: an official process to find out the cause of something or to find out information about something
example: a murder inquiry

translation: 昆虫（有六条腿、身体分三部分的微小生物，通常带翅膀）
definition: any small creature with six legs and a body divided into three parts. Insects usually also have wings. Ants, bees and flies are all insects.
example: Most birds spend most of the day eating insects.

translation: 插入（将某物放入另一物中或两物之间）
definition: to put something into something else or between two things
example: insert something (in/into something), Insert coins into the slot and press for a ticket.

translation: 插入（将某物放入另一物内部的行为；被插入之物）
definition: the act of putting something inside something else; a thing that is put inside something else
example: An examination is carried out before the insertion of the tube.

translation: 里面的（构成事物内部的；非外部的）
definition: forming the inner part of something; not on the outside
example: the inside pages of a newspaper

translation: 在里面（在内部）
definition: on or to the inside
example: She shook it to make sure there was nothing inside.

translation: 内部（事物的内部部分、侧面或表面）
definition: the inner part, side or surface of something
example: The inside of the box was blue.

translation: 在...里面（在某人/某物的内部；在...之内）
definition: on or to the inner part of something/somebody; within something/somebody
example: Go inside the house.

translation: 知情者，内部人员（因身处其中而对群体或组织非常了解的人）
definition: a person who knows a lot about a group or an organization, because they are part of it
example: The situation was described by one insider as ‘absolute chaos’.

translation: 洞察力（对事物本质的理解）
definition: an understanding of what something is like
example: There are many valuable insights in her book.

translation: 坚持（要求某事发生或某人同意做某事）
definition: to demand that something happen or that somebody agree to do something
example: I didn't really want to go but he insisted.

translation: 检查（仔细查看，尤指为了核实是否符合要求）
definition: to look closely at something/somebody, especially to check that everything is as it should be
example: inspect something/somebody, The teacher walked around inspecting their work.

translation: 检查，视察（对学校、工厂等的官方访问，以核实规则遵守及标准情况）
definition: an official visit to a school, factory, etc. in order to check that rules are being obeyed and that standards are acceptable
example: Regular inspections are carried out at the prison.

translation: 督察，检查员（警察部门的中级官员；或负责检查的官员）
definition: an officer of middle rank in the police force
example: Inspector Maggie Forbes

translation: 灵感（看到或听到某物后产生新想法或创作欲望的过程，尤指在艺术领域）
definition: the process that takes place when somebody sees or hears something that causes them to have exciting new ideas or makes them want to create something, especially in art, music or literature
example: Dreams can be a rich source of inspiration for an artist.

translation: 激励，鼓舞（给予某人做好某事的渴望、信心或热情）
definition: to give somebody the desire, confidence or enthusiasm to do something well
example: inspire somebody, The actors' enthusiasm inspired the kids.

translation: 安装（将设备或家具固定到位以便使用）
definition: to fix equipment or furniture into position so that it can be used
example: They're planning to install a new drainage system.

translation: 安装（将设备或家具固定到位的行为）
definition: the act of fixing equipment or furniture in position so that it can be used
example: installation costs

translation: 例子，事例（某事物的特定示例或情况）
definition: a particular example or case of something
example: instance of somebody/something, The report highlights a number of instances of injustice.

translation: 立即的（立即发生的）
definition: happening immediately
example: This account gives you instant access to your money.

translation: 立即地（立刻地）
definition: immediately
example: Her voice is instantly recognizable.

translation: 代替（作为某人/某物的替代）
definition: in the place of somebody/something
example: Lee was ill so I went instead.

translation: 本能（人或动物天生的行为特质，基于生而具有的知识而非学习）
definition: a natural quality that makes people and animals tend to behave in a particular way using the knowledge and abilities that they were born with rather than thought or training
example: She did not seem to have any of the usual maternal instincts.

translation: 学院，学会（具有特定目的的组织，尤指与教育或专业相关的；其建筑）
definition: an organization that has a particular purpose, especially one that is connected with education or a particular profession; the building used by this organization
example: The report was compiled by Germany's five leading economic research institutes.

translation: 机构，制度（具有特定目的的大型重要组织，如大学或银行）
definition: a large important organization that has a particular purpose, for example a university or bank
example: The deal is backed by one of the country's largest financial institutions.

translation: 制度的，机构的（与大型重要组织相关的）
definition: connected with a large important organization, for example a university or bank
example: institutional investors

translation: 指示，指导（告诉某人去做某事，尤指以正式或官方方式）
definition: to tell somebody to do something, especially in a formal or official way
example: instruct somebody to do something, The letter instructed him to report to headquarters immediately.

translation: 说明，指令（关于如何做或使用某物的详细信息）
definition: detailed information on how to do or use something
example: Follow the instructions on the packet carefully.

translation: 教练，教员（职业是教人实用技能或体育的人）
definition: a person whose job is to teach somebody a practical skill or sport
example: a fitness/driving/ski instructor

translation: 乐器，仪器（用于产生乐音的物体；或测量仪器）
definition: an object used for producing musical sounds, for example a piano or a drum
example: to play an instrument

translation: 起作用的，有帮助的（在使某事发生中起重要作用的）
definition: important in making something happen
example: The Conservation Trust performs an instrumental role in the protection of rural environments.

translation: 不足的（对特定目的来说不够大、不够强或不够重要的）
definition: not large, strong or important enough for a particular purpose
example: insufficient time

translation: 侮辱（为了冒犯某人而说的言语或做的行为）
definition: a remark or an action that is said or done in order to offend somebody
example: The crowd were shouting insults at the police.

translation: 侮辱（说或做冒犯某人的事）
definition: to say or do something that offends somebody
example: I have never been so insulted in my life!

translation: 保险（与公司达成的安排，定期交费以在出事时获得经济补偿）
definition: an arrangement with a company in which you pay them regular amounts of money and they agree to pay the costs, for example, if you die or are ill, or if you lose or damage something
example: health/medical insurance

translation: 完好无损的（完整的且未受损的）
definition: complete and not damaged
example: Most of the house remains intact even after two hundred years.

translation: 摄入量（摄入体内的食物、饮料等的数量）
definition: the amount of food, drink, etc. that you take into your body
example: high fluid intake

translation: 不可或缺的（作为某物基本组成部分的）
definition: being an essential part of something
example: Music is an integral part of the school's curriculum.

translation: 整合，结合（将两个或更多事物结合使之共同工作）
definition: to combine two or more things so that they work together; to combine with something else in this way
example: integrate into/with something, These programs will integrate with your existing software.

translation: 整合的，综合的（各部分紧密联系并成功协作的）
definition: in which many different parts are closely connected and work successfully together
example: an integrated programme of patient care

translation: 整合，一体化（结合两个或更多事物使之共同工作的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of combining two or more things so that they work together
example: The aim is to promote closer economic integration.

translation: 正直，诚信（诚实且具有强烈的道德原则的品质）
definition: the quality of being honest and having strong moral principles
example: personal/professional/artistic integrity

translation: 智力的，理智的（与使用逻辑思维理解事物的能力相关的）
definition: connected with or using a person’s ability to think in a logical way and understand things
example: Gifted children typically show great intellectual curiosity and a wide range of interests.

translation: 知识分子（受过良好教育且喜欢严肃思考的人）
definition: a person who is well educated and enjoys activities in which they have to think seriously about things
example: He was a leading intellectual of his day.

translation: 智力（逻辑学习、理解和思考的能力；做好这些的能力）
definition: the ability to learn, understand and think in a logical way about things; the ability to do this well
example: a person of high/average/low intelligence

translation: 聪明的（擅长逻辑学习、理解和思考的；表现出这种能力的）
definition: good at learning, understanding and thinking in a logical way about things; showing this ability
example: a highly intelligent child

translation: 打算（做某事时脑中有计划、结果或目的）
definition: to have a plan, result or purpose in your mind when you do something
example: We finished later than we had intended.

translation: 预期的（你尝试去实现或达到的）
definition: that you are trying to achieve or reach
example: the intended purpose

translation: 强烈的（程度极大的；非常强劲的）
definition: very great; very strong
example: We were all suffering in the intense heat.

translation: 加强，加剧（在程度或强度上增加；使之增加）
definition: to increase in degree or strength; to make something increase in degree or strength
example: Violence intensified during the night.

translation: 强度（强烈程度的状态或品质）
definition: the state or quality of being intense
example: intensity of light/sound/colour

translation: 密集的（涉及在短时间内进行大量工作或活动的）
definition: involving a lot of work or activity done in a short time
example: an intensive language course

translation: 意图（你打算做的事）
definition: what you intend to do
example: She denies possessing the drug with intent to supply.

translation: 意图，目的（你打算或计划做的事；你的目标）
definition: what you intend or plan to do; your aim
example: intention of doing something, I have no intention of going to the wedding.

translation: 互动（与他人交流，尤指在工作、玩耍或共处时）
definition: to communicate with somebody, especially while you work, play or spend time with them
example: Teachers have a limited amount of time to interact with each child.

translation: 互动（与他人交流的行为，尤指在工作、玩耍或共处时）
definition: the act of communicating with somebody, especially while you work, play or spend time with them
example: the interaction between performers and their audience

translation: 互动的（允许用户与电脑/设备间进行双向、连续信息传递的）
definition: that allows information to be passed continuously and in both directions between a computer or other device and the person who uses it
example: interactive displays/video

translation: 兴趣，趣味（想了解或学习更多关于某人/某事的感觉）
definition: the feeling that you have when you want to know or learn more about somebody/something
example: Her research has generated interest around the world.

translation: 使感兴趣（吸引你的注意力并使你感到好奇；让自己关注某事）
definition: to attract your attention and make you feel interested; to make yourself give your attention to something
example: interest somebody, Politics doesn't interest me.

translation: 感兴趣的（因为喜欢了解或做某事而投入关注的；感到兴奋的）
definition: giving your attention to something because you enjoy finding out about it or doing it; showing interest in something and finding it exciting
example: He sounded genuinely interested.

translation: 有趣的（因特别、兴奋或不寻常而吸引注意力的）
definition: attracting your attention because it is/they are special, exciting or unusual
example: The article raises several interesting questions.

translation: 界面（电脑程序向用户展示信息或接收信息的方式，尤指屏幕布局）
definition: the way a computer program presents information to a user or receives information from a user, in particular the layout of the screen and the menus
example: the user interface

translation: 干涉（介入并尝试影响本不该涉及你的情况，以令人烦恼的方式）
definition: to get involved in and try to influence a situation that should not really involve you, in a way that annoys other people
example: I wish my mother would stop interfering and let me make my own decisions.

translation: 干涉（介入并尝试影响本不该涉及你的情况的行为）
definition: the act of getting involved in and trying to influence a situation that should not really involve you, in a way that annoys other people
example: interference (in something), They resent foreign interference in the internal affairs of their country.

translation: 临时的（旨在持续短时间，直到找到更永久的替代品）
definition: intended to last for only a short time until somebody/something more permanent is found
example: an interim government/measure/report

translation: 内部的（与事物内部相关的）
definition: connected with the inside part of something
example: interior walls

translation: 内部（事物的内部部分）
definition: the inside part of something
example: the interior of a building/a car

translation: 中间的，中级的（位于两个地方、事物、状态等之间的）
definition: located between two places, things, states, etc.
example: an intermediate stage/step in a process

translation: 内部的（与事物内部相连的）
definition: connected with the inside of something
example: the internal structure of a building

translation: 国际的（涉及两个或更多国家的）
definition: connected with or involving two or more countries
example: international trade/law

translation: 互联网（连接全球电脑的国际网络，允许人们分享信息）
definition: an international computer network connecting other networks and computers that allows people to share information around the world
example: to surf/browse/access the internet

translation: 解释，翻译（解释某事的含义）
definition: to explain the meaning of something
example: The students were asked to interpret the poem.

translation: 解释，演绎（理解或解释某事的特定方式）
definition: the particular way in which something is understood or explained
example: Her evidence suggests a different interpretation of the events.

translation: 打断（说话或做事时使某人停止）
definition: to say or do something that makes somebody stop what they are saying or doing
example: Sorry to interrupt, but there's someone to see you.

translation: 间隔（两个事件之间的时间段）
definition: a period of time between two events
example: The interval between major earthquakes might be 200 years.

translation: 干预（介入某种情况以改善或提供帮助）
definition: to become involved in a situation in order to improve or help it
example: She might have been killed if the neighbours hadn't intervened.

translation: 干预（为了改善或帮助情况而采取的行动）
definition: action taken to improve or help a situation
example: calls for government intervention to save the steel industry

translation: 面试，访谈（评估某人是否适合工作或学习的正式会议；或媒体访谈）
definition: a formal meeting at which somebody is asked questions to see if they are suitable for a particular job, or for a course of study at a college, university, etc.
example: a job interview

translation: 面试，访谈（在正式会议上提问以确定某人是否适合工作、学习等）
definition: to talk to somebody and ask them questions at a formal meeting to find out if they are suitable for a job, course of study, etc.
example: interview somebody, The university interviews all potential candidates.

translation: 亲密的（具有紧密且友好的关系的）
definition: having a close and friendly relationship
example: intimate friends

translation: 进入（到某物内部或某个位置）
definition: to a position in or inside something
example: Come into the house.

translation: 引人入胜的（因不寻常或无明显答案而非常有趣的）
definition: very interesting because of being unusual or not having an obvious answer
example: These discoveries raise intriguing questions.

translation: 介绍（告知未见过面的人彼此的名字；自我介绍）
definition: to tell two or more people who have not met before what each other’s names are; to tell somebody what your name is
example: introduce somebody, Allow me to introduce my mother.

translation: 介绍，引言（书籍或演说的开头部分，给出后续内容的概括）
definition: the first part of a book or speech that gives a general idea of what is to follow
example: a book with an excellent introduction and notes

translation: 入侵，侵略（使用武力进入国家、城镇等以夺取控制权）
definition: to enter a country, town, etc. using military force in order to take control of it
example: Troops invaded on August 9th that year.

translation: 入侵，侵略（军队强行进入他国以夺取控制权的行为）
definition: the act of an army entering another country by force in order to take control of it
example: the German invasion of Poland in 1939

translation: 发明（制造或设计以前不存在的东西）
definition: to produce or design something that has not existed before
example: Who invented the steam engine?

translation: 发明（被发明出来的东西或想法）
definition: a thing or an idea that has been invented
example: Fax machines were a wonderful invention at the time.

translation: 投资（购买房产、股份等以期获利）
definition: to buy property, shares in a company, etc. in the hope of making a profit
example: Now is a good time to invest.

translation: 调查（仔细检查情况、事件、犯罪等的事实以找出真相）
definition: to carefully examine the facts of a situation, an event, a crime, etc. to find out the truth about it or how it happened
example: The FBI has been called in to investigate.

translation: 调查（对情况、犯罪等事实的官方检查）
definition: an official examination of the facts about a situation, crime, etc.
example: a criminal/murder/police investigation

translation: 调查员（检查事故或犯罪等情况以找出真相的人）
definition: a person who examines a situation such as an accident or a crime to find out the truth
example: air safety investigators

translation: 投资（将钱投入某事物的行为）
definition: the act of investing money in something
example: foreign/private investment

translation: 投资者（将钱投入某事物的个人或组织）
definition: a person or an organization that invests money in something
example: small investors (= private people)

translation: 看不见的（不能被看到的）
definition: that cannot be seen
example: a wizard who could make himself invisible

translation: 邀请（向某人发出的做某事或去某处的口头或书面请求）
definition: a spoken or written request to somebody to do something or to go somewhere
example: to issue/extend an invitation

translation: 邀请（要求某人参加社交活动）
definition: to ask somebody to come to a social event
example: invite somebody to something, Have you been invited to their party?

translation: 援引，调用（提及或使用法律、规则等作为做某事的理由）
definition: to mention or use a law, rule, etc. as a reason for doing something
example: It is unlikely that libel laws will be invoked.

translation: 涉及，包含（如果一个情况/活动涉及某物，指其为重要组成或结果）
definition: if a situation, an event or an activity involves something, that thing is an important or necessary part or result of it
example: involve something, Any investment involves an element of risk.

translation: 参与其中的，涉及的（参加某事；成为某事的一部分或与之有联系）
definition: taking part in something; being part of something or connected with something
example: Some people tried to stop the fight but I didn't want to get involved.

translation: 参与，介入（参加某事或与他人打交道的行为）
definition: the act of taking part in something or dealing with somebody
example: involvement in something, US involvement in European wars

translation: 铁（一种金属化学元素，用于制造钢，也存在于血液和食物中）
definition: a chemical element. Iron is a hard strong metal that is used to make steel and is also found in small quantities in blood and food.
example: iron gates/bars/railings

translation: 熨烫（使用熨斗使衣服平整）
definition: to make clothes, etc. smooth by using an iron
example: He was ironing when I arrived.

translation: 讽刺的（表现出所言与本意相反的；表达讽刺的）
definition: showing that you really mean the opposite of what you are saying; expressing irony
example: an ironic comment

translation: 讽刺地（以表现出所言与本意相反的方式；表达讽刺地）
definition: in a way that shows that you really mean the opposite of what you are saying; in a way that expresses irony
example: He smiled ironically.

translation: 讽刺（情况中与预期完全不同的滑稽或奇怪的一面；这种情况）
definition: the funny or strange aspect of a situation that is very different from what you expect; a situation like this
example: It was one of life's little ironies.

translation: 无关的（对情况不重要或不相关的）
definition: not important to or connected with a situation
example: totally/completely/largely irrelevant

translation: 岛屿（完全被水包围的一块陆地）
definition: a piece of land that is completely surrounded by water
example: a small/tiny island

translation: 隔离，孤立（在物理上或社交上使某人/某物与他人/他物分开）
definition: to separate somebody/something physically or socially from other people or things
example: isolate somebody/yourself/something, Patients with the disease should be isolated.

translation: 偏远的，孤立的（远离其他的）
definition: far away from any others
example: isolated rural areas

translation: 隔离，孤立（使某人/某物分开的行为；分开的状态）
definition: the act of separating somebody/something; the state of being separate
example: geographical isolation

translation: 问题，议题（人们正在讨论或争论的重要话题）
definition: an important topic that people are discussing or arguing about
example: a key/major issue

translation: 发布，发行（正式使某事为人所知）
definition: to make something known formally
example: issue something, They issued a joint statement denying the charges.

translation: 信息技术，IT（使用电子设备存储和发送各类信息――文字、图片、数字等――的学科）
definition: the study and use of electronic processes and equipment to store and send information of all kinds, including words, pictures and numbers (the abbreviation for ‘information technology’)
example: the increasing use of IT in all aspects of today's society

translation: 它（指代已提到或正在谈论的动物或事物）
definition: used to refer to an animal or a thing that has already been mentioned or that is being talked about now
example: ‘Where's your car?’ ‘It's in the garage.’

translation: 项目，项（购买、执行、谈论清单上的一件事）
definition: one thing on a list of things to buy, do, talk about, etc.
example: What's the next item on the agenda?

translation: 它的（属于或与某物、动物、婴儿相关的）
definition: belonging to or connected with a thing, an animal or a baby
example: Turn the box on its side.

translation: 它自己（当动物或事物执行动作并受其影响时使用）
definition: used when the animal or thing that does an action is also affected by it
example: The cat was washing itself.

translation: 夹克（穿在衬衫外、带袖子、在前部系紧的短上衣）
definition: a piece of clothing worn on the top half of the body over a shirt, etc. that has arms and fastens down the front; a short, light coat
example: a leather/denim/tweed jacket

translation: 监狱（监狱）
definition: a prison
example: She spent a year in jail.

translation: 监禁（将某人关入监狱）
definition: to put somebody in prison
example: be jailed (for something), He was jailed for life for murder.

translation: 果酱（通过糖煮水果制成的浓稠甜味物质，常涂在面包上）
definition: a thick sweet substance made by boiling fruit with sugar, often sold in jars and spread on bread
example: strawberry jam

translation: 一月（一年中的第一个月）
definition: the 1st month of the year, between December and February
example: She was born in January.

translation: 爵士乐（20世纪初由非裔美国音乐人开创的带强节奏和即兴演奏的音乐）
definition: a type of music with strong rhythms, in which the players often improvise (= make up the music as they are playing), originally created by African American musicians at the beginning of the 20th century
example: traditional/modern jazz

translation: 牛仔裤（粗棉布制成的长裤）
definition: trousers made of denim (= a type of strong cotton)
example: I always wear jeans.

translation: 喷气式飞机（由喷气发动机驱动的飞机）
definition: a plane driven by jet engines
example: a jet aircraft/fighter/airliner

translation: 珠宝（人们佩戴作为装饰的戒指、项链等物品）
definition: objects such as rings and necklaces that people wear as decoration
example: silver/gold jewellery

translation: 工作，职业（获得定期报酬的工作）
definition: work for which you receive regular payment
example: I don't have a job at present.

translation: 连接，加入（将两个或更多事物固定或连接在一起）
definition: to fix or connect two or more things together
example: join A to/onto B, Join one section of pipe to the next.

translation: 共同的，联合的（涉及两个或更多人在一起的，如联名账户）
definition: involving two or more people together
example: a joint account (= a bank account in the name of more than one person, for example shared by a couple)

translation: 关节（身体中两块骨头连接并能弯曲移动的地方）
definition: a place where two bones are joined together in the body in a way that enables them to bend and move
example: inflammation of the knee joint

translation: 玩笑，笑话（说或做以使人发笑的事，如幽默故事）
definition: something that you say or do to make people laugh, for example a funny story that you tell
example: I can't tell jokes.

translation: 开玩笑（说些让人发笑的话；讲幽默故事）
definition: to say something to make people laugh; to tell a funny story
example: She was laughing and joking with the children.

translation: 期刊，杂志（涉及特定主题或专业的报纸或杂志）
definition: a newspaper or magazine that deals with a particular subject or profession
example: a scientific/an academic journal

translation: 新闻业（为媒体搜集并撰写新闻故事的工作；所写的这些故事）
definition: the work of collecting and writing news stories for newspapers, magazines, radio, television or online news sites; the news stories that are written
example: I'd like a career in journalism.

translation: 记者（职业是为媒体搜集并撰写新闻故事的人）
definition: a person whose job is to collect and write news stories for newspapers, magazines, radio, television or online news sites
example: a freelance journalist

translation: 旅行，旅程（从一处移动到另一处的行为，尤指距离较远时）
definition: an act of travelling from one place to another, especially when they are far apart
example: They went on a long train journey across India.

translation: 喜悦（极度快乐的感觉）
definition: a feeling of great happiness
example: Her books have brought joy to millions.

translation: 法官，裁判（法庭上有权决定惩罚或做出法律判决的人；比赛裁判）
definition: a person in a court who has the authority to decide how criminals should be punished or to make legal decisions
example: a High Court judge

translation: 判断（根据现有信息对某人/某物形成看法）
definition: to form an opinion about somebody/something, based on the information you have
example: As far as I can judge, all of them are to blame.

translation: 判断力（在仔细考虑后做出明智决定的能力）
definition: the ability to make sensible decisions after carefully considering the best thing to do
example: good/poor/sound judgement

translation: 司法的（与法院、法官或法律判决相关的）
definition: connected with a court, a judge or legal judgement
example: judicial powers

translation: 果汁（来自水果或蔬菜的液体；由此制成的饮料）
definition: the liquid that comes from fruit or vegetables; a drink made from this
example: a glass of fruit juice

translation: 七月（一年中的第七个月）
definition: the 7th month of the year, between June and August
example: in July, She was born in July.

translation: 跳跃（跳的行为）
definition: an act of jumping
example: to do a parachute jump

translation: 跳（通过双腿发力快速离开地面或表面）
definition: to move quickly off the ground or away from a surface by pushing yourself with your legs and feet
example: ‘Quick, jump!’ he shouted.

translation: 交叉点，枢纽（两条或更多道路/铁路线汇合的地方）
definition: the place where two or more roads or railway lines meet
example: It was near the junction of City Road and Old Street.

translation: 六月（一年中的第六个月）
definition: the 6th month of the year, between May and July
example: She was born in June.

translation: 资历较浅的，初级的（在组织或行业中职级较低的）
definition: having a low rank in an organization or a profession
example: a junior partner/minister/officer

translation: 管辖权（官方机构对某人/某物做出法律判决的权力）
definition: the authority that an official organization has to make legal decisions about somebody/something
example: jurisdiction over somebody/something, The English court had no jurisdiction over the defendants.

translation: 陪审团（法庭上听取事实并裁定是否有罪或主张是否成立的公众小组）
definition: a group of members of the public who listen to the facts of a case in a court and decide whether or not somebody is guilty of a crime, or whether a claim has been proved
example: members of the jury

translation: 公正的（大多数人认为在道德上公平合理的）
definition: that most people consider to be morally fair and reasonable
example: a just decision/law/society

translation: 仅仅，只是（仅仅）
definition: only
example: There is just one method that might work.

translation: 正义，公正（对人的公平对待）
definition: the fair treatment of people
example: She spent her life fighting for social justice and equality for women.

translation: 理由，辩解（某事存在或被执行的充足理由）
definition: a good reason why something exists or is done
example: justification for doing something, I can see no possible justification for any further tax increases.

translation: 证明...有理（证明某人/某事是正确或合理的）
definition: to show that somebody/something is right or reasonable
example: justify doing something, How can they justify paying such huge salaries?

translation: 热衷的（非常想要做某事或希望某事发生的）
definition: wanting to do something or wanting something to happen very much
example: keen to do something, John was very keen to help.

translation: 保持，保留（继续拥有某物而不归还或丢弃）
definition: to continue to have something and not give it back or throw it away
example: He kept all her letters.

translation: 关键的（最重要的；必不可少的）
definition: most important; essential
example: the key issue/factor/point

translation: 钥匙（用于锁门、启动汽车等的特殊形状的金属片）
definition: a piece of metal with a special shape used for locking a door, starting a car, etc.
example: to put/turn the key in the lock

translation: 输入（使用键盘将信息输入电脑）
definition: to put information into a computer using a keyboard
example: key something, I was busy keying data.

translation: 键盘（用于操作电脑或打字机的一组按键；或智能手机上的虚拟字母键）
definition: the set of keys for operating a computer or typewriter, or the set of letters that you can touch to write on a smartphone or tablet
example: The program locks the keyboard until a password is given.

translation: 踢，一脚（用脚或腿部的移动，通常指用脚击打某物）
definition: a movement with the foot or the leg, usually to hit something with the foot
example: the first kick of the game

translation: 踢（用脚击打某人/某物）
definition: to hit somebody/something with your foot
example: Stop kicking―it hurts!

translation: 小孩（儿童或青少年）
definition: a child or young person
example: Do you have any kids?

translation: 绑架（非法带走某人并将其扣押为囚犯，尤指为了勒索赎金）
definition: to take somebody away illegally and keep them as a prisoner, especially in order to get money or something else for returning them
example: Two businessmen have been kidnapped by terrorists.

translation: 肾脏（人体内从血液中移除废物并产生尿液的两个器官之一）
definition: either of the two organs in the body that remove waste products from the blood and produce urine
example: a kidney infection

translation: 杀死（使某人/某物死亡）
definition: to make somebody/something die
example: kill (somebody/something), Cancer kills thousands of people every year.

translation: 谋杀，杀戮（蓄意杀死某人的行为）
definition: an act of killing somebody deliberately
example: Their leader condemned the torture and killing of innocent civilians.

translation: 千米，公里（长度测量单位；1000米）
definition: a unit for measuring distance; 1?000 metres
example: The industrial estate is 6 kilometres from the city centre.

translation: 仁慈的，友好的（关心他人；温和、友好且慷慨的）
definition: caring about others; gentle, friendly and generous
example: a very kind and helpful person

translation: 种类，类型（在某方面相同的一组人或物；特定品种）
definition: a group of people or things that are the same in some way; a particular variety or type
example: kind of somebody/something, three kinds of cakes/cake

translation: 国王（拥有皇室家族的独立国家的男性统治者）
definition: the male ruler of an independent state that has a royal family
example: the kings and queens of England

translation: 王国（以国王或女王为国家首脑的国家）
definition: a country that has a king or queen as head of state (= official leader of the country)

translation: 一生，寿命（某人活着或某物持续的时间长度）
definition: the length of time that somebody lives or that something lasts
example: a lifetime of experience

translation: 电梯（在建筑内将人或货物上下运送到不同楼层的机器）
definition: a machine that carries people or goods up and down to different levels in a building or a mine
example: It's on the sixth floor―let's take the lift.

translation: 举起，抬高（将某人/某物升至更高的位置或水平）
definition: to raise somebody/something or be raised to a higher position or level
example: lift somebody/something, I lifted the lid of the box and peered in.

translation: 浅色的（颜色浅的）
definition: pale in colour
example: He's got light blue eyes.

translation: 光，光线（来自太阳、灯等的使看清物体成为可能的能量）
definition: the energy from the sun, a lamp, etc. that makes it possible to see things
example: bright/dim light

translation: 点燃（使某物开始燃烧）
definition: to make something start to burn
example: She lit a candle.

translation: 照明（地方的灯光布置或类型）
definition: the arrangement or type of light in a place
example: electric/natural lighting

translation: 喜欢的事物（你喜欢的东西）
definition: the things that you like
example: We all have different likes and dislikes.

translation: 像，类似（与某人/某物相似）
definition: similar to somebody/something
example: She's wearing a dress like mine.

translation: 喜欢（觉得某人/某物愉快、吸引人或达到足够标准；享受某事）
definition: to find somebody/something pleasant, attractive or of a good enough standard; to enjoy something
example: like somebody/something, She's nice. I like her.

translation: 可能性（某事发生的几率；某事发生的可能性有多大）
definition: the chance of something happening; how likely something is to happen
example: There is very little likelihood of that happening.

translation: 可能的（很有机会发生或成为某样的；很可能的）
definition: having a good chance of happening or being something; probable or expected
example: the most likely explanation/outcome/scenario

translation: 同样地（同样地；以相似的方式）
definition: the same; in a similar way
example: He voted for the change and he expected his colleagues to do likewise.

translation: 肢（手臂或腿；或动物的翅膀等类似部分）
definition: an arm or a leg; a similar part of an animal, such as a wing
example: an artificial limb

translation: 限制，限额（允许的某事物的最大或最小数额）
definition: the greatest or smallest amount of something that is allowed
example: They imposed a strict spending limit.

translation: 限制（阻止某事物超过特定数额或水平）
definition: to stop something from increasing beyond a particular amount or level
example: measures to limit carbon dioxide emissions

translation: 限制，局限（限制或控制某人/某物的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of limiting or controlling somebody/something
example: They would resist any limitation of their powers.

translation: 有限的（在数量或范围上不大的）
definition: not very great in amount or extent
example: We are doing our best with the limited resources available.

translation: 线（表面上的细长标记）
definition: a long, thin mark on a surface
example: a straight/solid/dotted/dashed line

translation: 内衬，衬里（在某物内部覆盖一层材料，以保持清洁或加固）
definition: to cover the inside of something with a layer of another material, especially to keep it clean or make it stronger
example: Butter and line a 25 cm cake tin.

translation: 阵容（参加特定活动的人员名单）
definition: the people who are going to take part in a particular event
example: an impressive line-up of speakers

translation: 线性的（线的或成直线的）
definition: of or in lines
example: In his art he broke the laws of scientific linear perspective.

translation: 徘徊，逗留（存在时间比预期的长）
definition: to continue to exist for longer than expected
example: The faint smell of her perfume lingered in the room.

translation: 联系，纽带（两人或物之间的关联）
definition: a connection between two or more people or things
example: link between A and B, Police suspect there may be a link between the two murders.

translation: 连接，链接（在两个物体、机器、地方等之间建立物理或电子连接）
definition: to make a physical or electronic connection between one object, machine, place, etc. and another
example: link A to B, The video cameras are linked to a powerful computer.

translation: 狮子（猫科大型强力动物，群居，生活在非洲及南亚部分地区）
definition: a large, powerful animal of the cat family that hunts in groups and lives in parts of Africa and southern Asia. Lions have yellow-brown fur and the male has a mane (= long, thick hair round its neck).
example: The lion shook its mane and roared.

translation: 嘴唇（嘴开口处的两个柔软边缘之一）
definition: either of the two soft edges at the opening to the mouth
example: The assistant pursed her lips.

translation: 液体的（液态的；非固体也非气体的）
definition: in the form of a liquid; not a solid or a gas
example: liquid nitrogen

translation: 液体（自由流动、非固体也非气体的物质，如水或油）
definition: a substance that flows freely and is not a solid or a gas, for example water or oil
example: She poured the dark brown liquid down the sink.

translation: 名单，列表（一系列书写或打印出来的名称、项目、数字等）
definition: a series of names, items, figures, etc., especially when they are written or printed
example: The guest list includes numerous celebrities.

translation: 列出（按特定顺序写下项目列表）
definition: to write a list of things in a particular order
example: We were asked to list our ten favourite songs.

translation: 听（注意听你所能听到的声音或某人说话）
definition: to pay attention to somebody/something that you can hear
example: Listen! What's that noise? Can you hear it?

translation: 听众，倾听者（听的人）
definition: a person who listens
example: a good listener (= somebody who you can rely on to listen with attention or sympathy)

translation: 列表，清单（列表，尤指官方或出版的按字母顺序排列的人或物名单）
definition: a list, especially an official or published list of people or things, often arranged in alphabetical order
example: a comprehensive listing of all airlines

translation: 识字，读写能力（阅读和书写的能力）
definition: the ability to read and write
example: a campaign to promote adult literacy

translation: 字面上地（以字面意思地）
definition: in a literal way
example: The word ‘planet’ literally means ‘wandering body’.

translation: 文学的（与文学相关的）
definition: connected with literature
example: literary criticism/theory

translation: 文学（被视为艺术作品的写作，尤指小说、戏剧和诗歌）
definition: pieces of writing that are valued as works of art, especially novels, plays and poems (in contrast to technical books and newspapers, magazines, etc.)
example: English/American/French literature

translation: 升（体积测量单位，约等于1.76英制品脱或2.11美制品脱）
definition: a unit for measuring volume, equal to 1.76 British pints or 2.11 American pints
example: 3 litres of water

translation: 垃圾（人们留在公共场所的小块废弃物，如纸张、瓶罐）
definition: small pieces of rubbish such as paper, cans and bottles, that people have left lying in a public place
example: There will be fines for people who drop litter.

translation: 小的（不大的；小的；比其他的更小的）
definition: not big; small; smaller than others
example: a little house

translation: 有一点（在小程度上）
definition: to a small degree
example: She seemed a little afraid of going inside.

translation: 一点（用于不可数名词，意为“少量”、“一些”）
definition: used with uncountable nouns to mean ‘a small amount’, ‘some’
example: a little milk/sugar/tea

translation: 一点（用于不可数名词，意为“少量”、“一些”）
definition: used with uncountable nouns to mean ‘a small amount’, ‘some’
example: a little milk/sugar/tea

translation: 活的（活着的；未死的）
definition: living; not dead
example: live animals

translation: 现场的，直播的（在事件发生时播出的；或现场表演录制的）
definition: broadcast at the time of an actual event; played or recorded at an actual performance
example: The show is going out live.

translation: 居住（在特定地方安家）
definition: to have your home in a particular place
example: to live in a house/a flat/an apartment

translation: 精力充沛的，活泼的（充满活力和能量的；积极且热情的）
definition: full of life and energy; active and enthusiastic
example: an intelligent and lively young woman

translation: 肝脏（人体内清理血液并产生胆汁的大器官）
definition: a large organ in the body that cleans the blood and produces bile
example: liver disease

translation: 活着的（现存的；所有的生物）
definition: alive now
example: all living things

translation: 生计（维持生活所需的金钱）
definition: money to buy the things that you need in life
example: She earns her living as a freelance journalist.

translation: 负载，装载物（由人、车等携带的物体，通常数量很大）
definition: something that is being carried (usually in large amounts) by a person, vehicle, etc.
example: The trucks waited at the warehouse to pick up their loads.

translation: 装载（将大量物或人放入或放在某物上）
definition: to put a large quantity of things or people onto or into something
example: load something, We loaded the car in ten minutes.

translation: 贷款（由银行等机构借出、某人借入的钱）
definition: money that an organization such as a bank lends and somebody borrows
example: to take out/repay a loan (= to borrow money/pay it back)

translation: 大厅，大堂（公共建筑入口内供人们见面和等待的大区域）
definition: a large area inside the entrance of a public building where people can meet and wait
example: a hotel lobby

translation: 游说（试图影响政治家或政府，例如说服其支持或反对法律修改）
definition: to try to influence a politician or the government and, for example, persuade them to support or oppose a change in the law
example: Farmers will lobby Congress for higher subsidies.

translation: 当地的（属于或与你谈论的特定地方或你居住的区域相关的）
definition: belonging to or connected with the particular place or area that you are talking about or with the place where you live
example: local people/residents/businesses

translation: 当地人（居住在特定地方或区域的人）
definition: a person who lives in a particular place or district
example: The locals are very friendly.

translation: 定位（找出某人/某物的确切位置）
definition: to find the exact position of somebody/something
example: The mechanic located the fault immediately.

translation: 位于（如果某物位于某处，指其存在于那里或被安置在那里）
definition: if something is located in a particular place, it exists there or has been put there
example: a small town located 30 miles south of Chicago

translation: 地点，位置（某事发生或存在的地方；某物的位置）
definition: a place where something happens or exists; the position of something
example: a honeymoon in a secret location

translation: 锁（通常需要钥匙开启的固定门、窗、盒子等的装置）
definition: a device that keeps a door, window, box, etc. shut, usually needing a key to open it
example: She turned the key in the lock.

translation: 上锁（用锁固定某物；被锁住）
definition: to fasten something with a lock; to be fastened with a lock
example: Did you lock the door?

translation: 原木（从树上砍下或落下的粗木块）
definition: a thick piece of wood that is cut from or has fallen from a tree
example: logs for the fire

translation: 记录（在官方记录中输入信息或记录事件）
definition: to put information in an official record or write a record of events
example: The police log all phone calls.

translation: 逻辑（思考或解释某事的方式）
definition: a way of thinking or explaining something
example: I fail to see the logic behind his argument.

translation: 合乎逻辑的（显得自然、合理或明智的）
definition: seeming natural, reasonable or sensible
example: It was a logical conclusion from the child's point of view.

translation: 标志，徽标（公司或组织用作其特别标志的打印图案或符号）
definition: a printed design or symbol that a company or an organization uses as its special sign
example: All over the world there are red and white paper cups bearing the company logo.

translation: 孤独的（因没有朋友或交流的人而感到不快乐的）
definition: unhappy because you have no friends or people to talk to
example: She lives alone and often feels lonely.

translation: 长的（在长度或距离上很大的，或超过通常水平的）
definition: measuring or covering a great length or distance, or a greater length or distance than usual
example: She had long dark hair.

translation: 长时间地（在很长一段时间内）
definition: for a long time
example: Have you been here long?

translation: 长期的（已经存在或持续了很长时间的）
definition: that has existed or lasted for a long time
example: a long-standing relationship

translation: 长期的（在长时期内持续或产生影响的）
definition: lasting or having an effect over a long period of time
example: Our long-term goal is to lower operating costs by 10 per cent.

translation: 长期地（在长时期内）
definition: over a long period of time
example: to benefit/affect somebody long-term

translation: 长期的（在很长时间内一直是提到的那种身份的）
definition: having been the particular thing mentioned for a long time
example: his long-time colleague

translation: 看（看某人/某物的动作）
definition: an act of looking at somebody/something
example: look at somebody/something, Here, have a look at this.

translation: 看（将眼睛转向特定方向）
definition: to turn your eyes in a particular direction
example: Look closely and tell me what you see.

translation: 隐约显现（以模糊且庞大的形状出现，尤指令人恐惧地）
definition: to appear as a large shape that is not clear, especially in a frightening way
example: A dark shape loomed up ahead of us.

translation: 环，圈（由线条绕圈形成的弧线或圆形形状）
definition: a shape like a curve or circle made by a line curving right round
example: The road went in a huge loop around the lake.

translation: 松的（未牢固固定的；能从某物上脱落的）
definition: not securely fixed where it should be; able to become separated from something
example: a loose button/tooth

translation: 勋爵，大人（英国高等级贵族，或作为荣誉给予的头衔）
definition: (in the UK) a man of high rank in the nobility (= people of high social class), or somebody who has been given the title ‘lord’ as an honour
example: She's married to a lord.

translation: 卡车，货车（用于通过公路运输重型货物的大型车辆）
definition: a large vehicle for carrying heavy loads by road
example: a lorry driver

translation: 丢失（无法找到某物/某人）
definition: to be unable to find something/somebody
example: I've lost my keys.

translation: 丢失，损失（不再拥有某物或拥有量减少的状态；导致此结果的过程）
definition: the state of no longer having something or as much of something; the process that leads to this
example: I want to report the loss of a package.

translation: 迷路的（无法找到路；不知道自己在何处的）
definition: unable to find your way; not knowing where you are
example: We always get lost in London.

translation: 很多地（与动词连用，意为“大量地”）
definition: used with verbs to mean ‘a great amount’
example: I care a lot about you.

translation: 许多（某人/某物的很大数量或金额）
definition: a large number or amount of somebody/something
example: What a lot of presents!

translation: 很多（很大的数量或金额）
definition: a large number or amount
example: ‘How many do you need?’ ‘A lot.’

translation: 彩票（通过出售带有不同号码的彩票为政府、慈善机构筹款的方式）
definition: a way of raising money for a government, charity, etc. by selling tickets that have different numbers on them that people have chosen. Numbers are then chosen by chance and the people who have those numbers on their tickets win prizes.
example: the national/state lottery

translation: 大声的（发出很大响声的）
definition: making a lot of noise
example: loud laughter

translation: 大声地（以很大响声或易被听见的方式）
definition: in a way that makes a lot of noise or can be easily heard
example: Do you have to play that music so loud?

translation: 大声地（以产生很大响声的方式）
definition: in a way that makes a lot of noise
example: She screamed as loudly as she could.

translation: 爱，热爱（对某人/某物――尤指家人或朋友――极强烈的喜爱和关怀感）
definition: a very strong feeling of liking and caring for somebody/something, especially a member of your family or a friend
example: She has earned the love and respect of many people.

translation: 爱（对某人有极强烈的喜爱和关怀感）
definition: to have very strong feelings of liking and caring for somebody
example: I love you.

translation: 可爱的，美丽的（美丽的；迷人的）
definition: beautiful; attractive
example: She looked particularly lovely that night.

translation: 低的（不高的；离地面不远的）
definition: not high or tall; not far above the ground
example: a low wall/building/table

translation: 低低地（处于离地面不远的位置）
definition: in or into a low position, not far above the ground
example: to crouch/bend low

translation: 低点（低水平或低点；低数字）
definition: a low level or point; a low figure
example: The temperature reached a record low in London last night.

translation: 降低（减少某物或使其价值、质量下降）
definition: to reduce something or to become less in value, quality, etc.
example: lower something, He lowered his voice to a whisper.

translation: 忠诚的（对自己支持的人或物保持恒定支持的）
definition: remaining constant in your support of somebody/something
example: a loyal friend/supporter

translation: 忠诚（对自己支持的人或物保持恒定支持的品质）
definition: the quality of being constant in your support of somebody/something
example: Can I count on your loyalty?

translation: 运气（偶然发生的而非因努力产生的好事）
definition: good things that happen to you by chance, not because of your own efforts or abilities
example: with (any) luck, With any luck, we'll be home before dark.

translation: 幸运的（有好运的）
definition: having good luck
example: lucky to do something, His friend was killed and he knows he is lucky to be alive.

translation: 午餐（在一日午间吃的饭）
definition: a meal eaten in the middle of the day
example: She's gone to lunch.

translation: 肺（胸腔内用于呼吸的两个器官之一）
definition: either of the two organs in the chest that you use for breathing
example: Her father died of lung cancer.

translation: 豪华的，奢侈的（昂贵且高质量的）
definition: expensive and of very high quality
example: a luxury hotel/car/apartment

translation: 奢侈，奢华（享受特殊且昂贵事物的实情，尤指食宿、衣物）
definition: the fact of enjoying special and expensive things, particularly food and drink, clothes and places
example: a life of unimaginable luxury

translation: 歌词（流行歌曲的歌词）
definition: the words of a popular song
example: music and lyrics by Rodgers and Hart

translation: 机器（由许多部件协作完成特定任务的设备，动力可来自电、蒸汽等）
definition: a piece of equipment with many parts that work together to do a particular task. The power used to work a machine may be electricity, steam, gas, etc. or human power.
example: Machines have replaced human labour in many industries.

translation: 机械（作为一个整体的机器，尤指大型机器）
definition: machines as a group, especially large ones
example: agricultural/industrial machinery

translation: 疯的，愚蠢的（非常愚蠢的；一点不明智的）
definition: very stupid; not at all sensible
example: You must be mad to risk it.

translation: 杂志（每周或每月出版的、包含文章照片的薄册子；或在线合集）
definition: a type of large thin book with a paper cover that you can buy every week or month, containing articles, photographs, etc., often on a particular topic; a similar collection of articles, etc. that appears regularly online
example: a weekly/monthly magazine

translation: 有魔力的（具有或使用特殊力量使不可能之事发生或看似发生的）
definition: having or using special powers to make impossible things happen or seem to happen
example: a magic spell/charm/potion

translation: 魔法（通过说特殊词语或做特殊动作使不可能之事发生的神秘力量）
definition: the secret power of appearing to make impossible things happen by saying special words or doing special things
example: Do you believe in magic?

translation: 魔幻的（包含魔法的；用于魔法的）
definition: containing magic; used in magic
example: magical powers

translation: 地方法官（在初级法院担任法官的官员）
definition: an official who acts as a judge in the lowest courts of law
example: to come up before the magistrates

translation: 有磁性的（表现得像磁铁的；能被磁铁吸引的）
definition: behaving like a magnet; that can be attracted by a magnet
example: magnetic materials

translation: 壮丽的，宏伟的（极具吸引力和感染力的；值得赞美的）
definition: extremely attractive and impressive; deserving praise
example: The Taj Mahal is a magnificent building.

translation: 巨大，规模（事物巨大的规模或重要性；事物的巨大程度）
definition: the great size or importance of something; the degree to which something is large or important
example: We did not realize the magnitude of the problem.

translation: 邮件（用于寄送和递送信件、包裹的官方系统）
definition: the official system used for sending and delivering letters, packages, etc.
example: a mail service/train/van

translation: 邮寄（利用邮政系统给某人寄送某物）
definition: to send something to somebody using the postal system
example: mail something (to somebody/something), Don't forget to mail that letter to your mother.

translation: 主要的（同类中最大或最重要的）
definition: being the largest or most important of its kind
example: Be careful crossing the main road.

translation: 大陆（国家或地区的主要陆地区域，不包括附近岛屿）
definition: the main area of land of a country or region, not including any islands near to it
example: to/from the mainland, a boat to/from the mainland

translation: 主要地（比其他任何事物都多；也用于说明最重要的原因）
definition: more than anything else; also used to talk about the most important reason for something
example: They eat mainly fruit and nuts.

translation: 主流的（被大多数人接受或视为正常的）
definition: considered normal because it reflects what is done or accepted by most people
example: mainstream culture/politics

translation: 主流（被视为正常的思想观点，因其被大多数人认同）
definition: the ideas and opinions that are thought to be normal because they are shared by most people; the people whose ideas and opinions are most accepted
example: His radical views place him outside the mainstream of American politics.

translation: 维持，保持（使某事保持在同一水平、标准等）
definition: to make something continue at the same level, standard, etc.
example: to maintain law and order/standards/a balance/control

translation: 维护，保养（通过定期检查或修理使某物保持良好状态的行为）
definition: the act of keeping something in good condition by checking or repairing it regularly
example: The school pays for heating and the maintenance of the buildings.

translation: 主要的，重大的（非常大或重要的）
definition: very large or important
example: a major road

translation: 多数（一群人或事物中的大部分）
definition: the largest part of a group of people or things
example: majority (of somebody/something), The majority of people interviewed prefer TV to radio.

translation: 品牌，型号（由特定公司制造的机器、设备的名称或类型）
definition: the name or type of a machine, piece of equipment, etc. that is made by a particular company
example: make of something, What make of car does he drive?

translation: 制造，做（通过组合材料或部件创造或准备某物）
definition: to create or prepare something by combining materials or putting parts together
example: make something, to make a table/dress/cake

translation: 化妆品（用于皮肤上以增加吸引力或改变外观的彩色物质）
definition: coloured substances used on the skin to make yourself look more attractive or to change your appearance
example: eye make-up

translation: 制造（制造或生产某物的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of making or producing something
example: strategic decision-making

translation: 男性的（男人或男孩的）
definition: being a man or boy
example: a male friend/colleague/partner

translation: 雄性（男性的人、动物或植物）
definition: a male person, animal or plant
example: The male of the species has a white tail.

translation: 制造业（在工厂大规模生产商品的业务或行业）

translation: 许多（用于复数名词，表示“大量”。也用于疑问句询及数量）
definition: used with plural nouns and verbs, especially in negative sentences or in more formal English, to mean ‘a large number of’. Also used in questions to ask about the size of a number, and with ‘as’, ‘so’ and ‘too’.
example: We don't have very many copies left.

translation: 地图（地球表面或其一部分的绘图，显示国家、城镇、河流等）

面具，口罩（戴在脸上以隐藏、吓人或娱乐的东西）

translation: 巨大的（非常大、重且坚固的）

translation: 媒介（向人们交流信息等的方式）

translation: 合并（将两个或更多组织、业务加入为一个的行为）

translation: 优点，功绩（优秀且值得称赞或奖赏的品质）

translation: 混乱（肮脏或杂乱的状态）

translation: 方法（做某事的特定方式）
