translation: 军事的（与士兵或武装部队相关的）
definition: connected with soldiers or the armed forces
example: We may have to take military action.

translation: 军队（士兵；武装部队的总称）
definition: soldiers; the armed forces
example: The military was/were called in to deal with the riot.

translation: 民兵组织（非职业士兵但受过军事训练、可作为军队行动的团体）
definition: a group of people who are not professional soldiers but who have had military training and can act as an army
example: He said he would call out the state militia if the rebels did not surrender.

translation: 牛奶（牛、山羊等产出的白色液体，供幼崽食用及人类饮用）
definition: the white liquid produced by cows, goats and some other animals as food for their young and used as a drink by humans
example: a pint/litre of milk

translation: 磨坊，磨粉机（装有将谷物磨成粉的设备的建筑或机器）
definition: a building fitted with equipment for grinding grain into flour; a machine for grinding grain
example: The old mill has been converted into apartments.
a population of half a million

translation: 头脑，心思（人能够感知、思考和感觉的部分，如意识或潜意识）
definition: the part of a person that makes them able to be aware of things, to think and to feel
example: the conscious/subconscious mind

translation: 介意（因某事感到不快、恼火或担心）
definition: to be upset, annoyed or worried by something
example: mind (something), I don't mind the cold―it's the rain I don't like.

translation: 矿山，矿井（地下的深洞，用于挖掘煤、金等矿物）
definition: a deep hole or holes under the ground where minerals such as coal, gold, etc. are dug
example: a copper/diamond mine

translation: 我的（属于说话者或作者的东西）
definition: of or belonging to the person writing or speaking
example: That's mine.

translation: 矿工（在矿井中从事挖掘煤、金、钻石等工作的人）
definition: a person who works in a mine taking out coal, gold, diamonds, etc.
example: Rescuers are trying to save miners trapped underground after a gas explosion.

translation: 矿物质，矿物（地壳中自然存在的非生物物质，如金、盐；也指食物中的矿物质）
definition: a substance that is naturally present in the earth and is not formed from animal or vegetable matter, for example gold and salt. Some minerals are also present in food and drink and in the human body and are essential for good health.
example: a country rich in mineral resources

translation: 最小的，极小的（在尺寸或数量上非常小的；尽可能小的）
definition: very small in size or amount; as small as possible
example: The work was carried out at minimal cost.

translation: 使最小化（将某事――尤指坏事――减少到最低水平）
definition: to reduce something, especially something bad, to the lowest possible level
example: Good hygiene helps to minimize the risk of infection.

translation: 最小的，最低限度的（尽可能小的或允许的最低限度）
definition: the smallest that is possible or allowed; extremely small
example: a minimum charge/price

translation: 最小值（可能的、要求的或记录的最小数量或数额）
definition: the smallest or lowest amount that is possible, required or recorded
example: The class needs a minimum of six students to continue.

translation: 采矿，采矿业（从地下获取煤和其他矿物的过程或行业）
definition: the process of getting coal and other minerals from under the ground; the industry involved in this
example: coal/diamond/gold/tin mining

translation: 部长，大臣（政府部门的高级负责人）
definition: a senior member of the government who is in charge of a government department or a branch of one
example: the Minister of Education

translation: 部，部委（具有特定职责范围的政府部门）
definition: a government department that has a particular area of responsibility
example: The Ministry of Defence has issued the following statement.

translation: 次要的，较小的（不很大、不重要或不严重的）
definition: not very large, important or serious
example: The new plan involves widening a minor road through the valley.

translation: 少数，少数民族（群体中较小的部分；不足总数的一半）
definition: the smaller part of a group; less than half of the people or things in a large group
example: Only a small minority of students is/are interested in politics these days.

translation: 极小的（极其微小的，如水中微量的化学物质）
definition: extremely small
example: minute amounts of chemicals in the water

translation: 分钟（一小时的六十分之一，等于60秒）
definition: each of the 60 parts of an hour, that are equal to 60 seconds
example: minutes to…, It's four minutes to six.

translation: 奇迹（不遵循自然法则且被认为是由神导致的行为或事件）
definition: an act or event that does not follow the laws of nature and is believed to be caused by God
example: the miracle of rising from the grave

translation: 镜子（能反射影像的特殊平面玻璃）
definition: a piece of special flat glass that reflects images, so that you can see yourself when you look in it
example: in the mirror, He looked at himself in the mirror.

translation: 痛苦的，悲惨的（非常不快乐或不舒服的）
definition: very unhappy or uncomfortable
example: We were cold, wet and thoroughly miserable.

translation: 痛苦，苦难（极大的身体或精神痛苦）
definition: great physical or mental pain
example: Fame brought her nothing but misery.

translation: 误导性的（给出错误的想法或印象，使人相信不真实之事的）
definition: giving the wrong idea or impression and making you believe something that is not true
example: misleading information/advertisements

translation: 错过，错过（迟到或未赶上某事，如飞机）
definition: to be or arrive too late for something
example: If I don't leave now I'll miss my plane.

translation: 导弹（在空中发射并在击中目标时爆炸的武器）
definition: a weapon that is sent through the air and that explodes when it hits the thing that it is aimed at
example: nuclear missiles

translation: 失踪的，缺失的（找不到的或不在原处的；丢失或毁坏的）
definition: that cannot be found or that is not in its usual place; that has been removed, lost or destroyed
example: I never found the missing piece.

translation: 任务，使命（必须完成的特定任务或目标，尤指重要的）
definition: that cannot exist or be done; not possible
example: almost/virtually/nearly impossible

translation: 错误（不正确的行为或观点，或产生不想要结果的行为）
definition: an action or an opinion that is not correct, or that produces a result that you did not want
example: It's easy to make a mistake.

translation: 弄错，误解（未能正确理解或判断某人/某物）
definition: to not understand or judge somebody/something correctly
example: mistake somebody/something, I admit that I mistook his intentions.

translation: 混合（不同人或物的结合）
definition: a combination of different people or things
example: It's a school with a good social and ethnic mix of children.

translation: 混合（两种或多种物质结合在一起，通常指难以再分开）
definition: if two or more substances or things mix or you mix them, they combine, usually in a way that means they cannot easily be separated
example: Oil and water do not mix.

translation: 混合的（由不同的品质或元素组成的）
definition: consisting of different qualities or elements
example: a mixed diet

translation: 混合物（不同事物的结合体）
definition: a combination of different things
example: She was a curious mixture, part grand lady, part wild child.

translation: 暴民，暴民（一大群人，尤指可能变得暴力或引起混乱的）
definition: a large crowd of people, especially one that may become violent or cause trouble
example: an angry/unruly mob

translation: 移动的，手机的（与手机、平板电脑等相关的）
definition: connected with mobile phones, tablets, etc.
example: What's your mobile number?

translation: 手机（移动电话）
definition: a mobile phone
example: Call me on my mobile.

translation: 流动性（从一处、一个阶层或一份工作轻松移动到另一处的能力）
definition: the ability to move easily from one place, social class or job to another
example: social/geographical/career mobility

translation: 动员（为了特定目的共同工作；或组织一群人这样做）
definition: to work together in order to achieve a particular aim; to organize a group of people to do this
example: The unions mobilized thousands of workers in a protest against the cuts.

translation: 模式，方式（做某事的特定方式或某物的特定类型）
definition: a particular way of doing something; a particular type of something
example: a mode of communication

translation: 模型，模型（事物的复制品，通常比原物小）
definition: a copy of something, usually smaller than the original object
example: a working model (= one in which the parts move) of a fire engine

translation: 模拟（创建活动或情况的副本或描述以便研究）
definition: to create a copy or description of an activity, a situation, etc. so that you can study it before dealing with the real thing
example: The program can model a typical home page for you.

translation: 适度的，中等的（既不太好/大也不太坏/小的；中等的）
definition: that is neither very good, large, hot, etc. nor very bad, small, cold, etc.
example: students of moderate ability

translation: 现代的（当今时代或近代的）
definition: of the present time or recent times
example: the modern industrial world

translation: 谦虚的，适度的（不很大、不昂贵或不重要的）
definition: not very large, expensive, important, etc.
example: modest improvements/reforms

translation: 修改，改进（为了改进或使其更易接受而改变某事物的行为或改变本身）
definition: the act or process of changing something in order to improve it or make it more acceptable; a change that is made
example: Considerable modification of the existing system is needed.

translation: 修改（微调某物，尤指为了使其更适合特定目的）
definition: to change something slightly, especially in order to make it more suitable for a particular purpose
example: Patients are taught how to modify their diet.

translation: 时刻，瞬间（极短的一段时间）
definition: a very short period of time
example: Could you wait a moment, please?

translation: 势头，动力（持续增长或发展的能力）
definition: the ability to keep increasing or developing
example: The fight for his release gathers momentum each day.

translation: 星期一（周日之后、周二之前的一天）
definition: the day of the week after Sunday and before Tuesday, the first day of the working week
example: It's Monday today, isn't it?

translation: 钱（通过工作或销售获得的用于购买东西的货币）
definition: what you earn by working or selling things, and use to buy things
example: to borrow/save/spend/earn money

translation: 显示器，监视器（显示电脑信息或特定电视信号的屏幕）
definition: a screen that shows information from a computer; a television screen used to show particular kinds of information
example: The details of today's flights are displayed on the monitor.

translation: 监控，监视（在一段时间内观察并核实某事的发展，以便做出必要改变）
definition: to watch and check something over a period of time in order to see how it develops, so that you can make any necessary changes
example: monitor something, Each student's progress is closely monitored.

translation: 修道士，僧侣（住在修道院中、不结婚、无私人财产的男性宗教团体成员）
definition: a member of a religious group of men who often live apart from other people in a monastery and who do not marry or have personal possessions
example: Benedictine/Buddhist monks

translation: 猴子（生活在热带国家、会爬树的长尾动物，与类人猿及人类亲缘较近）
definition: an animal with a long tail, that climbs trees and lives in hot countries. There are several types of monkey and they are related to apes and humans.
example: Like humans, apes and monkeys live in complex social groupings.

translation: 垄断（对特定商品贸易或服务供应的完全控制）
definition: the complete control of trade in particular goods or the supply of a particular service; a type of goods or a service that is controlled in this way
example: In the past central government had a monopoly on television broadcasting.

translation: 怪物（故事中巨大、丑陋且令人恐惧的想象生物）
definition: (in stories) an imaginary creature that is very large, ugly and frightening
example: a monster with three heads

translation: 月（一年分成的十二个时段之一，如五月或六月）
definition: any of the twelve periods of time into which the year is divided, for example May or June
example: The months of July and August are the hottest.

translation: 每月的（每月发生一次的或每个月的）
definition: happening once a month or every month
example: a monthly meeting/visit/magazine

translation: 纪念碑，历史遗迹（为纪念名人或重要事件而建的建筑、雕像等）
definition: a building, column, statue, etc. built to remind people of a famous person or event
example: A monument to him was erected in St Paul's Cathedral.

translation: 情绪，心情（在特定时间的感觉）
definition: the way you are feeling at a particular time
example: in a … mood, She's in a good mood today (= happy and friendly).

translation: 月亮（每27.3天绕地球一周、在夜间反射太阳光的球体）
definition: the round object that moves around the earth once every 27? days and shines at night by light reflected from the sun
example: the surface of the moon

translation: 道德的（与对错行为原则相关的）
definition: connected with principles of right and wrong behaviour
example: a moral issue/dilemma

translation: 品行，道德（良好行为的标准或原则，尤指在性关系方面）
definition: standards or principles of good behaviour, especially in matters of sexual relationships
example: Young people these days have no morals.

translation: 道德（关于对错或好坏行为的原则）
definition: principles relating to right and wrong or good and bad behaviour
example: matters of public/private morality

translation: 更多地（用于构成多音节形容词和副词的比较级）
definition: used to form the comparative of most adjectives and adverbs with two or more syllables
example: She was far more intelligent than her sister.

translation: 更多的（更大数量或金额的）
definition: a larger number or amount of
example: I want some more!

translation: 更多（更大数量或金额的）
definition: used with plural nouns and verbs, especially in negative sentences or in more formal English, to mean ‘a large number of’. Also used in questions to ask about the size of a number, and with ‘as’, ‘so’ and ‘too’.
example: We don't have very many copies left.

translation: 而且，此外（用于引入补充或支持前言的新信息）
definition: used to introduce some new information that adds to or supports what you have said previously
example: A talented artist, he was, moreover, a writer of some note.

translation: 早晨，上午（从醒来到中午或午餐前的时间段）
definition: the early part of the day from the time when people wake up until 12 o'clock in the middle of the day or before lunch
example: They left for Spain early this morning.

translation: 抵押贷款（为了买房从银行借钱并分年归还的法律协议；所借款项）
definition: a legal agreement by which a bank or similar organization lends you money to buy a house, etc., and you pay the money back over a particular number of years; the sum of money that you borrow
example: to apply for/take out/pay off a mortgage

translation: 清真寺（穆斯林进行礼拜的建筑）
definition: a building where Muslims go to worship (= praise God)
example: I used to pray at the local mosque with my father and grandfather.

translation: 最（用于构成多音节形容词和副词的最高级）
definition: used to form the superlative of most adjectives and adverbs of two or more syllables
example: the most boring/beautiful part

translation: 最多的（数量或金额最大的）
definition: the largest in number or amount
example: Who do you think will get (the) most votes?

translation: 最多（数量或金额最大的）
definition: used with plural nouns and verbs, especially in negative sentences or in more formal English, to mean ‘a large number of’. Also used in questions to ask about the size of a number, and with ‘as’, ‘so’ and ‘too’.
example: We don't have very many copies left.

translation: 主要地（主要地；通常地）
definition: mainly; generally
example: The sauce is mostly cream.

translation: 母亲（孩子或动物的女性亲本；扮演母亲角色的人）
definition: a female parent of a child or animal; a person who is acting as a mother to a child
example: I want to buy a present for my mother and father.

translation: 运动，移动（移动的行为、过程或方式）
definition: the act or process of moving or the way something moves
example: What was Newton's first law of motion?

translation: 激励，促使（成为某人做某事或以特定方式表现的原因）
definition: to be the reason why somebody does something or behaves in a particular way
example: motivate somebody (to do something), What motivates people to carry out such attacks?

translation: 动机（某人做某事或以特定方式表现的原因）
definition: the reason why somebody does something or behaves in a particular way
example: motivation (behind something), What is the motivation behind this sudden change?

translation: 动机，目的（做某事的理由）
definition: a reason for doing something
example: There seemed to be no motive for the murder.

translation: 机动的（带引擎的；利用引擎动力的）
definition: having an engine; using the power of an engine
example: The street is closed to motor vehicles.

translation: 马达，发动机（利用电、汽油等产生动力使机器、车辆等工作的装置）
definition: a device that uses electricity, petrol, etc. to produce movement and makes a machine, a vehicle, a boat, etc. work
example: An electric motor is used to pump the water.

translation: 摩托车（带引擎的两轮道路车辆，通常有前后座）
definition: a road vehicle with two wheels, driven by an engine, with one seat for the driver and often a seat for a passenger behind the driver
example: He never learned to ride a motorcycle or to drive a car.

translation: 驾车者（驾驶汽车的人）
definition: a person driving a car
example: The accident was reported by a passing motorist.

translation: 组织，发起（组织并开始某项活动，如发起运动）
definition: to organize and begin something
example: Residents mounted a campaign to fight the plans.

translation: 山，山脉（非常高的山丘，顶部常有岩石）
definition: a very high hill, often with rocks near the top
example: the mountains of Andalusia

translation: 老鼠（覆盖皮毛、带长薄尾巴的小动物，生活在野外或建筑物内）
definition: a small animal that is covered in fur and has a long thin tail. Mice live in fields, in people’s houses or where food is stored.
example: a house mouse

translation: 嘴（脸上用于说话、进食的开口；头部的内部区域）
definition: the opening in the face used for speaking, eating, etc.; the area inside the head behind this opening
example: She opened her mouth to say something.

translation: 移动（地点或位置的改变）
definition: a change of place or position
example: Don't make a move!

translation: 移动（改变位置或使人/物改变位置，可被察觉）
definition: to change position or make somebody/something change position in a way that can be seen, heard or felt
example: Don't move―stay perfectly still.

translation: 运动，动作（身体或身体部位的移动行为）
definition: an act of moving the body or part of the body
example: hand/eye movements

translation: 电影（记录有声音的、讲述故事的一系列移动画面）
definition: a series of moving pictures recorded with sound that tells a story, watched at a movie theater or on a television or other device
example: You'll love this movie.

translation: 动人的（引起强烈情感的，常指悲伤的情感）
definition: causing strong, often sad, feelings about somebody/something
example: a deeply moving experience

translation: 非常（很大程度上）
definition: to a great degree
example: Thank you very much for the flowers.

translation: 很多（用于不可数名词，尤用于否定句表示“大量的”）
definition: used with uncountable nouns, especially in negative sentences to mean ‘a large amount of something’, or after ‘how’ to ask about the amount of something. It is also used with ‘as’, ‘so’ and ‘too’.
example: I don't have much money with me.

translation: 很多（很大数量或金额）
definition: used with plural nouns and verbs, especially in negative sentences or in more formal English, to mean ‘a large number of’. Also used in questions to ask about the size of a number, and with ‘as’, ‘so’ and ‘too’.
example: We don't have very many copies left.

translation: 泥，泥浆（潮湿、柔软且黏稠的土地）
definition: wet earth that is soft and sticky
example: The car wheels got stuck in the mud.

translation: 多种的，倍数（数量很多的；涉及许多不同人或物的）
definition: many in number; involving many different people or things
example: The shape appears multiple times within each painting.

translation: 乘，增加（将一个数与自身相加特定次数；使增加）
definition: to add a number to itself a particular number of times
example: The children are already learning to multiply and divide.

translation: 妈妈（母亲的昵称）
definition: a mother
example: Call your mum.

translation: 市政的，市的（与拥有地方政府的城镇或地区相关的）
definition: connected with or belonging to a town, city or district that has its own local government
example: municipal elections/councils

translation: 谋杀（蓄意杀死某人的罪行）
definition: the crime of killing somebody deliberately
example: He was found guilty of murder.

translation: 谋杀（蓄意且非法地杀死某人）
definition: to kill somebody deliberately and illegally
example: He denies murdering his wife's lover.

translation: 肌肉（身体中通过收缩和舒张使部位移动的组织）
definition: a piece of body tissue that you make tight and relax in order to move a particular part of the body; the tissue that forms the muscles of the body
example: a calf/neck/thigh muscle

translation: 博物馆（保存并向公众展示艺术、文化、历史或科学物品的建筑）
definition: a building in which objects of artistic, cultural, historical or scientific interest are kept and shown to the public
example: a museum of modern art

translation: 音乐（以令人愉快或兴奋的方式安排的声音，通过歌唱或乐器表现）
definition: sounds that are arranged in a way that is pleasant or exciting to listen to. People sing music or play it on instruments.
example: I like any kind of pop or dance music.

translation: 音乐的（与音乐相关的；包含音乐的）
definition: connected with music; containing music
example: musical styles/tastes

translation: 音乐剧（部分或全部故事通过歌曲和舞蹈讲述的戏剧或电影）
definition: a play or film in which part or all of the story is told using songs and often dancing
example: a Broadway/Hollywood musical

translation: 音乐家（演奏乐器或创作音乐的人，尤指以此为业者）
definition: a person who plays a musical instrument or writes music, especially as a job
example: a jazz/rock/classical musician

translation: 必须（用于表示某事是必要的或非常重要的）
definition: used to say that something is necessary or very important (sometimes involving a rule or a law)
example: All visitors must report to reception.

translation: 相互的（用于描述两人间程度平等的感情或行动）
definition: used to describe feelings that two or more people have for each other equally, or actions that affect two or more people equally
example: mutual respect/understanding

translation: 我的（属于说话者或作者的）
definition: of or belonging to the speaker or writer
example: Where's my passport?

translation: 我自己（当说话者同时也是动作的受影响者时使用）
definition: used when the speaker or writer is also the person affected by an action
example: I cut myself on a knife.

translation: 神秘的（难以理解或解释的；奇怪的）
definition: difficult to understand or explain; strange
example: He died in mysterious circumstances.

translation: 神秘，谜（难以理解或解释的事物）
definition: something that is difficult to understand or to explain
example: It is one of the great unsolved mysteries of this century.

translation: 神话（古代关于自然现象或早期历史的故事，真假不一）
definition: a story from ancient times, especially one that was told to explain natural events or to describe the early history of a people; this type of story
example: ancient Greek myths

translation: 指甲，钉子（手指或脚趾尖端的薄硬层；或金属钉）
definition: the thin hard layer covering the outer tip of the fingers or toes
example: Stop biting your nails!

translation: 裸体的（未穿任何衣服的）
definition: not wearing any clothes
example: She was clutching the sheet around her naked body.

translation: 名字（人、动物或地方被称呼的词语）
definition: a word or words that a particular person, animal, place or thing is known by
example: What's your name?

translation: 命名（给某人/某物起名字）
definition: to give a name to somebody/something
example: name somebody/something (after somebody), He was named after his father (= given his father's first name).

translation: 即，也就是（用于引入对刚提到事物的更精确详细的信息）
definition: used to introduce more exact and detailed information about something that you have just mentioned
example: We need to concentrate on our target audience, namely women aged between 20 and 30.

translation: 叙述性的（描述事件或讲述故事的）
definition: describing events or telling a story
example: narrative fiction

translation: 叙事，故事（对事件的描述，尤指故事性的）
definition: a description of events
example: a gripping narrative of their journey up the Amazon

translation: 狭窄的（从一侧到另一侧距离短的，尤指相对于长度而言）
definition: measuring a short distance from one side to the other, especially in relation to length
example: Stray dogs wander the steep narrow lanes of the old town.

translation: 变窄（变窄或使某物变窄）
definition: to become or make something less wide
example: This is where the river narrows.

translation: 下流的，糟糕的（非常坏或令人不快的）
definition: very bad or unpleasant
example: He had a nasty accident.

translation: 民族，国家（作为一个整体的、具有相同语言文化及政府的人群或国家）
definition: a country considered as a group of people with the same language, culture and history, who live in a particular area under one government
example: European/Arab/Asian nations

translation: 国家的（与特定民族相关的；全国共享的）
definition: connected with a particular nation; shared by a whole nation
example: Decide whether it would be better to advertise in a national or a local newspaper.

translation: 国民（特定国家的公民）
definition: a citizen of a particular country
example: Polish nationals living in Germany

translation: 全国范围的（在特定国家的所有部分发生或存在的）
definition: happening or existing in all parts of a particular country
example: a nationwide campaign

translation: 本国的，本土的（与出生及度过早年生活的地方相关的）
definition: connected with the place where you were born and lived for the first years of your life
example: your native land/country/city

translation: 本地人（出生在特定国家或地区的人）
definition: a person who was born in a particular country or area
example: a native of New York

translation: 自然的（自然界存在的；非人造的）
definition: existing in nature; not made or caused by humans
example: the natural world (= of trees, rivers, animals and birds)

translation: 自然地（以预料中的方式）
definition: in a way that you would expect
example: Naturally, I get upset when things go wrong.

translation: 自然（宇宙中存在的所有非人造的植物、动物及事物）
definition: all the plants, animals and things that exist in the universe that are not made by people
example: Take time to appreciate the beauties of nature.

translation: 海军的（与国家的海军相关的）
definition: connected with the navy of a country
example: a naval base/officer/battle

translation: 导航，航行（为船只或车辆规划路线并将其引向目的地的技能或过程）
definition: the skill or the process of planning a route for a ship or other vehicle and taking it there
example: a maker of in-car navigation systems

translation: 近的（距离短的）
definition: a short distance away
example: His house is very near.

translation: 在附近（在较短的距离处）
definition: at a short distance away
example: A bomb exploded somewhere near.

translation: 在...附近（在离某人/某物较短的距离处）
definition: at a short distance away from somebody/something
example: Do you live near here?

translation: 附近的（位置靠近的；不远的）
definition: near in position; not far away
example: Her mother lived in a nearby town.

translation: 在附近（离某人/某物距离不远地）
definition: a short distance from somebody/something; not far away
example: They live nearby.

translation: 几乎（几乎；不完全地）
definition: almost; not quite; not completely
example: The bottle's nearly empty.

translation: 整洁的（整洁有序的；细心安排的）
definition: tidy and in order; carefully done or arranged
example: She kept her desk extremely neat.

translation: 必然地（用于表示某事无法回避）
definition: used to say that something cannot be avoided
example: The number of places available is necessarily limited.

translation: 必要的（为了某种目的或理由所需要的）
definition: that is needed for a purpose or a reason
example: necessary to do something, It may be necessary to buy a new one.

translation: 必要性（某事必须发生或执行的事实；对某物的需求）
definition: the fact that something must happen or be done; the need for something
example: necessity for something, We recognize the necessity for a written agreement.

translation: 脖子（头部与肩膀之间的身体部位）
definition: the part of the body between the head and the shoulders
example: He tied a scarf around his neck.

translation: 需要（某事必须执行或必要的情况）
definition: a situation when something is necessary or must be done
example: to satisfy/meet/fulfil a need

translation: 需要（需要某物/某人，因其必不可少或非常重要）
definition: to require something/somebody because they are essential or very important, not just because you would like to have them
example: need something/somebody, Do you need any help?

translation: （情态动词）需要（用于说明某事不必执行或询问是否必要）
definition: used to state that something is/was not necessary or that only very little is/was necessary; used to ask if something is/was necessary
example: need (not) do something, You needn't bother asking Rick―I know he's too busy.

translation: 针（一端带尖头、另一端带孔供穿线的细钢片，用于缝纫）
definition: a small thin piece of steel that you use for sewing, with a point at one end and a hole for the thread at the other
example: a needle and thread

translation: 负面的，消极的（坏的或有害的）
definition: bad or harmful
example: The crisis had a negative effect on trade.

translation: 否定（表示“不”的词语或陈述；拒绝或否认的行为）
definition: a word or statement that means ‘no’; an act of refusing to do something or of denying something
example: in the negative, She answered in the negative (= said ‘no’).

translation: 忽视，疏忽（未给予足够照料或关注的事实；未受照料的状态）
definition: the fact of not giving enough care or attention to something/somebody; the state of not receiving enough care or attention
example: The buildings are crumbling from years of neglect.

translation: 忽视，遗弃（未能照顾好某人/某物）
definition: to fail to take care of somebody/something
example: She denies neglecting her baby.

translation: 谈判（通过正式讨论尝试达成协议）
definition: to try to reach an agreement by formal discussion
example: negotiate (with somebody) (for something), The government will not negotiate with terrorists.

translation: 谈判（尝试达成协议的人们之间的正式讨论）
definition: formal discussion between people who are trying to reach an agreement
example: peace/trade/contract negotiations

translation: 邻居（住在你旁边或附近的人）
definition: a person who lives next to you or near you
example: We've had a lot of support from all our friends and neighbours.

translation: 社区，街区（城镇的一个区或区域；其中的居民）
definition: a district or an area of a town; the people who live there
example: We grew up in the same neighbourhood.

translation: 邻近的（位于或居住在某处/某人附近的）
definition: located or living near or next to a place or person
example: a neighbouring house

translation: 也不（用于表示否定陈述同样适用于他人/他物）
definition: used to show that a negative statement is also true of somebody/something else
example: He didn't remember and neither did I.

translation: 两者都不（两者中没有一个）
definition: not one nor the other of two things or people
example: Neither answer is correct.

translation: 两者都不（两者中没有一个）
definition: not one nor the other of two things or people
example: Neither answer is correct.

translation: 神经（在大脑与身体部位间传递信息、使能移动及感知疼痛的纤维）
definition: any of the long fibres that carry messages between the brain and parts of the body, enabling you to move, feel pain, etc.
example: the optic nerve

translation: 紧张的（对某事感到忧虑或害怕的）
definition: anxious about something or afraid of something
example: I felt really nervous before the interview.

translation: 鸟巢（鸟类为了产卵和育雏而建造或选择的中空结构）
definition: a hollow place or structure that a bird makes or chooses for laying its eggs in and sheltering its young
example: sparrows building a nest of twigs and dry grass

translation: 净的（扣除所有项后剩余的数额，如净利润）
definition: a net amount of money is the amount that remains when nothing more is to be taken away
example: a net profit of ￡500

translation: 网（由绳、线等拧成带小孔的材料；这种材料制成的工具）
definition: material that is made of string, thread or wire twisted or tied together, with small spaces in between; a piece of this material used for a particular purpose
example: Unfortunately the animals are often caught in fishing nets.

translation: 网络（相互连接并共同运行的道路、线路、管道或神经系统）
definition: a complicated system of roads, lines, tubes, nerves, etc. that are connected to each other and operate together
example: a rail/road/canal network

translation: 中立的（在分歧、竞争中不偏袒任何一方的）
definition: not supporting or helping either side in a disagreement, competition, etc.
example: Journalists are supposed to be politically neutral.

translation: 从不（在任何时间都不；在任何场合都不）
definition: not at any time; not on any occasion
example: You never help me.

translation: 尽管如此（尽管刚提到的某事）
definition: despite something that you have just mentioned
example: There is little chance that we will succeed in changing the law. Nevertheless, it is important that we try.

translation: 新的（以前不存在的；最近制造、发明或引入的）
definition: not existing before; recently made, invented, introduced, etc.
example: Have you read her new novel?

translation: 新近地（最近地）
definition: recently
example: a newly qualified doctor

translation: 新闻，消息（关于最近发生之事的最新信息）
definition: new information about something that has happened recently
example: What's the latest news?

translation: 简报，通讯（包含俱乐部或组织活动新闻并定期发给成员的报告）
definition: a report containing news of the activities of a club or organization that is sent regularly to all its members
example: Our sailing club produces a monthly newsletter.

translation: 报纸（每天或每周出版的包含新闻文章的纸张或网站；其制作机构）
definition: a set of large printed sheets of paper, or a website, containing news, articles, advertisements, etc. and published every day or every week; the organization responsible for producing this
example: a daily/weekly newspaper

translation: 下一个（在时间、顺序或空间上紧随其后的）
definition: coming straight after somebody/something in time, order or space
example: The next train to Baltimore is at ten.

translation: 接下来（在另一件事之后；然后）
definition: after something else; then; afterwards
example: What happened next?

translation: 下一个（紧接在后的那个人或事物）
definition: a person or thing that is next
example: One moment he wasn't there, the next he was.

translation: 在...旁边（紧挨着某人/某物的位置）
definition: in or into a position right by somebody/something
example: We sat next to each other.

translation: 好的，迷人的（愉快或吸引人的）
definition: pleasant or attractive
example: a nice day/smile/place

translation: 利基，合适的地位（舒适或合适的角色、工作或生活方式）
definition: a comfortable or suitable role, job, way of life, etc.
example: He eventually found his niche in sports journalism.

translation: 夜晚（天黑到次日天明、通常人们睡觉的时间段）
definition: the time between one day and the next when it is dark, when people usually sleep
example: at night, These animals only come out at night.

translation: 噩梦（非常可怕或令人不快的梦）
definition: a dream that is very frightening or unpleasant
example: He still has nightmares about the accident.

translation: 九（数字9）
example: There are only nine of these rare animals left.

translation: 十九（数字19）
九十（数字90）
example: The temperature must be in the nineties today.

translation: 没有，不（不一个；没有任何；一个也没有）
definition: not one; not any; not a
example: No student is to leave the room.

translation: 不（用于给出否定的回答或陈述）
definition: used to give a negative reply or statement
example: Just say yes or no.

translation: 没有人（没有任何人）
definition: not anyone; no person
example: No one was at home.

translation: 高尚的，贵族的（具有人们钦佩的优秀品质，如勇气、诚实和博爱）
definition: having or showing fine personal qualities that people admire, such as courage, honesty and care for others
example: a noble leader

translation: 没有人（没有任何人）
definition: not anyone; no person
example: Nobody knew what to say.

translation: 点头（通过上下移动头部来表示同意、理解等）
definition: if you nod, nod your head or your head nods, you move your head up and down to show agreement, understanding, etc.
example: I asked him if he would help me and he nodded.

translation: 噪音（响亮、不快或令人恐惧的声音）
definition: a sound, especially when it is loud, unpleasant or frightening
example: There was a rattling noise coming from the back of the car.

translation: 吵闹的（发出很大响声的）
definition: making a lot of noise
example: noisy children/traffic/crowds

translation: 提名（正式建议某人/某物被选为重要的角色、奖项或职位）
definition: to formally suggest that somebody/something should be chosen for an important role, prize, position, etc.
example: nominate somebody/something (for something), She has been nominated for the presidency.

translation: 提名（建议或选择某人作为候选人或获奖者的行为）
definition: the act of suggesting or choosing somebody as a candidate in an election, or for a job or an award; the fact of being suggested for this
example: Membership of the club is by nomination only.

translation: 被提名者（被正式建议担任某工作或领取某奖项的人）
definition: a person who has been formally suggested for a job, a prize, etc.
example: He was chosen as the party's presidential nominee.

translation: 非营利性的（不以营利为目的的）
definition: without the aim of making a profit
example: an independent non-profit organization

translation: 一个也没有（一群人或物中没有任何一个）
definition: not one of a group of people or things; not any
example: None of these pens works/work.

translation: 尽管如此（尽管有此事实）
definition: despite this fact
example: The book is too long but, nonetheless, informative and entertaining.

translation: 废话，胡说（你认为愚蠢或不真实的想法、陈述或信念）
definition: ideas, statements or beliefs that you think are silly or not true
example: Reports that he has resigned are nonsense.

translation: 正午（中午12点）
definition: 12 o’clock in the middle of the day
example: We should be there by noon.

translation: 也不（和...也不）
definition: and not
example: She seemed neither surprised nor worried.

translation: 也不（和...也不）
definition: and not
example: She seemed neither surprised nor worried.

translation: 规范，常态（通常或预期的行为模式或情况）
definition: a situation or a pattern of behaviour that is usual or expected
example: The new design is a departure from the norm.

translation: 正常的（典型的、寻常的或普通的；预料中的）
definition: typical, usual or ordinary; what you would expect
example: quite/perfectly (= completely) normal

translation: 常态，正常水平（寻常或平均的状态、水平或标准）
definition: the usual or average state, level or standard
example: above/below normal, The rainfall has been above normal for the time of year.

translation: 通常（通常地；在正常情况下）
definition: usually; in normal circumstances
example: I would never normally discuss this.

translation: 北方的（在北方或向北的）
definition: in or towards the north
example: North London

translation: 向北（朝向北方）
definition: towards the north
example: The house faces north.

translation: 北方（看日出时在你左侧的方向；罗盘四个主要点之一）
definition: the direction that is on your left when you watch the sun rise; one of the four main points of the compass
example: Which way is north?

translation: 北方的（位于北方或面向北方的；与北方地区相关的）
definition: located in the north or facing north; connected with or typical of the north part of the world or a region
example: the northern slopes of the mountains

translation: 鼻子（脸上突出的用于呼吸和嗅觉的部分）
definition: the part of the face that sticks out above the mouth, used for breathing and smelling things
example: She had dark eyes and a long narrow nose.

translation: 不（与be、do、have连用构成动词否定；或用于情态动词否定）
definition: used with be, do or have to form the negative of verbs; used to form the negative of modal verbs like can or must
example: She did not/didn’t see him.

translation: 显著的，值得注意的（值得被注意或关注的；重要的）
definition: deserving to be noticed or to receive attention; important
example: a notable success/achievement/example

translation: 尤其是，特别地（用于给出某事物中一个好或最重要的例子）
definition: used for giving a good or the most important example of something
example: The house had many drawbacks, most notably its price.

translation: 笔记，便条（为了帮助记忆而写的短句）
definition: a short piece of writing to help you remember something
example: Please make a note of the dates.

translation: 注意（察觉或仔细关注某事）
definition: to notice or pay careful attention to something
example: note something, Note the fine early Baroque altar inside the chapel.

translation: 笔记本（用于记笔记的小薄本）
definition: a small book of plain paper for writing notes in
example: The police officer wrote the details down in his notebook.

translation: 没有什么（没有任何东西；没有任何一件事）
definition: not anything; no single thing
example: There was nothing in her bag.

translation: 通知，布告（通常张贴在公共场所的给出书面信息的一张纸）
definition: a sheet of paper giving written or printed information, usually put in a public place
example: There was a notice on the board saying the class had been cancelled.

translation: 注意到（看到或听到某人/某事；察觉到）
definition: to see or hear somebody/something; to become aware of somebody/something
example: People were making fun of him but he didn't seem to notice.

translation: 通知，告知（正式或官方地告诉某人某事）
definition: to formally or officially tell somebody about something
example: notify somebody, Competition winners will be notified by post.

translation: 观念，见解（对某事的想法、信仰或理解）
definition: an idea, a belief or an understanding of something
example: notion of something, a political system based on the notions of equality and liberty

translation: 臭名昭著的（因坏事而众所周知的）
definition: well known for being bad
example: a notorious criminal

translation: 新颖的（与以前所知不同的；新奇有趣的，常带有一点奇怪感）
definition: different from anything known before; new, interesting and often seeming slightly strange
example: a novel feature

translation: 小说（足够填满一整本书的长篇虚构故事）
definition: a story long enough to fill a complete book, in which the characters and events are usually imaginary
example: to write/publish/read a novel

translation: 小说家（写小说的人）
definition: a person who writes novels
example: a romantic/historical novelist

translation: 十一月（一年中的第十一个月）
definition: the 11th month of the year, between October and December
example: She was born in November.

translation: 现在（在现时）
definition: (at) the present time
example: Where are you living now?

translation: 既然（因为提到的事情正在发生或刚刚发生）
definition: because the thing mentioned is happening or has just happened
example: Now that the kids have left home we've got a lot of extra space.

translation: 现今（与过去相比的现时）
definition: at the present time, in contrast with the past
example: Nowadays most kids prefer going online to reading books.

translation: 无处（不在或不到任何地方）
definition: not in or to any place
example: I had nowhere to live, so I was sleeping on my sister's couch.

translation: 核能的，原子的（使用、产生核能或由核能产生的）
definition: using, producing or resulting from nuclear energy
example: a nuclear power plant/station

translation: 数字，数量（代表数额或数量的词或符号）
definition: a word or symbol that represents an amount or a quantity
example: Think of a number and multiply it by two.

translation: 给...编号（作为系列或列表的一部分给某物标号）
definition: to give a number to something as part of a series or list
example: number something, All the seats in the stadium are numbered.

translation: 许多的，众多的（大量存在的）
definition: existing in large numbers
example: He has been late on numerous occasions.

translation: 护士（工作是照料病人和伤员的人，通常在医院）
definition: a person whose job is to take care of sick or injured people, usually in a hospital
example: a registered nurse

translation: 托儿所（父母工作时照顾幼儿的地方）
definition: a place where young children are cared for while their parents are at work; a day nursery or nursery school
example: at nursery, Her youngest child is at nursery now.

translation: 护理（照料病人和伤员的工作或技能）
definition: the job or skill of caring for people who are sick or injured
example: a career in nursing

translation: 坚果（生长在某些树上的带硬壳的小硬果）
definition: a small hard fruit with a very hard shell that grows on some trees
example: to crack a nut (= open it)

translation: 营养（生物摄取生长和健康所需食物的过程）
definition: the process by which living things receive the food necessary for them to grow and be healthy
example: advice on diet and nutrition

translation: 点钟（报时，指整点）
definition: used with the numbers 1 to 12 when telling the time, to mean an exact hour
example: He left between five and six o'clock.

translation: 肥胖（过胖以至于不健康的品质或事实）
definition: the quality or fact of being very fat, in a way that is not healthy
example: Obesity can increase the risk of heart disease.

translation: 服从（按被告知或被预期的要求去做）
definition: to do what you are told or expected to do
example: obey something, to obey a command/an order/rules/the law

translation: 物体，物体（能看见并触摸但没有生命的实体）
definition: a thing that can be seen and touched, but is not alive
example: everyday objects such as cups and saucers

translation: 反对（表示不同意或反对某事）
definition: to say that you disagree with or oppose something
example: If nobody objects, we'll postpone the meeting till next week.

translation: 反对，异议（不喜欢或反对某事的理由；相关的陈述）
definition: a reason why you do not like or are opposed to something; a statement about this
example: I'd like to come too, if you have no objection.

translation: 客观的（不受个人感情影响的；仅考虑事实的）
definition: not influenced by personal feelings or opinions; considering only facts
example: an objective assessment of the situation

translation: 目标（你试图实现的事物）
definition: something that you are trying to achieve
example: the primary/principal/key objective

translation: 义务（因职责、法律等而被迫做某事的状态）
definition: the state of being forced to do something because it is your duty, or because of a law, etc.
example: obligation to do something, You are under no obligation to buy anything.

translation: 迫使（因法律或职责等迫使某人做某事）
definition: to force somebody to do something, by law, because it is a duty, etc.
example: Parents are obliged by law to send their children to school.

translation: 观察（在一段时间内仔细观看某人/某事，尤指为了学习）
definition: the act of watching somebody/something carefully for a period of time, especially to learn something
example: Most information was collected by direct observation of the animals' behaviour.

translation: 观察（看到或察觉到某人/某物）
definition: to see or notice somebody/something
example: observe somebody/something, Have you observed any changes lately?

translation: 观察者（观看某人/某事的人）
definition: a person who watches somebody/something
example: According to observers, the plane exploded shortly after take-off.

translation: 使着迷（以一种不合理的方式完全占据某人的头脑）
definition: to completely fill your mind so that you cannot think of anything else, in a way that is not reasonable or normal
example: be obsessed by somebody/something, He's obsessed by computers.

translation: 痴迷（脑中完全充满了对某人/某事想法的状态，常不合理）
definition: the state in which a person’s mind is completely filled with thoughts of one particular thing or person in a way that is not reasonable or normal
example: Her fear of flying is bordering on obsession.

translation: 障碍（使你难以去做或实现某事的情况、事件等）
definition: a situation, an event, etc. that makes it difficult for you to do or achieve something
example: So far, we have managed to overcome all the obstacles that have been placed in our path.

translation: 获得（获得某物，尤指通过努力）
definition: to get something, especially by making an effort
example: to obtain information/data/results

translation: 明显的（易于看见或理解的）
definition: easy to see or understand
example: I know you don't like her but try not to make it so obvious.

translation: 显而易见地（用于给出你预料他人已知道或同意的信息）
definition: used when giving information that you expect other people to know already or agree with
example: Obviously, we don't want to spend too much money.

translation: 时刻，场合（某事发生的特定时间）
definition: a particular time when something happens
example: on an occasion, on this/that occasion

translation: 偶尔的（有时发生或做的，但不频繁）
definition: happening or done sometimes but not often
example: He works for us on an occasional basis.

translation: 偶尔地（有时但不是经常地）
definition: sometimes but not often
example: We occasionally meet for a drink after work.

translation: 职业（工作或专业）
definition: a job or profession
example: Please state your name, age and occupation below.

translation: 占据（填充或使用空间、区域或一段时间）
definition: to fill or use a space, an area or an amount of time
example: The bed seemed to occupy most of the room.

translation: 发生（发生）
definition: to happen
example: When exactly did the incident occur?

translation: 发生的事情（发生或存在的事物）
definition: something that happens or exists
example: a common/everyday/frequent/regular occurrence

translation: 海洋（覆盖地球表面大部分区域的大片咸水）
definition: the mass of salt water that covers most of the earth’s surface
example: The ship was dredged from the depths of the ocean.

translation: 十月（一年中的第十个月）
definition: the 10th month of the year, between September and November
example: She was born in October.

translation: 奇特的，古怪的（奇怪或不寻常的）
definition: strange or unusual
example: They're very odd people.

translation: 几率，胜算（某事发生的可能性程度）
definition: the degree to which something is likely to happen
example: The odds are very much in our favour (= we are likely to succeed).

translation: ...的（属于某人的；与某人相关的）
definition: belonging to somebody; relating to somebody
example: a friend of mine

translation: 掉，脱落（用于说明某物被移除或分开了）
definition: used to say that something has been removed or become separated
example: He's had his beard shaved off.

translation: 离开，从...（从某处向下、移开或在空间/时间上有距离）
definition: down or away from a place or at a distance in space or time
example: I fell off the ladder.

translation: 犯罪，违法行为（违法行为）
definition: an illegal act
example: a criminal/serious/minor/sexual offence

translation: 冒犯（因粗鲁或令人尴尬的言行使某人感到不快）
definition: to make somebody feel upset because of something you say or do that is rude or embarrassing
example: They'll be offended if you don't go to their wedding.

translation: 违法者（犯罪的人，尤指惯犯）
definition: a person who commits a crime
example: a persistent/serious/violent, etc. offender

translation: 冒犯性的（因缺乏尊重而使人感到不快或恼火的言行）
definition: rude in a way that causes somebody to feel upset or annoyed because it shows a lack of respect
example: offensive remarks

translation: 提议，出价（表示愿意为某人做某事或给予某物的行为）
definition: an act of saying that you are willing to do something for somebody or give something to somebody
example: to receive a job offer

translation: 提供（表示愿意给某人某物）
definition: to say that you are willing to give something to somebody
example: offer (something), Josie had offered her services as a guide.

translation: 提供的作品/物品（为他人使用、观看、欣赏而生产出来的东西）
definition: something that is produced for other people to use, watch, enjoy, etc.
example: the latest offering from the Canadian-born writer

translation: 办公室（人们通常坐在办公桌前工作的房间或建筑）
definition: a room, set of rooms or building where people work, usually sitting at desks
example: The company is moving to new offices on the other side of town.

translation: 官员，军官（在武装部队中担任领导职位的人）
definition: a person who is in a position of authority in the armed forces
example: army/military/naval officers

translation: 官方的（由具有权力的人同意、说出、做出的）
definition: agreed to, said, done, etc. by somebody who is in a position of authority
example: an official announcement/decision/statement

translation: 官员（在大型组织中担任管理职位的人）
definition: a person who is in a position of authority in a large organization
example: She is the government official in charge of the project.

translation: 后代，子女（特定人或夫妇的孩子）
definition: a child of a particular person or couple
example: the problems parents have with their teenage offspring

translation: 经常（多次）
definition: many times
example: We often go there.

translation: 噢（对刚听到或不知道的事产生反应时使用）
definition: used when you are reacting to something that has been said, especially if you did not know it before
example: ‘I saw Ben yesterday.’ ‘Oh yes, how is he?’

translation: 油，石油（在地底岩石中发现的浓稠液体）
definition: a thick liquid that is found in rock underground
example: Several companies are drilling for oil in the region.

translation: 好的（安全健康的；处于冷静或快乐状态的）
definition: safe and well; in a calm or happy state
example: Are you OK?

translation: 好的（安全健康的；处于冷静或快乐状态的）
definition: safe and well; in a calm or happy state
example: Are you OK?

translation: 好的（是的；没问题）
definition: yes; all right
example: ‘Shall we go for a walk?’ ‘OK.’

translation: ...岁的（具有特定年龄的）
definition: of a particular age
example: be… years, months, etc. old, The baby was only a few hours old.

translation: 过时的（不现代的；不再流行的）
definition: not modern; no longer fashionable
example: old-fashioned clothes/styles/methods/equipment

translation: 穿上，戴上（在身体上；穿着状态）
definition: on somebody’s body; being worn
example: Put your coat on.

translation: 在...上（在覆盖、接触或形成表面一部分的位置）
definition: in or into a position covering, touching or forming part of a surface
example: a picture on a wall

translation: 一次（仅有一次）
definition: on one occasion only; one time
example: I've only been there once.

translation: 一旦（一旦...就；当...时）
definition: as soon as; when
example: We didn't know how we would cope once the money had gone.

translation: 一（数字1）
definition: the number 1
example: Do you want one or two?

translation: 一（数字1）
definition: the number 1
example: Do you want one or two?

translation: （代词）一个（用于避免名词重复，指代已提到或已知的人或物）
definition: used to avoid repeating a noun, when you are referring to somebody/something that has already been mentioned, or that the person you are speaking to knows about
example: I'd like an ice cream. Are you having one, too?

translation: 进行中的（持续存在或发展的）
definition: continuing to exist or develop
example: an ongoing debate/discussion/process

translation: 洋葱（带有许多层次、皮棕/红/白色的圆形蔬菜，气味重）
definition: a round vegetable with many layers inside each other and a brown, red or white skin. Onions have a strong smell and taste.
example: Chop the onions finely.

translation: 在线的（在互联网或计算机网络上可用或进行的）
definition: available on or done using the internet or other computer network
example: Online shopping is both cheap and convenient.

translation: 在线地（连接到互联网；使用互联网或计算机网络）
definition: onto the internet; using the internet or other computer network
example: Many children would rather go online than watch television.

translation: 唯一的（表示该群体中没有其他的人或物）
definition: used to say that no other or others of the same group exist or are there
example: She's their only daughter.

translation: 只有，仅仅（除了...之外别无）
definition: nobody or nothing except
example: There are only a limited number of tickets available.

translation: 到...之上（与动词连用表示向特定位置移动）
definition: used with verbs to express movement on or to a particular place or position
example: Move the books onto the second shelf.

translation: 开着的（允许事物或人通过的；未关闭或阻塞的）
definition: allowing things or people to go through; not closed or blocked
example: A wasp flew in the open window.

translation: 打开（将门、盖等移至不再关闭的位置）
definition: to move a door, window, lid, etc. into a position that is no longer closed; to get into this position
example: Mr Chen opened the car door for his wife.

translation: 开口，孔（某人/某物能通过的空间或孔洞）
definition: a space or hole that somebody/something can pass through
example: We could see the stars through an opening in the roof.

translation: 公开地（不隐藏任何感情、观点或信息地）
definition: without hiding any feelings, opinions or information
example: Can you talk openly about sex with your parents?

translation: 歌剧（全部或大部分台词用歌唱表现的戏剧作品）
definition: a dramatic work in which all or most of the words are sung to music; works of this type as an art form or entertainment
example: Puccini’s operas

translation: 运作，操作（以特定方式工作）
definition: to work in a particular way
example: Most domestic freezers operate at below ?18°C.

translation: 手术（为了移除或修复受损部位而切开人体的过程）
definition: the process of cutting open a part of a person’s body in order to remove or repair a damaged part
example: Will I need to have an operation?

translation: 运作的（与业务、机器、系统运行方式相关的）
definition: connected with the way in which a business, machine, system, etc. works
example: operational activities/costs/difficulties

translation: 操作员（操作设备或机器的人）
definition: a person who operates equipment or a machine
example: a computer/machine operator

translation: 观点，意见（对某事的感觉或想法，而非事实）
definition: your feelings or thoughts about somebody/something, rather than a fact
example: He has very strong political opinions.

translation: 对手（在游戏、比赛、争论等中与你对抗的人）
definition: a person that you are playing or fighting against in a game, competition, argument, etc.
example: a political opponent

translation: 机会（使实现某事成为可能的时机或情况）
definition: a time when a particular situation makes it possible to do or achieve something
example: Don't miss this opportunity!

translation: 反对（强烈不同意某人的计划、政策并试图阻止其成功）
definition: to disagree strongly with somebody’s plan, policy, etc. and try to change it or prevent it from succeeding
example: oppose somebody/something, This party would bitterly oppose the re-introduction of the death penalty.

translation: 反对的（强烈不同意某事并试图停止它的）
definition: disagreeing strongly with something and trying to stop it
example: opposed to something, He was strongly opposed to modernism in art.

translation: 对面的（在特定区域另一侧并通常面向某人/某物的）
definition: on the other side of a particular area from somebody/something and usually facing them
example: Answers are given on the opposite page.

translation: 在对面（在特定区域另一侧）
definition: on the other side of a particular area from somebody/something and usually facing them
example: There's a newly married couple living opposite (= on the other side of the road).

translation: 相反的事物（与某人/某物尽可能不同的事物）
definition: a person or thing that is as different as possible from somebody/something else
example: Hot and cold are opposites.

translation: 在...对面（在某人/某物另一侧且通常面向其）
definition: on the other side of a particular area from somebody/something, and usually facing them
example: I sat opposite him during the meal (= on the other side of the table).

translation: 反对（强烈不同意某人/某事，尤指为了阻止其发生）
definition: the act of strongly disagreeing with somebody/something, especially with the aim of preventing something from happening
example: Opposition came primarily from students.

translation: 选择（选择采取或不采取特定的行动方案）
definition: to choose to take or not to take a particular course of action
example: opt for/against something, After graduating she opted for a career in music.

translation: 光学的（与视觉或光与视觉的关系相关的）
definition: connected with the sense of sight or the relationship between light and sight
example: optical effects

translation: 乐观（相信好事会发生且某事会成功的这种感觉）
definition: a feeling that good things will happen and that something will be successful
example: a mood of cautious optimism

translation: 乐观的（期待好事发生或某事成功的）
definition: expecting good things to happen or something to be successful; showing this feeling
example: We are now taking a more optimistic view.

translation: 选择，选项（你可以选择拥有或做的事物；选择的自由）
definition: something that you can choose to have or do; the freedom to choose what you do
example: As I see it, we have two options…

translation: 或者（用于引入另一种可能性）
definition: used to introduce another possibility
example: Is your sister older or younger than you?

translation: 口头的（口说的而非书写的）
definition: spoken rather than written
example: a test of both oral and written French

translation: 橙色的（介于红色和黄色之间的颜色）
definition: between red and yellow in colour
example: yellow and orange flames

translation: 橙子，柑橘（圆形柑橘类水果，皮色介于红黄之间，果汁甜）
definition: a round citrus fruit with thick skin of a colour between red and yellow and a lot of sweet juice
example: orange peel/zest/rind

translation: 管弦乐队（在指挥带领下一起演奏多种乐器的大型团体）
definition: a large group of people who play various musical instruments together, led by a conductor
example: She plays the flute in the school orchestra.

translation: 顺序（人或物相互排列的方式）
definition: the way in which people or things are placed or arranged in relation to each other
example: in… order, The names are listed in alphabetical order.

translation: 订购，点餐（在餐厅等要求食物或饮料）
definition: to ask for something to eat or drink in a restaurant, bar, etc.
example: order (something), I ordered a coffee and a sandwich.

translation: 平凡的（没有任何不寻常或不同的）
definition: not unusual or different in any way
example: an ordinary sort of day

translation: 器官（身体中具有特定用途的部分，如心脏或大脑）
definition: a part of the body that has a particular purpose, such as the heart or the brain; part of a plant with a particular purpose
example: the internal organs

translation: 有机的（不使用人工化学物质生产或实践的）
definition: produced or practised without using artificial chemicals
example: organic cheese/vegetables/wine, etc.

translation: 组织，机构（为了实现特定目标共同组成的业务、俱乐部等）
definition: a group of people who form a business, club, etc. together in order to achieve a particular aim
example: He's the president of a large international organization.

translation: 组织的（与事物各部分的排列或与组织相关的）
definition: connected with the way in which the different parts of something are arranged; connected with an organization
example: organizational changes within the party

translation: 组织（为某事的发生或提供做出所有安排）
definition: to make all the arrangements for something to happen or be provided
example: He helped to organize various events.

translation: 有组织的（涉及大量人员协作且经过仔细计划的）
definition: involving large numbers of people who work together to do something in a way that has been carefully planned
example: an organized body of workers

translation: 组织者（为某事做出安排的人）
definition: a person who makes the arrangements for something
example: the organizers of the festival

translation: 取向，定位（一个人对特定主题的基本信念或感觉）
definition: a person’s basic beliefs or feelings about a particular subject
example: religious/political orientation

translation: 起源，起因（某事开始的点；某事的原因）
definition: the point from which something starts; the cause of something
example: origin of something, the origins of life on earth

translation: 原始的，最初的（在特定时期、过程或活动开始时存在的）
definition: existing at the beginning of a particular period, process or activity
example: The room still has many of its original features.

translation: 原件，原作（首次制作的文件、艺术品，副本由此产生）
definition: a document, work of art, etc. produced for the first time, from which copies are later made
example: This painting is a copy; the original is in Madrid.

translation: 最初（用于描述在改变前、在一段时期开端存在的情况）
definition: used to describe the situation that existed at the beginning of a particular period or activity, especially before something was changed
example: The school was originally very small.

translation: 起源于（在特定地点或情况首次发生或出现）
definition: to happen or appear for the first time in a particular place or situation
example: The disease is thought to have originated in the tropics.

translation: 其他的（用于指代提到或已知的之外的人或物）
definition: used to refer to people or things that are additional or different to people or things that have been mentioned or are known about
example: Mr Harris and Mrs Bate and three other teachers were there.

translation: 其他的（用于指代提到或已知的之外的人或物）
definition: used to refer to people or things that are additional or different to people or things that have been mentioned or are known about
example: Mr Harris and Mrs Bate and three other teachers were there.

translation: 否则（用于说明如果情况不同或某事不发生会产生什么结果）
definition: used to state what the result would be if something did not happen or if the situation were different
example: My parents lent me the money. Otherwise, I couldn't have afforded the trip.

translation: 应当（用于表示什么是正确该做的事）
definition: used to say what is the right thing to do
example: They ought to apologize.

translation: 我们的（属于我们的；与我们相关的）
definition: belonging to us; connected with us
example: our daughter/dog/house

translation: 我们的（属于我们的那一个或那些）
definition: the one or ones that belong to us
example: Their house is very similar to ours, but ours is bigger.

translation: 我们自己（we的反身代词）
definition: the reflexive form of we; used when you and another person or other people together cause and are affected by an action
example: We shouldn't blame ourselves for what happened.

translation: 出去（从某处内部向外）
definition: away from the inside of a place or thing
example: She ran out into the corridor.

translation: 出去（从某处内部向外）
definition: away from the inside of a place or thing
example: She ran out into the corridor.

translation: 爆发（不快之事――尤指暴力或疾病――的突然开始）
definition: the sudden start of something unpleasant, especially violence or a disease
example: the outbreak of war

translation: 结果（行动或事件的结果或影响）
definition: the result or effect of an action or event
example: The likely outcome is a compromise.

translation: 户外的（在户外而非在建筑内使用、发生或位于户外的）
definition: used, happening or located outside rather than in a building
example: outdoor pursuits/recreation/activities

translation: 在户外（在外面，而非在建筑内部）
definition: outside, rather than in a building
example: The rain prevented them from eating outdoors.

translation: 外部的（在某物的外面）
definition: on the outside of something
example: the outer layers of the skin

translation: 全套服装（为了特定场合或目的穿在一起的一套衣服）
definition: a set of clothes that you wear together, especially for a particular occasion or purpose
example: She was wearing an expensive new outfit.

translation: 远足，郊游（为了娱乐或教育进行的短途旅行，通常为期一天内）
definition: a trip that you go on for pleasure or education, usually with a group of people and lasting no more than one day
example: a family outing

translation: 零售店，直销店（销售特定公司或特定类型商品的商店或组织）
definition: a shop or an organization that sells goods made by a particular company or of a particular type
example: The business has 34 retail outlets in this state alone.

translation: 概要（涉及某事的主要事实或要点的描述）
definition: a description of the main facts or points involved in something
example: outline of something, This is a brief outline of the events.

translation: 概述（给出涉及某事的主要事实或要点的描述）
definition: to give a description of the main facts or points involved in something
example: outline something, He outlined his plan to leave St. Petersburg.

translation: 观点，看法（特定个人、群体或文化对生活和世界的态度）
definition: the attitude to life and the world of a particular person, group or culture
example: Travel broadens your outlook.

translation: 产量，产出（人、机器或组织生产的某物的数量）
definition: the amount of something that a person, a machine or an organization produces
example: Manufacturing output has increased by 8 per cent.

translation: 愤慨，义愤（极度震惊和愤怒的感觉）
definition: a strong feeling of shock and anger
example: The judge's remarks caused public outrage.

translation: 激怒（使某人感到极度震惊和愤怒）
definition: to make somebody very shocked and angry
example: He was outraged at the way he had been treated.

translation: 外面的（外部的，面向外侧的）
definition: of, on or facing the outer side
example: The outside walls are damp.

translation: 在外面（不在房间、建筑内而是在其外部）
definition: not in a room, building or container but on or to the outside of it
example: I'm seeing a patient―please wait outside.

translation: 外部（事物的外部表面）
definition: the outer side or surface of something
example: The outside of the house needs painting.

translation: 在...外面（在某物外部的某个地方）
definition: on or to a place on the outside of something
example: You can park your car outside our house.

translation: 局外人（不被社会、群体等接受为成员的人）
definition: a person who is not accepted as a member of a society, group, etc.
example: Here she felt she would always be an outsider.

translation: 出色的，杰出的（极其好的；优秀的）
definition: extremely good; excellent
example: an outstanding player/achievement/success

translation: 烤箱（炊具中像盒子一样的部分，带前门，用于烹饪或加热食物）
definition: the part of a cooker that is like a box with a door on the front, in which food is cooked or heated
example: Take the cake out of the oven.

translation: 越过（穿过街道、开阔空间等）
definition: across a street, an open space, etc.
example: I stopped and crossed over.

translation: 在...上方（在某人/某物表面之上，并部分或全部遮盖）
definition: resting on the surface of somebody/something and partly or completely covering them/it
example: She put a blanket over the sleeping child.

translation: 全面的，总体的（包括特定情况涉及的所有人或物；总体的）
definition: including all the things or people that are involved in a particular situation; general
example: There will be winners in each of three age groups, and one overall winner.

translation: 总共，总计（包括一切或所有人；总计）
definition: including everything or everyone; in total
example: The company will invest $1.6m overall in new equipment.

translation: 克服，控制（成功处理或控制阻碍你实现目标的问题）
definition: to succeed in dealing with or controlling a problem that has been preventing you from achieving something
example: She overcame injury to win the Olympic gold medal.

translation: 忽视，忽略（未能看到或注意到某事）
definition: to fail to see or notice something
example: He seems to have overlooked one important fact.

translation: 过度地（太；非常）
definition: too; very
example: I'm not overly fond of pasta.

translation: 在夜间，一夜之间（在夜间或持续整个晚上）
definition: during or for the night
example: We stayed overnight in London after the theatre.

translation: 海外的，国外的（与外国相关的，尤指隔海相望的国家）
definition: connected with foreign countries, especially those separated from your country by the sea or ocean
example: The firm is expanding into overseas markets.

translation: 在海外，向国外（到外国或在外国，尤指隔海相望的国家）
definition: to or in a foreign country, especially those separated from your country by the sea or ocean
example: to live/work/go overseas

translation: 监督，监视（观看某人/某物并确保工作或活动正确进行）
definition: to watch somebody/something and make sure that a job or an activity is done correctly
example: United Nations observers oversaw the elections.

translation: 推翻，翻转（使某物翻转到顶部朝下或侧向的位置）
definition: if something overturns, or if somebody overturns it, it turns into a position in which the top of it is where the bottom of it normally is or on its side
example: The car skidded and overturned.

translation: 使受不了，淹没（产生极强烈的情感影响，使人难以抵抗或不知如何反应）
definition: to have such a strong emotional effect on somebody that it is difficult for them to resist or know how to react
example: She was overwhelmed by feelings of guilt.

translation: 压倒性的，巨大的（极大的或极强烈的；强大到无法抵抗或不知如何反应）
