example: She was forced to resign due to ill health.

translation: 辞职（放弃工作或职位的行为；这种情况）
definition: the act of giving up your job or position; the occasion when you do this
example: a letter of resignation

translation: 抵抗（拒绝接受某事并试图阻止其发生）
definition: to refuse to accept something and try to stop it from happening
example: resist something, They are determined to resist pressure to change the law.

translation: 抵抗（对计划、想法等的不喜欢或反对；拒绝服从的行为）
definition: dislike of or opposition to a plan, an idea, etc.; the act of refusing to obey
example: As with all new ideas it met with resistance.

translation: 决定，决议（做或不做某事的明确决定）
definition: a definite decision to do or not to do something
example: Have you made any New Year's resolutions (= for example, to give up smoking from 1 January)?

translation: 解决（为问题或困难找到可接受的方案）
definition: to find an acceptable solution to a problem or difficulty
example: resolve something, to resolve an issue/a dispute/a conflict/a crisis

translation: 度假胜地（很多人去度假的地方）
definition: a place where a lot of people go on holiday
example: seaside/mountain resorts

translation: 资源（国家、组织或个人拥有的可供使用的供应品，尤指为了增加财富）
definition: a supply of something that a country, an organization or a person has and can use, especially to increase their wealth
example: the exploitation of minerals and other natural resources

translation: 尊重（因他人的优秀品质或成就而产生的强烈认可感）
definition: a strong feeling of approval of somebody/something because of their good qualities or achievements
example: I have the utmost respect for her and her work.

translation: 尊重（对某人/某物有非常好的看法；钦佩）
definition: to have a very good opinion of somebody/something; to admire somebody/something
example: I respect Jack's opinion on most subjects.

translation: 各自的（分别属于或关于已提到的每个人或物的）
definition: belonging or relating separately to each of the people or things already mentioned
example: They are each recognized specialists in their respective fields.

translation: 分别地（按已提到的人或物的顺序分别地）
definition: in the same order as the people or things already mentioned
example: Julie and Mark, aged 17 and 19 respectively

translation: 回答，做出反应（给出言语或书面的回答；做出反应）
definition: to give a spoken or written answer to somebody/something
example: I asked him his name, but he didn't respond.

translation: 回答，响应（言语或书面的回答）
definition: a spoken or written answer
example: She made no response.

translation: 责任（处理或照顾某人/某物的职责，出错时可能被归咎）
definition: a duty to deal with or take care of somebody/something, so that you may be blamed if something goes wrong
example: to be in a position of responsibility

translation: 负责的（承担做某事或照顾某人职责的，出错时可能被归咎）
definition: having the job or duty of doing something or taking care of somebody/something, so that you may be blamed if something goes wrong
example: responsible for doing something, Mike is responsible for designing the entire project.

translation: 其余，剩余部分（事物留下的部分）
definition: the part of something that remains
example: Take what you want and throw the rest away.

translation: 休息（在活动或患病后放松、睡觉或什么都不做）
definition: to relax, sleep or do nothing after a period of activity or illness; to not use a part of your body for some time
example: The doctor told me to rest.

translation: 餐厅（可以购买并进餐的场所）
definition: a place where you can buy and eat a meal
example: We're going to try this Italian restaurant that just opened.

translation: 修复（修理和清理旧建筑、绘画等使其恢复原状的工作）
definition: the work of repairing and cleaning an old building, a painting, etc. so that its condition is as good as it originally was
example: restoration work

translation: 恢复（带回以前存在的情况或感觉）
definition: to bring back a situation or feeling that existed before
example: restore something, The measures are intended to restore public confidence in the economy.

translation: 限制，克制（限制或控制人们行为的规则、事实、想法等）
definition: a rule, a fact, an idea, etc. that limits or controls what people can do
example: The government has imposed export restraints on some products.

translation: 限制（限制某事的大小、数量或范围）
definition: to limit the size, amount or range of something
example: restrict something to something, Speed is restricted to 30 mph in towns.

translation: 限制，规定（限制你能做什么或能发生什么的规则或法律）
definition: a rule or law that limits what you can do or what can happen
example: import/speed/travel restrictions

translation: 结果（由另一件事引起或产生的事物）
definition: a thing that is caused or produced because of something else
example: And did your intervention produce the desired result?

translation: 导致（引起某事发生）
definition: to make something happen
example: A heavy frost could result in loss of the crop.

translation: 重新开始，恢复（停止或中断后再次开始或继续活动）
definition: if you resume an activity, or if it resumes, it begins again or continues after being interrupted
example: resume (something), to resume talks/negotiations

translation: 零售（通常通过商店向公众销售商品）
definition: the selling of goods to the public, usually through shops
example: The recommended retail price is ￡9.99.

translation: 保留，保持（保留某物；继续拥有某物）
definition: to keep something; to continue to have something
example: to retain your independence

translation: 退休（离开工作岗位停止工作，尤指达到特定年龄或因病）
definition: to leave your job and stop working, especially because you have reached a particular age or because you are ill; to tell somebody they must stop doing their job
example: He is retiring next year after 30 years with the company.

translation: 退休的（已从工作岗位退休的）
definition: having retired from work
example: a retired doctor/teacher/officer/general

translation: 退休（离开工作岗位停止工作的事实，尤指由于年龄）
definition: the fact of leaving your job and stopping work, usually because you have reached a particular age; the time when you do this
example: At 60, he was now approaching retirement.

translation: 撤退（因危险或战败而离开某地或避开敌人的行动）
definition: a movement away from a place or an enemy because of danger or defeat
example: Napoleon’s retreat from Moscow

translation: 撤退（因危险或战败而离开某地或避开敌人）
definition: to move away from a place or an enemy because you are in danger or because you have been defeated
example: The army was forced to retreat after suffering heavy losses.

translation: 取回，恢复（带回或找回某物，尤指从不该在的地方）
definition: to bring or get something back, especially from a place where it should not be
example: retrieve something from somebody/something, She bent to retrieve her comb from the floor.

translation: 归来，返回（到达或回到以前所在地方的行动）
definition: the action of arriving in or coming back to a place that you were in before
example: return of somebody to…, A week had passed since their return to Geneva.

translation: 归来，返回（从一处回到另一处）
definition: to come or go back from one place to another
example: I waited a long time for him to return.

translation: 揭露，展示（使某事为人所知）
definition: to make something known to somebody
example: reveal something, to reveal a secret

translation: 揭露，启示（让人察觉到的事实，尤指先前保密且令人惊讶的）
definition: a fact that people are made aware of, especially one that has been secret and is surprising
example: revelation about/concerning something, startling/sensational revelations about her private life

translation: 报复（为了让曾使你受苦的人受苦而做的事）
definition: something that you do in order to make somebody suffer because they have made you suffer
example: revenge for something, She is seeking revenge for the murder of her husband.

translation: 收入，税收（政府从税收中获得的钱，或组织从业务中获得的钱）
definition: the money that a government receives from taxes or that an organization, etc. receives from its business
example: The government is currently facing a shortfall in tax revenue.

translation: 相反的（与所提到的相反的）
definition: opposite to what has been mentioned
example: to travel in the reverse direction

translation: 相反的事物（与刚才提到的相反的事物）
definition: the opposite of what has just been mentioned
example: This problem is the reverse of the previous one.

translation: 反转，彻底改变（完全改变某事使其与以前相反）
definition: to change something completely so that it is the opposite of what it was before
example: Falling birth rates may reverse the trend towards early retirement.

translation: 评论，回顾（媒体上某人对书、戏、产品等的看法的报道；撰写此报道的行为）
definition: a report in a newspaper or magazine, or on the internet, television or radio, in which somebody gives their opinion of a book, play, film, product, etc.; the act of writing this kind of report
example: a book review

translation: 评论，回顾（撰写对书、戏、产品等的看法报道）
definition: to write a report of a book, play, film, product, etc. in which you give your opinion of it
example: Please rate and review your purchase on our website.

translation: 修改，修订（由于学到了新东西而改变观点或计划）
definition: to change your opinions or plans, for example because of something you have learned
example: I can see I will have to revise my opinions of his abilities now.

translation: 修订，校订（对某事物做出的一个或一组改动）
definition: a change or set of changes to something
example: He made some minor revisions to the report before printing it out.

translation: 复兴，复苏（某物状况或强度的改善）
definition: an improvement in the condition or strength of something
example: the revival of trade

translation: 使苏醒，复兴（变得或使某人/某物重新恢复意识或健康强壮）
definition: to become, or to make somebody/something become, conscious or healthy and strong again
example: The flowers soon revived in water.

translation: 革命（大量人群试图改变国家政府的尝试，尤指通过暴力）
definition: an attempt, by a large number of people, to change the government of a country, especially by violent action
example: a socialist revolution

translation: 革命的（与政治革命相关的）
definition: connected with political revolution
example: a revolutionary leader

translation: 奖赏，报酬（因做了好事、努力工作等而得到的报酬）
definition: a thing that you are given because you have done something good, worked hard, etc.
example: a financial reward

translation: 奖赏，给以报酬（因他人做了好事、努力工作等而给予报酬）
definition: to give something to somebody because they have done something good, worked hard, etc.
example: reward somebody for something, She was rewarded for her efforts with a cash bonus.

translation: 修辞（旨在影响他人的言论或写作，但往往非完全诚实）
definition: speech or writing that is intended to influence people, but that is not completely honest or sincere
example: the rhetoric of political slogans

translation: 节奏（声音或动作的强有力的规律重复模式）
definition: a strong regular repeated pattern of sounds or movements
example: to dance to the rhythm of the music

translation: 大米，米饭（在热带湿地生长的短窄谷物；这种作物）
definition: short, narrow white or brown grain grown on wet land in hot countries as food; the plant that produces this grain
example: a grain of rice

translation: 富有的（有很多钱或财产的）
definition: having a lot of money or property
example: She's one of the richest women in the world.

translation: 摆脱（脱离令你恼火或不想要的人/物）
definition: to be free of somebody/something that has been annoying you or that you do not want
example: She wanted to be rid of her parents and their authority.

translation: 骑行，旅程（乘车、骑车的短途旅行）
definition: a short journey in a vehicle, on a bicycle, etc.
example: a train ride through beautiful countryside

translation: 骑（坐在动物――尤指马――身上并控制其移动）
definition: to sit on an animal, especially a horse, and control it as it moves
example: I learnt to ride as a child.

translation: 荒谬的（非常铺蠢或不合理的）
definition: very silly or unreasonable
example: I look ridiculous in this hat.

translation: 步枪（持于肩部发射的长管枪）
definition: a gun with a long barrel which you hold to your shoulder to fire
example: a hunting rifle

translation: 正确的（作为事实是真实的或正确的）
definition: true or correct as a fact
example: Did you get the answer right?

translation: 向右（向着右侧）
definition: on or to the right side
example: Turn right at the end of the street.

translation: 右侧（右侧的位置或方向）
definition: the right side or direction
example: on the right, Take the first street on the right.

translation: 戒指（戴在手指上的由金、银等制成的圆环形珠宝）
definition: a piece of jewellery that you wear on your finger, consisting of a round band of gold, silver, etc., sometimes decorated with precious stones
example: a gold ring

translation: 包围（环绕某人/某物）
definition: to surround somebody/something
example: Thousands of demonstrators ringed the building.

translation: 暴乱（一群人在公共场所进行的暴力行为，常作为抗议）
definition: a situation in which a group of people behave in a violent way in a public place, often as a protest
example: One prison guard was killed when a riot broke out in the jail.

translation: 撕裂（撕开某物，常为突然或猛烈地）
definition: to tear something or to become torn, often suddenly or violently
example: rip (something), I ripped my jeans on the fence.

translation: 上升，上涨（数量、数字或水平的增加）
definition: an increase in an amount, a number or a level
example: The industry is feeling the effects of recent price rises.

translation: 上升，升高（向上移动；达到更高水平或位置）
definition: to come or go upwards; to reach a higher level or position
example: The curtain rose to reveal an empty stage.

translation: 风险（未来某时可能发生坏事的可能性；危险的情况）
definition: the possibility of something bad happening at some time in the future; a situation that could be dangerous or have a bad result
example: The health risks are very low.

translation: 冒风险（将重要或有价值的事物置于可能损失或损坏的危险境地）
definition: to put something valuable or important in a dangerous situation, in which it could be lost or damaged
example: He risked his life to save her.

translation: 冒险的，有风险的（涉及可能发生坏事的情况）
definition: involving the possibility of something bad happening
example: Life as an aid worker can be a risky business (= dangerous).

translation: 仪式，典礼（总以相同方式执行的一系列行动，尤指宗教仪式）
definition: a series of actions that are always performed in the same way, especially as part of a religious ceremony
example: religious rituals

translation: 竞争的，对手的（与另一人、公司或事物竞争的）
definition: competing with another person, company, thing, etc.
example: a rival bid/claim/offer

translation: 对手，竞争者（在体育、商业等领域与他人竞争的人或公司）
definition: a person, company or thing that competes with another in sport, business, etc.
example: The two teams have always been rivals.

translation: 河流（横跨陆地流向海洋的自然长条水流）
definition: a natural flow of water that continues in a long line across land to the sea
example: Eventually we came to the mouth of the River Thames.

translation: 道路，马路（为车辆行驶建造的坚硬表面）
definition: a hard surface built for vehicles to travel on
example: a main/major/minor road

translation: 抢劫，掠夺（从人或地方盗取金钱或财产）
definition: to steal money or property from a person or place
example: to rob a bank

translation: 抢劫罪（从银行、商店或人处盗取钱财的罪行，尤指涉及暴力或威胁）
definition: the crime of stealing money or goods from a bank, shop, person, etc., especially using violence or threats
example: armed robbery (= using a gun, knife, etc.)

translation: 机器人（能独立执行复杂系列任务的机器）
definition: a machine that can perform a complicated series of tasks by itself
example: These cars are built by robots.

translation: 强健的，稳固的（强壮且健康的；或系统稳固的）
definition: strong and healthy
example: She was almost 90, but still very robust.

translation: 岩石（构成地球及其他行星表面的坚硬固体物质）
definition: the hard solid material that forms part of the surface of the earth and some other planets
example: They drilled through several layers of rock to reach the oil.

translation: 摇晃（使某人/某物前后或左右轻轻移动；或以此方式移动）
definition: to move gently backwards and forwards or from side to side; to make somebody/something move in this way
example: (+ adv./prep.), The boat rocked from side to side in the waves.

translation: 火箭（管状航天器，通过内部燃料燃烧向后喷射气流驱动）
definition: a spacecraft in the shape of a tube that is driven by a stream of gases let out behind it when fuel is burned inside
example: a space rocket

translation: 杆，棒（木制、金属或玻璃制的长直条）
definition: a long straight piece of wood, metal or glass
example: The concrete is reinforced with steel rods.

translation: 角色（演艺人员在戏或电影中扮演的部分，或某人的社会职责）
definition: an actor’s part in a play, film, etc.
example: She has landed the lead role (= the most important one) in a new play.

translation: 小圆面包（供一人食用的小型面包）
definition: a small loaf of bread for one person
example: Soup and a roll: ￡3.50

translation: 滚动，翻滚（翻转着向特定方向移动；或使圆状物这样做）
definition: to turn over and over and move in a particular direction; to make a round object do this
example: #NAME?

translation: 浪漫史（两人间令人兴奋的、通常短暂的恋爱关系）
definition: an exciting, usually short, relationship between two people who are in love with each other
example: a holiday romance

translation: 浪漫的（与爱情或性关系相关的）
definition: connected with or about love or a sexual relationship
example: a romantic candlelit dinner

translation: 屋顶，车顶（覆盖或构成建筑或车辆顶部的结构）
definition: the structure that covers or forms the top of a building or vehicle
example: a flat/sloping/pitched roof

translation: 房间（建筑中拥有墙壁、地板和天花板的独立空间，常有特定用途）
definition: a part of a building that has its own walls, floor and ceiling and is usually used for a particular purpose
example: I heard him enter the room.

translation: 根，根源（植物生长在地下、吸收水分和养分的部分）
definition: the part of a plant that grows under the ground and takes in water and minerals that it sends to the rest of the plant
example: deep spreading roots

translation: 绳索（由多股细线、金属丝等拧成的强韧粗绳）
definition: very strong thick string made by twisting thinner strings, wires, etc. together
example: The rope broke and she fell 50 metres onto the rocks.

translation: 玫瑰（一种带香味的花，长在带刺的灌木上）
definition: a flower with a sweet smell that grows on a bush with thorns (= sharp points) on its stems
example: a bunch of red roses

translation: 旋转（围绕中心固定点移动或转动；使之旋转）
definition: to move or turn around a central fixed point; to make something do this
example: Stay well away from the helicopter when its blades start to rotate.

translation: 旋转（物体围绕中心固定点圆周运动的行为）
definition: the action of an object moving in a circle around a central fixed point
example: the daily rotation of the earth on its axis

translation: 粗糙的，不平整的（表面不平整或不规则的）
definition: having a surface that is not even or regular
example: rough ground

translation: 大约，粗略地（大约，但不精确）
definition: approximately but not exactly
example: Sales are up by roughly 10 per cent.

translation: 圆的（形状像圆圈或球的）
definition: having a shape like a circle or a ball
example: a round plate

translation: 旋转地（以圆周运动移动地）
definition: moving in a circle
example: Everybody joins hands and dances round.

translation: 一轮，一局（竞赛或体育赛事中的一个阶段）
definition: a stage in a competition or sports event
example: the qualifying rounds of the National Championships

translation: 环绕（绕圈子，如绕世界航行）
definition: in a circle
example: the first woman to sail round the world

translation: 路线，路径（从一处到另一处所遵循的道路）
definition: a way that you follow to get from one place to another
example: Which is the best route to take?

translation: 常规的，例行的（作为工作或过程正常部分而进行的）
definition: done or happening as a normal part of a particular job, situation or process
example: routine enquiries/questions/tests/screening

translation: 常规，惯例（定期做事的正常顺序和方式）
definition: the normal order and way in which you regularly do things
example: to settle/get/fall into a routine

translation: 行，排（排成一行的若干人或物）
皇室的（与国家的国王或女王相关或属于他们的）
definition: connected with or belonging to the king or queen of a country
example: the royal family

translation: 擦，揉（在表面上来回移动手、布等并施加压力）
definition: to move your hand, a cloth, etc., backwards and forwards over a surface while pressing it
example: rub something, He sat up on the hard bunk and rubbed his eyes.

translation: 橡胶制的（由橡胶制成的）
definition: made of rubber
example: a rubber ball

translation: 橡胶（一种可拉伸、不透水的强韧物质，用于制造轮胎等）
definition: a strong substance that can be stretched and does not allow liquids to pass through it, used for making tyres, boots, etc. It is made from the liquid (= sap) inside a tropical plant or is produced using chemicals.
example: a ball made of rubber

translation: 垃圾（因不想要或不需要而扔掉的东西）
definition: things that you throw away because you no longer want or need them
example: a rubbish bag/bin

translation: 粗鲁的（表现出对他人的不尊重或不顾及他人感受的）
definition: having or showing a lack of respect for other people and their feelings
example: a rude comment/remark

translation: 橄榄球（由两队13或15人进行的、使用椭圆形球的比赛）
definition: a game played by two teams of 13 or 15 players, using an oval ball which may be kicked or carried. Teams try to put the ball over the other team’s line.
example: to play a game of rugby

translation: 废墟，毁坏（被毁坏或严重受损的状态或过程）
definition: the state or process of being destroyed or severely damaged
example: A large number of churches fell into ruin after the revolution.

translation: 毁掉，破坏（严重损坏某物使其失去价值或乐趣）
definition: to damage something so badly that it loses all its value, pleasure, etc.
example: The bad weather ruined our trip.

translation: 规则（在特定情况下或游戏中规定该做什么、不该做什么的陈述）
definition: a statement of what may, must or must not be done in a particular situation or when playing a game
example: She laid down strict rules for her tenants, including prompt payment of rent.

translation: 统治，治理（控制并对国家、群体等拥有权威）
definition: to control and have authority over a country, a group of people, etc.
example: rule (something), At that time, King John ruled England.

translation: 裁定，判决（权力部门――尤指法官――做出的官方决定）
definition: an official decision made by somebody in a position of authority, especially a judge
example: The court will make its ruling on the case next week.

translation: 传闻，谣言（人们谈论的、可能非真实的信息或故事）
definition: a piece of information, or a story, that people talk about, but that may not be true
example: to start/spread a rumour

translation: 跑步，路程（跑步的行为；或跑步的一段时间、距离）
definition: an act of running; a period of time spent running or the distance that somebody runs
example: I go for a run every morning.

translation: 跑（用腿移动，速度快于走）
definition: to move using your legs, going faster than when you walk
example: Can you run as fast as Mike?

translation: 跑步者（跑步的人或动物，尤指参加比赛者）
definition: a person or an animal that runs, especially one taking part in a race
example: a long-distance/cross-country/marathon runner

translation: 跑步（跑步的动作或这项运动）
definition: the action or sport of running
example: to go running

translation: 农村的，乡下的（与乡村相关的或像乡村的）
definition: connected with or like the countryside
example: rural areas

translation: 冲，猛冲（突然强烈的移动或行动）
definition: a sudden strong movement or action
example: rush for something, Shoppers made a rush for the exits.

translation: 冲，急促（以很快的速度移动或做事，常过快）
definition: to move or to do something with great speed, often too fast
example: We've got plenty of time; there's no need to rush.

translation: 解雇（将某人从工作中辞退）
definition: to dismiss somebody from a job
example: She was sacked for refusing to work on Sundays.

translation: 神圣的（与神相关的；被认为是神圣的）
definition: connected with God or a god; considered to be holy
example: a sacred image/shrine/temple

translation: 牺牲（为了更重要的事而放弃重要或有价值之物的事实；所放弃之物）
definition: the fact of giving up something important or valuable to you in order to get or do something that seems more important; something that you give up in this way
example: The makers of the product assured us that there had been no sacrifice of quality.

translation: 牺牲（为了自己或他人放弃重要或有价值之物）
definition: to give up something that is important or valuable to you in order to get or do something that seems more important for yourself or for another person
example: sacrifice something for somebody/something, She sacrificed everything for her children.

translation: 悲伤的（不快乐的或表现出不快乐的）
definition: unhappy or showing unhappiness
example: sad to do something, We are very sad to hear that you are leaving.

translation: 悲哀地，遗憾地（以悲伤的方式）
definition: in a sad way
example: ‘I'm so sorry,’ she said sadly.

translation: 安全的（受保护免受危险、伤害或损失的）
definition: protected from any danger, harm or loss
example: The children are quite safe here.

translation: 安全（处于安全、受保护免受危险的状态）
definition: the state of being safe and protected from danger or harm
example: in safety, a place where children can play in safety

translation: 帆（风吹在其上使船航行的强韧布片）
definition: a sheet of strong cloth which the wind blows against to make a boat or ship travel through the water
example: As the boat moved down the river the wind began to fill the sails.

translation: 航行（利用帆或引擎在水上旅行）
definition: to travel on water using sails or an engine
example: #NAME?

translation: 航行，帆船运动（在带帆船只中旅行的运动或活动）
definition: the sport or activity of travelling in a boat with sails
example: to go sailing

translation: 水手（在船上工作的船员）
definition: a person who works on a ship as a member of the crew
example: a crew of two officers and 13 sailors

translation: 圣人（教会因其生前或死后的神圣事迹而认可的人）
definition: a person that the Christian Church recognizes as being very holy, because of the way they have lived or died
example: St John

translation: 缘故，利益（为了某人的利益或某事的原因）
沙拉（通常随餐食用的生蔬菜混合物，如生菜、西红柿等）
definition: a mixture of raw vegetables such as lettuce, tomato and cucumber, usually served with other food as part of a meal
example: All main courses come with salad or vegetables.

translation: 薪水（雇员――尤指办公室职员――因工作收到的钱，通常按月支付）
definition: money that employees receive for doing their job, especially professional employees or people working in an office, usually paid every month
example: an annual salary of $40?000

translation: 出售，销售（卖出某物的行为或过程）
definition: an act or the process of selling something
example: regulations governing the sale of alcoholic beverages

translation: 盐（添加到食物中以调味或防腐的白色物质，主要成分是氯化钠）
definition: a white substance that is added to food to make it taste better or to preserve it. Salt is obtained from mines and is also found in seawater. It is sometimes called common salt to show that it is different from other chemical salts. Its chemical name is sodium chloride.
example: Pass the salt, please.

translation: 相同的（指代已提到的那一个或那些，没有任何不同的）
definition: exactly the one or ones referred to or mentioned; not different
example: We have lived in the same house for twenty years.

translation: 同样地（以相同的方式）
definition: in the same way
example: We treat boys exactly the same as girls.

translation: 同样的事物（同样的东西或事情）
definition: the same thing or things
example: I would do the same again.

translation: 样本，样品（从大群体中提取用于测试以提供信息的少量人或物）
definition: a number of people or things taken from a larger group and used in tests to provide information about the group
example: The interviews were given to a random sample of students.

translation: 品尝，体验（尝试少量的食物；或短时间体验某事以了解其样子）
definition: to try a small amount of a particular food to see what it is like; to experience something for a short time to see what it is like
example: I sampled the delights of Greek cooking for the first time.

translation: 制裁（为了促使某国遵守国际法而对其贸易、接触等进行的官方限制）
definition: an official order that limits trade, contact, etc. with a particular country, in order to make it do something, such as obeying international law
example: Trade sanctions were imposed against any country that refused to sign the agreement.

translation: 沙，沙子（由极细小的岩石颗粒组成的物质，见于海滩、沙漠等）
definition: a substance that consists of very small fine grains of rock. Sand is found on beaches, in deserts, etc.
example: a grain of sand

translation: 三明治（两片面包，中间夹有肉、奶酪等，常抹有黄油）
definition: two slices of bread, often spread with butter, with a layer of meat, cheese, etc. between them
example: a ham/tuna/egg sandwich

translation: 卫星（被送入太空绕行星运动的电子设备，用于通信或搜集信息）
definition: an electronic device that is sent into space and moves around the earth or another planet. It is used for communicating by radio, television, etc. and for gathering information.
example: a weather/communications/spy satellite

translation: 满意（实现目标或想要的事发生后的良好感觉；给人此感觉的事物）
definition: the good feeling that you have when you have achieved something or when something that you wanted to happen does happen; something that gives you this feeling
example: to gain/get/derive satisfaction from something

translation: 满意的（因实现目标或想要的事发生而感到高兴的）
definition: pleased because you have achieved something or because something that you wanted to happen has happened
example: a satisfied customer

translation: 使满意（通过做或给某人想要的东西使其高兴）
definition: to make somebody pleased by doing or giving them what they want
example: Nothing satisfies him―he's always complaining.

translation: 星期六（周五之后、周日之前的一天）
definition: the day of the week after Friday and before Sunday
example: It's Saturday today, isn't it?

translation: 酱汁，调味汁（配餐食用以增加风味的浓稠液体）
definition: a thick liquid that is eaten with food to add taste to it
example: tomato/cranberry/chilli sauce

translation: 拯救，节省（使某人/某物免于死亡、伤害、损失；或节省金钱、时间）
definition: to keep somebody/something safe from death, harm, loss, etc.
example: save somebody/something, to save somebody’s life

translation: 节省（不需要使用或花费的量，如时间或金钱）
definition: an amount of something such as time or money that you do not need to use or spend
example: saving of something, Buy three and make a saving of 55p.

translation: 发言权（在决策前通过给出意见来产生影响的权利）
definition: the right to influence something by giving your opinion before a decision is made
example: say (in something), We had no say in the decision to sell the company.

translation: 说（用言语表达或告知）
definition: to speak or tell somebody something, using words
example: + speech, ‘Hello!’ she said.

translation: 规模（某事的大小或程度，尤指与他物相比时）
definition: the size or extent of something, especially when compared with something else
example: on a … scale, They entertain on a large scale (= they hold expensive parties with a lot of guests).

translation: 扫描，浏览（快速但非非常仔细地查看文档等）
definition: to look quickly but not very carefully at a document, etc.
example: scan something for something, I scanned the list quickly for my name.

translation: 丑闻（人们认为在道德或法律上错误并引起公愤的行为或事件）
definition: behaviour or an event that people think is morally or legally wrong and causes public feelings of shock or anger
example: a series of sex scandals

translation: 惊恐（许多人对某事感到焦虑或恐惧的情况）
definition: a situation in which a lot of people are anxious or frightened about something
example: a health scare

translation: 惊吓（惊吓某人）
definition: to frighten somebody
example: scare somebody, You scared me.

translation: 受惊的（害怕某事或担心坏事可能发生）
definition: frightened of something or afraid that something bad might happen
example: The thieves got scared and ran away.

translation: 吓人的（令人恐惧的）
definition: frightening
example: It was a really scary moment.

translation: 分散的（在大面积区域或长时期内散布得很开的）
definition: spread far apart over a wide area or over a long period of time
example: a few scattered settlements

translation: 方案，设想（对未来可能发生情况的描述）
definition: a description of how things might happen in the future
example: Let me suggest a possible scenario.

translation: 现场（事情发生的地方，尤指不快之事发生地）
definition: the place where something happens, especially something unpleasant
example: the scene of the accident/crime/crash

translation: 怀疑的（对主张或陈述的真实性或某事是否发生持有怀疑的）
definition: having doubts that a claim or statement is true or that something will happen
example: She looked highly sceptical.

translation: 时间表，进度表（列出所有要做的工作及其时间的计划）
definition: a plan that lists all the work that you have to do and when you must do each thing
example: I have a hectic schedule for the next few days.

translation: 安排（安排某事在特定时间发生）
definition: to arrange for something to happen at a particular time
example: schedule something for something, The meeting is scheduled for Friday afternoon.

translation: 计划，方案（做某事或组织某事的计划或系统）
definition: a plan or system for doing or organizing something
example: a training scheme

translation: 学者（因详细研究而对特定学科了解很多的人）
definition: a person who knows a lot about a particular subject because they have studied it in detail
example: a classical scholar

translation: 奖学金（组织给予某人以资助其教育的款项）
definition: an amount of money given to somebody by an organization to help pay for their education
example: She won a scholarship to study at Stanford.

translation: 学校（儿童接受教育的地方）
definition: a place where children go to be educated
example: My brother and I went to the same school.

translation: 科学（基于可证明事实――如通过实验――对自然和物理世界的结构和行为的认识）
definition: knowledge about the structure and behaviour of the natural and physical world, based on facts that you can prove, for example by experiments
example: new developments in science and technology

translation: 科学的（涉及科学的；与科学相关的）
definition: involving science; connected with science
example: a scientific discovery/theory/fact

translation: 科学家（研究一门或多门自然科学――如物理、化学、生物――的人）
definition: a person who studies one or more of the natural sciences (= for example, physics, chemistry or biology)
example: a research scientist

translation: 范围，余地（做或实现某事的机会或能力）
definition: the opportunity or ability to do or achieve something
example: scope for something, There's still plenty of scope for improvement.

translation: 分数，得分（比赛中选手或团队得到的分数、进球数等）
definition: the number of points, goals, etc. scored by each player or team in a game or competition
example: a high/low score

translation: 得分（在比赛或竞赛中赢得点数、进球等）
definition: to win points, goals, etc. in a game or competition
example: Fraser scored again in the second half.

translation: 划痕，抓痕（抓挠皮肤或物体表面留下的痕迹、切口或伤口）
definition: a mark, a cut or an injury made by scratching somebody’s skin or the surface of something
example: Her hands were covered in scratches from the brambles.

translation: 抓挠（用指甲揉搓皮肤，通常是因为发痒）
definition: to rub your skin with your nails, usually because it is itching
example: scratch something, John yawned and scratched his chin.

translation: 尖叫（因受伤、惊吓、兴奋等发出的响亮高音叫喊）
definition: a loud high shout made by somebody who is hurt, frightened, excited, etc.; a loud high noise
example: scream of something, She let out a scream of pain.

translation: 尖叫（发出响亮的高音叫喊，因为受伤、害怕等）
definition: to give a loud, high shout, because you are hurt, frightened, excited, etc.
example: There was a bang and I heard someone scream.

translation: 屏幕（电视、电脑等电子设备前部显示图像或信息的平整表面）
definition: the flat surface at the front of a television, computer, or other electronic device, on which you see pictures or information
example: a computer screen

translation: 放映（在影院或电视上播放电影等）
definition: to show a film, etc. in a cinema or on television
example: a list of films to be screened as part of the festival

translation: 放映，筛查（放映电影或电视节目的行为）
definition: the act of showing a film or television programme
example: This will be the movie's first screening in this country.

translation: 螺钉（带螺旋纹的钉状金属片，通过旋转旋入物体以起到固定作用）
definition: a thin pointed piece of metal like a nail with a raised spiral line (called a thread) along it and a line or cross cut into its head. Screws are turned and pressed into wood, metal, etc. with a screwdriver in order to fasten two things together.
example: One of the screws is loose.

translation: 拧紧（用螺钉将一物固定到另一物上或使之变紧）
definition: to fasten one thing to another or make something tight with a screw or screws
example: The bookcase is screwed to the wall.

translation: 剧本，脚本（戏剧、电影、广播等的书面文本）
definition: a written text of a play, film, broadcast, talk, etc.
example: That line isn't in the original script.

translation: 审查，细看（仔细且全面的检查）
definition: careful and complete examination
example: Her argument doesn't really stand up to scrutiny.

translation: 雕塑（通过雕刻或塑造木、石、粘土等制成的立体艺术品）
definition: a work of art that is a solid figure or object made by carving or shaping wood, stone, clay, metal, etc.
example: a marble sculpture of Venus

translation: 海，海洋（覆盖地球大部分表面并包围大陆岛屿的咸水）
definition: the salt water that covers most of the earth’s surface and surrounds its continents and islands
example: The waste was dumped in the sea.

translation: 印章，封条（盖在文件上以证明其真实性并带有特定机构权威的标志）
definition: an official design or mark, stamped on a document to show that it is real and carries the authority of a particular person or organization
example: The letter bore the president's seal.

translation: 密封（通过粘住开口边缘来关闭信封等）
definition: to close an envelope, etc. by sticking the edges of the opening together
example: Make sure you've signed the cheque before sealing the envelope.

translation: 搜索，搜寻（尝试寻找某人/某物，尤指通过仔细寻找）
definition: an attempt to find somebody/something, especially by looking carefully for them/it
example: search for somebody/something, a long search for the murder weapon

translation: 搜寻（仔细寻找某物/某人；或检查特定地点以寻找）
definition: to look carefully for something/somebody; to examine a particular place when looking for something/somebody
example: search for something/somebody, She searched in vain for her passport.

translation: 季节（一年的四个主要时段之一：春夏秋冬）
definition: any of the four main periods of the year: spring, summer, autumn and winter
example: the changing seasons

translation: 座位（可以坐的地方，如椅子）
definition: a place where you can sit, for example a chair
example: She sat back in her seat.

translation: 就座（给某人安排座位；在某处坐下）
definition: to give somebody a place to sit; to sit down in a place
example: Please wait to be seated (= in a restaurant, etc.).

translation: 第二地（在顺序或重要性上排在另一人/物之后）
definition: after one other person or thing in order or importance
example: She came second in the marathon.

translation: 第二个（在类似事物或人的系列中紧随第一个之后的；2nd）
definition: happening or coming next after the first in a series of similar things or people; 2nd
example: This is the second time it's happened.

translation: 秒（时间测量单位，一分钟等于60秒）
definition: a unit for measuring time. There are 60 seconds in one minute.
example: in… seconds, She can run 100 metres in just over 11 seconds.

translation: 第二个（在类似事物或人的系列中紧随第一个之后的；2nd）
definition: happening or coming next after the first in a series of similar things or people; 2nd
example: This is the second time it's happened.

translation: 中学的（与11-18岁儿童教学相关的）
definition: connected with teaching children of 11C18 years
example: secondary teachers

translation: 其次（用于引入演说或文章要点列表中的第二项）
definition: used to introduce the second of a list of points you want to make in a speech or piece of writing
example: Firstly, it's expensive, and secondly, it's too slow.

translation: 秘密的（仅被少数人知晓的；对他人隐藏的）
definition: known about by only a few people; kept hidden from others
example: secret information/meetings/talks

translation: 秘密（仅被少数人知晓且不告知他人的事情）
definition: something that is known about by only a few people and not told to others
example: Can you keep a secret?

translation: 秘书（在办公室为他人工作、处理邮件电话、记录和安排会议等的人）
definition: a person who works in an office, working for another person, dealing with mail and phone calls, keeping records, arranging meetings with people, etc.
example: a legal/medical secretary

translation: 部分（事物划分出的任何一个部分）
definition: any of the parts into which something is divided
example: section of something, That section of the road is still closed.

translation: 部门（活动领域的一部分，尤指国家经济的部门）
definition: a part of an area of activity, especially of a country’s economy
example: the service/banking/manufacturing/financial sector

translation: 世俗的（与精神或宗教事务无关的）
definition: not connected with spiritual or religious matters
example: secular music

translation: 安全的，稳固的（很可能长期持续或成功的）
definition: likely to continue or be successful for a long time
example: a secure job/income

translation: 获得（获得或实现某事，尤指通过大量努力）
definition: to obtain or achieve something, especially when this means using a lot of effort
example: secure something, to secure a contract/deal/funding

translation: 安全（保护国家、建筑或人免受攻击、危险等的活动）
definition: the activities involved in protecting a country, building or person against attack, danger, etc.
example: national/homeland security (= the defence of a country)

translation: 看见（利用眼睛察觉到某人/某物）
definition: to become aware of somebody/something by using your eyes
example: see somebody/something, She looked for him but couldn't see him in the crowd.

translation: 种子（由植物产出的能长成新植株的微小硬块）
definition: the small hard part produced by a plant, from which a new plant can grow
example: a packet of wild flower seeds

translation: 寻找，寻求（寻找某物/某人）
definition: to look for something/somebody
example: seek something/somebody, Drivers are advised to seek alternative routes.

translation: 寻找者（尝试寻找或获得所提到的事物的人）
definition: a person who is trying to find or get the thing mentioned
example: an attention/a publicity seeker

translation: 似乎（给出作为或正在做某事的印象）
definition: to give the impression of being or doing something
example: + adj., You seem happy.

translation: 表面上（以看似真实但实际可能并非如此的方式）
definition: in a way that appears to be true but may in fact not be
example: a seemingly stupid question

translation: 部分，段（事物中与其他部分分开或可被单独考虑的一部分）
definition: a part of something that is separate from the other parts or can be considered separately
example: She cleaned a small segment of the painting.

translation: 夺取（突然用力将某人/某物抓在手中）
definition: to take somebody/something in your hand suddenly and using force
example: seize something from somebody, She tried to seize the gun from him.

translation: 很少，不常（不经常）
definition: not often
example: He had seldom seen a child with so much talent.

translation: 选择（通常根据某种体系从一群人或物中挑选）
definition: to choose somebody/something from a group of people or things, usually according to a system
example: select somebody/something for something, He hasn't been selected for the team.

translation: 选择（通常根据某种体系从一群人或物中挑选的过程）
definition: the process of choosing somebody/something from a group of people or things, usually according to a system
example: She took a long time to make her selection.

translation: 选择性的（仅影响或涉及大群体中少数人或物的）
definition: affecting or involving only a small number of people or things from a larger group
example: the selective breeding of cattle

translation: 自我（你作为人的类型，尤指你通常的表现、外貌或感觉）
definition: the type of person you are, especially the way you normally behave, look or feel
example: You'll soon be feeling your old self again (= feeling well or happy again).

translation: 卖（给某人某物以换取金钱）
definition: to give something to somebody in exchange for money
example: sell (something), I recently sold my bike.

translation: 研讨会（大学中师生就特定主题进行讨论或研究的课程）
definition: a class at a university or college when a small group of students and a teacher discuss or study a particular topic
example: Teaching is by lectures and seminars.

translation: 参议员（参议院的成员）
definition: a member of a senate
example: Senator McCarthy

translation: 发送（使某物移动或被带到某处，尤指通过邮政、电邮等）
definition: to make something go or be taken to a place, especially by post, email, radio, etc.
example: send something, She sent a letter of support.

translation: 高级的，资深的（职级或地位高的；比他人职级更高的）
definition: high in rank or status; higher in rank or status than others
example: a senior official/officer/manager/executive

translation: 感觉（当某物影响身体时产生的感觉）
definition: a feeling that you get when something affects your body
example: a tingling/burning sensation

translation: 感觉，感官（对某事的理解；判断某事的能力）
definition: an understanding about something; an ability to judge something
example: One of the most important things in a partner is a sense of humour (= the ability to find things funny or make people laugh).

translation: 感觉到（察觉到某事，尽管无法直接看见或听到）
definition: to become aware of something even though you cannot see it, hear it, etc.
example: sense something, Sensing danger, they started to run.

translation: 明智的（能基于理智而非情感做出良好判断的；务实的）
definition: able to make good judgements based on reason and experience rather than emotion; practical
example: She's a sensible sort of person.

translation: 敏感的（察觉到并能理解他人及其感受的）
definition: aware of and able to understand other people and their feelings
example: a sensitive and caring man

translation: 敏感性（理解他人感受的能力）
definition: the ability to understand other people’s feelings
example: sensitivity to the needs of children

translation: 句子（表达陈述、疑问或命令的一组词，通常含主谓语）
definition: a set of words expressing a statement, a question or an order, usually containing a subject and a verb. In written English sentences begin with a capital letter and end with a full stop/period (.), a question mark (?) or an exclamation mark (!).
example: Does the sentence contain an adverb?

translation: 判决（在法庭上正式宣布某人应受的特定惩罚）
definition: to say officially in court that somebody is to receive a particular punishment
example: sentence somebody to something, He sentenced the defendant to life in prison.

translation: 情感，情绪（感觉或观点，尤指基于情感的）
definition: a feeling or an opinion, especially one based on emotions
example: the spread of nationalist sentiments

translation: 分开的（单独成一个单元的；未连接的）
definition: forming a unit by itself; not joined to something else
example: They have begun to sleep in separate rooms.

translation: 分开（划分为不同的部分或群体）
definition: to divide into different parts or groups; to divide things into different parts or groups
example: Stir the sauce constantly so that it does not separate.

translation: 分开，分离（将人或物分开的行为；分开的状态）
definition: the act of separating people or things; the state of being separate
example: separation from somebody/something, the state’s eventual separation from the federation

translation: 九月（一年中的第九个月）
definition: the 9th month of the year, between August and October
example: She was born in September.

translation: 顺序，序列（具有特定顺序并导致特定结果的一组事件、数字等）
definition: a set of events, actions, numbers, etc. which have a particular order and which lead to a particular result
example: He described the sequence of events leading up to the robbery.

translation: 连环的（多次以相同方式做相同事情的）
definition: doing the same thing in the same way several times; done in the same way several times
example: a serial rapist

translation: 系列，丛书（涉及相同主题或具有相同人物的一套节目或出版物）
definition: a set of television or radio programmes or podcasts that deal with the same subject or that have the same characters
example: The first episode of the new series is on Saturday.

translation: 严重的（坏的或危险的）
definition: bad or dangerous
example: a serious illness/offence/crime

translation: 严重地（以严重的方式）
definition: in a serious way
example: to be seriously ill/injured/wounded/hurt

translation: 仆人（在他人雇主家中为其做饭、打扫等工作的人）
definition: a person who works in another person’s house, and cooks, cleans, etc. for them
example: a domestic servant

translation: 供应，端上（给某人食物或饮料，例如在餐厅或用餐时）
definition: to give somebody food or drink, for example at a restaurant or during a meal
example: serve (something), Breakfast is served between 7 and 10 a.m.

translation: 服务，公共事业（由政府或私企组织的满足公众需求的系统）
definition: a system that provides something that the public needs, organized by the government or a private company
example: the ambulance/bus/postal service

translation: 会议，时间段（花费在进行特定活动上的一段时间）
definition: a period of time that is spent doing a particular activity
example: a training/practice session

translation: 一套，一组（以某种方式属于一类的类似事物的组合）
definition: a group of similar things that belong together in some way
example: a set of six chairs

translation: 放置，安排（准备或安排某物使其就绪或到位）
definition: to prepare or arrange something so that it is ready for use or in position
example: set something, Have you set the alarm clock?

translation: 组织结构，体制（组织某事的方式；一个系统）
definition: a way of organizing something; a system
example: I've only been here a couple of weeks and I don't really know the set-up.

translation: 背景，环境（某物所在的环境；某事发生的地点）
definition: an environment where something is located; the place at which something happens
example: a rural/an ideal/a beautiful/an idyllic setting

translation: 解决（结束争论或分歧）
definition: to put an end to an argument or a disagreement
example: settle something, to settle a dispute/a matter/an issue

translation: 解决，协议（结束人或群体间争论的正式协议）
definition: an official agreement that ends an argument between two people or groups
example: to negotiate a peace settlement

translation: 移居者（前往新国家或地区定居的人）
definition: a person who goes to live in a new country or region
example: Most of the settlers came from England.

translation: 七（数字7）
example: There are seven cookies left.

translation: 十七（数字17）
七十（数字70）
几个，若干（多于两个但不是很多）
definition: more than two but not very many
example: Several letters arrived this morning.

translation: 几个，若干（多于两个但不是很多）
definition: more than two but not very many
example: Several letters arrived this morning.

translation: 严重的，严厉的（极其糟糕或严重的）
definition: extremely bad or serious
example: His injuries are severe.

translation: 严重地，严厉地（非常糟糕或严重地）
definition: very badly or seriously
example: severely injured

translation: 性别（男性或女性的状态）
definition: the state of being male or female
example: How can you tell what sex a fish is?

translation: 性的（与性活动相关的）
definition: connected with the physical activity of sex
example: sexual behaviour/activity/desire

translation: 性取向，性征（与人的性欲相关的感觉和活动）
definition: the feelings and activities connected with a person’s sexual desires
example: He was confused about his sexuality.

translation: 性感的（具有性吸引力的）
definition: sexually attractive
example: the sexy lead singer

translation: 阴凉处（因阳光照不到而在物体下方或后面形成的阴暗凉爽区域）
definition: an area that is dark and cool under or behind something, for example a tree or building, because the sun’s light does not get to it
example: shade of something, The shade of the pine tree provided some protection from the sun.

translation: 影子（光线被物体遮挡而在表面形成的暗影）
definition: the dark shape that somebody/something’s form makes on a surface, for example on the ground, when they are between the light and the surface
example: The children were having fun, chasing each other's shadows.

translation: 摇动（摇晃某人/某物的动作）
definition: an act of shaking somebody/something
example: She gave him a shake to wake him.

translation: 摇晃（以短促快速的动作左右或上下移动某人/某物）
definition: to move or make somebody/something move with short quick movements from side to side or up and down
example: The whole house shakes when a train goes past.

translation: （助动词）将要（与I和we连用，用于谈论或预测未来）
definition: used with I and we for talking about or predicting the future
example: This time next week I shall be in Scotland.

translation: 浅的（顶部或表面到底部距离不大的）
definition: not having much distance between the top or surface and the bottom
example: a shallow dish/pan/bowl

translation: 遗憾（用于表示某事令人难过或失望）
definition: used to say that something is a cause for feeling sad or disappointed
example: She's retiring because of ill health, which is a great shame.

translation: 形状（物体的外缘或表面的形式；特定形式的示例）
definition: the form of the outer edges or surfaces of something; an example of something that has a particular form
example: a rectangular/spherical/cylindrical shape

translation: 使成形（将某物做成特定的形状）
definition: to make something into a particular shape
example: shape A into B, Shape the dough into a ball.

translation: ...形状的（具有所提到的形状类型的）
definition: having the type of shape mentioned
example: a huge balloon shaped like a giant cow

translation: 份额（两人或多人间分配的事物的一份）
definition: one part of something that is divided between two or more people
example: share of something, Next year we hope to have a greater share of the market.

translation: 分享，共有（与他人同时拥有、使用或体验某事）
definition: to have, use or experience something at the same time as somebody else
example: There isn't an empty table. Would you mind sharing?

translation: 股东（公司或企业的股份拥有者）
definition: an owner of shares in a company or business
example: the major shareholders in the company

translation: 锋利的（有细薄边缘或尖端的，尤指能切割或刺穿的）
definition: having a fine edge or point, especially of something that can cut or make a hole in something
example: a sharp knife

translation: 破碎，震碎（突然破碎成小片；使之破碎）
definition: to suddenly break into small pieces; to make something suddenly break into small pieces
example: shatter (into something), He dropped the vase and it shattered into pieces on the floor.

translation: 她（代指已提到或易识别的女性或雌性动物）
definition: a female person or animal that has already been mentioned or is easily identified
example: ‘What does your sister do?’ ‘She's a dentist.’

translation: 摆脱，裁减（去掉不再想要的东西，如裁减职位）
definition: to get rid of something that is no longer wanted
example: The factory is shedding a large number of jobs.

translation: 羊（农场饲养的产肉或产毛的长毛动物）
definition: an animal with a thick coat, kept on farms for its meat (called mutton or lamb) or its wool
example: a flock of sheep

translation: 十足的，纯粹的（用于强调某事物的规模、程度或数量）
definition: used to emphasize the size, degree or amount of something
example: The area is under threat from the sheer number of tourists using it.

translation: 床单，薄片（床上的大薄布片；或纸张等薄片）
definition: a large piece of thin cloth used on a bed to lie on or lie under
example: Have you changed the sheets (= put clean sheets on the bed)?

translation: 搁板（固定在墙上或橱柜中用于放置物品的扁平木/金属/玻璃板）
definition: a flat board, made of wood, metal, glass, etc., fixed to the wall or forming part of a cupboard, bookcase, etc., for things to be placed on
example: I helped him put up some shelves in his bedroom.

translation: 壳，外壳（蛋、坚果、种子或某些动物的坚硬外部）
definition: the hard outer part of eggs, nuts, some seeds, and some animals
example: We collected shells on the beach.

translation: 避难所，住所（基本的居住地；遮风避雨处）
definition: the fact of having a place to live or stay, considered as a basic human need
example: Human beings need food, clothing and shelter.

translation: 庇护，遮蔽（给予某人/某物免受天气或危险影响的场所；保护）
definition: to give somebody/something a place where they are protected from the weather or from danger; to protect somebody/something
example: shelter somebody/something from somebody/something, Trees shelter the house from the wind.

translation: 轮班（一组工人在另一组下班后开始工作的时间段）
definition: a period of time worked by a group of workers who start work as another group finishes
example: to work a shift

translation: 转移，移动（从一个位置或地方移动到另一个）
definition: to move, or move something, from one position or place to another
example: Lydia shifted uncomfortably in her chair.

translation: 发光，闪耀（产生或反射光线；明亮）
definition: to produce or reflect light; to be bright
example: The sun shone brightly in a cloudless sky.

translation: 发光的，闪亮的（光滑明亮的；反射光线的）
definition: smooth and bright; reflecting the light
example: shiny black hair

translation: 船（通过海洋运送人或货物的大型船只）
definition: a large boat that carries people or goods by sea
example: The yard builds ships for the Navy.

translation: 运输，运送（通过船或其他交通工具发送或运输人/物）
definition: to send or transport somebody/something by ship or by another means of transport
example: The company ships its goods all over the world.

translation: 运输，航运（所有的船只；或通过船只进行的运输业务）
definition: ships in general or considered as a group
example: The canal is open to shipping.

translation: 衬衫（穿在身体上半部的由轻薄布料制成的带袖上衣，通常带领和扣）
definition: a piece of clothing worn on the upper part of the body, made of light cloth, with sleeves and usually with a collar and buttons down the front
example: to wear a shirt

translation: 震惊（由于发生不快之事而产生的强烈惊讶感；引起此感的事）
definition: a strong feeling of surprise as a result of something happening, especially something unpleasant; the event that causes this feeling
example: I got a terrible shock the other day.

translation: 使震惊（使某人感到惊讶且沮丧）
definition: to surprise and upset somebody
example: shock somebody, President Kennedy's assassination in Dallas on November 22, 1963, shocked the world.

translation: 震惊的（感到惊讶且沮丧的；表现出此情绪的）
definition: surprised and upset; showing that somebody feels surprised and upset
example: I was quite shocked when I found out what he'd done.

translation: 令人震惊的（冒犯或令他人沮丧的；在道德上错误的）
definition: that offends or upsets people; that is morally wrong
example: shocking behaviour

translation: 鞋（穿在脚上的皮革或塑料制品的一只）
definition: one of a pair of objects usually made of leather or plastic that you wear on your feet
example: a pair of shoes

translation: 嫩芽，幼苗（植物开始生长时从地里长出的部分；植物的新芽）
definition: the part that grows up from the ground when a plant starts to grow; a new part that grows on plants or trees
example: new green shoots

translation: 射击（发射枪支或其他武器；从武器中射出某物）
definition: to fire a gun or other weapon; to fire something from a weapon
example: Don't shoot―I surrender.

translation: 射击，枪击（人被枪击中的情况）
definition: a situation in which a person is shot with a gun
example: Terrorist groups claimed responsibility for the shootings and bomb attacks.

translation: 商店（可以购买商品或服务的建筑或其中一部分）
definition: a building or part of a building where you can buy goods or services
example: to open/close/run a shop

translation: 购物（在商店购买东西）
definition: to buy things in shops
example: I shop there from time to time.

translation: 购物（去商店买东西或在线订购的活动）
definition: the activity of going to shops and buying things or ordering them online
example: to go shopping

translation: 岸（沿着海、洋或湖边的一块土地）
definition: the land along the edge of the sea, the ocean or a lake
example: a rocky/sandy shore

translation: 短的，矮的（测量或覆盖的长度或距离短的；比通常短的）
definition: measuring or covering a small length or distance, or a smaller length or distance than usual
example: He had short curly hair.

translation: 短期的（持续时间短的；仅为未来短期设计的）
definition: lasting a short time; designed only for a short period of time in the future
example: a short-term loan

translation: 短缺（所需人或物不足的情况）
definition: a situation when there is not enough of the people or things that are needed
example: food/housing/water shortages

translation: 不久，很快（短时间内；不长久）
definition: a short time; not long
example: She arrived shortly after us.

translation: 射击，开枪（发射枪支的行为；发出的响声）
definition: the act of firing a gun; the sound this makes
example: We heard some shots in the distance.

translation: 应该（用于表示什么是正确的、恰当的，尤用于批评他人）
definition: used to show what is right, appropriate, etc., especially when criticizing somebody’s actions
example: You shouldn't drink and drive.

translation: 肩膀（手臂顶端与脖子之间的身体部位）
definition: either of the two parts of the body between the top of each arm and the neck
example: your left/right shoulder

translation: 大叫（因愤怒、恐惧、兴奋等发出的响亮叫喊）
definition: a loud cry of anger, fear, excitement, etc.
example: angry shouts

translation: 叫喊（以响亮的嗓门说话；愤怒地对某人说话）
definition: to say something in a loud voice; to speak loudly/angrily to somebody
example: Stop shouting and listen!

translation: 节目，演出（电视或广播节目）
definition: a programme on television or the radio
example: Millions of people watch the show.

translation: 显示，展示（使某事清晰；证明某事）
definition: to make something clear; to prove something
example: show (that)…, The figures clearly show that her claims are false.

translation: 阵雨，淋浴（人站立其下洗澡的流水设备；淋浴间）
definition: a piece of equipment producing a flow of water that you stand under to wash yourself; the small room or part of a room that contains a shower
example: in the shower, He's in the shower.

translation: 缩水，缩小（变得更小，尤指由于热水洗涤；使衣物等变小）
definition: to become smaller, especially when washed in water that is too hot; to make clothes, cloth, etc. smaller in this way
example: My sweater shrank in the wash.

translation: 耸肩（抬起并放下肩膀以示不知道或不在乎）
definition: to raise your shoulders and then drop them to show that you do not know or care about something
example: Sam shrugged and said nothing.

translation: 关闭的（未开启的）
definition: not open
example: The door was shut.

translation: 关上（关闭某物；变关闭）
definition: to close something; to become closed
example: The window won't shut.

translation: 害羞的（在见人或说话时感到紧张或尴尬的）
definition: nervous or embarrassed about meeting and speaking to other people
example: He is not exactly the shy and retiring type.

translation: 兄弟姐妹（兄弟或姐妹）
definition: a brother or sister
example: squabbles between siblings

translation: 生病的（身体或精神生病的）
definition: physically or mentally ill
example: a sick child

translation: 侧面（由假想中心线分成的平面、物体或区域的一半）
definition: either of the two halves of a surface, an object or an area that is divided by an imaginary central line
example: the right side of the brain

translation: 叹息（叹气的行为或声音）
definition: an act or the sound of sighing
example: to give/heave/let out a sigh

translation: 叹气（深吸一口气并出声呼出，以示失望、悲伤或疲倦）
definition: to take and then let out a long deep breath that can be heard, to show that you are disappointed, sad, tired, etc.
example: He sighed deeply at the thought.

translation: 视力，视力（看的能力）
definition: the ability to see
example: to lose your sight (= to become blind)

translation: 迹象，标志（显示某事存在、正在发生或未来可能发生的事件、事实）
definition: an event, an action, a fact, etc. that shows that something exists, is happening or may happen in the future
example: Looking back, I should have seen the signs.

translation: 签名，签署（在文件上写下名字以表示它是你写的或你同意其内容）
definition: to write your name on a document, letter, etc. to show that you have written it, that you agree with what it says, or that it is real
example: Sign here, please.

translation: 信号（向他人提供信息、指令、警告等的动作或声音）
definition: a movement or sound that you make to give somebody information, instructions, a warning, etc.
example: a danger/warning/distress signal

translation: 发信号（发出动作或声音以给他人消息或命令）
definition: to make a movement or sound to give somebody a message, an order, etc.
example: Don't fire until I signal.

translation: 签名（你通常写名字的方式，如在支票末尾）
definition: your name as you usually write it, for example at the end of a letter
example: Someone had forged her signature on the cheque.

translation: 意义，重要性（某事的重要性，尤指其对未来的影响）
definition: the importance of something, especially when this has an effect on what happens in the future
example: a decision of major political significance

translation: 显著的，重要的（大到或重要到足以产生影响或被注意到的）
definition: large or important enough to have an effect or to be noticed
example: There are no significant differences between the two groups of students.

translation: 显著地（以足够大或重要到产生影响或被注意到的方式）
definition: in a way that is large or important enough to have an effect on something or to be noticed
example: significantly higher/lower/larger/smaller

translation: 沉默（完全没有响声或声音）
definition: a complete lack of noise or sound
example: Their footsteps echoed in the silence.

translation: 沉默的（几乎没有或完全没有声音的；不发声的）
definition: where there is little or no sound; making little or no sound
example: At last the traffic fell silent.

translation: 丝，丝绸（蚕产出的精细柔软纤维）
definition: fine soft thread produced by silkworms
example: The caterpillar spins the silk around its entire body.

translation: 愚蠢的（表现出缺乏思考、理解或判断的）
definition: showing a lack of thought, understanding, or judgement
example: a silly idea/question/name

translation: 银色的（发亮的灰白色的）
definition: shiny grey-white in colour
example: a silver car

translation: 银（一种发亮的灰白色贵金属化学元素，用于制造钱币、珠宝等）
definition: a chemical element. Silver is a shiny, grey-white precious metal used for making coins, jewellery, beautiful objects, etc.
example: a silver ring/chain

translation: 相似的（像某人/某物但不完全一样的）
definition: like somebody/something but not exactly the same
example: We have very similar interests.

translation: 相似性（与某人/某物相似但不完全一样的状态）
definition: the state of being similar to somebody/something but not exactly the same
example: similarity between A and B, The report highlights the similarity between the two groups.

translation: 相似地（以几乎相同的方式）
definition: in almost the same way
example: It is a little cheaper than other similarly sized cars.

translation: 简单的（不复杂的；易于理解或执行的）
definition: not complicated; easy to understand or do
example: a simple solution/explanation/question/task/example

translation: 简单地（用于强调某事是多么容易或基础）
definition: used to emphasize how easy or basic something is
example: To order, simply click here.

translation: 模拟（使用电脑、模型等创造现实生活中的特定条件，用于研究培训）
definition: to create particular conditions that exist in real life using computers, models, etc., usually for study or training purposes
example: Computer software can be used to simulate conditions on the seabed.

translation: 模拟（人工创造一套特定条件以研究或体验现实中可能存在的情况）
definition: a situation in which a particular set of conditions is created artificially in order to study or experience something that could exist in reality
example: a computer simulation of how the planet functions

translation: 同时地（与另一件事在同一时间）
definition: at the same time as something else
example: The game will be broadcast simultaneously on TV and radio.

translation: 罪，罪孽（对上帝或宗教/道德法律的触犯）
definition: an offence against God or against a religious or moral law
example: to commit a sin

translation: 自...以来（从过去的某个时间直到后来或现在）
definition: from a time in the past until a later past time, or until now
example: She went for a run on Monday and has not been seen since.

translation: 自从（从过去的某个事件直到后来或现在）
definition: from an event in the past until a later past event, or until now
example: Cath hasn't phoned since she went to Berlin.

translation: 自...以来（从过去的某个时间直到后来或现在）
definition: from a time in the past until a later past time, or until now
example: She's been off work since Tuesday.

translation: 诚挚的（表现出真实想法或感受的）
definition: showing what you really think or feel
example: a sincere apology

translation: 唱（用嗓音发出歌曲或旋律的音乐声）
definition: to make musical sounds with your voice in the form of a song or tune
example: I just can't sing in tune!

translation: 歌手（唱歌的人，尤指以此为业者）
definition: a person who sings, or whose job is singing, especially in public
example: She's a wonderful singer.

translation: 歌唱（发出歌曲旋律的嗓音活动）
definition: the activity of making musical sounds with your voice
example: the beautiful singing of birds

translation: 单一的，唯一的（仅有的一个）
definition: only one
example: He sent her a single red rose.

translation: 单程票（允许去某地但不返回的票）
definition: a ticket that allows you to travel to a place but not back again
example: How much is a single to York?

translation: 沉没（在液体或软物质中降至表面以下或底部）
definition: to go down below the surface or towards the bottom of a liquid or soft substance
example: The ship sank to the bottom of the sea.

translation: 先生（在商店或餐厅礼貌称呼不知名的男性）
definition: used as a polite way of addressing a man whose name you do not know, for example in a shop or restaurant
example: Good morning, sir. Can I help you?

translation: 姐妹（具有相同父母的女孩或女性）
definition: a girl or woman who has the same mother and father as another person
example: She's my sister.

translation: 坐（背挺直地将重心压在臀部休息，如在椅子上）
definition: to rest your weight on your bottom with your back straight, for example on/in a chair
example: She sat and stared at the letter in front of her.

translation: 地点，遗址（建筑或城镇过去、现在或未来所在的地点）
definition: a place where a building, town, etc. was, is or will be located
example: the site of a sixteenth-century abbey

translation: 位于（处于特定位置或地点的）
definition: in a particular place or position
example: My bedroom was situated on the top floor of the house.

translation: 情况，处境（特定时间和地点的所有环境和发生的事情）
definition: all the circumstances and things that are happening at a particular time and in a particular place
example: the present economic/financial/political situation

translation: 六（数字6）
example: There are six cookies left.

translation: 十六（数字16）
六十（数字60）
尺寸，大小（人或物多大多小的度量）
definition: how large or small a person or thing is
example: population/sample/group/class size

translation: 素描（快速画出的、不含细节的简单图画）
definition: a simple picture that is drawn quickly and does not have many details
example: The artist is making sketches for his next painting.

translation: 滑雪的（与滑雪运动相关的）
definition: connected with the sport of skiing
example: a ski resort

translation: 滑雪板（系在靴子上以便在雪上平稳滑行的一对长窄木/金属/塑料板之一）
definition: one of a pair of long narrow pieces of wood, metal or plastic that you attach to boots so that you can move smoothly over snow
example: a pair of skis

translation: 滑雪（在雪上滑行，尤指作为运动）
definition: to move over snow on skis, especially as a sport
example: Our children want to learn to ski.

translation: 滑雪（在雪上滑行的运动或活动）
definition: the sport or activity of moving over snow on skis
example: He also enjoys skiing and mountain biking.

translation: 技能（做好某事的能力）
definition: the ability to do something well
example: The job requires skill and an eye for detail.

translation: 熟练的（具备足够的完成某事所需的能力、经验和知识的）
definition: having enough ability, experience and knowledge to be able to do something well
example: a skilled engineer/negotiator/craftsman

translation: 皮肤（覆盖身体的组织层）
definition: the layer of tissue that covers the body
example: to have dark/pale skin

translation: 跳过，蹦跳（轻快地向前移动，每步带有一个小跳跃）
definition: to move forwards lightly and quickly making a little jump with each step
example: She skipped happily along beside me.

translation: 裙子（从身体中部垂下的服装）
definition: a piece of clothing that hangs from the middle part of the body
example: a short/long/pleated/denim skirt

translation: 头骨（构成头部、包围并保护大脑的骨骼结构）
definition: the bone structure that forms the head and surrounds and protects the brain
example: a fractured skull

translation: 天空（地球上方的、能看见云及日月星辰的空间）
definition: the space above the earth that you can see when you look up, where clouds and the sun, moon and stars appear
example: The sky suddenly went dark and it started to rain.

translation: 砰地关上（用力且发出巨大响声地关闭某物）
definition: to shut, or to make something shut, with a lot of force, making a loud noise
example: I heard the door slam behind him.

translation: 拍，扇（用手掌击打某人/某物）
definition: to hit somebody/something with the flat part of your hand
example: She slapped his face hard.

translation: 割，划（用锋利物品切出长口子，尤指猛烈地）
definition: to make a long cut with a sharp object, especially in a violent way
example: slash something, Someone had slashed the tyres on my car.

translation: 奴隶（被他人拥有并被迫为其工作、服从的人）
definition: a person who is owned by another person and is forced to work for and obey them
example: A former slave, he graduated from Clafflin University in South Carolina.

translation: 奴隶制度（被迫作为奴隶工作的状态）
definition: the state of being forced to work as a slave
example: to be sold into slavery

translation: 睡眠（眼睛闭合、身体静止、意识清醒的自然休息状态）
definition: the natural state of rest in which your eyes are closed, your body is not active, and your mind is not conscious
example: I need to get some sleep.

translation: 睡觉（闭眼休息，身体和精神不活跃）
definition: to rest with your eyes closed and your mind and body not active
example: Let her sleep―it'll do her good.

translation: 薄片，切片（从较大部分切下的薄平片，如面包、肉、蛋糕片）
definition: a thin flat piece of bread, meat, cheese, etc. that has been cut off a larger piece; a piece of cake that has been cut from a larger cake
example: Cut the meat into thin slices.

translation: 切片（将某物切成薄片）
definition: to cut something into slices
example: to slice (up) onions

translation: 幻灯片（电子演示文稿的一页，通常在屏幕上观看或投影）
definition: one page of an electronic presentation, that may contain text and images, that is usually viewed on a computer screen or projected onto a larger screen
example: Here's a slide showing target markets.

translation: 滑动（在光滑或湿润表面上轻松移动；使之滑动）
definition: to move easily over a smooth or wet surface; to make something move in this way
example: As I turned left on a bend, my car started to slide.

translation: 轻微的（程度非常小的）
definition: very small in degree
example: a slight increase/change/difference

translation: 稍微（有一点）
definition: a little
example: a slightly different version

translation: 滑倒（因意外在短距离内滑动导致摔倒或几乎摔倒）
definition: to slide a short distance by accident so that you fall or nearly fall
example: She slipped and landed flat on her back.

translation: 口号（易记的词或短语，如政党或广告中使用以吸引注意）
definition: a word or phrase that is easy to remember, used for example by a political party or in advertising to attract people’s attention or to suggest an idea quickly
example: an advertising slogan

translation: 斜坡，坡度（倾斜的表面或土地）
definition: a surface or piece of land that slopes (= is higher at one end than the other)
example: on a slope, The town is built on a slope.

translation: 倾斜（处于一个角度，使一端高于另一端）
definition: to be at an angle so that it is higher at one end than the other
example: a sloping roof

translation: 槽，狭缝（放入或嵌入某物的狭长开口）
definition: a long, narrow opening, into which you put or fit something
example: to put some coins in the slot

translation: 慢的（移动、行动不快的；耗时长的）
definition: not moving, acting or done quickly; taking a long time; not fast
example: a slow pace/speed

translation: 变慢（以更慢的速度行进或使之变慢）
definition: to go or to make something/somebody go at a slower speed or be less active
example: Economic growth has slowed a little.

translation: 缓慢地（以慢速；不快地）
definition: at a slow speed; not quickly
example: to move/walk/turn slowly

translation: 小的（在尺寸、数量、程度等方面不大的）
definition: not large in size, number, degree, amount, etc.
example: a small town/village/community

translation: 时髦的，整洁的（看起来干净整洁的；穿着入时的）
definition: looking clean and neat; well dressed in fashionable and/or formal clothes
example: I have to be smart for work.

translation: 智能手机（也具备电脑功能――如应用和网络――的手机）
definition: a mobile phone that also has some of the functions of a computer, for example the facility to use apps and the internet
example: You can use your smartphone to access the internet.

translation: 撞碎，粉碎（猛烈且响亮地破碎成许多碎片；使之粉碎）
definition: to break something, or to be broken, violently and noisily into many pieces
example: Several windows had been smashed.

translation: 气味（人或动物通过鼻子感知的特质）
definition: the quality of something that people and animals sense through their noses
example: a sweet/pleasant smell

translation: 闻起来（具有某种特定的气味）
definition: to have a particular smell
example: + adj., The room smelt damp.

translation: 微笑（高兴或觉得滑稽时嘴角上扬的面部表情）
definition: the expression that you have on your face when you are happy or you think something is funny, in which the corners of your mouth turn upwards
example: a broad/warm/bright/slight smile

translation: 微笑（面部露出笑容）
definition: to make a smile appear on your face
example: to smile slightly/broadly

translation: 烟（物体燃烧产生的灰、白或黑色的气体）
definition: the grey, white or black gas that is produced by something burning
example: cigarette/tobacco smoke

translation: 吸烟（吸入香烟等的烟雾并吐出）
definition: to take smoke from a cigarette, pipe, etc. into your mouth and let it out again
example: Do you mind if I smoke?

translation: 吸烟（吸烟的活动或习惯）
definition: the activity or habit of smoking cigarettes, etc.
example: No Smoking (= for example, on a notice)

translation: 光滑的（完全平整的，没有粗糙区域或孔洞）
definition: completely flat and even, without any rough areas or holes
example: the smooth surface of the metal

translation: 蛇（长而细、无足的爬行动物，有些有毒）
definition: a reptile with a very long thin body and no legs. There are many types of snake, some of which are poisonous.
example: a snake coiled up in the grass

translation: 啪地折断（发出尖锐响声并突然断开；以此方式变断）
definition: to break something suddenly with a sharp noise; to be broken in this way
example: snap something, The wind had snapped the tree in two.

translation: 雪（寒冷天气从天空落下的白色冻水薄片）
definition: small soft white pieces (called flakes) of frozen water that fall from the sky in cold weather; this substance when it is lying on the ground
example: Snow was falling heavily.

translation: 下雪（雪从天空落下）
definition: when it snows, snow falls from the sky
example: It's been snowing heavily all day.

translation: 那么（到如此大的程度）
definition: to such a great degree
example: Don't look so angry.

translation: 所以（用于说明某事的原因）
definition: used to show the reason for something
example: It was still painful, so I went to see a doctor.

translation: 所谓的（用于表示你认为用于描述某人/某物的词语不恰当）
definition: used to show that you do not think that the word or phrase that is being used to describe somebody/something is appropriate
example: the opinion of a so-called ‘expert’

translation: 浸泡（将某物放入液体一段时间使其湿透；变湿透）
definition: to put something in liquid for a time so that it becomes completely wet; to become completely wet in this way
example: soak something (in something), I usually soak the beans overnight.

translation: 肥皂（洗涤身体时随水使用的物质）
definition: a substance that you use with water for washing your body
example: Wash the affected area with soap and water.

translation: 猛增，翱翔（某物的价值、数量或水平极快地上升）
definition: if the value, amount or level of something soars, it rises very quickly
example: soaring costs/prices/temperatures

translation: 足球（两队各11名球员、将圆球踢入对方球门的比赛）
definition: a game played by two teams of 11 players, using a round ball which players kick up and down the playing field. Teams try to kick the ball into the other team’s goal.
example: I played soccer when I was younger.

translation: 社交的（与人际交往活动相关的）
definition: connected with activities in which people meet each other for pleasure
example: She has a busy social life.

translation: 社会主义的（与社会主义相关的）
definition: connected with socialism
example: socialist beliefs

translation: 社会（居住在社区中的广大民众）
definition: people in general, living together in communities
example: She believes that the arts benefit society as a whole.

translation: 袜子（穿在脚和脚踝上的衣物，通常在鞋内穿）
definition: a piece of clothing that is worn over the foot, ankle and lower part of the leg, especially inside a shoe
example: a pair of socks

translation: 柔软的（被按压时易改变形状的；不僵硬的）
definition: changing shape easily when pressed; not stiff or hard
example: soft margarine

translation: 软件（电脑用于执行特定任务的程序）
definition: the programs used by a computer for doing particular jobs
example: management/editing software

translation: 土壤（植物、树木生长的地球表层）
definition: the top layer of the earth in which plants, trees, etc. grow
example: instruments for measuring soil moisture

translation: 太阳的（属于或与太阳相关的）
definition: of or connected with the sun
example: solar radiation

translation: 士兵（军队成员，尤指非军官成员）
definition: a member of an army, especially one who is not an officer
example: They visited the graves of US soldiers killed in the First World War.

translation: 唯一的（唯一的；单人的）
definition: only; single
example: the sole surviving member of the family

translation: 唯一地（仅仅；不涉及他人/他物地）
definition: only; not involving somebody/something else
example: She was motivated solely by self-interest.

translation: 初级律师（准备法律文件、提供法律建议并在某些法庭发言的律师）
definition: a lawyer who prepares legal documents, for example for the sale of land or buildings, advises people on legal matters, and can speak for them in some courts of law
example: Her first step was to contact a solicitor for advice.

translation: 固体的（硬的；非液体或气体的）
definition: hard; not in the form of a liquid or gas
example: The planet Jupiter may have no solid surface at all.

translation: 固体（固体物质或物体，非液体或气体）
definition: a substance or an object that is solid, not a liquid or a gas
example: liquids and solids

translation: 团结（因情感、观点、目标一致而对他人的支持）
definition: support by one person or group of people for another because they share feelings, opinions, aims, etc.
example: community solidarity

translation: 单独的（由一人独自完成且无他人帮助的）
definition: done by one person alone, without anyone helping them
example: his first solo flight

translation: 独奏，独舞（仅由一人表演的音乐、舞蹈或娱乐节目）
definition: a piece of music, dance or entertainment performed by only one person
example: The song features an extended guitar solo.

translation: 解决方案（解决问题或处理困难局面的方式）
definition: a way of solving a problem or dealing with a difficult situation
example: Attempts to find a solution have failed.

translation: 解决（找出处理问题或困难局面的方式）
definition: to find a way of dealing with a problem or difficult situation
example: Attempts are being made to solve the problem of waste disposal.

translation: 一些（用于不可数或复数名词，表示未给具体数额的“一些”）
definition: used with uncountable nouns or plural countable nouns to mean ‘an amount of’ or ‘a number of’, when the amount or number is not given
example: There's some milk in the fridge.

translation: 一些（指代未给具体数额的一些人或物）
definition: used to refer to an amount of something or a number of people or things when the amount or number is not given
example: Some disapprove of the idea.

translation: 某人（未指名道姓的人）
definition: a person who is not known or mentioned by name
example: Somebody should have told me.

translation: 以某种方式（以一种不为人知或不确定的方式）
definition: in a way that is not known or certain
example: We must stop him from seeing her somehow.

translation: 某人（未指名道姓的人）
definition: a person who is not known or mentioned by name
example: There's someone at the door.

translation: 某事（未指名道姓的事物）
definition: a thing that is not known or mentioned by name
example: We stopped for something to eat.

translation: 在某时（在将来或过去某个不确定的时间）
definition: at a time that you do not know exactly or has not yet been decided
example: I saw him sometime last summer.

translation: 有时（偶尔而非始终）
definition: occasionally rather than all of the time
example: Sometimes I go by car.

translation: 稍微，有点（在某种程度上）
definition: to some degree
example: somewhat different/similar

translation: 在某处（在一个不确定或未指名的地方）
definition: in, at or to a place that you do not know or do not mention by name
example: I read somewhere that she refuses to do interviews.

translation: 某个地方（一个不确定或未指名的地方）
definition: a place that you do not know or do not mention by name
example: We need to find somewhere to live.

translation: 儿子（男性的孩子）
definition: a person’s male child
example: their four-year-old son

translation: 歌曲（带有歌词的简短乐曲）
definition: a short piece of music with words that you sing
example: a love/pop/rock song

translation: 很快（从现在起很短时间内；某事发生后不久）
definition: in a short time from now; a short time after something else has happened
example: She sold the house soon after her husband died.

translation: 复杂的，高级的（在运作或呈现方式上精巧复杂的）
definition: clever and complicated in the way that it works or is presented
example: highly sophisticated computer systems

translation: 难过的，遗憾的（对已做之事感到悲伤或羞愧）
definition: feeling sad and ashamed about something that has been done
example: sorry about something, We're very sorry about the damage to your car.
