translation: 抱歉（用于道歉时）
definition: used when you are apologizing for something
example: Sorry I'm late!

translation: 种类，类别（在某方面相似的一组人或物）
definition: a group or type of people or things that are similar in a particular way
example: sort of somebody/something, ‘What sort of music do you like?’ ‘Oh, all sorts.’

translation: 分类，整理（根据类型等将事物分组或按序排列；将一类与他类分开）
definition: to arrange things in groups or in a particular order according to their type, etc.; to separate things of one type from others
example: sort something, I started at the bottom, answering phones and sorting the mail.

translation: 灵魂（人的精神部分，被认为死后依然存在）
definition: the spiritual part of a person, believed to exist after death
example: He believed his immortal soul was in peril.

translation: 明智的，可靠的（理智的；可信赖且可能产生好结果的）
definition: sensible; that you can rely on and that will probably give good results
example: He's a person of very sound judgement.

translation: 声音（能听到的响声）
definition: something that you can hear
example: a loud/soft/faint sound

translation: 听起来（听起来或读起来给出某种印象）
definition: to give a particular impression when heard or read about
example: + adj., to sound good/great/right/interesting

translation: 汤（通过加水煮肉、菜等制成的液体食物）
definition: a liquid food made by boiling meat, vegetables, etc. in water, often eaten as the first course of a meal
example: a bowl/cup of soup

translation: 来源，源头（获得某物的地点、人或事物）
definition: a place, person or thing that you get something from
example: renewable energy sources

translation: 南方的（在南方或向南的）
definition: in or towards the south
example: South Wales

translation: 向南（朝向南方）
definition: towards the south
example: This room faces south.

translation: 南方（看日出时在你右侧的方向；罗盘四个主要点之一）
definition: the direction that is on your right when you watch the sun rise; one of the four main points of the compass
example: Which way is south?

translation: 南方的（位于南方或面向南方的；与南方地区相关的）
definition: located in the south or facing south; connected with or typical of the south part of the world or a region
example: the southern slopes of the mountains

translation: 主权（统治国家的完全权力）
definition: complete power to govern a country
example: The country claimed sovereignty over the island.

translation: 太空（地球大气层以外的、有星辰存在的区域）
definition: the area outside the earth’s atmosphere where all the other planets and stars are
example: in space, Valentina Tereshkova was the first woman in space.

translation: 垃圾邮件（未经请求通过电邮发送的广告材料）
definition: advertising material sent by email to people who have not asked for it; advertising material on the internet that is not wanted
example: to send/block spam

translation: 跨度，时段（某事持续的时间长度）
definition: the length of time that something lasts or is able to continue
example: I worked with him over a span of six years.

translation: 跨越，持续（持续贯穿一段时间或覆盖其全部）
definition: to last all through a period of time or to cover the whole of it
example: His acting career spanned 55 years.

translation: 空闲的（可供支配而非工作的，如空闲时间）
definition: available to do what you want with rather than work
example: He's studying music in his spare time.

translation: 腾出，抽出（拨出时间或金钱给他人或某事，尤指费力做到）
definition: to make something such as time or money available to somebody or for something, especially when it requires an effort for you to do this
example: spare something/somebody, I'd love to have a break, but I can't spare the time just now.

translation: 引发，触发（导致某事开始或发展，尤指突然引发）
definition: to cause something to start or develop, especially suddenly
example: spark something, The proposal would spark a storm of protest around the country.

translation: 说话，谈话（就某事与某人交谈）
definition: to talk to somebody about something; to have a conversation with somebody
example: speak to somebody, The President refused to speak to reporters.

translation: 发言者，演说者（进行演说或讲座的人）
definition: a person who gives a talk or makes a speech
example: He was a guest speaker at the conference.

translation: 特别的（非普通的；与平常不同的）
definition: not ordinary or usual; different from what is normal
example: The school will only allow this in special circumstances.

translation: 专家的，专门的（在特定领域具有或涉及专门知识技能的）
definition: having or involving expert knowledge of a particular area of work, study or medicine
example: specialist knowledge/training/skills

translation: 专家（特定领域的专家）
definition: a person who is an expert in a particular area of work or study
example: specialist in something, a specialist in Japanese history

translation: 专门研究，专攻（成为特定领域的专家；在某方面投入更多时间）
definition: to become an expert in a particular area of work, study or business; to spend more time on one area of work, etc. than on others
example: Many students prefer not to specialize too soon.

translation: 专门的，专业的（为特定目的或领域设计开发的）
definition: designed or developed for a particular purpose or area of knowledge
example: specialized equipment

translation: 物种（能相互交配并产生健康后代的一群生物）
definition: a group into which animals, plants, etc. that are able to have sex with each other and produce healthy young are divided, smaller than a genus and identified by a Latin name
example: a conservation area for endangered species

translation: 具体的，特定的（仅与一特定事物相关的）
definition: connected with one particular thing only
example: specific needs/requirements

translation: 具体地，专门地（仅与一特定事物相关或为此设计的）
definition: connected with or intended for one particular thing only
example: liquid vitamins specifically designed for children

translation: 规格，说明书（关于某物如何设计或制造的详细描述）
definition: a detailed description of how something is, or should be, designed or made
example: the technical specifications of the new model (= of car)

translation: 指定，具体说明（通过给出精确度量、时间、指令等说明某事）
definition: to state something, especially by giving an exact measurement, time, exact instructions, etc.
example: specify something, Remember to specify your size when ordering clothes.

translation: 标本，样本（能显示同类事物全貌的少量物质）
definition: a small amount of something that shows what the rest of it is like
example: Astronauts have brought back specimens of rock from the moon.

translation: 眼镜（戴在鼻梁和耳朵上的矫正视力或保护眼睛的镜片）
definition: two lenses in a frame that rests on the nose and ears. People wear spectacles in order to be able to see better or to protect their eyes from bright light.
example: a pair of spectacles

translation: 壮观的（给人留下深刻印象的）
definition: very impressive
example: The coastal road has spectacular scenery.

translation: 观众（观看活动――尤指体育赛事――的人）
definition: a person who is watching an event, especially a sports event
example: The new football stadium will hold 75?000 spectators.

translation: 光谱，光谱（按波长排列的彩色光带，如彩虹）
definition: a band of coloured lights in order of their wavelengths, as seen in a rainbow and into which light may be separated
example: A spectrum is formed by a ray of light passing through a prism.

translation: 推测，猜测（在不了解所有细节的情况下形成观点）
definition: to form an opinion about something without knowing all the details or facts
example: speculate (about/on/as to something), We all speculated about the reasons for her resignation.

translation: 推测，投机（在不了解所有事实的情况下对已发生或可能发生之事的观点形成）
definition: the act of forming opinions about what has happened or what might happen without knowing all the facts
example: His private life is the subject of much speculation.

translation: 演说，说话能力（向听众做的正式讲话；或说话的能力）
definition: a formal talk that a person gives to an audience
example: Several people made speeches at the wedding.

translation: 速度（人或物移动或旅行的速率）
definition: the rate at which somebody/something moves or travels

translation: 快速移动（快速移动）
definition: to move along quickly

translation: 一段时期（某事持续的短时间）
definition: a short period of time during which something lasts
example: We had a spell of warm weather in April.

translation: 拼写（按正确顺序说出或写出单词的字母）
definition: to say or write the letters of a word in the correct order
example: How do you spell your surname?

translation: 拼写（正确组合字母构成单词的行为；这种能力）
definition: the act of forming words correctly from individual letters; the ability to do this
example: the differences between British and American spelling

translation: 花费，度过（花钱购买商品服务；或度过时间）
definition: to give money to pay for goods, services, etc.
example: spend something, I've spent all my money already.

translation: 开支，支出（政府、组织或个人花费的金额）
definition: the amount of money that is spent by a government, an organization or a person
example: to increase/cut/reduce spending

translation: 球体，范围（表面各点离中心距离相等的立体图形；或活动范围）
definition: a solid figure that is completely round, with every point on its surface at an equal distance from the centre
example: The Earth is not a perfect sphere.

translation: 香料，辛香料（来自植物的、用于烹饪的带强味粉末或种子）
definition: one of the various types of powder or seed that come from plants and are used in cooking. Spices have a strong taste and smell.
example: common spices such as ginger and cinnamon

translation: 辛辣的（因加入香料而具有强烈味道的）
definition: having a strong taste because spices have been added to it
example: I don't like spicy food.

translation: 蜘蛛（有八条细腿的小生物，常结网捕食）
definition: a small creature with eight thin legs. Many spiders spin webs to catch insects for food.
example: a poisonous spider

translation: 溢出，洒出（因意外从容器边缘流出；使之流出）
definition: to flow over the edge of a container by accident; to make liquid do this
example: Water had spilled out of the bucket onto the floor.

translation: 旋转，旋转（极快的转动动作）
definition: a very fast turning movement
example: Only in the last 50 years have we had clocks accurate enough to measure changes in the earth's spin.

translation: 旋转（快速地转圈；使之转动）
definition: to turn round and round quickly; to make something do this
example: (+ adv./prep.), The plane was spinning out of control.

translation: 脊柱（背部中间连接在一起的一行小骨头）
definition: the row of small bones that are connected together down the middle of the back
example: A shiver went down my spine.

translation: 精神，灵魂（人的思想、情感和性格而非身体的部分）
definition: the part of a person that includes their mind, feelings and character rather than their body
example: You are underestimating the power of the human spirit to overcome difficulties.

translation: 精神的，心灵的（与人类精神而非身体或物质相关的）
definition: connected with the human spirit, rather than the body or physical things
example: a spiritual experience

translation: 恶意，怨恨（想伤害或使人不快的感觉）
definition: a feeling of wanting to hurt or upset somebody
example: out of spite, I'm sure he only said it out of spite.

translation: 分裂，分歧（导致群体分开或个人脱离的分歧）
definition: an argument or disagreement that divides a group of people or makes somebody separate from somebody else
example: Ten years after their acrimonious split, the band has reformed.

translation: 分裂，分开（分成两个或多个部分；使之分开）
definition: to divide, or to make something divide, into two or more parts
example: split something, He was a member of the team that split the atom in 1932.

translation: 破坏，宠坏（使好事变坏、变不快等；或溺爱孩子）
definition: to change something good into something bad, unpleasant, etc.
example: Our camping trip was spoilt by bad weather.

translation: 口语的（涉及说话而非书写的；口头表达的）
definition: involving speaking rather than writing; expressed in speech rather than in writing
example: spoken English

translation: 发言人（代表群体或组织讲话的人）
definition: a person who speaks for a group or an organization
example: a police spokesman

translation: 发言人（代表群体或组织讲话的人）
definition: a person who speaks for a group or an organization
example: a council spokesperson

translation: 女发言人（代表群体或组织讲话的女性）
definition: a woman who speaks for a group or an organization
example: a government spokeswoman

translation: 赞助者（为节目、活动等付费以换取广告权利的个人或公司）
definition: a person or company that pays for a radio or television programme, or for a concert or sporting event, usually in return for advertising
example: The programme is funded by a number of corporate sponsors.

translation: 赞助（作为广告方式为特定活动等付费）
definition: to pay the costs of a particular event, programme, etc. as a way of advertising
example: Sports events are no longer sponsored by the tobacco industry.

translation: 赞助，资助（来自赞助者的财务支持）
definition: financial support from a sponsor
example: a $50 million sponsorship deal

translation: 勺子（带柄且末端有浅碗状部的搅拌、进食工具）
definition: a tool that has a handle with a shallow bowl at the end, used for mixing, serving and eating food
example: a plastic/metal spoon

translation: 体育（为了快乐进行的、需要体力或技能的、有规则的活动）
definition: activity that you do for pleasure and that needs physical effort or skill, usually done in a special area and according to fixed rules
example: There are excellent facilities for sport and recreation.

translation: 体育的（与体育运动相关的）
definition: connected with sports
example: a major sporting event

translation: 斑点（颜色或感觉与周围表面不同的小圆区域）
definition: a small round area that has a different colour or feels different from the surface it is on
example: Which has spots, the leopard or the tiger?

translation: 发现，看出（看见或注意到某人/某事，尤指突然或在不易发现时）
definition: to see or notice a person or thing, especially suddenly or when it is not easy to do so
example: spot somebody/something, Can you spot the difference between these two pictures?

translation: 聚光灯（能指向特定位置或人的单束极强光线）
definition: a light with a single, very bright beam that can be directed at a particular place or person, especially a performer on the stage
example: The room was lit by spotlights.

translation: 配偶（丈夫或妻子）
definition: a husband or wife
example: Fill in your spouse’s name here.

translation: 传播，扩展（事物数量、范围的增加或影响区域的扩大）
definition: an increase in the amount or number of something that there is, or in the area that is affected by something
example: measures to halt the spread of the disease

translation: 传播，散布（影响越来越多的人，或被越来越多的人知晓）
definition: to affect or make something affect, be known by, or be used by more and more people
example: The news had spread and was causing great excitement.

translation: 春天（冬夏之间植物开始生长的季节）
definition: the season between winter and summer when plants begin to grow
example: The following spring, the three artists travelled to California.

translation: 跳跃，弹起（向特定方向突然且快速地移动）
definition: to move suddenly and with one quick movement in a particular direction
example: The cat crouched ready to spring.

translation: 间谍（试图获取他国或组织秘密信息的人，尤指受雇于政府警察者）
definition: a person who tries to get secret information about another country, organization or person, especially somebody who is employed by a government or the police
example: He was denounced as a foreign spy.

translation: 从事间谍活动（收集关于他国、组织或个人的秘密信息）
definition: to collect secret information about another country, organization or person
example: He spied for his government for more than ten years.

translation: 小组，小队（警察部队中处理特定类型犯罪的部门）
definition: a section of a police force that deals with a particular type of crime
example: the drugs/fraud/bomb/riot squad

translation: 正方形的，平方的（有四条相等直边且角为90度的）
definition: having four straight equal sides and four angles of 90°
example: a square room

translation: 正方形，广场（有四条相等直边且角为90度的形状；广场）
definition: a shape with four straight sides of equal length and four angles of 90°; a piece of something that has this shape
example: First break the chocolate into squares.

translation: 挤，捏（用力按压，尤指用手指）
definition: to press something, especially with your fingers
example: to squeeze a tube of toothpaste

translation: 刺，戳（将锋利尖锐物――如刀――刺入人体导致伤亡）
definition: to push a sharp, pointed object, especially a knife, into somebody, killing or injuring them
example: He was stabbed to death in a racist attack.

translation: 稳定性（稳固、不改变或不被打乱的品质或状态）
definition: the quality or state of being steady and not changing or being upset in any way (= the quality of being stable)
example: political/economic/social stability

translation: 稳定（变得或使之变得稳固且不易改变）
definition: to become or to make something become steady and unlikely to change; to make something stable
example: The patient's condition stabilized.

translation: 稳定的（固定的或稳固的；不易移动、改变或失败的）
definition: fixed or steady; not likely to move, change or fail
example: The patient's condition is stable (= it is not getting worse).

translation: 体育场（由看台环绕的大型运动场）
definition: a large sports ground surrounded by rows of seats and usually other buildings
example: a football/sports stadium

translation: 全体员工（组织中雇佣的所有工作人员的总称）
definition: all the workers employed in an organization considered as a group
example: medical/nursing/teaching/coaching staff

translation: 阶段（发展或进步过程中的一段时间或状态）
definition: a period or state that something/somebody passes through while developing or making progress
example: at… stage, I can't make a decision at this stage.

translation: 上演，举行（组织并呈现戏剧、活动或展览供人观看）
definition: to organize and present a play or an event for people to see
example: to stage a play/an event/an exhibition

translation: 楼梯（建筑内两层楼之间的台阶）
definition: a set of steps built between two floors inside a building
example: We had to carry the piano up three flights of stairs.

translation: 股份，赌注（在公司中投入的资金；或赌注）
definition: money that somebody invests in a company
example: a 20 per cent stake in the business

translation: 摊位（市场上卖东西的桌子或前部开敞的小铺子）
definition: a table or small shop with an open front that people sell things from, especially at a market
example: He works on a market stall in the Square.

translation: 邮票（贴在信封或包裹上表示已付邮费的小纸片）
definition: a small piece of paper with a design on it that you buy and stick on an envelope or a package before you post it
example: a 67p stamp

translation: 立场（某人对某事所持并公开表达的观点）
definition: the opinions that somebody has about something and expresses publicly
example: What is the newspaper's stance on the war?

translation: 立场，态度（向他人明确表达的对某事的态度或观点）
definition: an attitude towards something or an opinion that you make clear to people
example: He has avoided taking a firm stand.

translation: 站立（双脚着地，身体处于垂直位置）
definition: to be on your feet; to be in a vertical position
example: She was too weak to stand.

translation: 标准的（普通的或正常的，而非特殊的）
definition: average or normal rather than having special or unusual features
example: the standard rate of tax (= paid by everyone)

translation: 标准，水平（人们认为可接受的质量水平）
definition: a level of quality, especially one that people think is acceptable
example: There has been a fall in living standards.

translation: 站立的（从站立姿势而非坐姿或跑姿进行的）
definition: done from a position in which you are standing rather than sitting or running
example: a standing jump/start

translation: 星星（天空中发光的恒星）
definition: a large ball of burning gas in space that we see as a point of light in the sky at night
example: There was a big moon and hundreds of stars were shining overhead.

translation: 主演（在电影、戏剧中担任主角）
definition: to have one of the main parts in a film, play, etc.
example: star in something, He starred in that movie about the crazy professor.

translation: 凝视（长时间盯着某人/某物看）
definition: to look at somebody/something for a long time
example: I screamed and everyone stared.

translation: 严酷的，赤裸裸的（令人不快的；真实的且无法回避的）
definition: unpleasant; real, and impossible to avoid
example: The author paints a stark picture of life in a prison camp.

translation: 开始，开端（某事开始的点）
definition: the point at which something begins
example: If we don't hurry, we'll miss the start.

translation: 开始（开始做或使用某事）
definition: to begin doing or using something
example: start (something), I start work at nine.

translation: 挨饿（因食物不足而受苦或死亡；使之挨饿）
definition: to suffer or die because you do not have enough food to eat; to make somebody suffer or die in this way
example: The animals were left to starve to death.

translation: 国家的，州的（由政府提供或控制的）
definition: provided or controlled by the government of a country
example: state officials/agencies

translation: 国家，州（作为一个有组织的政治共同体的国家或地区）
definition: a country considered as an organized political community controlled by one government
example: the Baltic States

translation: 陈述，声明（正式地书写或说出某事，尤指仔细且清晰地）
definition: to formally write or say something, especially in a careful and clear way
example: state something, He has already stated his intention to run for election.

translation: 陈述，声明（给出信息或观点的言语或文字）
definition: something that you say or write that gives information or an opinion
example: Are the following statements true or false?

translation: 车站，站（火车停靠供乘客上下车的地方；相关建筑）
definition: a place where trains stop so that passengers can get on and off; the buildings connected with this
example: the main station

translation: 统计数据（以数字显示的收集到的信息）
definition: a collection of information shown in numbers
example: Analysis of crime statistics showed high levels of violent crime within the area.

translation: 统计的（与统计学相关的或基于统计学的）
definition: connected with or based on statistics
example: statistical analysis

translation: 雕像（由石头、金属等制成的通常与真人同大或更大的形象）
definition: a figure of a person or an animal in stone, metal, etc., usually the same size as in real life or larger
example: a bronze/marble statue

translation: 身份，地位（个人、群体或国家在法律上的位置）
definition: the legal position of a person, group or country
example: They were granted refugee status.

translation: 停留，访问（停留的一段时间；访问）
definition: a period of staying; a visit
example: I enjoyed my stay in Prague.

translation: 停留（继续在某处而不离开）
definition: to continue to be in a particular place for a period of time without moving away
example: + adv./prep., Stay there and don't move!

translation: 稳定地（逐渐且均匀规律地）
definition: gradually and in an even and regular way
example: The company's exports have been increasing steadily.

translation: 稳定的（逐渐且均匀规律地发展、增长的）
definition: developing, growing, etc. gradually and in an even and regular way
example: We've had five years of steady economic growth.

translation: 偷窃（未经许可且不打算归还或付钱地拿走他人财物）
definition: to take something from a person, shop, etc. without permission and without intending to return it or pay for it
example: I'll report you to the police if I catch you stealing again.

translation: 蒸汽（水沸腾时变成的热气）
definition: the hot gas that water changes into when it boils
example: Steam rose from the boiling kettle.

translation: 钢，钢铁（铁和碳混合制成的坚硬强韧金属）
definition: a strong, hard metal that is made of a mixture of iron and carbon
example: the iron and steel industry

translation: 陡峭的（上升或下降极快而非逐渐的）
definition: rising or falling quickly, not gradually
example: a steep hill/slope

translation: 驾驶，掌舵（控制船、车等移动的方向）
definition: to control the direction in which a boat, car, etc. moves
example: He steered the boat into the harbour.

translation: 茎，干（植物在地上的长窄部分，叶花由此长出）
definition: the main long, thin part of a plant above the ground from which the leaves or flowers grow; a smaller part that grows from this and supports flowers or leaves
example: long, trailing stems of ivy

translation: 阻止，遏制（停止流动事物的蔓延或增加）
definition: to stop something that is flowing from spreading or increasing
example: The cut was bandaged to stem the bleeding.

translation: 步骤，台阶（为了实现目标而采取的一系列行动之一；或台阶）
definition: one of a series of things that you do in order to achieve something
example: We are taking steps to prevent pollution.

translation: 迈步，跨步（举起脚向特定方向移动；或移动一短段距离）
definition: to lift your foot and move it in a particular direction or put it on or in something; to move a short distance
example: to step onto/off a bus

translation: 刻板印象（许多人对某类人或物的固定看法，往往非事实且具伤害性）
definition: a fixed idea or image that many people have of a particular type of person or thing, but which is often not true in reality and may cause hurt and offence
example: cultural/gender/racial stereotypes

translation: 木棍，枝条（从树上落下或折断的细木块）
definition: a thin piece of wood that has fallen or been broken from a tree
example: We collected dry sticks to start a fire.

translation: 粘贴，粘住（通常用粘性物质将一物固定在另一物上；粘住）
definition: to fix something to something else, usually with a sticky substance; to become fixed to something in this way
example: stick something + adv./prep., He stuck a stamp on the envelope.

translation: 黏的（由粘性物质制成或覆盖其上的）
definition: made of or covered in a substance that sticks to things that touch it
example: sticky fingers covered in jam

translation: 僵硬的（难以弯曲或移动的）
definition: difficult to bend or move
example: a sheet of stiff black cardboard

translation: 静止的（不移动的；平静且安静的）
definition: not moving; calm and quiet
example: A fallen tree floated in the still water.

translation: 仍然（持续到特定时间点且未结束）
definition: continuing until a particular point in time and not finishing
example: I am very happy that you all are still alive and well.

translation: 刺激，激励（使某事发展或变得更活跃；鼓励）
definition: to make something develop or become more active; to encourage something
example: The exhibition has stimulated interest in her work.

translation: 刺激物（帮助某人/某事更好或更快发展的事物）
definition: something that helps somebody/something to develop better or more quickly
example: stimulus for something, Books provide children with ideas and a stimulus for play.

translation: 搅拌（使用勺子等搅动液体使之完全混合）
definition: to move a liquid or substance around, using a spoon or something similar, in order to mix it completely
example: stir something, She stirred her tea.

translation: 库存（商店中可供出售的商品供应）
definition: a supply of goods that is available for sale in a shop
example: We have a fast turnover of stock.

translation: 胃（进食后食物进入的体内器官）
definition: the organ inside the body where food goes when you eat it
example: stomach pains/cramps

translation: 石头（在地下发现的坚硬固体矿物质，常用于建筑）
definition: a hard solid mineral substance that is found in the ground, often used for building
example: Most of the houses are built of stone.

translation: 站，车站（公交、火车定期停靠供乘客上下车的地方）
definition: a place where a bus or train stops regularly for passengers to get on or off
example: I get off at the next stop.

translation: 停止，停止（不再移动；使人/物不再移动）
definition: to no longer move; to make somebody/something no longer move
example: The car stopped at the traffic lights.

translation: 储存（将某物存放在特定地方直至需要的行为；储存空间）
definition: the process of keeping something in a particular place until it is needed; the space where things can be kept
example: tables that fold flat for storage

translation: 商店（出售多种不同商品的大型商店）
definition: a large shop that sells many different types of goods
example: It's available at London's three biggest stores.

translation: 储存（将某物放在某处保留以备后用）
definition: to put something somewhere and keep it there to use later
example: store something, We do not have adequate space to store these documents.

translation: 暴风雨（伴有强风和雨、常有雷电的恶劣天气）
definition: very bad weather with strong winds and rain, and often thunder and lightning
example: fierce/heavy/severe/violent storms

translation: 故事（为了娱乐而虚构的事件和人物描述）
definition: a description of events and people that the writer or speaker has invented in order to entertain people
example: a tragic love story

translation: 直的（无弯曲的；仅朝一个方向的）
definition: without a bend or curve; going in one direction only
example: a straight road

translation: 直地（不弯曲地；成直线地）
definition: not in a curve or at an angle; in a straight line
example: Keep straight on for two miles.

translation: 简单的，直接的（易于执行或理解的；不复杂的）
definition: easy to do or to understand; not complicated
example: It's a relatively straightforward process.

translation: 压力，负担（由于巨大需求对系统或关系产生的压力）
definition: pressure on a system or relationship because great demands are being placed on it
example: The transport service cannot cope with the strain of so many additional passengers.

translation: 股，缕（单根细长的线、丝、头发等）
definition: a single thin piece of thread, wire, hair, etc.
example: He pulled at a loose strand of wool in his sweater.

translation: 奇怪的（不寻常或令人惊讶的，尤指难以理解的）
definition: unusual or surprising, especially in a way that is difficult to understand
example: A strange thing happened this morning.

translation: 陌生人（你不认识的人）
definition: a person that you do not know
example: There was a complete stranger sitting at my desk.

translation: 战略性的（作为旨在实现特定目的或获取优势的计划一部分而进行的）
definition: done as part of a plan that is meant to achieve a particular purpose or to gain an advantage
example: strategic planning

translation: 战略，策略（旨在实现特定目的的计划）
definition: a plan that is intended to achieve a particular purpose
example: the government’s economic strategy

translation: 小溪（狭窄的小河）
definition: a small, narrow river
example: a mountain stream

translation: 街道（城市或城镇中一侧或两侧有建筑的公共道路）
definition: a public road in a city or town that has houses and buildings on one side or both sides
example: along/down/up the street, I was just walking along the street when it happened.

translation: 力量，强度（身体强健的品质）
definition: the quality of being physically strong
example: He pushed against the rock with all his strength.

translation: 加强，增强（变得或使某人/某事更有力或更有效）
definition: to become more powerful or effective; to make somebody/something more powerful or effective
example: Her position in the party has strengthened in recent weeks.

translation: 压力，紧张（因生活问题或事务过多导致的压力或忧虑）
definition: pressure or worry caused by problems in somebody’s life or by having too much to do
example: emotional/mental stress

translation: 重读，强调（说话时对单词或音节加重语气）
definition: to give extra force to a word or syllable when saying it
example: You stress the first syllable in ‘happiness’.

translation: 一段，一段距离（长条状的陆地或水域，尤指长的一段）
definition: an area of land or water, especially a long one
example: a particularly dangerous stretch of road

translation: 拉伸，延伸（通过拉动使之变长、变宽或变松；以此方式变长）
definition: to make something longer, wider or looser, for example by pulling it; to become longer, etc. in this way
example: Is there any way of stretching shoes?

translation: 严格的（必须被精确遵守的）
definition: that must be obeyed exactly
example: strict rules/regulations

translation: 严格地（带着大量的控制和必须遵守的规则）
definition: with a lot of control and rules that must be obeyed
example: She was brought up very strictly.

translation: 罢工（因薪酬等争议而组织的集体停止工作的行为）
definition: a period of time when an organized group of employees of a company stops working because of an argument over pay or conditions
example: the miners'/firefighters'/teachers' strike

translation: 打击，撞击（有力地击打某人/某物）
definition: to hit somebody/something hard or with force
example: strike somebody/something, The ship struck a rock.

translation: 显著的，引人注目的（足够有趣或不寻常以吸引注意力的）
definition: interesting and unusual enough to attract attention
example: a striking feature

translation: 线，绳（用于捆绑的细长材料，由多股纤维拧成）
definition: long, thin material used for tying things together, made of several threads that have been twisted together; a piece of string used to fasten or pull something or keep something in place
example: a piece/length/ball of string

translation: 条，带（纸、金属、布等制成的长窄片）
definition: a long narrow piece of paper, metal, cloth, etc.
example: a strip of material

translation: 脱掉（脱掉自己或他人的全部或大部分衣服）
definition: to take off all or most of your clothes or another person’s clothes
example: I stripped and washed myself all over.

translation: 努力，奋斗（非常努力地去实现某事）
definition: to try very hard to achieve something
example: strive for something, We encourage all members to strive for the highest standards.

translation: 击球（用球棒或球拍击球的动作）
definition: an act of hitting a ball, for example with a bat or racket
example: What a beautiful stroke!

translation: 强壮的（具有很强体力，能举重物或干重活的）
definition: having a lot of physical power so that you can lift heavy weights, do hard physical work, etc.
example: He's strong enough to lift a car!

translation: 强烈地（以展示明确且严肃观点或信念的方式）
definition: in a way that shows definite and serious opinions or beliefs
example: a strongly worded protest

translation: 结构上的（与建筑或组织的构建方式相关的）
definition: connected with the way in which something is built or organized
example: Storms have caused structural damage to hundreds of homes.

translation: 结构（事物各部分连接、排列或组织的方式；特定的排列）
definition: the way in which the parts of something are connected together, arranged or organized; a particular arrangement of parts
example: the structure of the building

translation: 组织，构建（将某事按体系或模式排列组织）
definition: to arrange or organize something into a system or pattern
example: structure something, How well does the teacher structure the lessons?

translation: 斗争（为了获得某物而进行的艰苦战斗，尤指他人阻挠时）
definition: a hard fight in which people try to obtain or achieve something, especially something that somebody else does not want them to have
example: Marx wrote about the class struggle.

translation: 奋斗（在困难或问题重重时非常努力地去做某事）
definition: to try very hard to do something when it is difficult or when there are a lot of problems
example: life as a struggling artist (= one who is very poor)

translation: 学生（在大学或学院学习的人）
definition: a person who is studying at a university or college
example: a college/university student

translation: 工作室，演播室（录制播放节目或录制音乐的房间）
definition: a room where radio or television programmes are recorded and broadcast from, or where music is recorded
example: a television/recording studio

translation: 研究，学习（通过读书或观察世界来学习或获取知识的活动）
definition: the activity of learning or gaining knowledge, either from books or by examining things in the world
example: a room set aside for private study

translation: 学习，研究（花时间通过读书、上大学等了解某一学科）
definition: to spend time learning about a subject by reading, going to college, etc.
example: He sat up very late that night, studying.

translation: 东西，物品（用于指代不具名或名字不重要的物质、材料或物体）
definition: used to refer to a substance, material, group of objects, etc. when you do not know the name, when the name is not important or when it is obvious what you are talking about
example: What's all that sticky stuff on the carpet?

translation: 填充，塞进（将某物紧紧填满空间或容器）
definition: to fill a space or container tightly with something
example: stuff A with B, She had 500 envelopes to stuff with leaflets.

translation: 绊，踉跄（在走或跑时脚碰到某物几乎摔倒）
definition: to hit your foot against something while you are walking or running and almost fall
example: The child stumbled and fell.

translation: 使昏迷，打晕（使人或动物短时间失去知觉，尤指击打头部）
definition: to make a person or an animal unconscious for a short time, especially by hitting them on the head
example: The fall stunned me for a moment.

translation: 极漂亮的，极好的（极具吸引力或令人印象深刻的）
definition: extremely attractive or impressive
example: You look absolutely stunning!

translation: 愚蠢的（表现出缺乏思考或良好判断的）
definition: showing a lack of thought or good judgement
example: a stupid mistake/question/idea

translation: 风格，方式（做某事的特定方式）
definition: the particular way in which something is done
example: a wide range of musical styles

translation: 受制于，易受影响的（很可能受某事影响的，尤指坏事）
definition: likely to be affected by something, especially something bad
example: At this stage these are proposals and are still subject to change.

translation: 主题，题目（正在讨论、描述或处理的事物或人）
definition: a thing or person that is being discussed, described or dealt with
example: subject of something, Walker's work has been the subject of much debate.

translation: 屈服，投降（接受某人已击败你且必须服从其的行为）
definition: the act of accepting that somebody has defeated you and that you must obey them
example: a gesture of submission

translation: 提交，递交（将文件、建议等交给权力机构以便其研究或考虑）
definition: to give a document, proposal, etc. to somebody in authority so that they can study or consider it
example: submit something, to submit an application/a claim/a proposal

translation: 订阅者，用户（定期付钱以接收杂志、报纸或使用在线服务的人）
definition: a person who pays money, usually once a year, to receive regular copies of a magazine or newspaper or have access to it online
example: subscribers to ‘New Scientist’

translation: 订阅，会员费（为了获取服务、成为会员或接收报刊定期支付的款项）
definition: an amount of money that you pay regularly to receive a service, be a member of a club, support a charity or receive regular copies of a newspaper or magazine; the act of paying this money
example: an annual subscription

translation: 随后的，后来的（发生在某事之后或随之而来的）
definition: happening or coming after something else
example: subsequent generations

translation: 随后，后来（在某事发生之后）
definition: afterwards; later; after something else has happened
example: The original interview notes were subsequently lost.

translation: 补贴，补助金（政府或组织为降低服务或商品生产成本而支付的钱）
definition: money that is paid by a government or an organization to reduce the costs of services or of producing goods so that their prices can be kept low
example: agricultural subsidies

translation: 物质（具有特定性质的固体、液体或气体）
definition: a type of solid, liquid or gas that has particular qualities
example: a sticky substance

translation: 大量的，实质性的（在数量、价值或重要性上很大的）
definition: large in amount, value or importance
example: substantial sums of money

translation: 显著地，基本上（非常多地；很大程度上）
definition: very much; a lot
example: The costs have increased substantially.

translation: 替代品，代用品（用于替代通常使用的人或物的人或物）
definition: a person or thing that you use or have instead of the one you normally use or have
example: a meat substitute

translation: 替代（取代他人/他物的位置；使用他人/他物作为替代）
definition: to take the place of somebody/something else; to use somebody/something instead of somebody/something else
example: substitute for somebody/something, Nothing can substitute for the advice your doctor is able to give you.

translation: 替换，换人（用一人或一物代替另一人的行为；或换下场）
definition: an act of using one person or thing in the place of another
example: Two substitutions were made during the game.

translation: 微妙的，精细的（不明显的或不易察觉的）
definition: not very obvious or easy to notice
example: subtle colours/flavours/smells, etc.

translation: 郊区（城市中心以外的居住区域）
definition: an area where people live that is outside the centre of a city
example: a suburb of London

translation: 郊区的（在郊区的或与郊区相关的）
definition: in or connected with a suburb
example: suburban areas

translation: 成功（实现一直在尝试做或获得的事；产生预期的结果）
definition: to achieve something that you have been trying to do or get; to have the result or effect that was intended
example: Our plan succeeded.

translation: 成功（实现想要或一直在尝试的事实）
definition: the fact that you have achieved something that you want and have been trying to do or get
example: The company has achieved considerable success in this market.

translation: 成功的（实现目标的或达到预期效果的）
definition: achieving your aims or what was intended
example: The experiment was entirely successful.

translation: 成功地（以实现目标或达到预期效果的方式）
definition: in a way that achieves your aims or what was intended
example: She had already successfully completed these courses.

translation: 接替，连续（在时间或顺序上相互接续的一系列人或物）
definition: a number of people or things that follow each other in time or order
example: a succession of visitors

translation: 连续的（一个接一个紧接着发生的）
definition: following immediately one after the other
example: This was their fourth successive win.

translation: 继承者，接替者（在他人之后接替其位置或职位的人或物）
definition: a person or thing that comes after somebody/something else and takes their/its place
example: Who's the likely successor to him as party leader?

translation: 如此的，那样的（用于强调某事物的程度极大）
definition: used to emphasize the great degree of something
example: This issue was of such importance that we could not afford to ignore it.

translation: 如此的，那样的（用于强调某事物的程度极大）
definition: used to emphasize the great degree of something
example: This issue was of such importance that we could not afford to ignore it.

translation: 吸，吮（利用唇部肌肉将液体、空气等吸入口中）
definition: to take liquid, air, etc. into your mouth by using the muscles of your lips
example: to suck the juice from an orange

translation: 突然的（快速且出乎意料发生的）
definition: happening or done quickly and unexpectedly
example: News of his sudden and unexpected death came as a great shock.

translation: 突然地（快速且出乎意料地）
definition: quickly and unexpectedly
example: I suddenly realized what I had to do.

translation: 起诉，控告（在法庭上对个人或组织提出索赔，因其言行造成伤害）
definition: to make a claim against a person or an organization in court about something that they have said or done to harm you
example: They threatened to sue if the work was not completed.

translation: 受苦，遭受（受疾病、疼痛、悲伤或匮乏的严重影响）
definition: to be badly affected by a disease, pain, sad feelings, a lack of something, etc.
example: I hate to see animals suffering.

translation: 痛苦，苦难（身体或精神上的疼痛）
definition: physical or mental pain
example: Death finally brought an end to her suffering.

translation: 足够的，充足的（对特定目的而言够用的；达到你所需的）
definition: enough for a particular purpose; as much as you need
example: Allow sufficient time to get there.

translation: 足够地，充分地（对特定目的而言够用地）
definition: enough for a particular purpose; as much as you need
example: The following day she felt sufficiently well to go to work.

translation: 糖（从植物汁液中提取的甜味物质，常为白色或棕色结晶，用于调味）
definition: a sweet substance, often in the form of white or brown crystals, made from the juices of various plants, used in cooking or to make tea, coffee, etc. sweeter
example: Do you take sugar (= have it in your tea, coffee, etc.)?

translation: 建议，提议（提出想法或计划供他人考虑）
definition: to put forward an idea or a plan for other people to think about
example: suggest something, I'd like to suggest a different explanation for the company's decline.

translation: 建议，提议（提及供他人考虑的想法或计划）
definition: an idea or a plan that you mention for somebody else to think about
example: Can I make a suggestion?

translation: 自杀（故意杀死自己的行为）
definition: the act of killing yourself deliberately
example: to commit suicide

translation: 套装，西装（由相同布料制成的一套衣服，包括上衣和长裤/裙子）
definition: a set of clothes made of the same cloth, including a jacket and trousers or a skirt
example: She was wearing a grey business suit.

translation: 适合，相配（对某人方便或有用）
definition: to be convenient or useful for somebody
example: suit somebody/something, If we met at two, would that suit you?

translation: 合适的（对特定目的或场合而言正确或恰当的）
definition: right or appropriate for a particular purpose or occasion
example: a suitable candidate

translation: 套房，套间（一组房间，尤指旅馆中的）
definition: a set of rooms, especially in a hotel
example: a hotel/private/honeymoon suite

translation: 金额，总数（一笔钱的数额）
definition: an amount of money
example: You will be fined the sum of ￡200.

translation: 合计，总结（总计）
总结，概括（给出某事的简短摘要）
definition: to give a summary of something
example: This essay briefly summarizes some of our approaches.

translation: 总结，摘要（给出某事要点而非细节的简短陈述）
definition: a short statement that gives only the main points of something, not the details
example: a news summary

translation: 夏天，夏季（一年中最暖的季节，在春秋之间）
definition: the warmest season of the year, coming between spring and autumn
example: in the summer, We're going away in the summer.

translation: 顶点，巅峰（某事物的最高点，尤指山顶）
definition: the highest point of something, especially the top of a mountain
example: We reached the summit at noon.

translation: 太阳（白天在天空中发光、为地球提供热和光的恒星）
definition: the star that shines in the sky during the day and gives the earth heat and light
example: The sun was shining and birds were singing.

translation: 星期日（周六之后、周一之前的一天，被视为一周的第一天或最后一天）
definition: the day of the week after Saturday and before Monday, thought of as either the first or the last day of the week
example: It's Sunday today, isn't it?

translation: 极好的（极其好的）
definition: extremely good
example: a super meal

translation: 精湛的，极好的（优秀的；质量非常好的）
definition: excellent; of very good quality
example: a superb player

translation: 优越的，较好的（在质量上比他人/他物更好；更伟大的）
definition: better in quality than somebody/something else; greater than somebody/something else
example: vastly superior

translation: 超市（出售食品、饮料和家居用品的大型商店，顾客自选后结账）
definition: a large shop that sells food, drinks and goods used in the home. People choose what they want from the shelves and pay for it as they leave.
example: I only shop at this supermarket.

translation: 监督，指导（负责某人/某事并确保工作正确、安全地进行）
definition: to be in charge of somebody/something and make sure that everything is done correctly, safely, etc.
example: supervise (somebody/something), to supervise building work

translation: 监督，管理（负责某人/某事并确保工作正确、安全进行的活动）
definition: the work or activity involved in being in charge of somebody/something and making sure that everything is done correctly, safely, etc.
example: Very young children should not be left to play without supervision.

translation: 监督者，主管（监督某人/某事的人）
definition: a person who supervises somebody/something
example: I have a meeting with my supervisor about my research topic.

translation: 补充，补充物（为了改进或完成某事而添加的东西，如维生素补充剂）
definition: a thing that is added to something else to improve or complete it
example: vitamin/dietary supplements (= vitamins and other foods eaten in addition to what you usually eat)

translation: 补充，增补（向某物添加东西使其更完善或更完整）
definition: to add something to something in order to improve it or make it more complete
example: supplement something with something, a diet supplemented with vitamin pills

translation: 供应，供应量（提供或可供使用的某物的数量）
definition: an amount of something that is provided or available to be used
example: Advances in agriculture increased the food supply.

translation: 供应，提供（向某人提供其所需或所欲之物，尤指大量提供）
definition: to provide somebody/something with something that they need or want, especially in large quantities
example: supply something to somebody/something, The company supplied sports equipment to schools.

translation: 支持，拥护（因希望某人成功而给予的认可或帮助）
definition: approval that you give to somebody/something because you want them to be successful
example: support for something, There is strong public support for the policy.

translation: 支持，拥护（通过言行展示你同意某人/某事，从而给予帮助或鼓励）
definition: to help or encourage somebody/something by saying or showing that you agree with them/it
example: support somebody/something, to support an idea/a view

translation: 支持者，拥护者（支持政党、想法等的人）
definition: a person who supports a political party, an idea, etc.
example: a strong/loyal/staunch/ardent supporter

translation: 给予支持的（给予他人鼓励、帮助或同情的）
definition: encouraging somebody or giving them help or sympathy
example: a supportive family

translation: 假设，猜想（基于已知知识认为某事属实或可能）
definition: to think or believe that something is true or possible (based on the knowledge that you have)
example: Getting a visa isn't as simple as you might suppose.

translation: 据推测（根据普遍认为但非确知的事实）
definition: according to what is generally thought or believed but not known for certain
example: The novel is supposedly based on a true story.

translation: 镇压，压制（通过武力结束被认为威胁权威的群体或活动）
definition: to put an end, often by force, to a group or an activity that is believed to threaten authority
example: The rebellion was brutally suppressed.

translation: 至高无上的（职级或地位最高的）
definition: highest in rank or position
example: the Supreme Commander of the armed forces

translation: 确定的（确信自己知道某事或自己是正确的）
definition: confident that you know something or that you are right
example: ‘Is that John over there?’ ‘I'm not sure’.

translation: 当然（用于表示同意）
definition: used to say ‘yes’ to somebody
example: ‘Will you get me my coat?’ ‘Sure, where is it?’

translation: 想必，确定（用于表示你几乎确信所言并希望他人同意）
definition: used to show that you are almost certain of what you are saying and want other people to agree with you
example: Surely we should do something about it?

translation: 表面（事物的外部或顶层）
definition: the outside or top layer of something
example: We need a flat, smooth surface to play the game on.

translation: 激增，涌动（强烈情感的突然增加）
definition: a sudden increase of a strong feeling
example: She felt a sudden surge of anger.

translation: 激增，冲（向特定方向快速且有力地移动）
definition: to move quickly and with force in a particular direction
example: The gates opened and the crowd surged forward.

translation: 外科医生（受过执行手术培训的医生）
definition: a doctor who is trained to perform surgery (= medical operations that involve cutting open a person’s body)
example: a brain/heart surgeon

translation: 外科手术（通过切开人体来移除或修复部位的医疗手段；外科学）
definition: medical treatment of injuries or diseases that involves cutting open a person’s body and often removing or replacing some parts; the branch of medicine connected with this treatment
example: major/minor surgery

translation: 外科的（用于手术或与手术相关的）
definition: used in or connected with surgery
example: surgical procedures

translation: 剩余，盈余（多于所需的数额）
definition: an amount that is extra or more than you need
example: food surpluses

translation: 惊喜，惊讶（出乎意料或突然发生的事件、消息等）
definition: an event, a piece of news, etc. that is unexpected or that happens suddenly
example: What a nice surprise!

translation: 使惊讶（使某人感到惊讶）
definition: to make somebody feel surprised
example: surprise somebody, It wouldn't surprise me if they got married soon.

translation: 惊讶的（感到或表现出惊讶的）
definition: feeling or showing surprise
example: a surprised look

translation: 令人惊讶的（引起惊讶的）
definition: causing surprise
example: It’s not surprising (that) they lost.

translation: 投降（承认被击败并停止战斗；让自己被抓获）
definition: to admit that you have been defeated and want to stop fighting; to allow yourself to be caught, taken prisoner, etc.
example: The rebel soldiers were forced to surrender.

translation: 包围，环绕（在某人/某物周围）
definition: to be all around something/somebody
example: surround something/somebody, Tall trees surround the lake.

translation: 周围的（在某物附近或周围的）
definition: that is near or around something
example: Oxford and the surrounding area

translation: 监视，监控（对疑似罪犯或犯罪地点进行的仔细观察）
definition: the act of carefully watching a person suspected of a crime or a place where a crime may be committed
example: The police are keeping the suspects under constant surveillance.

translation: 调查，民意调查（对特定人群意见、行为等的调查，通常通过提问进行）
definition: an investigation of the opinions, behaviour, etc. of a particular group of people, which is usually done by asking them questions
example: A recent survey showed 75 per cent of those questioned were in favour of the plan.

translation: 调查，勘测（仔细查看某物的整体，尤指为了获得总体印象）
definition: to look carefully at the whole of something, especially in order to get a general impression of it
example: The next morning we surveyed the damage caused by the fire.

translation: 生存，幸存（继续活着或存在状态，尤指在困难危险中）
definition: the state of continuing to live or exist, often despite difficulty or danger
example: the struggle/battle/fight for survival

translation: 生存，幸存（继续活着或存在）
definition: to continue to live or exist
example: She was the last surviving member of the family.

translation: 幸存者（在经历危险或几乎丧命后继续活着的人）
definition: a person who continues to live, especially despite being nearly killed or experiencing great danger or difficulty
example: the sole/only survivor of the massacre

translation: 嫌疑人（被怀疑犯罪或做错事的人）
definition: a person who is suspected of a crime or of having done something wrong
example: a murder suspect

translation: 怀疑（认为某事可能是真实的，尤指坏事，但无确凿证据）
definition: to have an idea that something is probably true or likely to happen, especially something bad, but without having definite proof
example: As I had suspected all along, he was not a real policeman.

translation: 悬挂（将一物吊在另一物上）
definition: to hang something from something else
example: be suspended from something, A lamp was suspended from the ceiling.

translation: 停职，停学（正式暂时剥夺某人的工作、学业或参赛资格，通常作为惩罚）
definition: the act of officially removing somebody from their job, school, team, etc. for a period of time, usually as a punishment
example: suspension from school

translation: 怀疑（认为某人做了错事、违法或不诚实的感觉，即使无证据）
definition: a feeling that somebody has done something wrong, illegal or dishonest, even though you have no proof
example: They drove away slowly to avoid arousing suspicion.

translation: 怀疑的，可疑的（认为某人做了错事、违法或不诚实的，即使无证据）
definition: feeling that somebody has done something wrong, illegal or dishonest, without having any proof
example: They became suspicious of his behaviour and contacted the police.

translation: 维持，支撑（提供足够的生存或存在所需之物）
definition: to provide enough of what somebody/something needs in order to live or exist
example: Which planets can sustain life?

translation: 可持续的（以不损害环境的方式使用自然产品和能源的）
definition: involving the use of natural products and energy in a way that does not harm the environment
example: sustainable forest management

translation: 吞咽（使食物、饮料等从喉咙进入胃部）
definition: to make food, drink, etc. go down your throat into your stomach
example: swallow (something), Always chew food well before swallowing it.

translation: 咒骂，发誓（使用粗鲁冒犯的语言，通常因愤怒）
definition: to use rude or offensive language, usually because you are angry
example: She fell over and swore loudly.

translation: 毛衣（羊毛或棉制的长袖上衣）
definition: a piece of clothing for the upper part of the body, made of wool or cotton, with long sleeves
example: She wore jeans and a sweater.

translation: 扫，清扫（使用扫帚清洁房间、表面等）
definition: to clean a room, surface, etc. using a broom (= a type of brush on a long handle)
example: sweep (something), to sweep the floor

translation: 甜的（含有大量糖分或尝起来有甜味的）
definition: containing, or tasting as if it contains, a lot of sugar
example: a cup of hot sweet tea

translation: 糖果（糖或巧克力制成的小块甜食，常在两餐间吃）
definition: a small piece of sweet food, usually made with sugar and/or chocolate and eaten between meals
example: a packet of sweets

translation: 游泳（游泳的一段时间）
definition: a period of time during which you swim
example: Let's go for a swim.

translation: 游泳（在水中移动手臂和腿部行进，不接触底部）
definition: to move through water by moving your arms and legs, without touching the bottom
example: I can't swim.

translation: 游泳（游泳运动或活动）
definition: the sport or activity of swimming
example: Swimming is a good form of exercise.

translation: 秋千，摆动（摆动的动作或节奏）
definition: a swinging movement or rhythm
example: He took a wild swing at the ball.

translation: 摆动，摇摆（悬挂在固定点前后或左右移动；使之摆动）
definition: to move backwards or forwards or from side to side while hanging from a fixed point; to make something do this
example: His arms swung as he walked.

translation: 开关（控制电灯或设备通断的小装置）
definition: a small device that you press or move up and down in order to turn a light or piece of electrical equipment on and off
example: a light switch

translation: 切换，转换（从一物改变或使之改变为另一物）
definition: to change or make something change from one thing to another
example: switch (over) to something, We're in the process of switching over to a new system of invoicing.

translation: 剑（带长金属刃和柄的武器）
definition: a weapon with a long metal blade (= sharp cutting part) and a handle
example: to draw/sheathe a sword (= to take it out of/put it into its cover)

translation: 象征，符号（代表更广泛特质或情况的人、物或事件）
definition: a person, an object, an event, etc. that represents a more general quality or situation
example: The vase is decorated with religious symbols.

translation: 象征性的（包含象征的或作为象征使用的）
definition: containing symbols, or being used as a symbol
example: He shook his fist in a symbolic gesture of defiance.

translation: 同情的，体谅的（对受难者友好的；表现出理解其问题的）
definition: kind to somebody who is hurt or sad; showing that you understand and care about their problems
example: a sympathetic listener

translation: 同情（对他人的不幸感到难过；理解并关心他人的问题）
definition: the feeling of being sorry for somebody; showing that you understand and care about somebody’s problems
example: sympathy for somebody, to express/feel sympathy for somebody

translation: 症状（表明身体或精神不健康的改变）
definition: a change in your body or mind that shows that you are not healthy
example: Symptoms include a headache and sore throat.

translation: 综合征，综合症（表明患有特定疾病的一组身体状况）
definition: a set of physical conditions that show you have a particular disease or medical problem
example: PMS or premenstrual syndrome

translation: 综合，合成（将不同的主意、信念、风格等结合的行为；其结合体）
definition: the act of combining separate ideas, beliefs, styles, etc.; a mixture or combination of ideas, beliefs, styles, etc.
example: synthesis of A with B, the synthesis of art with everyday life

translation: 系统，体制（一套有组织的思想理论或特定的做事方式）
definition: an organized set of ideas or theories or a particular way of doing something
example: reform of the country's education system

translation: 系统化的，有计划的（按照系统或计划以彻底高效的方式进行的）
definition: done according to a system or plan, in a complete, efficient or determined way
example: a systematic approach to solving the problem

translation: T恤（非正式的短袖上衣，通常无领无扣）
definition: an informal shirt, usually with short sleeves (= arms) no collar or buttons, or just a few buttons at the top
example: He was wearing a faded pair of blue jeans and an old T-shirt.

translation: 桌子（由支脚支撑的平整台面的家具）
definition: a piece of furniture that consists of a flat top supported by legs
example: at a/the table, We sat at a round table in the corner.

translation: 平板电脑（带大触摸屏、通常无物理键盘的易携带小型电脑）
definition: a small computer that is easy to carry, with a large touch screen and usually without a physical keyboard
example: The company has launched its latest 10-inch tablet.

translation: 抢断，铲球（在足球等运动中尝试抢球；或在橄榄球中将人撞倒）
definition: an act of trying to take the ball from an opponent in football (soccer), hockey, etc.; an act of knocking somebody to the ground, for example in rugby or American football
example: He was booked for a late tackle on Torres.

translation: 处理，解决（下定决心处理困难问题或局面）
definition: to make a determined effort to deal with a difficult problem or situation
example: The government is determined to tackle inflation.

translation: 策略，战术（为实现目标而采取的特定方法）
definition: the particular method you use to achieve something
example: They tried all kinds of tactics to get us to go.

translation: 战术的（与实现目标所采取的特定方法相关的）
definition: connected with the particular method you use to achieve something
example: tactical planning

translation: 标签（贴在物体上用于识别或提供信息的小纸、布或塑料片）
definition: a small piece of paper, cloth, plastic, etc. attached to something to identify it or give information about it
example: He put name tags on all his shirts.

translation: 给...贴标签（将标签固定在某物/某人上）
definition: to fasten a tag onto something/somebody
example: Each animal was tagged with a number for identification.

translation: 尾巴（动物、鸟或鱼身体后部伸出的部分，可移动）
definition: the part that sticks out at the back of the body of a bird, an animal or a fish, which the animal can move from side to side or up and down
example: The dog ran up, wagging its tail.

translation: 拿，带（将某物从一处携带或移动到另一处）
definition: to carry or move something from one place to another
example: take something, Remember to take your coat when you leave.

translation: 故事，传说（虚构的、常充满动作和冒险的故事）
definition: a story created using the imagination, especially one that is full of action and adventure
example: a coming-of-age/morality tale

translation: 天赋，才能（做好某事的自然能力）
definition: a natural ability to do something well
example: The festival showcases the talent of young musicians.

translation: 有天赋的（具备做好某事的自然能力的）
definition: having a natural ability to do something well
example: a talented player/musician/artist

translation: 谈话，讲座（就特定主题进行的演说或讲课）
definition: a speech or lecture on a particular subject
example: I went to several interesting talks at the conference.

translation: 说话，交谈（为了给出信息或表达情感、主意而说话）
definition: to say things; to speak in order to give information or to express feelings, ideas, etc.
example: Stop talking and listen!

translation: 高的（高度超过平均水平的）
definition: having a greater than average height
example: She's tall and thin.

translation: 罐，箱（盛放液体或气体的大型容器，如油箱、水箱）
definition: a large container for holding liquid or gas
example: a fuel/water/storage tank

translation: 水龙头（控制管道中流向浴缸或水槽的水流的装置）
definition: a device for controlling the flow of water from a pipe into a bath or sink
example: bath taps

translation: 敲，拍（快速轻微地击打某人/某物）
definition: to hit somebody/something quickly and lightly
example: tap (away) (at something), Someone tapped at the door.

translation: 胶带（一侧带粘性物质、用于粘贴物品的长条材料）
definition: a long, narrow piece of material with a sticky substance on one side that is used for sticking things together
example: adhesive/sticky tape

translation: 目标（尝试实现的结果）
definition: a result that you try to achieve
example: to meet/hit a target

translation: 瞄准，针对（将攻击或批评针对某人/某物）
definition: to aim an attack or a criticism at somebody/something
example: target somebody/something, He accused the group of deliberately targeting civilians.

translation: 任务（某人必须完成的工作，尤指艰巨或不快的）
definition: a piece of work that somebody has to do, especially a hard or unpleasant one
example: to accomplish/perform/undertake/complete a task

translation: 味道（食物和饮料进入口中时让你辨别它们的特质）
definition: the particular quality that different foods and drinks have that allows you to recognize them when you put them in your mouth
example: a sweet/salty/bitter/sour taste

translation: 尝起来（具有某种特定的味道）
definition: to have a particular taste
example: + adj., to taste good/delicious/sweet

translation: 税，税收（付给政府以支持公共服务的钱，根据收入、利润或商品支付）
definition: money that you have to pay to the government so that it can pay for public services. People pay tax according to their income and businesses pay tax according to their profits. Tax is also often paid on goods and services.
example: to pay your taxes

translation: 向...征税（对某人/某物征税；使之交税）
definition: to put a tax on somebody/something; to make somebody pay tax
example: tax somebody/something, His declared aim was to tax the rich.

translation: 出租车（你付钱让司机送你去某处的汽车，通常带计价器）
definition: a car with a driver that you pay to take you somewhere. Taxis usually have meters that show how much money you have to pay.
example: We took a taxi to the airport.

translation: 纳税人（向政府交税的人，尤指根据收入交税者）
definition: a person who pays tax to the government, especially on the money that they earn
example: Hundreds of thousands of pounds of taxpayers' money (= money paid in taxes) have been spent on the project.

translation: 茶，茶叶（茶树干燥后的叶子）
definition: the dried leaves (called tea leaves) of the tea bush
example: a packet of tea

translation: 教，教学（在学校、大学等给学生讲课；或通过提供信息帮助他人学习）
definition: to give lessons to students in a school, college, university, etc.; to help somebody learn something by giving information about it
example: She teaches at our local school.

translation: 教师（以教学为职业的人，尤指在学校中）
definition: a person whose job is teaching, especially in a school
example: an English/a science teacher

translation: 教学（教师的工作）
definition: the work of a teacher
example: She wants to go into teaching (= make it a career).

translation: 团队，队（在游戏或运动中与另一组对抗的一群人）
definition: a group of people who play a particular game or sport against another group of people
example: a football/basketball/soccer team

translation: 裂缝，撕痕（因撕扯而在某物上形成的孔洞）
definition: a hole that has been made in something by tearing
example: This sheet has a tear in it.

translation: 撕，撕碎（通过用力拉扯或被尖锐物划破使某物受损）
definition: to damage something by pulling it apart or into pieces or by cutting it on something sharp; to become damaged in this way
example: tear something + adv./prep., I tore my jeans on the fence.

translation: 技术的，技术上的（与科学和工业中机器、方法的实际使用相关的）
definition: connected with the practical use of machines, methods, etc. in science and industry
example: We offer free technical support for those buying our software.

translation: 技术，技能（做某事的特定方式，尤指需学习专门技能者）
definition: a particular way of doing something, especially one in which you have to learn special skills
example: management techniques

translation: 科技的（与科学技术相关的）
definition: connected with technology
example: technological advances

translation: 科技，技术（在工业中实际使用的科学知识，如设计新机器）
definition: scientific knowledge used in practical ways in industry, for example in designing new machines
example: science and technology

translation: 青少年的（13至19岁之间的；与此年龄段人群相关的）
definition: between 13 and 19 years old; connected with people of this age
example: a teenage girl/boy

translation: 青少年（13至19岁之间的人）
definition: a person who is between 13 and 19 years old
example: a magazine aimed at teenagers

translation: 青少年时期（一个人13至19岁之间的那段岁月）
definition: the years of a person’s life when they are between 13 and 19 years old
example: in your teens, She began writing poetry in her teens.

translation: 电话（利用线路或无线电进行远距离交谈的系统；这种机器）
definition: a system for talking to somebody else over long distances, using wires or radio; a machine used for this
example: The telephone rang and Pat answered it.

translation: 打电话（通过电话与某人交谈）
definition: to speak to somebody by phone
example: Please write or telephone for details.

translation: 电视机（带有屏幕、可观看带音画节目的电子设备）
definition: a piece of electrical equipment with a screen on which you can watch programmes with moving pictures and sounds
example: a widescreen/flat-screen/plasma television

translation: 告诉（通过说话或书写向某人提供信息）
definition: to give information to somebody by speaking or writing
example: tell something to somebody, He told the news to everybody he saw.

translation: 温度（以度数衡量的物体或地方的热冷程度）
definition: the measurement in degrees of how hot or cold a thing or place is
example: high/low temperatures

translation: 寺庙，寺院（用于宗教礼拜的建筑，尤指非基督教的）
definition: a building used for religious worship, especially in religions other than Christianity
example: the Temple of Diana at Ephesus

translation: 暂时地（以持续短时间或非永久的方式）
definition: in a way that lasts or is intended to last or be used only for a short time; in a way that is not permanent
example: We regret this service is temporarily unavailable.

translation: 暂时的（仅持续或预定使用短时间的；非永久的）
definition: lasting or intended to last or be used only for a short time; not permanent
example: to hire temporary workers

translation: 引诱，诱惑（吸引某人做某事，即使其知道这是错的）
definition: to attract somebody or make somebody want to do or have something, even if they know it is wrong

translation: 十（数字10）
example: There are only ten of these rare animals left.

translation: 租户，房客（向房东付房租以使用房间、建筑或土地的人）
definition: a person who pays rent for the use of a room, building, land, etc. to the person who owns it

translation: 往往，倾向于（很可能以特定方式做事或发生，因其经常如此）
definition: to be likely to do something or to happen in a particular way because this is what often or usually happens

translation: 倾向，习性（某人/某物很可能以特定方式表现的特质）
definition: if somebody/something has a particular tendency, they are likely to behave or act in a particular way
example: to display artistic tendencies

translation: 温柔的（和蔼、温和且充满爱的）
definition: kind, gentle and loving
example: tender words

translation: 网球（两或四人在专用球场上用球拍隔网击球的比赛）
definition: a game in which two or four players use rackets to hit a ball backwards and forwards across a net on a specially marked court
example: to play tennis

translation: 紧张，张力（人们互不信任、不友好且可能导致攻击的局面）
definition: a situation in which people do not trust each other, or feel unfriendly towards each other, and that may cause them to attack each other
example: There is mounting tension along the border.

translation: 帐篷（由帆布、尼龙制成、用杆和绳支撑在地面上的野营住所）
definition: a shelter made of a large sheet of canvas, nylon, etc. that is supported by poles and ropes fixed to the ground, and is used especially for camping

translation: 任期，任职（担任重要职位――尤指政治职位――的时期；担任的行为）
definition: the period of time when somebody holds an important job, especially a political one; the act of holding an important job
example: his four-year tenure as president

translation: 术语，词语（作为某物名称的词或短语，尤指与特定语言相关的）
definition: a word or phrase used as the name of something, especially one connected with a particular type of language
example: a technical/legal/generic term

translation: 称为，称作（使用特定的名称或词语描述某人/某物）
definition: to use a particular name or word to describe somebody/something

translation: 晚期的（无法治愈并将导致死亡的，通常指疾病）
definition: that cannot be cured and will lead to death, often slowly
example: He has terminal lung cancer.

translation: 航站楼，航站（机场供旅客到达和离开的建筑群）
definition: a building or set of buildings at an airport where passengers arrive and leave

translation: 终止，结束（结束；使某事结束）
definition: to end; to make something end

translation: 条款，条件（协议、安排或合同中人们提供、要求或接受的条件）
definition: the conditions that people offer, demand or accept when they make an agreement, an arrangement or a contract

translation: 地形，地势（提到土地自然特征时的区域，如崎岖、平坦等）
definition: used to refer to an area of land when you are mentioning its natural features, for example, if it is rough, flat, etc.
example: difficult/rough/mountainous terrain

translation: 可怕的，糟糕的（非常令人不快、忧虑或惊吓的）

translation: 非常，极度（用于道歉或强调，意为“非常”）

translation: 极好的，了不起的（优秀的；美妙的）

translation: 使恐怖，惊吓（使某人感到极度恐惧）
definition: to make somebody feel extremely frightened

translation: 领土，领土（处于特定国家或政治领袖控制下的土地）
definition: land that is under the control of a particular country or political leader
example: enemy/disputed/foreign territory

translation: 恐惧，恐怖（极度恐惧的感觉）
definition: a feeling of extreme fear
example: a feeling of sheer/pure terror

translation: 恐怖主义（为了达到政治目的而使用的暴力行为）
definition: the use of violent action in order to achieve political aims or to force a government to act

translation: 恐怖分子（参加恐怖活动的人）
definition: a person who takes part in terrorism
example: The terrorists are threatening to blow up the plane.

translation: 测试，考试（对某人知识或能力的检查，含问题或活动）
definition: an examination of somebody’s knowledge or ability, consisting of questions for them to answer or activities for them to perform
example: an IQ/a fitness test

translation: 测试（通过提问或活动找出某人知道多少或能做什么）
definition: to find out how much somebody knows, or what they can do by asking them questions or giving them activities to perform
example: test somebody, Students will be tested at the end of each module.

translation: 作证（正式陈述某事已发生或属实，尤指作为法庭证人）
definition: to make a statement that something happened or that something is true, especially as a witness in court

translation: 证明，证据（显示他物存在或属实的事物）
definition: a thing that shows that something else exists or is true

translation: 测试，试验（为了发现某事、核实其是否有效而进行的活动）
definition: the activity of testing somebody/something in order to find something out, see if it works, etc.

translation: 文本，正文（任何形式的书面材料）
definition: any form of written material

translation: 发短信（发送手机短信）
教科书（教授特定学科的书，尤用于学校和学院）
definition: a book that teaches a particular subject and that is used especially in schools and colleges
example: a school/medical/history textbook

translation: 质感，纹理（表面、物质或布料摸起来的感觉，如粗糙、光滑等）
definition: the way a surface, substance or piece of cloth feels when you touch it, for example how rough, smooth, hard or soft it is
example: the soft texture of velvet

translation: 比（用于引入比较的第二部分）
definition: used to introduce the second part of a comparison
example: I'm older than her.

translation: 比（用于引入比较的第二部分）
definition: used to introduce the second part of a comparison
example: I'm older than her.

translation: 感谢（告诉某人你对其所做之事表示感激）
definition: to tell somebody that you are grateful for something
example: thank somebody for something, I must write and thank Mary for the present.

translation: 谢天谢地（用于表示对好事发生或坏事避免感到高兴）
definition: used to show that you are pleased that something good has happened or that something bad has been avoided
example: There was a fire in the building, but thankfully no one was hurt.

translation: 谢谢（用于表示感激）
definition: used to show that you are grateful to somebody for something they have done
example: ‘How are you?’ ‘Fine, thanks (= thanks for asking).’

translation: 感谢（表示感激的言语或行动）
definition: words or actions that show that you are grateful to somebody for something
example: thanks to somebody for something, How can I ever express my thanks to you for all you've done?

translation: 那么（到那种程度；那么）
definition: to such a degree; so
example: I can't walk that far (= as far as that).

translation: （连词）那（用于动词、形容词或名词后引导句子的新部分）
definition: used after some verbs, adjectives and nouns to introduce a new part of the sentence
example: She said (that) the story was true.

translation: 那个（指代离说话者较远的人或物）
definition: used for referring to a person or thing that is not near the speaker or as near to the speaker as another
example: Look at that man over there.

translation: 那个（指代离说话者较远的人或物）
definition: used for referring to a person or thing that is not near the speaker, or not as near to the speaker as another
example: Who's that?

translation: 这个/那个（定冠词，指代已提到或易理解的人/物）
definition: used to refer to somebody/something that has already been mentioned or is easily understood
example: There were three questions. The first two were relatively easy but the third one was hard.

translation: 剧院（表演戏剧或类似娱乐形式的建筑或户外区域）
definition: a building or an outdoor area where plays and similar types of entertainment are performed

translation: 戏剧的（与剧院或戏剧相关的）
definition: connected with the theatre
example: a theatrical agent

translation: 偷窃，盗窃罪（从人或地方窃取某物的犯罪）
definition: the crime of stealing something from a person or place
example: car theft

translation: 他们的（属于已提到或易识别的人、动物或事物的）
definition: of or belonging to people, animals or things that have already been mentioned or are easily identified
example: Their parties are always fun.

translation: 他们的东西（属于他们的东西）
definition: of or belonging to them
example: Theirs are the children with very fair hair.

translation: 他们（用作动词或介词的宾语，指代已提到的人或物）
definition: used when referring to people, animals or things as the object of a verb or preposition, or after the verb be
example: Tell them the news.

translation: 主题（谈话、文章或艺术作品的主题或核心思想）
definition: the subject or main idea in a talk, piece of writing or work of art

translation: 他们自己（themselves的反身形式）
definition: used when people or animals performing an action are also affected by it
example: They seemed to be enjoying themselves.

translation: 那时，然后（指代过去或未来的特定时间）
definition: used to refer to a particular time in the past or future

translation: 神学（宗教和信仰的研究）
definition: the study of religion and beliefs

translation: 理论上的（与学科的基本想法和原则相关的，而非实践）
definition: connected with the ideas and principles on which a particular subject is based, rather than with practice and experiment

translation: 理论（旨在解释某事发生原因或存在的一套正式想法）
definition: a formal set of ideas that is intended to explain why something happens or exists

translation: 治疗师（治疗特定类型疾病或问题的专家）
definition: a specialist who treats a particular type of illness or problem, or who uses a particular type of treatment

translation: 治疗，疗法（对身体问题或疾病的治疗）
definition: the treatment of a physical problem or an illness

translation: 那里（用于显示某物存在或发生）
definition: used to show that something exists or happens

translation: 此后（在提到的时间或事件之后）
definition: after the time or event mentioned
example: She married at 17 and gave birth to her first child shortly thereafter.

translation: 从而，因此（用于引入提到行动或情况的结果）
definition: used to introduce the result of the action or situation mentioned
example: Regular exercise strengthens the heart, thereby reducing the risk of heart attack.

translation: 因此，所以（用于引入刚提到之事的逻辑结果）
definition: used to introduce the logical result of something that has just been mentioned
example: He's only 17 and therefore not eligible to vote.

translation: 论文（学生作为大学学位一部分完成的长篇书面研究作品）
definition: a long piece of writing completed by a student as part of a university degree, based on their own research
example: Students must submit a thesis on an agreed subject within four years.

translation: 他们（指代已提到或易识别的人、动物或事物）
definition: people, animals or things that have already been mentioned or are easily identified
example: ‘Where are John and Liz?’ ‘They went for a walk.’

translation: 厚的（两面间距离大的；比平常厚的）
definition: having a larger distance between opposite sides or surfaces than other similar objects or than normal
example: a thick slice of bread

translation: 小偷（从他人或他处窃取财物的人）
definition: a person who steals something from another person or place
example: a car/jewel thief

translation: 薄的，细的（两面间距离小的；比平常薄的）
definition: having a smaller distance between opposite sides or surfaces than other similar objects or than normal
example: Cut the vegetables into thin strips.

translation: 东西（不知道名字或不想使用名字的物体）
definition: an object whose name you do not use because you do not need to or want to, or because you do not know it
example: Can you pass me that thing over there?

translation: 想，认为（对某人/某事有特定的看法；相信某事）
definition: to have a particular idea or opinion about something/somebody; to believe something

translation: 思考，想法（思考某事的过程）
definition: the process of thinking about something

translation: 三分之一（某物三个相等部分中的一个）
definition: each of three equal parts of something

translation: 第三（序数词3rd）

translation: 渴的（需要或想要喝水的）
definition: needing or wanting to drink

translation: 十三（数字13）
三十（数字30）
这么（到这种程度；这么）
definition: to this degree; so
example: It's about this high (= as high as I am showing you with my hands).

translation: 这，这个（指代离说话者较近的人、物或事件）
definition: used to refer to a particular person, thing or event that is close to you, especially compared with another
example: How long have you been living in this country?

translation: 这，这个（指代离说话者较近的人、物或事件）
彻底的，详尽的（完全做好的；非常注重细节的）
definition: done completely; with great attention to detail
example: a thorough knowledge of the subject

translation: 彻底地（非常多地；完全地）
definition: very much; completely
example: We thoroughly enjoyed ourselves.

translation: 不过（尤其用于句末，使前述陈述语气减弱或不那么重要）
definition: used especially at the end of a sentence or clause to add a fact or an opinion that makes the previous statement less strong or less important
example: Our team lost. It was a good game though.

translation: 尽管（尽管事实是...）
definition: despite the fact that
example: Anne was fond of Tim, though he often annoyed her.

translation: 想法，念头（你想到或记起的事情）
definition: something that you think of or remember
example: thought of doing something, I couldn't bear the thought of waiting any longer.

translation: 发人深省的（使人严肃思考特定主题或问题的）
definition: making people think seriously about a particular subject or issue
example: a brilliant and thought-provoking play

translation: 沉思的（因在思考而安静的）
definition: quiet, because you are thinking
example: He looked thoughtful.

translation: 一千（数字1000）

translation: 线（缝纫或织布用的棉、毛、丝细线）
definition: a thin string of cotton, wool, silk, etc. used for sewing or making cloth

translation: 威胁（告知某人若不按要求做将受惩罚或伤害的陈述）
definition: a statement in which you tell somebody that you will punish or harm them, especially if they do not do what you want

translation: 威胁（表示如果不得到想要的东西将制造麻烦或伤害他人）

example: threaten somebody/something, They broke my windows and threatened me.

translation: 三（数字3）

translation: 门槛（门口底部的地面或地板，被视为进入建筑的入口）
definition: the floor or ground at the bottom of a doorway, considered as the entrance to a building or room
example: He stepped across the threshold.

translation: 激动，欣喜若狂（非常兴奋和高兴的）
definition: very excited and pleased

translation: 繁荣，茁壮成长（变得且持续成功、强壮、健康等）
definition: to become, and continue to be, successful, strong, healthy, etc.

translation: 喉咙（颈部内食物和空气经过的通道；颈部前部）
definition: a passage in the neck through which food and air pass on their way into the body; the front part of the neck
