translation: 穿过（从一端或一侧到另一端）
definition: from one end or side of something to the other
example: Put the coffee in the filter and let the water run through.

translation: 穿过（从一端或一侧到另一端）
definition: from one end or side of something/somebody to the other
example: The burglar got in through the window.

translation: 贯穿（在某物的每一个部分）
definition: in or into every part of something
example: They export their products to markets throughout the world.

translation: 贯穿（在某物的每一个部分）
definition: in or into every part of something
example: They export their products to markets throughout the world.

translation: 扔，投（通过快速移动手或臂将某物从手中掷向空中）
definition: to send something from your hand through the air by moving your hand or arm quickly
example: Practise throwing and catching.

translation: 拇指（手侧面短而粗的手指，与其他四个分开）
definition: the short, thick finger at the side of the hand, slightly apart from the other four
example: She still sucks her thumb when she's worried.

translation: 星期四（周三之后、周五之前的一天）
definition: the day of the week after Wednesday and before Friday
example: It's Thursday today, isn't it?

translation: 如此，因此（以这种方式；像这样）
definition: in this way; like this
example: Many scholars have argued thus.

translation: 票（证明你有权乘坐车、进入剧院等的打印纸片或电子信息）
definition: a printed piece of paper, or a message or image received on your phone or computer, that gives you the right to travel on a particular bus, train, etc. or to go into a theatre, etc.
example: a plane/bus/train ticket

translation: 潮汐（月球和太阳引力引起的海平面定期涨落；及其水流）
definition: a regular rise and fall in the level of the sea, caused by the pull of the moon and sun; the flow of water that happens as the sea rises and falls
example: the ebb and flow of the tide

translation: 整洁的（排列整齐、井井有条的）
definition: arranged neatly and with everything in order
example: a tidy desk

translation: 整理（把东西放在应有的位置使之看起来整洁）
definition: to make something look neat by putting things in the place where they belong
example: I spent all morning cleaning and tidying.

translation: 领带（系在脖子上的、前面带结的长条布，尤指男子穿戴）
definition: a long, narrow piece of cloth worn around the neck, especially by men, with a knot in front
example: He was dressed impeccably in a suit and tie.

translation: 系，捆（使用绳、索等将两物连接或固定在一起）
definition: to attach or hold two or more things together using string, rope, etc.; to fasten somebody/something with string, rope, etc.
example: tie something + adv./prep., She tied the newspapers in a bundle.

translation: 紧的，牢固的（牢牢固定在位置上的；难以移动、打开或分开的）
definition: held or fixed in position securely; difficult to move, open or separate
example: He kept a tight grip on her arm.

translation: 变紧，拉紧（将某物更牢固地固定；使之更难移动或打开）
definition: to hold or fix something more securely in position; to make something or become more difficult to move, open or separate
example: tighten something, to tighten a lid/screw/rope/knot

translation: 直到（直到...时）
definition: until
example: We're open till 6 o'clock.

translation: 直到（直到...时）
definition: until
example: We're open till 6 o'clock.

translation: 木材（种来用于建筑或制作物品的树木）
definition: trees that are grown to be used in building or for making things
example: the timber industry

translation: 时间（以分、时、天等衡量的事物）
definition: what is measured in minutes, hours, days, etc.
example: The world exists in time and space.

translation: 计时（测量某事发生或某人做某事所花的时间）
definition: to measure how long it takes for something to happen or for somebody to do something
example: time something, ‘How long does it take to get to Leeds from here?’ ‘I don’t know, I’ve never timed it.’

translation: 及时的（在恰当的时间发生的）
definition: happening at exactly the right time
example: A nasty incident was prevented by the timely arrival of the police.

translation: 时机（选择某事发生时间的行为；某事发生的时间点）
definition: the act of choosing when something happens; a particular point or period of time when something happens or is planned
example: The timing of the decision was a complete surprise.

translation: 锡罐，罐头（出售食品用的金属容器；及其内含物）
definition: a metal container in which food is sold; the contents of one of these containers
example: Open the tin and drain the tuna.

translation: 极小的（尺寸或数量上非常小的）
definition: very small in size or amount
example: a tiny baby

translation: 小建议，贴士（关于实用事项的一小条建议）
definition: a small piece of advice about something practical
example: tip on/for doing something, handy tips for buying a computer

translation: 给小费（给从事服务工作的人额外的一笔钱以示感谢）
definition: to give somebody an extra amount of money to thank them for something they have done for you as part of their job
example: Americans were always welcome because they tended to tip heavily.

translation: 疲倦的（想要睡觉或休息的；需要休息的）
definition: feeling that you would like to sleep or rest; needing rest
example: to be/look/feel tired

translation: 纸巾（柔软的纸片，尤用作手帕）
definition: a piece of soft paper, used especially as a handkerchief
example: a box of tissues

translation: 标题，题目（书、诗、画、乐曲的名字）
definition: the name of a book, poem, painting, piece of music, etc.
example: What's title of her new book?

translation: 给...定名（给书、乐曲等起特定的名字）
definition: to give a book, piece of music, etc. a particular name
example: be titled…, Their first album was titled ‘Made in Valmez’.

translation: （不定式标志）（用于表示目的或意图）
definition: used to show purpose or intention
example: I set out to buy food.

translation: 到，向（朝向某物或某方向）
definition: in the direction of something; towards something
example: I walked to the office.

translation: 烟草（用于制作香烟、烟斗等的烟草植物干燥叶子）
definition: the dried leaves of the tobacco plant that are used for making cigarettes, smoking in a pipe, etc.
example: tobacco smoke

translation: 今天（在今天这一天）
definition: on this day
example: I've got a piano lesson later today.

translation: 今天（今天这一天）
definition: this day
example: Today is her tenth birthday.

translation: 脚趾（脚上的五个小突出部之一）
definition: one of the five small parts that stick out from the foot; any similar part on the foot of an animal or bird
example: the big/little toe (= the largest/smallest toe)

translation: 一起（与他人在一起；相互之间）
definition: with or near to somebody/something else; with each other
example: We grew up together.

translation: 厕所，马桶（冲洗身体排泄物的大碗状容器及管道）
definition: a large bowl attached to a pipe that you sit on or stand over when you get rid of waste matter from your body
example: Have you flushed the toilet?

translation: 宽容，容忍（乐于接受不同意见、行为或不同人群的品质）
definition: the quality of being willing to accept or tolerate somebody/something, especially opinions or behaviour that you may not agree with, or people who are not like you
example: She had no tolerance for jokes of any kind.

translation: 容忍，忍受（允许他人做你不同意或不喜欢的事）
definition: to allow somebody to do something that you do not agree with or like
example: tolerate something, Their relationship was tolerated but not encouraged.

translation: 通行费（使用特定道路或桥梁支付的钱）
definition: money that you pay to use a particular road or bridge
example: motorway tolls

translation: 西红柿（带很多汁液、红色发亮表皮的软质水果，常作蔬菜食用）
definition: a soft fruit with a lot of juice and shiny red skin that is eaten as a vegetable either raw or cooked
example: a bacon, lettuce, and tomato sandwich

translation: 明天（在明天这一天）
definition: on or during the day after today
example: I'm off now. See you tomorrow.

translation: 明天（明天这一天）
definition: the day after today
example: Today is Tuesday, so tomorrow is Wednesday.

translation: 吨（重量单位；英制2240磅，美制2000磅）
definition: a unit for measuring weight, in the UK 2?240 pounds (long ton) and in the US 2?000 pounds (short ton)
example: (informal), What have you got in this bag? It weighs a ton (= is very heavy).

translation: 语气，音调（某人嗓音的特质，尤指表达某种情感）
definition: the quality of somebody’s voice, especially expressing a particular emotion
example: speaking in hushed/low/clipped/measured, etc. tones

translation: 舌头（口中移动的柔软部分，用于味觉、吞咽、说话等）
definition: the soft part in the mouth that moves around, used for tasting, swallowing, speaking, etc.
example: He clicked his tongue to attract their attention.

translation: 今晚（在今晚这一时间）
definition: on or during the evening or night of today
example: Will you have dinner with me tonight?

translation: 今晚（今晚这一时间）
definition: the evening or night of today
example: Here are tonight's football results.

translation: 吨（重量单位，等于1000公斤）
definition: a unit for measuring weight, equal to 1?000 kilograms
example: a record grain harvest of 236m tonnes

translation: 太（用于形容词、副词前，表示程度超过了所需或可能的）
definition: used before adjectives and adverbs to say that something is more than is good, necessary, possible, etc.
example: He's far too young to go on his own.

translation: 工具（手持的用于制造或修理物品的器具，如锤子、锯子）
definition: an instrument such as a hammer, screwdriver, saw, etc. that you hold in your hand and use for making things, repairing things, etc.
example: garden tools

translation: 牙齿（口中用于咬碎食物的白色坚硬结构之一）
definition: any of the hard white structures in the mouth used for biting food
example: I've just had a tooth out at the dentist's.

translation: 顶部的（处于最高位置的）
definition: highest in position
example: He lives on the top floor.

translation: 顶部（某物的最高部分或点）
definition: the highest part or point of something
example: at the top of something, She was standing at the top of the stairs.

translation: 超过，胜过（高于特定的数额）
definition: to be higher than a particular amount
example: Worldwide sales look set to top $1 billion.

translation: 话题，主题（谈论、书写或学习的主题）
definition: a subject that you talk, write or learn about
example: The main topic of conversation was Tom's new girlfriend.

translation: 折磨，酷刑（为了惩罚或逼供而使人遭受剧烈疼痛的行为）
definition: the act of causing somebody severe pain in order to punish them or make them say or do something
example: Many of the refugees have suffered torture.

translation: 折磨，拷打（为了惩罚或逼供而在肉体或精神上伤害他人）
definition: to hurt somebody physically or mentally in order to punish them or make them tell you something
example: torture somebody, Many of the rebels were captured and tortured by secret police.

translation: 扔，投（轻微或不经意地抛掷某物）
definition: to throw something lightly or carelessly
example: toss something + adv./prep., I tossed the book aside and got up.

translation: 总的，全部的（所有人或物计入后的总数或数量）
definition: being the amount or number after everyone or everything is counted or added together
example: Their total cost was $18?000.

translation: 总计，合计（多个数字相加后的总额；计算后的总人数）
definition: the amount you get when you add several numbers or amounts together; the final number of people or things when they have all been counted
example: a total of something, You got 47 points on the written examination and 18 on the oral, making a total of 65.

translation: 总计达（达到特定的总数）
definition: to reach a particular total
example: Imports totalled $1.5 billion last year.

translation: 完全地，彻底地（完全地）
definition: completely
example: They come from totally different cultures.

translation: 触觉，触摸（通过手和手指感知物体及其特质的感官）
definition: the sense that enables you to be aware of things and what they are like when you put your hands and fingers on them
example: the sense of touch

translation: 触摸（将手或身体其他部位碰到他人/他物）
definition: to put your hand or another part of your body onto somebody/something
example: Don't touch that plate―it's hot!

translation: 艰苦的，棘手的（产生或引起问题和困难的）
definition: having or causing problems or difficulties
example: a tough childhood

translation: 旅行，游览（为了娱乐而访问多个不同城镇或国家的旅程）
definition: a journey made for pleasure during which several different towns, countries, etc. are visited
example: a walking/sightseeing/bus tour

translation: 游览，巡演（在某处到处旅行，如度假、表演或宣传）
definition: to travel around a place, for example on holiday, or to perform, to advertise something, etc.
example: tour something, He toured America with his one-man show.

translation: 旅游业（为度假游客提供住宿、服务和娱乐的商业活动）
definition: the business activity connected with providing accommodation, services and entertainment for people who are visiting a place for pleasure
example: The area is heavily dependent on tourism.

translation: 游客（为了娱乐而旅行或访问某地的人）
definition: a person who is travelling or visiting a place for pleasure
example: busloads of foreign tourists

translation: 锦标赛，联赛（涉及多个团队或选手参与、输者出局的体育竞赛）
definition: a sports competition involving a number of teams or players who take part in different games and must leave the competition if they lose. The competition continues until there is only the winner left.
example: a golf/tennis/soccer/chess tournament

translation: 朝向，向着（朝着某人/某物的方向）
definition: in the direction of somebody/something
example: They were heading towards the German border.

translation: 毛巾（用于擦干身体等的布片或纸片）
definition: a piece of cloth or paper used for drying things, especially your body
example: Help yourself to a clean towel.

translation: 塔，塔楼（高而窄的建筑或建筑的一部分，如教堂或城堡塔）
definition: a tall narrow building or part of a building, especially of a church or castle
example: a bell tower

translation: 城镇，市镇（有许多住房商店、供人工作生活的居住区，大于村小于城）
definition: a place with many houses, shops, etc. where people live and work. It is larger than a village but smaller than a city.
example: The nearest town is ten miles away.

translation: 有毒的（含有毒素的；有毒的）
definition: containing poison; poisonous
example: toxic chemicals/fumes/gases/substances

translation: 玩具的（作为某物副本供玩耍的）
definition: made as a copy of a particular thing and used for playing with
example: a toy car

translation: 玩具（供儿童玩耍的物品）
definition: an object for children to play with
example: cuddly/stuffed toys

translation: 痕迹，踪迹（显示某人/某物曾存在或到场的迹象、物体或痕迹）
definition: a mark, an object or a sign that shows that somebody/something existed or was present
example: It's exciting to discover traces of earlier civilizations.

translation: 追踪，找到（通过仔细寻找发现或找到某人/某物）
definition: to find or discover somebody/something by looking carefully for them/it
example: We finally traced him to an address in Chicago.

translation: 轨道，铁轨（火车行驶其上的金属条）
definition: rails (= metal bars) that a train moves along
example: railway/railroad tracks

translation: 追踪，跟踪（通过跟随他人留下的痕迹、信息等找到他们）
definition: to find somebody/something by following the marks, signs, information, etc., that they have left behind them
example: track somebody/something, hunters tracking and shooting bears

translation: 贸易（人或国家间买卖、交换商品或服务的活动）
definition: the activity of buying and selling or of exchanging goods or services between people or countries
example: international/foreign/global/world trade

translation: 交易，经商（买卖物品）
definition: to buy and sell things
example: trade in something, The firm openly traded in arms.

translation: 商标（公司用于其产品且他人不得使用的名称、符号或设计）
definition: a name, symbol or design that a company uses for its products and that cannot be used by anyone else
example: ‘Big Mac’ is McDonald's best-known trademark.

translation: 交易，营业（买卖物品的活动，如周日营业）
definition: the activity of buying and selling things
example: new laws on Sunday trading (= shops being open on Sundays)

translation: 传统（长期存在于特定人群中的信仰、习俗或做事方式）
definition: a belief, custom or way of doing something that has existed for a long time among a particular group of people; a set of these beliefs or customs
example: religious/cultural/ancient traditions

translation: 传统的（属于特定人群长期未变的信仰、习俗或生活方式一部分的）
definition: being part of the beliefs, customs or way of life of a particular group of people, that have not changed for a long time
example: traditional dress/music/art/culture/dance

translation: 交通（特定时间道路上的车辆）
definition: the vehicles that are on a road at a particular time
example: There's always a lot of traffic at this time of day.

translation: 悲剧（非常悲惨的事件或情况，尤指涉及死亡）
definition: a very sad event or situation, especially one that involves death
example: It's a tragedy that she died so young.

translation: 悲剧性的（令人非常悲伤的，通常因为涉及伤亡）
definition: making you feel very sad, usually because somebody has died or suffered a lot
example: He was killed in a tragic accident at the age of 24.

translation: 踪迹，痕迹（某人/某物留下的一行长长的标记或痕迹）
definition: a long line or series of marks that is left by somebody/something
example: a trail of blood

translation: 拖，拉（在身后拉某物，通常沿地面；或被拖着走）
definition: to pull something behind somebody/something, usually along the ground; to be pulled along in this way
example: trail something, A jeep trailing a cloud of dust was speeding in my direction.

translation: 拖车，挂车（由另一辆车牵引的卡车或带轮容器）
definition: a truck, or a container with wheels, that is pulled by another vehicle
example: a car towing a trailer with a boat on it

translation: 火车（由车头牵引的、连接在一起运送人或货物的车厢）
definition: a number of connected coaches or trucks, pulled by an engine or powered by a motor in each one, taking people and goods from one place to another
example: to get on/off a train

translation: 训练，培训（教导人或动物特定工作的技能；或接受教导）
definition: to teach a person or an animal the skills for a particular job or activity; to be taught in this way
example: train somebody/something, highly trained professionals

translation: 运动鞋（用于运动或作为非正式服装穿的鞋）
definition: a shoe that you wear for sports or as informal clothing
example: a pair of trainers

translation: 培训（学习工作所需技能的过程）
definition: the process of learning the skills that you need to do a job
example: staff training

translation: 特质，性格（性格中的特定品质）
definition: a particular quality in your personality
example: personality traits

translation: 交易（人与人之间进行的业务，尤指买卖行为）
definition: a piece of business that is done between people, especially an act of buying or selling
example: financial transactions between companies

translation: 誊本，录音文本（所言内容的文字或打印副本）
definition: a written or printed copy of words that have been spoken
example: a transcript of the interview

translation: 转让，转移（将某人/某物从一处、群体或工作移到另一处；及其过程）
definition: the act of moving somebody/something from one place, group or job to another; an occasion when this happens
example: electronic data transfer

translation: 转移，迁移（从一处移到另一处；使人/物移到另一处）
definition: to move from one place to another; to move something/somebody from one place to another
example: transfer (to something), The film studio is transferring to Hollywood.

translation: 改变，转化（改变某物的形式；在形式上发生改变）
definition: to change the form of something; to change in form
example: transform something/somebody (into something), The photochemical reactions transform the light into electrical impulses.

translation: 转变，变革（某人/某物的彻底改变）
definition: a complete change in somebody/something
example: The way in which we work has undergone a complete transformation in the past decade.

translation: 运输，过境（被移动或从一处运往另一处的过程）
definition: the process of being moved or carried from one place to another
example: The cost includes transit.

translation: 过渡，转变（从一种状态或状况改变为另一种的过程或时期）
definition: the process or a period of changing from one state or condition to another
example: transition from something to something, the transition from school to full-time work

translation: 翻译（以另一种语言表达言语或文字的含义）
definition: to express the meaning of speech or writing in a different language
example: translate something into something, He translated the letter into English.

translation: 翻译（将文字或言语改为另一种语言的过程）
definition: the process of changing something that is written or spoken into another language
example: an error in translation

translation: 传播，传递（将某物从一人、地、物传给另一人的行为或过程）
definition: the act or process of passing something from one person, place or thing to another
example: the transmission of the disease

translation: 传送，发射（发送电子信号、无线电或电视广播等）
definition: to send an electronic signal, radio or television broadcast, etc.
example: signals transmitted from a satellite

translation: 透明度（事物――如局面或论点――易于理解的特质）
definition: the quality of something, such as a situation or an argument, that makes it easy to understand
example: a need for greater transparency in legal documents

translation: 透明的（允许光线穿过、能看清背后的）
definition: allowing you to see through it
example: The insect's wings are almost transparent.

translation: 交通工具，运输（使用车辆、道路等将人或货从一处运往另一处的系统）
definition: a system for carrying people or goods from one place to another using vehicles, roads, etc.
example: air/freight/road transport

translation: 运输（使用车辆将人/物从一处带到另一处）
definition: to take something/somebody from one place to another in a vehicle
example: to transport goods/passengers

translation: 交通运输（使用车辆、道路等将人或货从一处运往另一处的系统）
definition: a system for carrying people or goods from one place to another using vehicles, roads, etc.
example: public transportation (= the system of buses, trains, etc. provided for people to travel from one place to another)

translation: 陷阱（用于捕捉动物的装置）
definition: a piece of equipment for catching animals
example: a fox with its leg in a trap

translation: 困住（将某人置于无法脱身的危险境地）
definition: to put somebody in a dangerous place that they cannot get out of
example: be trapped, Help! I'm trapped!

translation: 创伤，创伤（由严重震惊、压力或恐惧引起的精神状况，尤指后果长期存在时）
definition: a mental condition caused by severe shock, stress or fear, especially when the harmful effects last for a long time
example: the effects of trauma and stress on the body

translation: 旅行，旅游（旅行的动作或活动）
definition: the act or activity of travelling
example: air/rail/space travel

translation: 旅行（从一处到另一处，尤指长途旅行）
definition: to go from one place to another, especially over a long distance
example: I go to bed early if I'm travelling the next day.

translation: 旅客（正在旅行或经常旅行的人）
definition: a person who is travelling or who often travels
example: She is a frequent traveller to Belgium.

translation: 财宝，宝藏（金银、珠宝等贵重物品的集合）
definition: a collection of valuable things such as gold, silver and jewellery
example: buried treasure

translation: 对待，对待（以特定方式对待某人/某物）
definition: to behave in a particular way towards somebody/something
example: treat somebody/something with something, to treat people with respect

translation: 治疗（为了治愈疾病或使人感觉良好而采取的措施）
definition: something that is done to cure an illness or injury, or to make somebody look and feel good
example: The drug is used in the treatment of depression.

translation: 条约，协议（两国或多国间的正式协议）
definition: a formal agreement between two or more countries
example: the Treaty of Rome

translation: 树（长寿的高大植物，有木质主干和分出的枝叶）
definition: a tall plant that can live a long time. Trees have a thick central wooden trunk from which branches grow, usually with leaves on them
example: an oak/olive/apple tree

translation: 巨大的（极大的，如巨大的爆炸）
definition: very great
example: a tremendous explosion

translation: 趋势，趋向（局面改变或发展的总体方向）
definition: a general direction in which a situation is changing or developing
example: social/economic/political/demographic trends

translation: 假期，度假（旅行或休息离开家的一段时间）
definition: a period of time spent travelling or resting away from home
example: on vacation, They're on vacation in Hawaii right now.

translation: 真空（没有任何物质的空间，包括空气）
definition: a space that is completely empty of all substances, including all air or other gas
example: a vacuum pump (= one that creates a vacuum)

translation: 模糊的（脑中不清晰的印象或记忆）
definition: not clear in a person’s mind
example: to have a vague impression/memory/recollection of something

translation: 有效的（法律或官方认可的）
definition: that is legally or officially acceptable
example: Do you have a valid passport?

translation: 有效性（法律或官方认可的状态）
definition: the state of being legally or officially acceptable
example: The period of validity of the agreement has expired.

translation: 山谷（丘陵或山脉之间的低地，常有河流经）
definition: an area of low land between hills or mountains, often with a river flowing through it; the land that a river flows through
example: in a valley, In the valley below cows were grazing peacefully.

translation: 值钱的（值很多钱的）
definition: worth a lot of money
example: My home is my most valuable asset.

translation: 价值（某物所值的金钱或可交换的商品量）
definition: how much something is worth in money or other goods for which it can be exchanged
example: to go up/rise/increase in value

translation: 重视（认为某人/某事很重要）
definition: to think that somebody/something is important
example: value somebody/something, He has come to value her advice and support.

translation: 面包车，小型货车（有顶棚、后部无侧窗的载货或载人车辆）
definition: a covered vehicle with no side windows in its back half, usually smaller than a lorry, used for carrying goods or people
example: the driver of a white van

translation: 消失（突然或以无法解释的方式不见了）
definition: to disappear suddenly and/or in a way that you cannot explain
example: He turned around and vanished into the house.

translation: 多变的（经常变化的；易变的）
definition: often changing; likely to change
example: variable temperatures

translation: 变量（可以变化或被改变的情况、数字或数量）
definition: a situation, number or quantity that can vary or be varied
example: With so many variables, it is difficult to calculate the cost.

translation: 变化，变动（某物数量或水平的改变）
definition: a change, especially in the amount or level of something
example: The dial records very slight variations in pressure.

translation: 多样的（有很多不同类型的）
definition: of many different types
example: varied opinions

translation: 品种，多样化（同类事物的不同种类）
definition: several different sorts of the same thing
example: There is a wide variety of patterns to choose from.

translation: 各种各样的（几种不同的）
definition: several different
example: various types/forms/kinds of somebody/something

translation: 变化，各异（在大小、形状等方面彼此不同）
definition: to be different from each other in size, shape, etc.
example: New techniques were introduced with varying degrees of success.

translation: 巨大的（在面积、尺寸、数量等方面极大的）
definition: extremely large in area, size, amount, etc.
example: a vast area of forest

translation: 蔬菜（作为食物食用的植物或其一部分，如土豆、豆类）
definition: a plant or part of a plant that is eaten as food. Potatoes, beans and onions are all vegetables.
example: The children don't eat enough fresh vegetables.

translation: 车辆（用于运送人或货物的工具，如车、卡车）
definition: a thing that is used for transporting people or goods from one place to another, such as a car or lorry
example: motor vehicles (= cars, buses, lorries, etc.)

translation: 静脉（将全身血液输送回心脏的血管）
definition: any of the tubes that carry blood from all parts of the body towards the heart
example: the jugular vein

translation: 风险项目，企业（涉及冒险的商业项目或活动）
definition: a business project or activity, especially one that involves taking risks
example: A disastrous business venture lost him thousands of dollars.

translation: 冒险去（去某处，尽管知道可能危险或不快）
definition: to go somewhere even though you know that it might be dangerous or unpleasant
example: They ventured nervously into the water.

translation: 场地，场馆（为有组织活动――如音乐会、会议――提供的地点）
definition: a place where people meet for an organized event, for example a concert, sporting event or conference
example: The band will be playing at 20 different venues on their UK tour.

translation: 口头的（与言语相关的）
definition: relating to words
example: The job applicant must have good verbal skills.

translation: 判决（法庭或死因调查做出的正式裁决）
definition: an official judgement made in court or at an inquest (= an official investigation into somebody's death)
example: Has the jury reached a verdict?

translation: 核实（核实某事是否真实或准确）
definition: to check that something is true or accurate
example: verify something, We have no way of verifying his story.

translation: 诗，韵文（按行排列、常带规律节奏或押韵的写作）
definition: writing that is arranged in lines, often with a regular rhythm or pattern of rhyme
example: in verse, Most of the play is written in verse, but some of it is in prose.

translation: 版本（与早期形式或其他形式略有不同的事物形式）
definition: a form of something that is slightly different from an earlier form or from other forms of the same thing
example: version of something, the latest version of the software package

translation: 对抗（用于表示两队或两方竞争）
definition: used to show that two teams or sides are against each other
example: It is France versus Brazil in the final.

translation: 垂直的（在平整表面上直上直下或从顶到底的）
definition: going straight up or down from a level surface or from top to bottom in a picture, etc.
example: the vertical axis of the graph

translation: 正是那个（用于强调正在谈论特定的那一个）
definition: used to emphasize that you are talking about a particular thing or person and not about another
example: He might be phoning her at this very moment.

translation: 非常（用于形容词、副词前表示程度极高）
definition: used before adjectives, adverbs and determiners to mean ‘in a high degree’ or ‘extremely’
example: Very few people know that.

translation: 血管，导管（体内输送血液的管道或植物中输送液体的部分）
definition: a tube that carries blood through the body of a person or an animal, or liquid through the parts of a plant
example: to burst/rupture a blood vessel

translation: 老兵，老手（在特定领域或活动中经验丰富的人）
definition: a person who has a lot of experience in a particular area or activity
example: the veteran American actor, Clint Eastwood

translation: 经由（通过某个地方）
definition: through a place
example: We flew home via Dubai.

translation: 可行的（可以做成的；会成功的）
definition: that can be done; that will be successful
example: a viable option/proposition

translation: 充满活力的（充满生命力和能量的）
definition: full of life and energy
example: a vibrant city

translation: 恶习，黄赌毒（涉及性或毒品的犯罪活动）
definition: criminal activities that involve sex or drugs
example: At the door were two plain-clothes detectives from the vice squad.

translation: 邪恶的，残忍的（暴力且残忍的）
definition: violent and cruel
example: a vicious attack

translation: 受害者（由于犯罪、疾病或事故而受害、受伤或丧命的人）
definition: a person who has been attacked, injured or killed as the result of a crime, a disease, an accident, etc.
example: shooting/murder victims

translation: 胜利（比赛、选举或战争中的成功）
definition: success in a game, an election, a war, etc.
example: to win a narrow victory

translation: 视频（录制音画的系统；或存储的数据）
definition: a system of recording moving pictures and sound, either using a digital method of storing data or (in the past) using videotape
example: A wedding is the perfect subject for video.

translation: 景色，视图（从特定位置能看到的，尤指美丽的乡间景色）
definition: what you can see from a particular place or position, especially beautiful countryside

translation: 看待（以特定方式思考某人/某事）
definition: to think about somebody/something in a particular way
example: view somebody/something + adv./prep., How do you view your position within the company?

translation: 观众（观看电视或网络视频的人）
definition: a person watching television or a video on the internet
example: The programme attracted millions of viewers.

translation: 观点（思考某一主题的方式）
definition: a way of thinking about a subject
example: from a… viewpoint, Try looking at things from a different viewpoint.

translation: 村庄（位于乡村的极小城镇）
definition: a very small town located in a country area
example: We visited towns and villages all over Spain.

translation: 村民（住在村庄里的人）
definition: a person who lives in a village
example: Some of the villagers have lived here all their lives.

translation: 违反（违背或拒绝遵守法律、协议等）
definition: to go against or refuse to obey a law, an agreement, etc.

translation: 违反，违背（违背或拒绝遵守法律、协议等的行为）
definition: the act of going against or refusing to obey a law, an agreement, etc.
example: They were in open violation of the treaty.

translation: 暴力，暴行（旨在伤害或杀害他人的暴力行为）
definition: violent behaviour that is intended to hurt or kill somebody
example: Police do not think this killing was a random act of violence.

translation: 暴力的（涉及或由物理武力造成的，旨在伤人）
definition: involving or caused by physical force that is intended to hurt or kill somebody
example: violent crime/criminals

translation: 虚拟的（通过电脑软件模拟出的，如互联网上的虚拟环境）
definition: made to appear to exist by the use of computer software, for example on the internet
example: a system to help programmers create virtual environments

translation: 美德，德行（表现出高道德标准的行为或态度）
definition: behaviour or attitudes that show high moral standards
example: He led a life of virtue.

translation: 病毒（显微镜下可见的、能引起疾病的极微小生物）
definition: a living thing, too small to be seen without a microscope, that causes disease in people, animals and plants
example: the flu/influenza virus

translation: 签证（外国官员在护照上加盖的准许出入境或过境的印记）
definition: a stamp or mark put in your passport by officials of a foreign country that gives you permission to enter, pass through or leave their country
example: to apply for a visa

translation: 可见的（能被看见的）
definition: that can be seen
example: The house is clearly visible from the beach.

translation: 视力，视觉（看的能力；或从特定位置看到的区域）
definition: the ability to see; the area that you can see from a particular position
example: to have good/perfect/poor/blurred/normal vision

translation: 访问，参观（去见人或看地方的一段时间）
definition: an occasion or a period of time when somebody goes to see a place or person and spends time there
example: a two-day/three-day visit

translation: 访问，拜访（去见人或看地方一段时间）
definition: to go to see a person or a place for a period of time
example: My parents are coming to visit me next week.

translation: 访客，客人（访问人或地方的人）
definition: a person who visits a person or place
example: We've got visitors coming this weekend.

translation: 视觉的（与看或视力相关的，如视觉艺术）
definition: of or connected with seeing or sight
example: the visual arts

translation: 至关重要的（为了成功或生存所必需的）
definition: necessary or essential in order for something to succeed or exist
example: vital for somebody/something, the vitamins that are vital for health

translation: 维生素（食物中发现的维持人类生长和健康的必需自然物质）
definition: a natural substance found in food that is an essential part of what humans and animals need to help them grow and stay healthy. There are many different vitamins.
example: vitamin A/B/D/E

translation: 嗓音的，口头的（与嗓音相关的，如声乐）
definition: connected with the voice
example: vocal music

translation: 声音，嗓音（人说话或唱歌时通过嘴发出的声音）
definition: the sound or sounds produced through the mouth by a person speaking or singing
example: I could hear voices in the next room.

translation: 体积，容量（物体或物质填充的空间量；或容器的容量）
definition: the amount of space that an object or a substance fills; the amount of space that a container has
example: volume of something, How do you measure the volume of a gas?

translation: 自愿的（自愿进行的，而非被迫的）
definition: done willingly, not because you are forced
example: a voluntary agreement

translation: 志愿者（无偿从事工作的人）
definition: a person who does a job without being paid for it
example: Schools need volunteers to help children to read.

translation: 自愿做（自愿提供服务而不获取报酬）
definition: to offer to do something without being forced to do it or without getting paid for it
example: He has been volunteering for 11 years now.

translation: 选票，投票（在选举中决定的正式选择）
definition: a formal choice that you make in an election or at a meeting in order to choose somebody or decide something
example: to win/lose votes

translation: 投票（通过标记纸张或举手正式选出人或决定方案）
definition: to show formally by marking a paper, raising your hand, using a voting machine, etc. which person you want to win an election, or which plan or idea you support
example: How did you vote at the last election?

translation: 投票（在选举或会议中选择人/事的过程）
definition: the action of choosing somebody/something in an election or at a meeting
example: He was eliminated in the first round of voting.

translation: 发誓（做出正式且严肃的承诺）
definition: to make a formal and serious promise to do something or a formal statement that is true
example: vow to do something, She vowed never to speak to him again.

translation: 脆弱性，易受伤害性（身体或情感上虚弱、易受伤害的事实）
definition: the fact of being weak and easily hurt physically or emotionally
example: the vulnerability of newborn babies to disease

translation: 脆弱的，易受伤害的（身体或情感上虚弱且易受伤害的）
definition: weak and easily hurt physically or emotionally
example: These offices are highly vulnerable to terrorist attack.

translation: 工资（因工作定期赚取的钱，通常按周或按月）
definition: a regular amount of money that you earn, usually every week or every month, for work or services
example: wage/wages of something, wages of ￡300 a week

translation: 等待（等待的行为或时间）
definition: an act of waiting; an amount of time waited
example: The wait seemed interminable.

translation: 等待（留在原处直至人/物到来或某事发生）
definition: to stay where you are or delay doing something until somebody/something comes or something happens
example: She rang the bell and waited.

translation: 服务员（在餐厅桌旁为顾客服务的人）
definition: a man whose job is to serve customers at their tables in a restaurant, etc.
example: I'll ask the waiter for the bill.

translation: 醒来，唤醒（停止睡觉；使人停止睡觉）
definition: to stop sleeping; to make somebody stop sleeping
example: I always wake early in the summer.

translation: 散步（步行的一段路程，尤指为了娱乐或锻炼）
definition: a journey on foot, usually for pleasure or exercise
example: Let's go for a walk.

translation: 走，步行（脚着地交替移动而不跑动）
definition: to move or go somewhere by putting one foot in front of the other on the ground, but without running
example: The baby is just learning to walk.

translation: 墙，围墙（地面上直立的石、砖结构，用于包围或分隔土地）
definition: a long, solid structure that rises straight up from the ground, made of stone, brick or concrete, that surrounds, divides or protects an area of land
example: to build a wall

translation: 漫步，闲逛（在某处缓慢走动，通常无明确目的）
definition: to walk slowly around or to a place, often without any particular sense of purpose or direction
example: #NAME?

translation: 想要（对某人/某物有欲望或愿望）
definition: to have a desire or a wish for something/somebody
example: want somebody/something, Do you want some more tea?

translation: 战争（两国或两组人间持续一段时间的战斗状态）
definition: a situation in which two or more countries or groups of people fight against each other over a period of time
example: the Second World War

translation: 病房（医院中为患有同类疾病的人准备的独立房间或区域）
definition: a separate room or area in a hospital for people with the same type of medical condition
example: a maternity/surgical/psychiatric/children’s ward

translation: 仓库（存放大量货物的建筑，尤指销售前）
definition: a building where large quantities of goods are stored, especially before they are sent to shops to be sold
example: Police are investigating a fire at a furniture warehouse.

translation: 战争，战斗（进行战争的活动，尤指使用特定武器方法）
definition: the activity of fighting a war, especially using particular weapons or methods
example: air/naval/guerrilla warfare

translation: 温暖的（温度较高且令人愉快的，非热或冷）
definition: at a fairly high temperature in a way that is pleasant, rather than being hot or cold
example: warm weather/temperatures/air

translation: 变暖（使某人/某物变温暖）
definition: to make something/somebody warm or warmer; to become warm or warmer
example: warm something/somebody/yourself, Come in and warm yourself by the fire.

translation: 变暖（变得或使之变温暖的过程）
definition: the process of making something, or of becoming, warm or warmer
example: atmospheric warming

translation: 警告（告知某人可能发生的危险或不快之事，以便避开）
definition: to tell somebody about something, especially something dangerous or unpleasant that is likely to happen, so that they can avoid it
example: warn somebody, I tried to warn him, but he wouldn't listen.

translation: 警告（告知未来可能发生坏事的陈述或事件）
definition: a statement, an event, etc. telling somebody that something bad or unpleasant may happen in the future so that they can try to avoid it
example: I had absolutely no warning.

translation: 搜查令，授权令（由法官签署的给予警察执行权力的法律文件）
definition: a legal document that is signed by a judge and gives the police authority to do something
example: an arrest warrant

translation: 使有必要（在特定情况下使某事成为必要或恰当）
definition: to make something necessary or appropriate in a particular situation
example: warrant something, Further investigation is clearly warranted.

translation: 武士，战士（尤指过去，在战斗或战争中奋斗的人）
definition: (especially in the past) a person who fights in a battle or war
example: a warrior nation (= whose people are skilled in fighting)

translation: 洗涤（使用水和肥皂清洁某人/某物的行为）
definition: an act of cleaning somebody/something using water and usually soap
example: These towels are ready for a wash.

translation: 洗（用水和肥皂清洁人或物）
definition: to make something/somebody clean using water and usually soap
example: wash something/somebody, These jeans need washing.

translation: 洗涤，洗（洗的行为）
definition: the act of cleaning something using water and usually soap
example: a gentle shampoo for frequent washing

translation: 废弃的，废物的（不再需要并因此被丢弃的）
definition: no longer needed for a particular process and therefore thrown away
example: the disposal of waste material

translation: 浪费（不小心或不必要地使用某物导致其损失的行为）
definition: the act of using something in a careless or unnecessary way, causing it to be lost or destroyed
example: I hate unnecessary waste.

translation: 浪费（使用超出必需或有用的量）
definition: to use more of something than is necessary or useful
example: waste something, Stop wasting time and just get on with it!

translation: 手表（戴在手腕上的小钟）
definition: a type of small clock that you wear on your wrist, or (in the past) carried in your pocket
example: She kept looking anxiously at her watch.

translation: 观看（看着某人/某物一段时间，关注发生的事）
definition: to look at somebody/something for a time, paying attention to what happens
example: watch somebody/something, I was in the living room, watching TV.

translation: 水（无色无味的液体，用于饮用、洗涤等）
definition: a liquid without colour, smell or taste that falls as rain, is in lakes, rivers and seas, and is used for drinking, washing, etc.
example: a glass of water

translation: 浇水（给植物等浇水）
definition: to pour water on plants, etc.
example: to water the plants/garden

translation: 浪，波浪（海面、洋面等移动的隆起水线）
definition: a raised line of water that moves across the surface of the sea, ocean, etc.
example: Huge waves were breaking on the shore.

translation: 挥手，挥动（在空中左右移动手/臂以吸引注意或打招呼）
definition: to move your hand or arm from side to side in the air in order to attract attention, say hello, etc.
example: The people on the bus waved and we waved back.

translation: 非常，远（距离很远；或程度很大）
definition: very far; by a large amount
example: She finished the race way ahead of the other runners.

translation: 方法，方式（做事的方式、风格或态度）
definition: a method, style or manner of doing something
example: I prefer to do things the easy way.

translation: 我们（代指说话者及他人）
definition: I and another person or other people; I and you
example: We've moved to Atlanta.

translation: 虚弱的（身体不强壮的）
definition: not physically strong
example: She is still weak after her illness.

translation: 变弱（使某人/某物变得更没力气或更不强壮）
definition: to make somebody/something less strong or powerful; to become less strong or powerful
example: The team has been weakened by injury.

translation: 虚弱（体力不足的品质）
definition: lack of physical strength
example: The disease causes progressive muscle weakness.

translation: 财富（个人或国家拥有的金钱、财产等总量）
definition: a large amount of money, property, etc. that a person or country owns
example: the desire to gain wealth and power

translation: 富有的（拥有大量金钱、财产等的）
definition: having a lot of money, possessions, etc.
example: a wealthy businessman/individual/family

translation: 武器（刀、枪、炸弹等用于战斗或攻击的工具）
definition: an object such as a knife, gun, bomb, etc. that is used for fighting or attacking somebody
example: Modern nuclear weapons are much more destructive than either biological or chemical weapons.

translation: 穿，戴（在身上穿着衣物或戴着饰品）
definition: to have something on your body as a piece of clothing, a decoration, etc.
example: He was wearing a new suit.

translation: 天气（特定时间和地点的天气状况，如温度、雨、阳光等）
definition: the condition of the atmosphere at a particular place and time, such as the temperature, and if there is wind, rain, sun, etc.
example: cold/hot/warm/wet/dry weather

translation: 编织（手工或用机器将线、条交织成布、地毯或篮子）
definition: to make cloth, a carpet, a basket, etc. by crossing threads or narrow pieces of material across, over and under each other by hand or on a machine called a loom
example: weave A from B, The baskets are woven from strips of willow.

translation: 网络（互联网上文档相互连接的系统）
definition: a system for finding information on the internet, in which documents are connected to other documents
example: to surf/browse/search the web

translation: 网站（公司、组织或个人在互联网上放置信息的一组页面）
definition: a set of pages on the internet, where a company or an organization, or an individual person, puts information
example: For current prices please visit our website.

translation: 婚礼（结婚仪式及随后的宴会聚会）
definition: a marriage ceremony, and the meal or party that usually follows it
example: I dreamed of having a big wedding, with all my family and friends.

translation: 星期三（周二之后、周四之前的一天）
definition: the day of the week after Tuesday and before Thursday
example: It's Wednesday today, isn't it?

translation: 杂草（生长在不想要之处的野生植物，尤指在庄稼中）
definition: a wild plant growing where it is not wanted, especially among crops or garden plants
example: The yard was overgrown with weeds.

translation: 星期，周（七天的时间段）
definition: a period of seven days, either from Monday to Sunday or from Sunday to Saturday
example: last/this/next week

translation: 周末（周六和周日）
definition: Saturday and Sunday
example: this/next/last weekend

translation: 每周的（每周发生、执行或出版一次的）
definition: happening, done or published once a week or every week
example: weekly meetings

translation: 称重（具有特定的重量）
definition: to have a particular weight
example: How much do you weigh (= how heavy are you)?

translation: 重量（某人或某物有多重，单位如公斤、磅）
definition: how heavy somebody/something is, which can be measured in, for example, kilograms or pounds
example: in weight, It is about 76 kilos in weight.

translation: 离奇的，古怪的（非常奇怪且难以解释的）
definition: very strange or unusual and difficult to explain
example: I had a really weird dream last night.

translation: 受欢迎的（被某处接受或欢迎的）
definition: accepted or wanted somewhere
example: I'll go, then. I know when I'm not welcome.

translation: 欢迎（用于打招呼表示对他人到场感到高兴）
definition: used as a greeting to tell somebody that you are pleased that they are there
example: Welcome home!

translation: 欢迎（对他人的到来所做的言行，使其感到高兴）
definition: something that you do or say to somebody when they arrive, especially something that makes them feel you are happy to see them
example: to get/receive a welcome

translation: 欢迎（在某人到达时友好地打招呼）
definition: to say hello to somebody in a friendly way when they arrive somewhere
example: welcome somebody, They were at the door to welcome us.

translation: 福利，福祉（人、动物或群体的健康、幸福和安全状况）
definition: the general health, happiness and safety of a person, an animal or a group
example: We are concerned about the child's welfare.

translation: 健康的（身体健康的）
definition: in good health
example: I don't feel very well.

translation: 好，正确地（以好的、正确的或可接受的方式）
definition: in a good, right or acceptable way
example: They played well in the tournament.

translation: （感叹词）好（用于表示惊讶、愤怒或宽慰）
definition: used to express surprise, anger or relief
example: Well, well―I would never have guessed it!

translation: 井（地面上获取水的深洞）
definition: a deep hole in the ground from which people obtain water. The sides of wells are usually covered with brick or stone and there is usually a cover or a small wall at the top of the well.
example: to dig/sink a well

translation: 幸福，安康（总体的健康和快乐状态）
definition: general health and happiness

translation: 西方的（在西方或向西的）

translation: 向西（朝向西方）

example: This room faces west.

translation: 西方（看日落时的方向；罗盘四个主要点之一）
definition: the direction that you look towards to see the sun go down; one of the four main points of the compass
example: Which way is west?

translation: 西方的（位于西方或面向西方的）
definition: located in the west or facing west
example: western Spain

translation: 潮湿的（被水覆盖或含有液体的）
definition: covered with or containing liquid, especially water
example: wet clothes/hair/grass

translation: 什么（疑问词，用于询问特定信息）
definition: used in questions to ask for particular information about somebody/something
example: What is your name?

translation: 什么（疑问词，用于询问特定信息）
definition: used in questions to ask for particular information about somebody/something
example: What is your name?

translation: 无论什么（一点也不；没有任何种类的）
definition: not at all; not of any kind
example: They received no help whatever.

translation: 任何，一切（任何一个或每一个；任何事或一切事）
definition: any or every; anything or everything
example: Take whatever action is needed.

translation: 任何，一切（任何一个或每一个；任何事或一切事）
definition: any or every; anything or everything
example: Take whatever action is needed.

translation: 一点也不（用于强调否定，意为“任何都不”）
definition: not at all; not of any kind
example: They received no help whatsoever.

translation: 小麦（一种谷类植物；其磨成的粉用于制作面包面条）
definition: a plant grown for its grain that is used to produce the flour for bread, cakes, pasta, etc.; the grain of this plant
example: wheat flour

translation: 轮子（车、自行车等下方移动时转动的圆状物）
definition: one of the round objects under a car, bicycle, bus, etc. that turns when it moves
example: He braked suddenly, causing the front wheels to skid.

translation: 什么时候（在什么时间；在什么场合）
definition: at what time; on what occasion
example: When did you last see him?

translation: 当...时（在...的时间里）
definition: at or during the time that
example: I loved history when I was at school.

translation: 什么时候（什么时间）
definition: what/which time
example: Until when can you stay?

translation: 每当，无论何时（在任何时间；在任何场合）
definition: at any time that; on any occasion that
example: You can ask for help whenever you need it.

translation: 在哪里（在什么地方或情况下）
definition: in or to what place or situation
example: Where do you live?

translation: 在...的地方（在那个地方或情况下）
definition: (in) the place or situation in which
example: This is where I live.

translation: 然而，而（用于对比两个事实）
definition: used to compare or contrast two facts
example: Some of the studies show positive results, whereas others do not.

translation: 凭此（借此；由于该原因）
definition: by which; because of which
example: They have introduced a new system whereby all employees must undergo regular training.

translation: 无论在哪里（在任何地方）
definition: in any place
example: Sit wherever you like.

translation: 是否（用于表示两个可能性之间的怀疑或选择）
definition: used to express a doubt or choice between two possibilities
example: He seemed undecided whether to go or stay.

translation: 哪个（疑问词，用于从有限数量中选出确切的）
definition: used in questions to ask somebody to be exact about one or more people or things from a limited number
example: Which is better exercise―swimming or tennis?

translation: 哪个（疑问词，用于从有限数量中选出确切的）
definition: used in questions to ask somebody to be exact about one or more people or things from a limited number
example: Which is better exercise―swimming or tennis?

translation: 当...时，而（在某事发生的时间里；或表示对比）
definition: during the time that something is happening; at the same time as something else is happening
example: We must have been burgled while we were asleep.

translation: 一段时间（一段时间）
definition: a period of time
example: for a while, I only stayed for a short while.

translation: 当...时（while的更正式形式）
definition: during the time that something is happening; at the same time as something else is happening
example: In the UK it is illegal to drive whilst holding a mobile phone.

translation: 鞭打（作为惩罚或为了加速而用力抽打人或动物）
definition: to hit a person or an animal hard with a whip, as a punishment or to make them go faster or work harder
example: He was taken back to the jail and soundly whipped.

translation: 耳语（低沉安静的声音；或其发出的响声）
definition: a low, quiet voice or the sound it makes
example: in a whisper, ‘I love you,’ he said in a whisper.

translation: 低声说（极安静地说话以便他人听不见）
definition: to speak very quietly to somebody so that other people cannot hear what you are saying
example: Don't you know it's rude to whisper?

translation: 白色的（新鲜积雪或牛奶的颜色）

translation: 白色（新鲜积雪或牛奶的颜色）
definition: the colour of fresh snow or of milk

translation: 谁（疑问词，询问一人或多人的名字、身份或功能）
definition: used in questions to ask about the name, identity or function of one or more people
example: Who is that woman?

translation: 无论谁（那个人或那些人；任何的人）
definition: the person or people who; any person who
example: Whoever says that is a liar.

translation: 整个的，全部的（完整的；全部的）
definition: full; complete
example: Let's forget the whole thing.

translation: 整个，全部（某事物的全部）
definition: all that there is of something
example: The scheme would cover the whole of the UK.

translation: 完全地（彻底地）
definition: completely
example: wholly inappropriate behaviour

translation: 谁（who的宾格，作为动词或介词的宾语）
definition: used instead of ‘who’ as the object of a verb or preposition
example: Whom did they invite?

translation: 谁的（疑问词，询问某物属于谁）
definition: used in questions to ask who something belongs to
example: Whose house is that?

translation: 谁的（疑问词，询问某物属于谁）
definition: used in questions to ask who something belongs to
example: Whose house is that?

translation: 为什么（疑问词，询问原因或目的）
definition: used in questions to ask the reason for or purpose of something
example: Why were you late?

translation: 宽的（两边间距离大的）
definition: measuring a large distance from one side to the other
example: It's a wide, fast-flowing river.

translation: 广泛地（被很多人地；或在很多地方地）
definition: by a lot of people; in or to many places
example: The term is widely used in everyday speech.

translation: 变宽（变得或使之变得更宽）
definition: to become wider; to make something wider
example: Her eyes widened in surprise.

translation: 广泛的（存在于大面积或多人之间的）
definition: existing or happening over a large area or among many people
example: The storm caused widespread damage.

translation: 寡妇，鳏夫（配偶去世后未再婚的女性/男性）
definition: a woman whose husband or wife has died and who has not married again
example: She gets a widow’s pension.

translation: 宽度（一侧到另一侧的度量；多宽）
definition: the measurement from one side of something to the other; how wide something is
example: The terrace runs the full width of the house.

translation: 妻子（某人与其结婚的女性；已婚女性）
definition: the woman that somebody is married to; a married woman
example: I met my wife at university.

translation: 野生的（在自然条件下生长生活的；非家养的）
definition: living or growing in natural conditions; not kept in a house or on a farm
example: wild animals/birds/flowers

translation: 野生动物（生活在自然环境中的野生动植物）
definition: animals, birds, insects, etc. that are wild and live in a natural environment
example: policies designed to protect wildlife

translation: 意志（控制思想行为以实现目标的这种能力；坚定的愿望）
definition: the ability to control your thoughts and actions in order to achieve what you want to do; a strong and determined desire to do something that you want to do
example: to have a strong will

translation: 将要（用于谈论或预测未来）
definition: used for talking about or predicting the future
example: You'll be in time if you hurry.

translation: 乐意的（不反对做某事的；无理由不做的）
definition: not objecting to doing something; having no reason for not doing something
example: Many consumers are willing to pay more for organic food

translation: 意愿（快乐且准备好做某事的特质）
definition: the quality of being happy and ready to do something
example: Success in studying depends on a willingness to learn.

translation: 胜利（在比赛或战争中的成功）
definition: a victory in a game, contest, etc.
example: two wins and three defeats

translation: 赢（在竞赛或战斗中成为最成功的那个）
definition: to be the most successful in a competition, race, battle, etc.
example: Which team won?

translation: 风（空气在地球表面的流动）
蜿蜒（有很多弯曲；绕圈子）
definition: to have many bends and twists
example: wind + adv./prep., The path wound down to the beach.

translation: 窗户（墙或屋顶上的开口，通常覆盖玻璃，供采光通风及观察）
definition: an opening in the wall or roof of a building, car, etc., usually covered with glass, that allows light and air to come in and people to see out; the glass in a window
example: out of the window, She looked out of the window.

translation: 葡萄酒（葡萄汁发酵制成的酒精饮料）
definition: an alcoholic drink made from the juice of grapes that has been left to ferment. There are many different kinds of wine.
example: sparkling wine

translation: 翅膀（鸟、昆虫或蝙蝠身上用于飞行的部分）
definition: one of the parts of the body of a bird, insect or bat that it uses for flying

translation: 获胜者（赢得某事的人、团队或动物）
definition: a person, a team, an animal, etc. that wins something
example: The lucky winner gets an all-expenses-paid trip to Sydney.

translation: 冬天，冬季（一年中最冷的季节，在秋冬之间）
definition: the coldest season of the year, between autumn and spring
example: a cold/mild/harsh winter

translation: 擦拭（将某物在表面揉搓以去除污垢；清洁表面）
definition: to rub something against a surface, in order to remove dirt or liquid from it; to rub a surface with a cloth, etc. in order to clean it
example: wipe something (on something), Please wipe your feet on the mat.

translation: 电线，金属线（细长绳状的金属；及其一段）
definition: metal in the form of thin thread; a piece of this
example: a coil of copper wire

translation: 智慧（因经验丰富而能做出明智决定并给出建议的能力）
definition: the ability to make sensible decisions and give good advice because of the experience and knowledge that you have
example: She was known to be a woman of great wisdom.

translation: 明智的（能根据经验做出明智决定并给出建议的）
definition: able to make sensible decisions and give good advice because of the experience and knowledge that you have
example: a wise man

translation: 祝愿（尤用于信件或贺卡，祝他人快乐、健康等）
definition: used especially in a letter, email or card to say that you hope that somebody will be happy, well or successful
example: Give my good wishes to the family.

translation: 希望（想要某事发生，尽管可能非事实或不可能）
definition: to want something to happen or to be true even though it is unlikely or impossible
example: wish (that)…, I wish I were taller.

translation: 风趣，才智（言谈精辟且幽默的能力）
definition: the ability to say or write things that are both clever and humorous
example: to have a quick/sharp/dry/ready wit

translation: 与...一起（在他人陪伴或到场的情况下）
definition: in the company or presence of somebody/something

translation: 取回，撤回（从银行账户取钱；或撤回陈述）
definition: to take money out of a bank account
example: withdraw something, With this account, you can withdraw up to ￡300 a day.

translation: 取款，撤回（从账户取钱的行为；或撤回的行为）
definition: the act of taking an amount of money out of your bank account
example: You can make withdrawals of up to $250 a day.

translation: 在...之内（在特定时段结束前；在特定范围内）
definition: before a particular period of time has passed; during a particular period of time

translation: 没有，无（未具有、未经历或未展示出某物）
definition: not having, experiencing or showing something

translation: 证人（目击事件并能向他人描述的人）
definition: a person who sees something happen and is able to describe it to other people
example: He failed to interview a key witness.

translation: 目击（看到某事发生，通常指犯罪或事故）
definition: to see something happen (typically a crime or an accident)
example: to witness an accident/a murder/an attack

translation: 女人（成年女性人类）
definition: an adult female human
example: a 54-year-old woman

translation: 奇迹，惊奇（看到美丽、不寻常之物时的惊讶和愉悦感）
definition: a feeling of surprise and pleasure that you have when you see or experience something beautiful, unusual or unexpected

definition: to think about something and try to decide what is true, what will happen, what you should do, etc.

translation: 极好的（非常好的、愉快的或有趣的）
definition: very good, pleasant or a lot of fun

translation: 木头，木材（树干和树枝的坚硬材料；这种建筑材料或燃料）
definition: the hard material that the trunk and branches of a tree are made of; this material when it is used to build or make things with, or as a fuel
example: He chopped some wood for the fire.

translation: 木制的（由木头制成的）
definition: made of wood
example: a wooden box/door/floor

translation: 羊毛（覆盖在羊等动物身上的柔软毛发）
definition: the soft hair that covers the body of sheep and some other animals

translation: 单词（具有特定含义、可口头或书面表达的语言单位）

translation: 工作，劳动（为了赚钱而从事的职业或任务）
definition: the job that a person does especially in order to earn money

translation: 工作（从事体力或脑力劳动，尤指作为职业）

translation: 工人（从事工作的人，尤指特定种类的工人）
definition: a person who works, especially one who does a particular kind of work
example: farm/factory/office workers

translation: 全体员工（组织中所有的工作人员）
definition: all the people who work for a particular company, organization, etc.
example: The factory has a 1?000-strong workforce.

translation: 工作的（正在从事有偿职业的）
definition: having a job for which you are paid
example: the working population

translation: 锻炼，健身（为了保持体型进行的体育锻炼）
definition: a period of physical exercise that you do to keep fit
example: She does a 20-minute workout every morning.

translation: 工作场所（人们工作的办公室、工厂等）
definition: the office, factory, etc. where people work
example: the introduction of new technology into the workplace

translation: 研讨会，车间（分享知识经验的讨论和实践课程；或车间）
definition: a period of discussion and practical work on a particular subject, in which a group of people share their knowledge and experience
example: There will be the opportunity for practical theatre work in drama workshops.

translation: 世界（地球及其所有国家、民族和自然特征）
definition: the earth, with all its countries, peoples and natural features
example: a map of the world

translation: 世界范围的（影响世界所有部分的）
definition: affecting all parts of the world
example: an increase in worldwide sales

translation: 在世界各地（在世界的所有部分）
definition: affecting all parts of the world
example: an increase in worldwide sales

translation: 蠕虫，虫子（长而细、身体柔软、无骨无足的生物）
definition: a long, thin creature with a soft body and no bones or legs
example: birds looking for worms

translation: 担心的（想到不快之事而感到不快乐和害怕的）
definition: thinking about unpleasant things that have happened or that might happen and therefore feeling unhappy and afraid
example: Don't look so worried!

translation: 担心，忧虑（对某事感到忧虑的状态）
definition: the state of worrying about something
example: The threat of losing their jobs is a constant source of worry to them.

translation: 担心，忧虑（一直想着不快之事或所持有的问题）
definition: to keep thinking about unpleasant things that might happen or about problems that you have
example: Don't worry. We have plenty of time.

translation: 更糟的（质量更差的；更不愉快的）
definition: of poorer quality or lower standard; more unpleasant
example: The rooms were awful and the food was worse.

translation: 更糟地（更差地）
definition: less well
example: Working-class children fared rather worse.

translation: 更糟的事（更多的问题或更坏的消息）
definition: more problems or bad news
example: I'm afraid there is worse to come.

translation: 崇拜，礼拜（对神灵表示尊重的行为，如祈祷、唱歌；这种仪式）
definition: the practice of showing respect for God or a god, by saying prayers, singing with others, etc.; a ceremony for this
example: an act/a place of worship

translation: 崇拜，礼拜（通过祈祷、唱歌等对神灵表示尊重）
definition: to show respect for God or a god, especially by saying prayers, singing, etc. with other people in a religious building
example: The Mayans built jungle pyramids to worship their gods.

translation: 最糟的（质量最差的；排在所有同类之后最不愉快的）
definition: of the poorest quality or lowest standard; worse than any other person or thing of a similar kind
example: It was by far the worst speech he had ever made.

translation: 最糟地（最坏地；最严重地）
definition: most badly or seriously
example: He was voted the worst dressed celebrity.

translation: 最坏的情况（可能发生的最严重或最不愉快的事）
definition: the most serious or unpleasant thing that could happen; the part, situation, possibility, etc. that is worse than any other
example: When they did not hear from her, they feared the worst.

translation: 值得（具有金钱等方面的价值）
definition: having a value in money, etc.
example: Our house is worth about ￡100?000.

translation: 价值（具有提到价值的某物的数量）
definition: an amount of something that has the value mentioned
example: The winner will receive fifty pounds' worth of books.

translation: 值得做的（重要的、愉快的或值得投入时间精力的）
definition: important, pleasant, interesting, etc.; worth spending time, money or effort on
example: It was in aid of a worthwhile cause (= a charity, etc.).

translation: 值得的（具备值得他人关注或相关品质的）
definition: having the qualities that deserve somebody/something
example: Very few of his ideas are worthy of further attention.

translation: （情态动词）愿意（用于礼貌地提议或邀请）
definition: used in polite offers or invitations
example: Would you like a sandwich?

translation: 伤口，伤（身体上的伤害，尤指被武器刺破皮肤）
definition: an injury to part of the body, especially one in which a hole is made in the skin using a weapon
example: a gunshot/stab wound

translation: 使受伤（伤害身体部位，尤指被武器刺破皮肤）
definition: to injure part of the body, especially by making a hole in the skin using a weapon
example: He had been wounded in the arm.

translation: 哇（感叹词，用于表示惊讶或印象深刻）
definition: used to show that you are very surprised or impressed by somebody/something
example: Wow! You look terrific!

translation: 包裹（将某物完全用纸等材料覆盖，如作为礼物）
definition: to cover something completely in paper or other material, for example when you are giving it as a present
example: wrap something up, He spent the evening wrapping up the Christmas presents.

translation: 手腕（连接手和手臂的关节）
definition: the joint between the hand and the arm
example: She's broken her wrist.

translation: 写（在表面上写下字母或数字，尤指用笔）
definition: to make letters or numbers on a surface, especially using a pen or a pencil
example: In some countries children don't start learning to read and write until they are six.

translation: 作家（以写作――如书籍、故事――为职业的人）
definition: a person whose job is writing books, stories, articles, etc.
example: Who's your favourite writer?

translation: 写作（书写的活动，与读、说相对）
definition: the activity of writing, in contrast to reading, speaking, etc.
example: Our son’s having problems with his reading and writing (= at school)

translation: 书面的（以书写而非口头表达的）
definition: expressed in writing rather than in speech
example: Having a written record of what I've done is very valuable.

translation: 错误的（不正确的；非事实的）
definition: not right or correct
example: I got all the answers wrong.

translation: 错误地（以产生不正确结果的方式）
definition: in a way that produces a result that is not correct or that you do not want
example: My name is spelt wrong.

translation: 错误，邪恶（不诚实或道德上不可接受的行为）
definition: behaviour that is not honest or morally acceptable
example: Children must be taught the difference between right and wrong.

translation: 院子（房屋旁边用于种花种菜的土地，通常有草坪）
definition: a piece of land next to or around your house where you can grow flowers, fruit, vegetables, etc., usually with a lawn (= an area of grass)
example: They have a gorgeous old oak tree in their front yard.

translation: 是的（yeah，yes的非正式表达）
年份（一年分成的12个月）
definition: the period from 1 January to 31 December, that is 365 or 366 days, divided into 12 months
example: Elections take place every year.

translation: 大叫（因愤怒、兴奋或痛苦而大声喊叫）
definition: to shout loudly, for example because you are angry, excited, frightened or in pain
example: yell (at somebody/something), He yelled at the other driver.

translation: 黄色的（柠檬或黄油的颜色）
definition: having the colour of lemons or butter
example: pale yellow flowers

translation: 黄色（柠檬或黄油的颜色）
definition: the colour of lemons or butter
example: She was dressed in yellow.

translation: 是的（用于肯定回答或陈述）
definition: used to answer a question and say that something is correct or true
example: ‘Is this your car?’ ‘Yes, it is.’

translation: 昨天（在今天之前的那一天）
definition: on the day before today
example: A company spokeswoman said yesterday that no final decision had been made yet.

translation: 昨天（今天之前的那一天）
definition: the day before today
example: Yesterday was Sunday.

translation: 还，尚（用于否定句或疑问句，谈论预期发生但尚未发生之事）
definition: used in negative sentences and questions to talk about something that has not happened but that you expect to happen
example: (British English), I haven't received a letter from him yet.

translation: 然而（尽管刚才所言）
definition: despite what has just been said
example: It's a small car, yet it's surprisingly spacious.

translation: 产量（生产出的作物、利润等的总量）
definition: the total amount of crops, profits, etc. that are produced
example: a high crop yield

translation: 产生（产出作物、利润等）
definition: the total amount of crops, profits, etc. that are produced
example: a high crop yield

translation: 你（代指说话或书写的对象）
definition: used as the subject or object of a verb or after a preposition to refer to the person or people being spoken or written to
example: You said you knew the way.

translation: 年轻的（生命时长短的；未发育完全的）
definition: having lived or existed for only a short time; not fully developed
example: Young babies need to be wrapped up warmly.

translation: 青年（作为群体的年轻人）
definition: young people considered as a group
example: It's a movie that will appeal to the young.

translation: 年轻人（年轻人或儿童）
definition: a young person or a child
example: The camp is for youngsters aged 8 to 14.

translation: 你的（属于说话对象的）
definition: of or belonging to the person or people being spoken or written to
example: I like your dress.

translation: 你的东西（属于你的东西）
definition: of or belonging to you
example: Is that book yours?

translation: 你自己（yourself的反身形式）
definition: used when the person or people being spoken to both cause and are affected by an action
example: Have you hurt yourself?

translation: 青春（年轻时期的岁月，尤指成年之前）
definition: the time of life when a person is young, especially the time before a child becomes an adult
example: in somebody's youth, He had been a talented musician in his youth.

translation: 零（数字0）
example: Five, four, three, two, one, zero… We have lift-off.

translation: 区域，地带（具有特定特征或用途的地区，如战争区域）
definition: an area or a region with a particular feature or use
example: a war/combat/demilitarized/exclusion zone
